INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: EASE // MiD - Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Product Launch Timeline and Priorities**

The team committed to launching a new product on **March 1st**, prompting an immediate push to finalize preparations (01:25).

- **Josh Santo confirmed the March 1st launch date**, describing it as a "small product launch" but requiring significant last-minute effort.
- The decision came only **two days prior**, creating a tight timeline and increased workload for the team.
- This urgency demands focused resource allocation to meet the deadline while managing existing client onboarding.
- The launch is positioned as a key near-term milestone, with success tied to smooth execution despite the compressed schedule.

## **Podcast Content and Outreach Strategy**

Podcast episodes and outreach campaigns are actively driving engagement and lead generation, with plans to sustain momentum during upcoming absences (02:12).

- **Paula Ocampo reported that the episode with Rajiv is growing steadily** across Buzzsprout, YouTube, and Spotify, indicating rising audience reach (03:15).
    - The episode is attracting new downloads and plays week over week, enhancing brand visibility.
- The outreach campaign is scheduled for a **new launch by Monday**, targeting previous contacts who did not respond initially (04:01).
    - This retargeting effort aims to increase conversion by reconnecting with lukewarm leads.
- **Josh Santo requested a blog post focused on executive themes related to leadership and manufacturing** during his absence next week, ensuring content continuity (04:20).
    - Paula agreed to deliver the blog copy by the following week to maintain engagement.
- Meeting cancellations were planned around team members’ time off, notably **Josh’s absence starting Thursday** and **Paula’s carnival trip**, ensuring workload alignment (05:18).

## **Product Overview Video Development**

The product overview video is undergoing detailed review with changes planned to improve clarity, flow, and visual support ahead of final release (08:07).

- **Baylee Gunnell initiated a review focused on shortening the video and refining transitions**, though Josh indicated the current length of **3:17 minutes** is acceptable for now (08:36).
- Specific animation adjustments were requested by Josh to minimize distracting movement and favor subtle effects like typing animation (09:23).
- Josh clarified that interactive elements like photo-taking buttons should start white and turn blue when selected, improving user interface clarity (09:53).
- The video sequence will be adjusted so menus and pop-ups appear in a specified order, with certain images replaced by dashboard visuals to better demonstrate reporting features (11:43).
    - Josh will provide dashboard screenshots, with Baylee’s team open to reusing existing assets to accelerate production.
- Text corrections and title screen additions were identified, such as adding a missing "On the Job Training" title and fixing spelling errors like "identification" (14:04).
- The team agreed to revisit the design stage to refine supporting visuals, including product icons and potential B-roll footage, to enhance storytelling (15:41).
- Josh suggested recording live video demos to replace some graphical elements, aiming to increase authenticity and viewer understanding (15:59).

## **Budget and Resource Management for Video Production**

Budget concerns were addressed, confirming a fixed-point system that safeguards the project from unexpected cost overruns despite extended editing time (17:09).

- Josh expressed worry about running out of hours or credits to complete the videos without additional budget (17:09).
- Baylee assured that the last contract was canceled and the current work is under a fixed points arrangement, meaning no extra charges regardless of editing hours used (17:37).
- This budgeting approach provides financial predictability and allows the team to focus on quality without resource constraints.
- It ensures ongoing support for podcasts and blog production without risking budget overruns.

## **Team Availability and Scheduling Impacts**

Upcoming team absences require adjustments to meeting schedules and content delivery plans to maintain workflow continuity (05:18).

- Josh will be off from Thursday through Tuesday, returning Wednesday, which affects scheduling for the week of the 18th (05:23).
- Paula will be out attending a carnival, impacting availability during the same time frame (05:30).
- Baylee confirmed awareness of these absences and coordinated cancellations accordingly.
- Planning includes producing additional content like blogs during these gaps to keep audience engagement steady.',
  '2026-02-04 21:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Share podcast episode images and blog post by Friday (02:12)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare new outreach campaign and aim to have it ready by Monday for launch and retargeting (03:52)","completed":false},{"text":"Draft executive-themed blog post for Josh’s week off and share copy by next week (04:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate meeting scheduling and cancellations for planned time off (Josh’s and Paula’s absences) (05:18)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and implement corrections and revisions for the product overview video based on discussion, including transition and visual flow adjustments (08:07)","completed":false},{"text":"Clarify supporting visuals requirements with the design team and integrate demo videos as needed (15:41)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide dashboard visuals or allow reuse from other scenes for video edits (12:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm and deliver any demo video recordings to assist with product overview video enhancements (15:41)","completed":false},{"text":"Manage communication and execution of video production updates including cuts, transitions, animations, and spelling corrections (08:07)","completed":false},{"text":"Ensure proper conveyance of Josh’s feedback to the video editing team (15:31)","completed":false},{"text":"Reassure Josh about budget and point allocation and maintain updated point tracking for ongoing content work (17:09)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Sync on Marketing Tools (2026-02-05 14:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'e50afe94-037e-49d6-8f2e-8c05ac7e3294',
    '2026-02-05 14:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KGJ5VPJJEW20248QFR7SA8PS',
    'Sync on Marketing Tools',
    '{"Maximilian Rabeler","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    1868,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83161830993?pwd=59osuMxQ5a65WM4Y6ghubtkRJrpPqh.1',
    '{"id":"01KGJ5VPJJEW20248QFR7SA8PS","title":"Sync on Marketing Tools","summary":{"notes":"## **Email and LinkedIn Campaign Execution**\n\nThe campaign is ready to launch immediately once final email signature feedback is approved, sending up to **240-250 emails daily** across **six warmed-up domains** to a target list of **200 contacts** (04:50).\n\n- **Emails and LinkedIn messages flow automatically** from Clay into Smart Lead and Heyreach, with Smart Lead handling emails and Heyreach sending LinkedIn connection requests and follow-ups (02:28).\n- Positive email replies trigger sentiment analysis using an AI model based on GPT-4.1 mini, achieving near **99% accuracy**, and prompt internal Slack and email notifications to Axle for quick team follow-up (09:17).\n- Unsubscribes and email bounces are tracked and recorded in Supabase, with bounce addresses verified through **six providers** upfront to minimize invalid contacts; weekly manual checks ensure data quality and automation flow (12:20).\n- Follow-up emails are scheduled in Smart Lead with specific delays, such as sending the second email **3-4 days** after the first, only if no reply or unsubscribe occurs, with HubSpot updated via private app integration to manage contact status and next steps (13:58).\n\n## **CRM and Data Integration**\n\nHubSpot is used as a CRM to track email engagement but does not send cold emails, relying on data pushes from the automation system with create-or-update logic keyed by email address (08:05).\n\n- HubSpot records email send events, replies, unsubscribes, and bounces through JSON payloads sent by N8N workflows, allowing the team to monitor campaign status and contact engagement centrally (07:46).\n- LinkedIn message replies and connection acceptances are not stored in HubSpot but logged in Supabase and notified directly to Bettina via LinkedIn and internal alerts; this separation maintains CRM cleanliness and respects platform limits (17:35).\n- Supabase acts as the campaign’s central database storing all webhook events, including email and LinkedIn actions, with data retention of up to **one year** to support reporting and performance analysis (16:56).\n\n## **Lead Scoring and Website Engagement Tracking**\n\nFactors AI provides GDPR-compliant company-level website visitor deanonymization and LinkedIn ad interaction tracking to enrich lead scoring and engagement insights (15:30).\n\n- Company visits, ad views, and ad clicks on LinkedIn are captured via Factors'' CAPI integration, correlating these events with email campaign contacts to identify highly engaged accounts (19:49).\n- Lead scores increase when a company visits the website multiple times or interacts with LinkedIn ads, enabling personalized email triggers for contacts at companies showing strong interest but no direct replies (16:11).\n- Weekly reports generated from Supabase highlight top engaged companies and aggregate weekly email/message volumes, helping the team prioritize outreach and optimize campaign content (20:27).\n\n## **Campaign Monitoring, Reporting, and Optimization**\n\nThe system provides comprehensive weekly reports detailing email volumes, engagement metrics, and ad interactions to inform content and targeting decisions (26:11).\n\n- Colin emphasized the importance of transparency and understanding the flow and volume of emails to properly interpret campaign responses and results (25:19).\n- A/B testing is planned across channels, with new email versions, LinkedIn messages, and ads introduced based on report-driven insights and team approvals before deployment into Smart Lead or Heyreach (29:26).\n- Rapid iteration on messaging and landing pages is possible, with the team monitoring engagement closely and adjusting language or offers to improve conversion rates continuously (29:40).\n\n## **Technical Workflow and Automation Architecture**\n\nThe campaign automation uses N8N for orchestrating webhook processing that routes events from Smart Lead and Heyreach into HubSpot and Supabase, enforcing routing logic based on email sent, reply, unsubscribe, or bounce events (02:57).\n\n- Webhooks trigger updates in real time, ensuring contact records reflect the latest engagement status and that positive replies prompt immediate team notification to accelerate follow-up (06:22).\n- The system employs a multi-step workflow where each contact’s interaction with the campaign determines subsequent actions, avoiding duplicate sends and ensuring compliance with opt-out requests (06:54).\n- Integration between LinkedIn ads and campaign systems is secured via partner access to the client’s LinkedIn Ads account, enabling direct access for reporting and campaign management without data silos (28:09).\n\n## **Strategic Context and Team Perspectives**\n\nMaximilian expressed strong interest in understanding every technical detail for full transparency and control, reflecting a culture valuing thorough knowledge over “black box” solutions (25:19).\n\n- Colin reassured that the campaign uses proven logic from around **50 prior campaigns**, emphasizing reliability and experience while remaining open to fast adjustments based on data (26:46).\n- The team views this automation as a major step up from prior marketing efforts focused on website and content alone, aiming for more effective outreach through data-driven, automated multi-channel touchpoints (28:37).\n- Ownership for ongoing monitoring and weekly data reviews lies with the internal team, with Colin offering continued support and quick iteration capabilities to optimize campaign success (30:18).","outline":null,"keywords":["Email Campaign","LinkedIn Messaging","Smart Lead","HubSpot CRM","Factors AI","Supabase Database"],"overview":"- **Email Campaign Launch:** Ready to send **240-250 emails daily** to **200 contacts** once final email signature is approved.  \n- **Automated Workflow:** Emails and LinkedIn messages flow from Clay to Smart Lead and Heyreach; tracking for unsubscribes and bounces in Supabase.  \n- **Data Recording & Management:** HubSpot tracks engagement, while Supabase logs LinkedIn replies and stores campaign data for one year.  \n- **Lead Scoring Mechanism:** Company interactions with ads or multiple site visits increase lead scores, prompting personalized email triggers.  \n- **Weekly Reporting System:** Comprehensive reports detail engagement metrics, assisting the team in optimizing outreach strategies and content.  \n- **Automation Infrastructure:** N8N manages webhook events, ensuring real-time updates on engagement, avoiding duplicates, and maintaining compliance.","action_items":"\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nReview the detailed workflow documentation once received from Colin (30:35)\nAccess LinkedIn Ads account using provided partner access to monitor ad performance (28:13)\nCheck Firefly notes and request access if necessary to maintain visibility of contact activity (15:16)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nFinalize email signature adjustments based on Bettina’s feedback to enable campaign launch (01:34)\nSend a summary or five-line documentation of the campaign flow and integrations for Maximilian’s review (30:27)\nMonitor campaign data weekly in Supabase, including unsubscribes and bounces, and ensure proper updating of CRM and databases (12:18)\nProvide direct email and LinkedIn campaign reports on weekly engagement and send those reports to Maximilian as part of ongoing updates (20:20)\nContinue refining campaign copy, landing pages, and A/B tests based on analysis of engagement data (29:26)\n"},"duration":31.1299991607666,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Wait.","index":0,"end_time":57.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":51.78,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Need to bit louder.","index":1,"end_time":59.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.3,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So again, hear me now?","index":2,"end_time":61.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.18,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yep.","index":3,"end_time":62.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":62.02,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":4,"end_time":63.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":62.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":5,"end_time":65.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.42,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"You doing all right?","index":6,"end_time":66.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Almost the end of the week.","index":7,"end_time":68.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":67.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, week was good, I guess.","index":8,"end_time":72.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.78,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":9,"end_time":73.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.14,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So maybe before we start, Axel asked me so can, how far are we with starting the email and LinkedIn campaign?","index":10,"end_time":89.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.1,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean, exactly is missing.","index":11,"end_time":93.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":90.86,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So I just asked a question about the email signature that Bettina came back with some feedback with.","index":12,"end_time":99.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, I mean, once we''re set on that, we''re.","index":13,"end_time":101.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re pretty much ready to hit go whenever you guys say ready to go.","index":14,"end_time":104.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":15,"end_time":106.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.59,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":16,"end_time":107.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.27,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Then a part of that.","index":17,"end_time":109.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.91,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I have questions for your net and flow.","index":18,"end_time":113.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.67,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So can you.","index":19,"end_time":115.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":114.31,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Could you just share the flow via your screen?","index":20,"end_time":120.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.91,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, one sec.","index":21,"end_time":122.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":120.39,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay, so we start somewhere.","index":22,"end_time":142.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.48,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":23,"end_time":143.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.8,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Let''s just assume we have the list, right?","index":24,"end_time":146.719,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.24,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yes.","index":25,"end_time":147.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So where would we be at that point?","index":26,"end_time":153.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":148.24,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So this is broken up more by channel.","index":27,"end_time":156.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":154,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Smart Lead is where we''re sending emails out of factors is how we''re de anonymizing website traffic.","index":28,"end_time":161.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Reach is where we''re sending LinkedIn messages from.","index":29,"end_time":164.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":162.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we have a free level of HubSpot because Axle didn''t want us to just upload contacts into your dynamic CRM.","index":30,"end_time":171.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":164.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we track them in HubSpot on the free level and then package them up and send them over.","index":31,"end_time":176.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":32,"end_time":177.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":33,"end_time":179.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":178.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the list is built in clay with all the enrichments and then automatically passed into Smart Lead and heyreach.","index":34,"end_time":185.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so they start going through the flows and then anytime.","index":35,"end_time":189.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":186.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is just a processor, so it depends on what type of data is flowing in.","index":36,"end_time":195.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":190.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did they reply to an email?","index":37,"end_time":196.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":195.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where they just sent an email, did they unsubscribe?","index":38,"end_time":199.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did they bounce?","index":39,"end_time":200.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":199.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So depending on what action was taken, it''ll go through a different path if it''s a reply goes through sentiment analysis.","index":40,"end_time":207.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then if we determine that there''s an action step needed from your team, we have an email automatically go to Axle for that.","index":41,"end_time":214.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":208.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":42,"end_time":216.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":215.98,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":43,"end_time":216.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":216.26,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And maybe just start at the beginning.","index":44,"end_time":220.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.34,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So you need some sort of trigger, Right?","index":45,"end_time":223.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.1,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So what is the trigger?","index":46,"end_time":226.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.82,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Do we, I mean, we have a list of, I don''t know, let''s say 200 people.","index":47,"end_time":230.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.86,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"What happens?","index":48,"end_time":232.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.58,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"What sort of trigger do we have?","index":49,"end_time":234.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":232.94,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So here we have triggers for email sent, email open email reply, email bounce, email unsubscribe.","index":50,"end_time":242.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":234.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So any of those actions happen, it gets caught in this webhook.","index":51,"end_time":245.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From there, it then is just going through the routing logic of like, what happened?","index":52,"end_time":253.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then do we update that contact in HubSpot?","index":53,"end_time":256.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":253.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we analyze the reply and then update them in HubSpot like, it just depends on the step that was taken.","index":54,"end_time":263.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":256.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but I mean, we are.","index":55,"end_time":266.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.35,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"We''re not sending an email to all the 200 contacts at first, are we?","index":56,"end_time":271.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.27,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean, yeah, we have about six email domains that we''re going to be sending out emails from, and they''ve been warming up for several weeks.","index":57,"end_time":279.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can.","index":58,"end_time":280.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can send out emails pretty fast.","index":59,"end_time":282.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so the second you hit go, every One of those 200 contacts will receive an email.","index":60,"end_time":289.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.89,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean, it flows through human characteristics.","index":61,"end_time":292.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''ll probably.","index":62,"end_time":293.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the.","index":63,"end_time":294.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re probably up to like 30 or 40 emails a day per inbox.","index":64,"end_time":298.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that math, what is that?","index":65,"end_time":302.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"240.","index":66,"end_time":302.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"250 emails going out.","index":67,"end_time":305.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":306.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":69,"end_time":308.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.87,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And that is.","index":70,"end_time":310.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.39,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"How is that managed?","index":71,"end_time":312.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.23,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"How do you.","index":72,"end_time":313.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.51,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Is that automatically in some software or do you just hard code it here that you have batches?","index":73,"end_time":320.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.43,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Oh, no, the email.","index":74,"end_time":321.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s all handled in Smart Lead.","index":75,"end_time":323.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":321.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a tool.","index":76,"end_time":324.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you just.","index":77,"end_time":326.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.96,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"The hook basically tells Smart Lead, hey.","index":78,"end_time":329.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"This hook is from Smart Lead.","index":79,"end_time":333.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we start the campaign from Clay.","index":80,"end_time":336.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It has a direct integration to Smart Lead.","index":81,"end_time":337.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":336.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all the contacts you guys have approved, they automatically get added into this campaign in Smart lead and in Heyreach.","index":82,"end_time":344.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they start getting emails and LinkedIn connection requests.","index":83,"end_time":347.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":344.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anytime an action happens in Smart Lead, such as an email reply or an unsubscribe or someone replies on LinkedIn by a message or accepting the connection request, those are caught by web hooks.","index":84,"end_time":359.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s.","index":85,"end_time":360.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":359.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is coming from Smart Lead or this is coming from heyreach.","index":86,"end_time":363.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":360.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but still.","index":87,"end_time":367.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":366.46,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay, so let''s start another way then.","index":88,"end_time":374.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.06,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So in case you hit go, what will happen?","index":89,"end_time":379.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.06,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I will start sending emails.","index":90,"end_time":383.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":382.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It will send the first batch.","index":91,"end_time":385.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.79,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":92,"end_time":386.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":93,"end_time":387.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.03,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And that''s, I mean, not important, but I guess picked random or something or pick that.","index":94,"end_time":393.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.47,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"You do not hit the same people.","index":95,"end_time":395.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.43,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Like people from the same organization or.","index":96,"end_time":398.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.75,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"No, there''s.","index":97,"end_time":400.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":399.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, you guys have the contact list, so.","index":98,"end_time":403.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it just.","index":99,"end_time":403.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":403.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It goes through that as fast as it can.","index":100,"end_time":405.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":403.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have like space between the emails.","index":101,"end_time":408.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":406.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like it waits a few days before sending the next email to that same contact.","index":102,"end_time":412.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":103,"end_time":414.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.15,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So.","index":104,"end_time":415.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.03,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And well, Smart Lead sends out the first batch of emails and then this webhook is called.","index":105,"end_time":421.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.39,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I guess.","index":106,"end_time":421.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":421.15,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I''m sorry, the webhook is then what?","index":107,"end_time":424.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The webhook here in Nanite n is triggered.","index":108,"end_time":428.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.47,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":109,"end_time":429.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anytime an action happens in Smart Lead, this webhook is triggered for.","index":110,"end_time":433.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can pull up smartly, but it''s for email replies.","index":111,"end_time":437.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":435.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Email, bounce email and subscribe.","index":112,"end_time":439,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So anytime something from that signal happens, it Gets caught by this webhook.","index":113,"end_time":442.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so yeah.","index":114,"end_time":445.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.56,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay, so emails are sent via Smart Lead and in theory does not know when an email is sent, but only knows the action after that.","index":115,"end_time":456.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.08,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Well, Smart lead will tell it that an email was sent because we do have it in this N8N flow to update a contact record in HubSpot to catch that an email was sent.","index":116,"end_time":464.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":456.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so how does that happen, for example?","index":117,"end_time":470.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":466.78,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Because I mean now you have Smart lead and HubSpot, so.","index":118,"end_time":473.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.7,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, so HubSpot is just the CRM.","index":119,"end_time":475.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":473.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re not allowed.","index":120,"end_time":476.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":475.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean HubSpot''s rules are not allowed to send cold emails.","index":121,"end_time":478.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have upSerts in this N8N flow which is updating the HubSpot contact record through a JSON value.","index":122,"end_time":485.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just for me to understand, if the webhook says okay, we send an email via Smart lead, then this decider will say okay, an email got sent.","index":123,"end_time":499.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.82,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So I upset a contact in HubSpot.","index":124,"end_time":502.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499.6,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Correct.","index":125,"end_time":504.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":503.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, is there any check whether the contact is already present in the CRM or not?","index":126,"end_time":511.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.56,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean, yes, because you send four emails in total in the end to.","index":127,"end_time":515.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":511.24,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, so.","index":128,"end_time":516.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":515.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the first step is to create.","index":129,"end_time":517.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":516.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a create or update.","index":130,"end_time":519.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":517.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All of these HubSpot nodes are create or update.","index":131,"end_time":522.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":520.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that logic is in HubSpot, I assume?","index":132,"end_time":525.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yes.","index":133,"end_time":526.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":526.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":134,"end_time":527.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.16,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Everything in HubSpot is email address based.","index":135,"end_time":530.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s how they do.","index":136,"end_time":531.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":530.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s basically case one email is sent.","index":137,"end_time":534.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.36,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So we adjust part in HubSpot and I guess what happens there, get contact ID, not the first email in HubSpot.","index":138,"end_time":544.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":534.4,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":139,"end_time":545.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.25,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And you add something else.","index":140,"end_time":549.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":547.97,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, let me store it in a database.","index":141,"end_time":551.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I mean that''s the boring part here.","index":142,"end_time":553.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.57,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":143,"end_time":554.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":553.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what''s case two?","index":144,"end_time":556.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.69,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So then the next one is a reply.","index":145,"end_time":559.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":557.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it goes through sentiment analysis processes, that email reply.","index":146,"end_time":562.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":559.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then if it''s a positive reply that demands like an action, it''ll notify us and then send an email to you guys.","index":147,"end_time":568.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If they unsubscribe, then we unsubscribe them.","index":148,"end_time":571.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":568.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If it''s an out of office reply, we log it as an out of office reply.","index":149,"end_time":576.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":573.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if it''s not relevant, we still capture it.","index":150,"end_time":578.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like if it''s like a spam response for any reason, just as a catch all.","index":151,"end_time":583.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you repeat the last one please?","index":152,"end_time":586.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.93,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, if it''s so we have like main buckets for like an actual reply unsubscribe or out of office or if they just.","index":153,"end_time":593.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":586.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just have like a catch all bucket outside of that.","index":154,"end_time":596.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, okay, okay.","index":155,"end_time":599.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.38,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So, okay, so this Analyze is just you give the.","index":156,"end_time":607.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.54,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"The information inside the email to some model and that''s it.","index":157,"end_time":613.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":607.18,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean it''s running through now.","index":158,"end_time":615.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thumb up, thumb down or something neutral.","index":159,"end_time":618.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.22,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, essentially.","index":160,"end_time":619.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":618.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":161,"end_time":619.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":619.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have.","index":162,"end_time":620.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":619.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We.","index":163,"end_time":620.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":620.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We code in the prompt or we give it a prompt to analyze by based on the campaign that we''ve set up and then, and then it''ll determine that.","index":164,"end_time":627.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":620.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you use a specified model for that or just some.","index":165,"end_time":630.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":627.46,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"This is a 4.1 mini that we''re using for this.","index":166,"end_time":633.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":167,"end_time":633.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.5,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"It''s a generic.","index":168,"end_time":634.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.78,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And that''s working.","index":169,"end_time":638.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.38,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean, I guess we are not the first one you''re testing.","index":170,"end_time":641.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.26,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"No, no, by far not the first one.","index":171,"end_time":644.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":641.699,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it seems to work, I guess.","index":172,"end_time":647.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.42,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yes.","index":173,"end_time":647.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":647.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And not only like 90% of the cases, but more like 99.","index":174,"end_time":651.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":647.94,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":175,"end_time":653,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":652.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we also have records of all of these.","index":176,"end_time":655.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":653.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean we catch all of these as they happen.","index":177,"end_time":657.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":655.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They get caught in this executions flow.","index":178,"end_time":659.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":657.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re able to analyze it and if we need to intervene, we do, but we have not ever had to.","index":179,"end_time":665,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":659.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":180,"end_time":666.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665.56,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":181,"end_time":667,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.16,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":182,"end_time":669.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.76,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And in case the.","index":183,"end_time":670.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.12,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"The answer is positive, then there is this colorful thing.","index":184,"end_time":674.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.2,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So we.","index":185,"end_time":674.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.2,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"You send an email to us.","index":186,"end_time":675.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.72,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, so we send an internal Slack notification.","index":187,"end_time":678.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":676.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We send an email to you that goes to Axle.","index":188,"end_time":681.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":678.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At this point we can add more emails to it if you would like.","index":189,"end_time":684.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":681.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we update the record in HubSpot.","index":190,"end_time":686.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":684.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":191,"end_time":689.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.71,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And I mean when.","index":192,"end_time":696.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.79,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"When you.","index":193,"end_time":696.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":696.31,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So okay, wait, how.","index":194,"end_time":700.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.07,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay, now let''s one by one, let''s do the third case first.","index":195,"end_time":703.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.47,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Um, so down here.","index":196,"end_time":707.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":705.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":197,"end_time":708.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.6,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So this is just capturing if they directly.","index":198,"end_time":710.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":708.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s an unsubscribe link in every email.","index":199,"end_time":712.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":710.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But sometimes people just reply unsubscribe.","index":200,"end_time":715.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":712.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why we have two different logics to catch.","index":201,"end_time":717.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":715.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":202,"end_time":718.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.48,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":203,"end_time":718.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.12,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So but if someone hits the unsubscribe link that''s not triggering an answer email.","index":204,"end_time":724.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.52,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Not triggering a what email?","index":205,"end_time":728.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":726.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like there is no.","index":206,"end_time":730.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.88,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"You are not receiving an email then that the person is unsubscribe.","index":207,"end_time":733.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":730.08,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Unsubscribing.","index":208,"end_time":734.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":733.99,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"No, but it''s captured in our database and we check that every week.","index":209,"end_time":738.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":735.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, okay, sure.","index":210,"end_time":740.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.71,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And then same thing for email bounced.","index":211,"end_time":742.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":212,"end_time":743.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":742.79,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Bounce means it''s.","index":213,"end_time":744.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":743.27,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"There is no valid email.","index":214,"end_time":746.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":744.75,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":215,"end_time":747.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":746.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or that their server has blocked where we''re trying to send from.","index":216,"end_time":750.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":747.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":217,"end_time":752.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.75,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So now in.","index":218,"end_time":753.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752.55,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So we have positive case, negative case and bounce case.","index":219,"end_time":758.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":754.23,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Let''s just look at those three.","index":220,"end_time":760.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.31,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"What is then happening to.","index":221,"end_time":765.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.12,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean in case it bounced.","index":222,"end_time":769.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":766,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Then we should adjust the email address maybe or whatever.","index":223,"end_time":774,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":770.16,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":224,"end_time":776.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":774.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":225,"end_time":776.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.36,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So we would analyze like the emails that have Bounced to date and then see if we can find anything updated.","index":226,"end_time":781.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":776.719,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We when we pull this contact list we already verify through six different email providers.","index":227,"end_time":786.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":781.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if it''s bouncing, I mean it''s pretty high chance that we''re not going to find another valid one.","index":228,"end_time":790.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":786.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it does go through a ch.","index":229,"end_time":792.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":790.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, how''s that check working?","index":230,"end_time":795.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.05,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"That''s by capturing so we have that data all going into Supabase.","index":231,"end_time":799.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":796.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Supabase is just a massive database that we have and so on our we''re managing this every week.","index":232,"end_time":804.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":799.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we go in and we check this, the Supabase for any rows that have like unsubscribed or bounce or anything like that and then making sure that all the automations are flowing correctly.","index":233,"end_time":815.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":804.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And how do you.","index":234,"end_time":821.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.82,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay, at which point do you send for example the second email?","index":235,"end_time":824.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.74,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Because I mean then you would send the second email if you either do not trigger path 2 or you trigger it and get out of office response.","index":236,"end_time":836.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":825.26,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Right.","index":237,"end_time":837.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":836.78,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So the second email I think in Smart Lead we have it set to come like three or four days after the first email.","index":238,"end_time":843.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":838.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if they respond or anything we''re only logging the first email in HubSpot that''s being sent because we don''t need to just like we already know what the emails are.","index":239,"end_time":852.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":844.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t need to just keep adding rows for that.","index":240,"end_time":854.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, any action they take on any of the emails they receive will trigger any of these workflows.","index":241,"end_time":861.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if they reply or unsubscribe or bounce or anything like that.","index":242,"end_time":864.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So but okay, so I mean this the HubSpot notes here I just editing or changing the entry.","index":243,"end_time":885.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.86,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So HubSpot knows to who the next email should be.","index":244,"end_time":891.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":885.589,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, it adds it as a note.","index":245,"end_time":892.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":891.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s just through a JSON payload we set up a private app, we built a private app connection between N8N and HubSpot to process that data.","index":246,"end_time":901.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":247,"end_time":906.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":902.56,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Now that''s understandable I guess.","index":248,"end_time":909.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.88,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"By the way, the Firefly notes are also accessible by me.","index":249,"end_time":914.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.48,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Right?","index":250,"end_time":915.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.72,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Oh the notes.","index":251,"end_time":917.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":916.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":252,"end_time":917.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":917.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can send these to you if you need.","index":253,"end_time":918.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":917.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great then.","index":254,"end_time":923.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.2,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":255,"end_time":924.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":923.62,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Factors AI.","index":256,"end_time":925.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.14,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah so this nodes which are not interacting with each other, correct?","index":257,"end_time":930.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.34,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":931.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":930.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So these are capturing three different web hooks.","index":259,"end_time":933.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":931.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So factors is GDPR compliant website de anonymization because it''s just by company level.","index":260,"end_time":940.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":933.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So anytime we see a company visit the website we determine if they are in the list that we are emailing out to and then add to a lead score for them.","index":261,"end_time":951.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":941.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re able to track that they''re coming to the website several times in a Week, but they haven''t responded or filled out a form.","index":262,"end_time":956.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":951.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We may trigger like a more personalized email to them.","index":263,"end_time":959.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":956.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Factors also connects to LinkedIn through a Capi.","index":264,"end_time":964.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":961.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they''re able to not only track what companies have clicked on ads, but what companies have viewed ads.","index":265,"end_time":969.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":964.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So those also filter into their lead score.","index":266,"end_time":971.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":267,"end_time":972.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":971.81,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And that for example LinkedIn connection, is that somehow built in or that''s down here?","index":268,"end_time":980.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":972.29,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"It''s okay.","index":269,"end_time":982.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.89,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":270,"end_time":983.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":983.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So connections accepted go through here and any replies that come from LinkedIn come through here.","index":271,"end_time":988.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":983.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":272,"end_time":992.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":992.25,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And then as soon as they reply we remove them from the email campaign.","index":273,"end_time":1000.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":997.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":274,"end_time":1001.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1001.28,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So and okay, maybe those, how do you call it?","index":275,"end_time":1013.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1003.92,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Those green.","index":276,"end_time":1014.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.4,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Add something.","index":277,"end_time":1015.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1014.4,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, this is to the Supabase database.","index":278,"end_time":1018.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1016.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that''s super base.","index":279,"end_time":1020.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1018.8,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":280,"end_time":1020.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.12,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And that''s somehow also external externally stored or how do you store?","index":281,"end_time":1030.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1022.24,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Well, it''s all stored in our Supabase.","index":282,"end_time":1033.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean that''s our database that we have servers for.","index":283,"end_time":1035.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1033.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It then sends an email notification to Axle and like I said, we can add any other emails to get notified there if we need.","index":284,"end_time":1041.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1036.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And from that Supabase you also have some connection to HubSpot or is that only via an add in?","index":285,"end_time":1053.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1044.98,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So yeah, we''re not capturing their LinkedIn replies in HubSpot, just the email replies because Bettina it''s, it''s straight from Bettina''s profile so she should see it as soon as it comes in.","index":286,"end_time":1066.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1055.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So but then if you, if you have that logic here within Heyreach, what is vectors AI doing for the LinkedIn things?","index":287,"end_time":1085.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1077.71,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"It''s just sending and whenever there''s.","index":288,"end_time":1088.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1085.69,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Or I mean sending slash.","index":289,"end_time":1091.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1088.65,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Like what is heyreach doing?","index":290,"end_time":1094.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, what not.","index":291,"end_time":1096.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.01,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean for Haywood it''s the notes are kind of, I''d say self explaining.","index":292,"end_time":1102.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1096.85,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So if someone answers on the auto generated messages from Bettina, then we actually get messaged.","index":293,"end_time":1110.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1102.69,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah but, and the first one, So.","index":294,"end_time":1120.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1110.94,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"But so if they accept Bettina''s connection request on LinkedIn then that will be triggered.","index":295,"end_time":1127.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1120.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But they are automatically sent a message as soon as they connect.","index":296,"end_time":1130.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1127.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the first one is just connection accepted and the second is a reply tag.","index":297,"end_time":1145.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1139.51,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yes, so, but so in case someone accepts the automatic connection request, we do not get information about that.","index":298,"end_time":1155.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.43,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean it''s stored in Supabase and Bettina gets a notification that someone accepted their request through LinkedIn.","index":299,"end_time":1161.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1156.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah, okay, sure.","index":300,"end_time":1163.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1162.08,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"LinkedIn sends that automatic.","index":301,"end_time":1165.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.4,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, then my confusion is gone at least.","index":302,"end_time":1167.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1165.28,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"But then can you screw up a bit again for the part above factors AI.","index":303,"end_time":1172.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.92,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So that''s only for the ads then it''s not about.","index":304,"end_time":1175.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1172.72,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And website visitors.","index":305,"end_time":1177.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1176.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, correct.","index":306,"end_time":1179.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1179.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And okay, so what is the webhook for?","index":307,"end_time":1187,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1183.12,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Website visit events.","index":308,"end_time":1188.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1187,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So Factors AI is a deanonymization pixel that we have on your website from by account level.","index":309,"end_time":1196.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1189.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s just de anonymizing traffic by IP and device ID and geolocation and everything.","index":310,"end_time":1201.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1196.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s GDPR compliant because it''s only account level.","index":311,"end_time":1206.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1202.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not person level.","index":312,"end_time":1207.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1206.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so we know.","index":313,"end_time":1211.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1210.32,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"We don''t know which person visited our.","index":314,"end_time":1213.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1211.52,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Website, but we know which company and we know which people from that company we''re emailing.","index":315,"end_time":1217.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1213.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, fair.","index":316,"end_time":1221.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1220.47,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And.","index":317,"end_time":1222.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1221.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that information is.","index":318,"end_time":1224.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1222.31,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"In the end, it''s only added to your superbase.","index":319,"end_time":1227.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1224.63,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, but we have a report that''s generated for you guys that pulls directly from Supabase to show top engaged companies and everything like that.","index":320,"end_time":1233.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1227.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we know who clicked on our website.","index":321,"end_time":1236.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1234.39,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Correct.","index":322,"end_time":1237.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1237.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":323,"end_time":1238.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1237.99,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":324,"end_time":1240.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1240.48,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":325,"end_time":1241.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1240.76,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":326,"end_time":1241.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1241.04,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay, so your report is basically just telling us which.","index":327,"end_time":1246.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1242.72,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Let''s call it keywords I added to the rows.","index":328,"end_time":1249.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1246.88,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Then in the end, basically it''s showing.","index":329,"end_time":1252.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a lot prettier than that.","index":330,"end_time":1254.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1252.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It just, it shows like the top engaged accounts, how many emails and messages have been sent throughout the week.","index":331,"end_time":1261.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1254.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Et.","index":332,"end_time":1261.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1261.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":333,"end_time":1266.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1265.69,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And then this last one down here is just.","index":334,"end_time":1269.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1268.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we use a HubSpot form, which we did not use on the new landing page.","index":335,"end_time":1273.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1269.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is when we ran the campaign in the U.S. on the U.S. dossy Dollar website that we built, we had HubSpot forms that were capturing this.","index":336,"end_time":1280.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1273.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s, this is just there if we need that again.","index":337,"end_time":1282.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1280.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is not used for the dev campaign.","index":338,"end_time":1285.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.45,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"No, not this one right here.","index":339,"end_time":1288.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1286.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because we''re using your own website form.","index":340,"end_time":1289.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1288.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":341,"end_time":1290.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1290.5,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":342,"end_time":1293.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1292.5,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And can we go, can we go back to the effective AI thing?","index":343,"end_time":1302.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1293.94,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So we have this LinkedIn add, click event stuff.","index":344,"end_time":1307.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1303.14,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Right.","index":345,"end_time":1308.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1307.86,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"How do we.","index":346,"end_time":1314.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1313.86,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Like what is.","index":347,"end_time":1316.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1316.11,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay, how do I say it?","index":348,"end_time":1319.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1318.51,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So we have some.","index":349,"end_time":1322.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1320.27,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"The webhook again just checks who clicked, right?","index":350,"end_time":1326.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1322.43,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":351,"end_time":1327.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1326.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Factors has a email address, I suppose.","index":352,"end_time":1329.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1327.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":353,"end_time":1330.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1330.11,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":354,"end_time":1332.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1332.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Factors has a relationship with LinkedIn.","index":355,"end_time":1334.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1332.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they have a capi where they''re able to identify this information.","index":356,"end_time":1337.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1334.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":357,"end_time":1339.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1338.59,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":358,"end_time":1339.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1339.31,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And why.","index":359,"end_time":1347.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1346.84,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So we have at click and add view.","index":360,"end_time":1349.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1347.64,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, they''re able to identify it just.","index":361,"end_time":1352,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1350.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Whether they view it.","index":362,"end_time":1353.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1352,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"It''s.","index":363,"end_time":1353.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.08,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Isn''t that just.","index":364,"end_time":1354.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.36,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean, don''t we know anyways how it is shown or to who it is shown?","index":365,"end_time":1360.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1355.48,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"We know to who it''s shown, but it''s.","index":366,"end_time":1362.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1360.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we''re still competing with other people running ads to that same audience.","index":367,"end_time":1367.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1362.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So knowing that we''re getting impressions is a good signal.","index":368,"end_time":1370.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1367.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":369,"end_time":1372.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1372.22,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I don''t get that.","index":370,"end_time":1373.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1372.62,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean, we need to know that we''re advertising to the people that we want to advertise to.","index":371,"end_time":1380.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1377.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re able to see like, hey, this, this is really built to help those conversations that we''ve had historically of we''ve been emailing this person for six months and then it seems like they randomly reached out to you guys.","index":372,"end_time":1391.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1380.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s like, actually we can set the stage that they viewed to 12 ads, they''ve seen 15 emails.","index":373,"end_time":1397.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1391.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All of that, some sort of logging, I guess.","index":374,"end_time":1399.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1397.67,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s everything in Supabase is being logged.","index":375,"end_time":1402.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1400.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the data is stored for up to a year.","index":376,"end_time":1404.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1403.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I was just, I was just wondering because, I mean, click ad click is straightforward to me.","index":377,"end_time":1413.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.83,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Like, okay, someone clicked on that ad and we need to know that somewhere.","index":378,"end_time":1418.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1413.23,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean, but what happens after someone clicks that ad?","index":379,"end_time":1422.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1418.99,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"He lands or she lands on our landing page, I guess.","index":380,"end_time":1425.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1422.31,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll have two different types of ads.","index":381,"end_time":1427.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1425.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a lead gen format on LinkedIn.","index":382,"end_time":1428.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1427.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they fill out the form directly without leaving LinkedIn.","index":383,"end_time":1431.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1429.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a lower barrier because the information''s already filled out for them.","index":384,"end_time":1435.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1432.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then there''s another ad that''ll take them to the landing page directly.","index":385,"end_time":1440.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1437.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you guys are already set up to get notifications from LinkedIn ads.","index":386,"end_time":1444.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, but in those cases, all of them, we do not take people out of our email campaign.","index":387,"end_time":1464.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1454.42,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"That makes no sense because maybe the chance is even higher that they answer correct.","index":388,"end_time":1470.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1465.22,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":389,"end_time":1472.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1471.3,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Can we go up again, please, just to see whether I missed something I wanted to see?","index":390,"end_time":1482.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1472.54,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I think.","index":391,"end_time":1487.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1487.23,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean, there is a lot of logic in smart lead itself.","index":392,"end_time":1495.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1492.03,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Right.","index":393,"end_time":1496.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.63,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So as far as I can see, And then I think for n, I''m good, but can you.","index":394,"end_time":1512.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1497.39,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Can you tell me or show me more about LinkedIn ad campaign and smart lead itself?","index":395,"end_time":1517.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1512.2,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I guess.","index":396,"end_time":1520.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1519.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Max, I''m pretty curious why we need to dive into all of these tools.","index":397,"end_time":1524.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1520.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So much to explain what is.","index":398,"end_time":1528.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1524.68,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean, I''m mainly here for the technical part and for the what is happening when and where.","index":399,"end_time":1534.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1528.44,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And I want to understand why.","index":400,"end_time":1538.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1535.13,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Like, for example, okay, when do we send emails, how many?","index":401,"end_time":1544.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1538.81,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And because we need to somehow also understand what is.","index":402,"end_time":1549.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1545.29,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"What is happening.","index":403,"end_time":1552.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1551.69,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So we can interpret the answers in the end or not the answer, but the results.","index":404,"end_time":1558.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1552.53,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Because, for example, if you just send one email a day is a whole different thing than sending 200.","index":405,"end_time":1563.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1559.3,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And also, I mean, in the end you will.","index":406,"end_time":1567.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1564.9,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"As I said, we have.","index":407,"end_time":1569.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1568.42,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"You have some reports then.","index":408,"end_time":1571.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1569.62,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, on a weekly basis.","index":409,"end_time":1572.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1571.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You also need to understand them.","index":410,"end_time":1574.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1572.66,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And also we want to think about how we can extend this later.","index":411,"end_time":1577.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1574.42,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Like, I mean, you''re also interested, I guess in follow up, so.","index":412,"end_time":1584.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1577.7,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"But we like understanding a lot and we don''t like someone doing something.","index":413,"end_time":1591.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1585.15,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"We don''t know what''s happening like this no matter how, and it just needs to work.","index":414,"end_time":1598.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1591.87,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"That''s not our way of thinking here.","index":415,"end_time":1599.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1598.15,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"That''s.","index":416,"end_time":1600.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1600.35,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s some cultural thing because in Germany most people are more like me.","index":417,"end_time":1605.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1600.91,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":418,"end_time":1607.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1606.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I don''t think we''ve ever like just said, it just happens.","index":419,"end_time":1612.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1607.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, it''s all built into pretty strong logic that we''ve built.","index":420,"end_time":1616.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1612.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, I mean I''ve probably set up 50 of these campaigns.","index":421,"end_time":1620.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1616.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":422,"end_time":1620.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1620.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean Smart Lead is, is.","index":423,"end_time":1623.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1622.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s pretty much just a cold email tool.","index":424,"end_time":1625.819,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1623.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You load in contacts and you set up a sequence so that it goes out on a regular basis.","index":425,"end_time":1631.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1625.819,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I can give you direct reports that the report does show you how many emails are going out on a weekly basis.","index":426,"end_time":1637.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1632.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it''s really just a processor.","index":427,"end_time":1641.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1639.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Same with Hate Reach.","index":428,"end_time":1644.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1643.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It just has some check whether an email should go out and then just sense.","index":429,"end_time":1652.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1646.59,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean it''s just, it''s a workflow logic.","index":430,"end_time":1655.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1652.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s like send email 1 and then 4 days later send email 2, 3 days later send email 3, 5 days later send email 4.","index":431,"end_time":1660.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1655.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And just if it has a check before whether.","index":432,"end_time":1663.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1661.07,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":433,"end_time":1665.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1665.41,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So there is not that much.","index":434,"end_time":1668.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1667.09,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":435,"end_time":1668.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1668.37,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And this LinkedIn ad campaign, I''m not sure.","index":436,"end_time":1672.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1670.21,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I think you, you did something before I went on to the project.","index":437,"end_time":1677.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1672.77,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So how is that even.","index":438,"end_time":1681.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1677.73,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I know that we are paying for it, but is it like we gave you access to our LinkedIn ads?","index":439,"end_time":1688.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1681.49,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":440,"end_time":1689.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1689.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re in your.","index":441,"end_time":1690.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1689.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You gave us a partner access into your LinkedIn ads account.","index":442,"end_time":1692.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1690.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":443,"end_time":1693.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1693.19,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So I can just log in and see.","index":444,"end_time":1696.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1693.63,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":445,"end_time":1696.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1696.23,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":446,"end_time":1697.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1697.27,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":447,"end_time":1698.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1697.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If your team''s added you to the account, then you can see it.","index":448,"end_time":1700.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1698.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":449,"end_time":1702.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1701.51,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Good.","index":450,"end_time":1705.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1704.87,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"We have two minutes left.","index":451,"end_time":1710.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1708.71,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, well, before I forget that.","index":452,"end_time":1713.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1712.07,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Thank you for the insights.","index":453,"end_time":1715.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1713.79,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, of course.","index":454,"end_time":1715.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1715.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s kind of, it''s really interesting for me to see how you did it.","index":455,"end_time":1722.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1717.11,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Like, because I mean, I like this pipeline thing.","index":456,"end_time":1727.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1724.32,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I''m doing stuff here and this automation is quite a good thing because I mean we never did, we never invest any time into this marketing stuff.","index":457,"end_time":1737.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1727.32,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"We had like one marketing person and that was mainly about building our website and like writing great LinkedIn blogs and stuff.","index":458,"end_time":1749.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1738.32,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Right.","index":459,"end_time":1750.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1749.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":460,"end_time":1750.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1750.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I think this should be at least more effective.","index":461,"end_time":1754.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1751.43,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And yeah, I''m happy, or I''m using the word here.","index":462,"end_time":1760.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1754.47,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I''M curious to see how it works out.","index":463,"end_time":1765.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1762.95,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, absolutely.","index":464,"end_time":1768.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1766.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we make tweaks pretty fast.","index":465,"end_time":1770.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1768.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I, I mean, we watch the data coming in.","index":466,"end_time":1772.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1770.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we''re not seeing people engaged, then we''ll update language, we''ll update landing pages, introduce new A B tests, things like that.","index":467,"end_time":1779.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1772.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":468,"end_time":1781.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1780.58,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So A B tests, where are they located?","index":469,"end_time":1785.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1782.58,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Are they also then located in N8N or is that some of the.","index":470,"end_time":1789.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1785.1,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Well, it depend on the channel.","index":471,"end_time":1790.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1789.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like if we''re testing a new email, we would get you guys to approve it and then we would load it into smart lead.","index":472,"end_time":1795.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If it''s a new email or if it''s a new hey, reach me message, we would load it there a new ad, etc.","index":473,"end_time":1799.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it''s based on the reports first and then we.","index":474,"end_time":1802.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1799.7,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So the reports know which, which ads or which email.","index":475,"end_time":1808.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1803.14,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"How do you call it?","index":476,"end_time":1810.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1808.98,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, like the content they.","index":477,"end_time":1813.379,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1812.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That they''ve engaged with.","index":478,"end_time":1814.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1813.379,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":479,"end_time":1815.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1814.7,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":480,"end_time":1816.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1815.98,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":481,"end_time":1818.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1817.94,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"All right, I do have to bounce to my next meeting, but if you have any other questions, feel free to reach out.","index":482,"end_time":1823.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1818.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Otherwise, I will see you tomorrow morning.","index":483,"end_time":1824.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1823.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, morning my time.","index":484,"end_time":1825.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1824.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Afternoon.","index":485,"end_time":1826.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1825.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":486,"end_time":1827.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1827.43,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"It would be great if you could send me the five lines.","index":487,"end_time":1830.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1827.99,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yes.","index":488,"end_time":1830.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1830.47,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I will make a note.","index":489,"end_time":1832.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1830.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m back to bag for the next about five hours, but I will try.","index":490,"end_time":1835.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1832.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To get this to you.","index":491,"end_time":1835.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1835.07,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":492,"end_time":1836.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1835.67,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"We can look at them tomorrow.","index":493,"end_time":1838.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1837.11,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":494,"end_time":1839.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1839.19,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you, Max.","index":495,"end_time":1842.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1840.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":496,"end_time":1842.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1842.15,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Have a nice day.","index":497,"end_time":1843.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1842.79,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Bye.","index":498,"end_time":1843.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1843.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You too.","index":499,"end_time":1844.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1843.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2026-02-05T14:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83161830993?pwd=59osuMxQ5a65WM4Y6ghubtkRJrpPqh.1","participants":["rabeler@data-assessment.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","rabeler@data-assessment.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KGJ5VPJJEW20248QFR7SA8PS","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.88,"bullets":["Confirmed Smart Lead and Heyreach campaigns are ready; launch can begin when approved.","Explained automated email logic and sentiment-based routing; positive replies notify Axle.","Validated GDPR-compliant company-level tracking using Factors AI and Supabase integration.","Clarified reporting cadence; weekly summary includes email counts and top engaged accounts.","Aligned on A/B test process; variants tracked through campaign tools and informed by reports."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We make tweaks pretty fast...update language, landing pages, A/B tests.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I like this pipeline thing...this automation is quite a good thing.","speaker":"Maximilian Rabeler"}],"topics":["delivery","automation","tracking","reporting"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-02-05T21:37:17Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Email and LinkedIn Campaign Execution**\n\nThe campaign is ready to launch immediately once final email signature feedback is approved, sending up to **240-250 emails daily** across **six warmed-up domains** to a target list of **200 contacts** (04:50).\n\n- **Emails and LinkedIn messages flow automatically** from Clay into Smart Lead and Heyreach, with Smart Lead handling emails and Heyreach sending LinkedIn connection requests and follow-ups (02:28).\n- Positive email replies trigger sentiment analysis using an AI model based on GPT-4.1 mini, achieving near **99% accuracy**, and prompt internal Slack and email notifications to Axle for quick team follow-up (09:17).\n- Unsubscribes and email bounces are tracked and recorded in Supabase, with bounce addresses verified through **six providers** upfront to minimize invalid contacts; weekly manual checks ensure data quality and automation flow (12:20).\n- Follow-up emails are scheduled in Smart Lead with specific delays, such as sending the second email **3-4 days** after the first, only if no reply or unsubscribe occurs, with HubSpot updated via private app integration to manage contact status and next steps (13:58).\n\n## **CRM and Data Integration**\n\nHubSpot is used as a CRM to track email engagement but does not send cold emails, relying on data pushes from the automation system with create-or-update logic keyed by email address (08:05).\n\n- HubSpot records email send events, replies, unsubscribes, and bounces through JSON payloads sent by N8N workflows, allowing the team to monitor campaign status and contact engagement centrally (07:46).\n- LinkedIn message replies and connection acceptances are not stored in HubSpot but logged in Supabase and notified directly to Bettina via LinkedIn and internal alerts; this separation maintains CRM cleanliness and respects platform limits (17:35).\n- Supabase acts as the campaign’s central database storing all webhook events, including email and LinkedIn actions, with data retention of up to **one year** to support reporting and performance analysis (16:56).\n\n## **Lead Scoring and Website Engagement Tracking**\n\nFactors AI provides GDPR-compliant company-level website visitor deanonymization and LinkedIn ad interaction tracking to enrich lead scoring and engagement insights (15:30).\n\n- Company visits, ad views, and ad clicks on LinkedIn are captured via Factors'' CAPI integration, correlating these events with email campaign contacts to identify highly engaged accounts (19:49).\n- Lead scores increase when a company visits the website multiple times or interacts with LinkedIn ads, enabling personalized email triggers for contacts at companies showing strong interest but no direct replies (16:11).\n- Weekly reports generated from Supabase highlight top engaged companies and aggregate weekly email/message volumes, helping the team prioritize outreach and optimize campaign content (20:27).\n\n## **Campaign Monitoring, Reporting, and Optimization**\n\nThe system provides comprehensive weekly reports detailing email volumes, engagement metrics, and ad interactions to inform content and targeting decisions (26:11).\n\n- Colin emphasized the importance of transparency and understanding the flow and volume of emails to properly interpret campaign responses and results (25:19).\n- A/B testing is planned across channels, with new email versions, LinkedIn messages, and ads introduced based on report-driven insights and team approvals before deployment into Smart Lead or Heyreach (29:26).\n- Rapid iteration on messaging and landing pages is possible, with the team monitoring engagement closely and adjusting language or offers to improve conversion rates continuously (29:40).\n\n## **Technical Workflow and Automation Architecture**\n\nThe campaign automation uses N8N for orchestrating webhook processing that routes events from Smart Lead and Heyreach into HubSpot and Supabase, enforcing routing logic based on email sent, reply, unsubscribe, or bounce events (02:57).\n\n- Webhooks trigger updates in real time, ensuring contact records reflect the latest engagement status and that positive replies prompt immediate team notification to accelerate follow-up (06:22).\n- The system employs a multi-step workflow where each contact’s interaction with the campaign determines subsequent actions, avoiding duplicate sends and ensuring compliance with opt-out requests (06:54).\n- Integration between LinkedIn ads and campaign systems is secured via partner access to the client’s LinkedIn Ads account, enabling direct access for reporting and campaign management without data silos (28:09).\n\n## **Strategic Context and Team Perspectives**\n\nMaximilian expressed strong interest in understanding every technical detail for full transparency and control, reflecting a culture valuing thorough knowledge over “black box” solutions (25:19).\n\n- Colin reassured that the campaign uses proven logic from around **50 prior campaigns**, emphasizing reliability and experience while remaining open to fast adjustments based on data (26:46).\n- The team views this automation as a major step up from prior marketing efforts focused on website and content alone, aiming for more effective outreach through data-driven, automated multi-channel touchpoints (28:37).\n- Ownership for ongoing monitoring and weekly data reviews lies with the internal team, with Colin offering continued support and quick iteration capabilities to optimize campaign success (30:18).","outline":null,"keywords":["Email Campaign","LinkedIn Messaging","Smart Lead","HubSpot CRM","Factors AI","Supabase Database"],"overview":"- **Email Campaign Launch:** Ready to send **240-250 emails daily** to **200 contacts** once final email signature is approved.  \n- **Automated Workflow:** Emails and LinkedIn messages flow from Clay to Smart Lead and Heyreach; tracking for unsubscribes and bounces in Supabase.  \n- **Data Recording & Management:** HubSpot tracks engagement, while Supabase logs LinkedIn replies and stores campaign data for one year.  \n- **Lead Scoring Mechanism:** Company interactions with ads or multiple site visits increase lead scores, prompting personalized email triggers.  \n- **Weekly Reporting System:** Comprehensive reports detail engagement metrics, assisting the team in optimizing outreach strategies and content.  \n- **Automation Infrastructure:** N8N manages webhook events, ensuring real-time updates on engagement, avoiding duplicates, and maintaining compliance.","action_items":"\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nReview the detailed workflow documentation once received from Colin (30:35)\nAccess LinkedIn Ads account using provided partner access to monitor ad performance (28:13)\nCheck Firefly notes and request access if necessary to maintain visibility of contact activity (15:16)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nFinalize email signature adjustments based on Bettina’s feedback to enable campaign launch (01:34)\nSend a summary or five-line documentation of the campaign flow and integrations for Maximilian’s review (30:27)\nMonitor campaign data weekly in Supabase, including unsubscribes and bounces, and ensure proper updating of CRM and databases (12:18)\nProvide direct email and LinkedIn campaign reports on weekly engagement and send those reports to Maximilian as part of ongoing updates (20:20)\nContinue refining campaign copy, landing pages, and A/B tests based on analysis of engagement data (29:26)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"2978947e-1e14-418f-8567-408e4a5667d3","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
