INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Sync on Marketing Tools',
  '## **Email and LinkedIn Campaign Execution**

The campaign is ready to launch immediately once final email signature feedback is approved, sending up to **240-250 emails daily** across **six warmed-up domains** to a target list of **200 contacts** (04:50).

- **Emails and LinkedIn messages flow automatically** from Clay into Smart Lead and Heyreach, with Smart Lead handling emails and Heyreach sending LinkedIn connection requests and follow-ups (02:28).
- Positive email replies trigger sentiment analysis using an AI model based on GPT-4.1 mini, achieving near **99% accuracy**, and prompt internal Slack and email notifications to Axle for quick team follow-up (09:17).
- Unsubscribes and email bounces are tracked and recorded in Supabase, with bounce addresses verified through **six providers** upfront to minimize invalid contacts; weekly manual checks ensure data quality and automation flow (12:20).
- Follow-up emails are scheduled in Smart Lead with specific delays, such as sending the second email **3-4 days** after the first, only if no reply or unsubscribe occurs, with HubSpot updated via private app integration to manage contact status and next steps (13:58).

## **CRM and Data Integration**

HubSpot is used as a CRM to track email engagement but does not send cold emails, relying on data pushes from the automation system with create-or-update logic keyed by email address (08:05).

- HubSpot records email send events, replies, unsubscribes, and bounces through JSON payloads sent by N8N workflows, allowing the team to monitor campaign status and contact engagement centrally (07:46).
- LinkedIn message replies and connection acceptances are not stored in HubSpot but logged in Supabase and notified directly to Bettina via LinkedIn and internal alerts; this separation maintains CRM cleanliness and respects platform limits (17:35).
- Supabase acts as the campaign’s central database storing all webhook events, including email and LinkedIn actions, with data retention of up to **one year** to support reporting and performance analysis (16:56).

## **Lead Scoring and Website Engagement Tracking**

Factors AI provides GDPR-compliant company-level website visitor deanonymization and LinkedIn ad interaction tracking to enrich lead scoring and engagement insights (15:30).

- Company visits, ad views, and ad clicks on LinkedIn are captured via Factors'' CAPI integration, correlating these events with email campaign contacts to identify highly engaged accounts (19:49).
- Lead scores increase when a company visits the website multiple times or interacts with LinkedIn ads, enabling personalized email triggers for contacts at companies showing strong interest but no direct replies (16:11).
- Weekly reports generated from Supabase highlight top engaged companies and aggregate weekly email/message volumes, helping the team prioritize outreach and optimize campaign content (20:27).

## **Campaign Monitoring, Reporting, and Optimization**

The system provides comprehensive weekly reports detailing email volumes, engagement metrics, and ad interactions to inform content and targeting decisions (26:11).

- Colin emphasized the importance of transparency and understanding the flow and volume of emails to properly interpret campaign responses and results (25:19).
- A/B testing is planned across channels, with new email versions, LinkedIn messages, and ads introduced based on report-driven insights and team approvals before deployment into Smart Lead or Heyreach (29:26).
- Rapid iteration on messaging and landing pages is possible, with the team monitoring engagement closely and adjusting language or offers to improve conversion rates continuously (29:40).

## **Technical Workflow and Automation Architecture**

The campaign automation uses N8N for orchestrating webhook processing that routes events from Smart Lead and Heyreach into HubSpot and Supabase, enforcing routing logic based on email sent, reply, unsubscribe, or bounce events (02:57).

- Webhooks trigger updates in real time, ensuring contact records reflect the latest engagement status and that positive replies prompt immediate team notification to accelerate follow-up (06:22).
- The system employs a multi-step workflow where each contact’s interaction with the campaign determines subsequent actions, avoiding duplicate sends and ensuring compliance with opt-out requests (06:54).
- Integration between LinkedIn ads and campaign systems is secured via partner access to the client’s LinkedIn Ads account, enabling direct access for reporting and campaign management without data silos (28:09).

## **Strategic Context and Team Perspectives**

Maximilian expressed strong interest in understanding every technical detail for full transparency and control, reflecting a culture valuing thorough knowledge over “black box” solutions (25:19).

- Colin reassured that the campaign uses proven logic from around **50 prior campaigns**, emphasizing reliability and experience while remaining open to fast adjustments based on data (26:46).
- The team views this automation as a major step up from prior marketing efforts focused on website and content alone, aiming for more effective outreach through data-driven, automated multi-channel touchpoints (28:37).
- Ownership for ongoing monitoring and weekly data reviews lies with the internal team, with Colin offering continued support and quick iteration capabilities to optimize campaign success (30:18).',
  '2026-02-05 14:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Review the detailed workflow documentation once received from Colin (30:35)","completed":false},{"text":"Access LinkedIn Ads account using provided partner access to monitor ad performance (28:13)","completed":false},{"text":"Check Firefly notes and request access if necessary to maintain visibility of contact activity (15:16)","completed":false},{"text":"Finalize email signature adjustments based on Bettina’s feedback to enable campaign launch (01:34)","completed":false},{"text":"Send a summary or five-line documentation of the campaign flow and integrations for Maximilian’s review (30:27)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor campaign data weekly in Supabase, including unsubscribes and bounces, and ensure proper updating of CRM and databases (12:18)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide direct email and LinkedIn campaign reports on weekly engagement and send those reports to Maximilian as part of ongoing updates (20:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue refining campaign copy, landing pages, and A/B tests based on analysis of engagement data (29:26)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
