-- Meeting: Aligned Growth Engine | Roadmap Meeting (2026-02-04 20:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'e50afe94-037e-49d6-8f2e-8c05ac7e3294',
    '2026-02-04 20:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KG58N6PWHZ5SKC534HYEKMYP',
    'Aligned Growth Engine | Roadmap Meeting',
    '{"lenforkas","ozzie","Justin Brown","Colin Costigan","oswaldoreyes-chica","matt f"}'::text[],
    4009,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86761224184?pwd=6XHa7isEgCFC6vLLbNwKiA78umTD9e.1',
    '{"id":"01KG58N6PWHZ5SKC534HYEKMYP","title":"Aligned Growth Engine | Roadmap Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Strategy and Competitive Positioning**\n\nThe team agreed on a tailored marketing roadmap leveraging the low competitive presence in paid advertising to build brand and lead generation momentum. (02:05)\n\n- **Colin Costigan** highlighted that major competitors **Tower Co, Diamond, and Everest** score a **1 out of 10** in paid advertising presence, creating a strong opportunity to capture market share with a strategic paid media approach focused on LinkedIn and targeted digital channels.\n- Competitors rely heavily on organic social media, with Tower Co having over **6,000 followers**, about **10.5 times** Milestone Towers’ **586 followers**, but lack paid ads, signaling an untapped area to reach decision makers.\n- Milestone Towers’ positioning as a **municipal partnership specialist** with over **25 years of experience** and transparent community engagement offers a key differentiator to leverage in marketing content and messaging.\n- The customer psychology insight showed municipal decision makers focus on **budget shortfalls and community opposition**, not just infrastructure needs, aligning well with Milestone’s value proposition to mitigate risk through transparent engagement.\n\n## **Target Market and Ideal Customer Profiles**\n\nThe team confirmed clear target accounts and personas focusing on wireless carriers, municipal governments, and public school systems, with a split of qualified leads expected from these segments. (11:54)\n\n- Target accounts primarily include **national and regional wireless carriers** like **T-Mobile, AT&T, and Verizon**, with focus on east coast markets and regional leadership teams as primary contacts.\n- The municipal segment targets **municipal governments and public school systems**, represented by personas such as **David Martinez, a fictional facilities director** facing budget cuts and community opposition.\n- A smaller but important segment includes **fire departments and emergency management agencies**, acting more as project supporters than decision makers.\n- The team agreed on a **60% carrier-sourced and 40% municipal-sourced split** for qualified inquiries, emphasizing decision makers with active coverage or property development needs.\n\n## **Annual Goals and Lead Generation Targets**\n\nThe agreed annual goal is to build a predictable pipeline reaching **12 qualified inquiries per month by month 12**, focusing on decision makers within the defined target accounts. (24:51)\n\n- These inquiries must represent **validated needs** from wireless carriers, municipalities, or school districts in the service areas, with discovery calls scheduled as a key conversion step.\n- The ramp-up expects gradual growth, targeting **6 inquiries per month by month 6**, scaling to **12 per month by month 12**, with flexibility based on business flow.\n- The team viewed **12 inquiries per month** as realistic and aligned with internal expectations, assuming that qualified leads will convert to real projects.\n- The split of inquiries includes both new business development and maintaining existing customer relationships, addressing both wireless customers and municipal owners.\n\n## **Marketing Tactics and Budget Allocation**\n\nThe marketing approach involves phased content creation, account-based marketing (ABM), and light paid advertising as a retargeting layer, with a monthly budget of **$6,000 for agency services plus $500 to $2,000 for ad spend**, starting cautiously in month two or three. (30:31)\n\n- Content production includes launching an **educational content and case study library**, web page updates, pitch decks, and potentially a monthly video series featuring carriers and municipal contacts.\n- Paid media will serve primarily as a **retargeting and brand awareness layer** supporting direct outreach rather than broad direct response ads, focusing on LinkedIn and targeted digital platforms.\n- The agency will build and manage marketing infrastructure using tools like **Clay, B2B, Factors, Supabase, and N8N** to collect engagement data, track lead signals, and integrate with Salesforce for lead management.\n- The team prioritized content creation and ABM over heavy ad spend initially, agreeing on testing lower ad budgets and scaling based on return on investment.\n\n## **Sales and Outreach Integration**\n\nDirect engagement and cold calling by internal teams remain the primary lead generation method, with marketing efforts designed to support and validate outreach through content and targeted ads. (44:54)\n\n- Lenforkas emphasized that **new opportunities come from hard-to-get sites and municipalities where competition is weak**, making trust and expertise critical selling points.\n- Ads and email campaigns will target prospects pre- and post-outreach to build familiarity and improve conversion rates, creating a “drum beat” of consistent brand presence.\n- Using AI tools, the agency can provide **contact-level engagement data** to prioritize follow-up calls and tailor outreach efforts based on prospect behavior.\n- Matt expressed that the marketing tech stack might be **overkill for the small, focused municipal and carrier contact lists**, suggesting the infrastructure is better suited for scaling to larger private landowner audiences.\n\n## **Emerging PR Challenge and Content Strategy**\n\nThe team identified an urgent need to prepare for an upcoming **federal-level PR challenge related to health concerns over cell towers near schools**, requiring proactive content and communication support. (57:11)\n\n- Lenforkas explained that the **Environmental Health Trust**, funded by **RFK Jr.**, will release a report this spring potentially restricting tower siting near schools due to alleged health risks.\n- This poses a risk to Milestone Towers’ core market and brand, necessitating early education and advocacy to “immunize” school partners against misinformation.\n- The marketing agency was asked to allocate points toward **reactive content creation and PR support** focused on countering negative narratives and protecting existing partnerships.\n- Matt prioritized a flexible point allocation between **content production, ABM outreach, and reactive PR efforts**, emphasizing the need to balance ongoing lead generation with emergent brand defense without increasing overall budget.","outline":null,"keywords":["Marketing roadmap","account-based marketing","paid media strategy","municipal targeting","competitive analysis","content creation"],"overview":"- **Marketing Opportunity:** Major competitors score low in paid ads, creating a chance for Milestone Towers to capture market share.\n\n- **Target Accounts:** Focus on wireless carriers, municipal governments, and public schools, with a lead split of 60% carriers and 40% municipalities.\n\n- **Annual Goal:** Aim for 12 qualified inquiries per month by month 12, starting with 6 by month 6 to ensure steady growth.\n\n- **Marketing Tactics:** Initial budget of $6,000 monthly for agency services, plus up to $2,000 for targeted ads, focusing on content and ABM.\n\n- **PR Challenge:** Urgent preparation needed for potential federal PR issues related to health concerns over cell towers near schools. \n\n- **Engagement Strategy:** Direct outreach supported by ads, with AI tools to enhance follow-up with prospects based on engagement data.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend marketing research document and roadmap overview to Milestone Towers for review (07:13)\nPrepare and share detailed marketing roadmap and points system breakdown for client feedback (55:30)\nSchedule follow-up meeting to discuss roadmap iterations and next steps, proposing times and accommodating participants'' availability (01:05:57)\n\n**Justin Brown**\nSupport preparation of content infrastructure including case studies, video series, outreach sequences, and marketing operations (31:00)\nClarify marketing engagement approach focusing on combined outreach, retargeting ads, and tracking engagement signals (48:26)\nCoordinate sending follow-up meeting invitations and ensure agenda includes iterative planning on content vs performance marketing balance (01:05:57)\n\n**Matt Forkas**\nReview and assess proposed point system deliverables and three-month marketing plan detailing content creation, outreach, and ABM activities (54:40)\nProvide feedback on priority areas including potential emphasis on content creation to support ongoing outreach and prepare for political/PR concerns (01:02:35)\nShare additional insight into internal lead generation practices, contacting relevant municipal and carrier decision makers (45:26)\n\n**Len Forkas**\nContinue prioritizing direct engagement and cold calling with carriers and municipalities and provide target lists as needed for marketing targeting (45:10)\nAlert the marketing team about upcoming political/PR issues and work collaboratively on messaging and educational content to prepare partners (57:00)\n\n**Oswaldo Reyes-Chica**\nCollaborate on validating qualified lead criteria and helping structure key performance indicators for inquiry quality and conversion (42:50)\nParticipate in roadmap review and contribute perspective on internal expectations and alignment on lead targets (50:02)\n"},"duration":66.80999755859375,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"lenforkas"},{"id":1,"name":"ozzie"},{"id":2,"name":"Justin Brown"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"id":5,"name":"matt f"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Well, hey, Colin.","index":0,"end_time":1.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.96,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":1,"end_time":2.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.56,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"All right.","index":2,"end_time":2.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2.32,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":3,"end_time":3.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Doing just fine, thank you.","index":4,"end_time":5.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.92,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Are you still.","index":5,"end_time":6.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":5.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Were you in the Dominican Republic?","index":6,"end_time":8.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":7.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Am I remembering that correctly?","index":7,"end_time":10,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":8.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s where I am right now.","index":8,"end_time":11.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.4,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":9,"end_time":12.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":11.72,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"How''s that going?","index":10,"end_time":13.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":12.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, good.","index":11,"end_time":14.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.84,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"I kind of bounce back and forth between here and Northern Virginia in the winter.","index":12,"end_time":17.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14.36,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":13,"end_time":18.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":18.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely a good way to avoid, you know, over a foot of snow.","index":14,"end_time":22.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":18.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, it''s.","index":15,"end_time":25.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":23.92,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"I had.","index":16,"end_time":26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":25.36,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I was.","index":17,"end_time":26.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"I was there last Monday to Monday to Saturday, so I suffer with everybody else.","index":18,"end_time":31.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.8,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And we moved our offices, too, so we moved into a larger office space, so that was part of the reason, too.","index":19,"end_time":36.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.44,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So.","index":20,"end_time":37.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":36.84,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":21,"end_time":37.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":37.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":22,"end_time":38.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":37.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, hello.","index":23,"end_time":41.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":40.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":24,"end_time":43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":42.12,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Going.","index":25,"end_time":44.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":44.36,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"All right.","index":26,"end_time":46.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":45.959,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"This is going to be our team today.","index":27,"end_time":49.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":47.64,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Tristan had a child situation arise.","index":28,"end_time":56.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":50.92,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I told him he was good, but the way you said that, it kind of sounded like he had a new child.","index":29,"end_time":60.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":56.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was just.","index":30,"end_time":60.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":60.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was.","index":31,"end_time":61.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":60.92,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I. I don''t.","index":32,"end_time":62.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":61.86,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Like.","index":33,"end_time":62.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":62.3,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It wasn''t even, like, a big deal.","index":34,"end_time":64.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":62.58,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I just, like.","index":35,"end_time":64.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":64.18,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I never know what information you''re allowed, like, you''re supposed to put out for other people.","index":36,"end_time":68.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":64.78,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"He can''t make it, but it''s okay.","index":37,"end_time":70.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":68.66,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Colin and I put this entire thing together anyway, so I told him it''s all good.","index":38,"end_time":74.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":70.14,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Anyway, column, if you want to jump in.","index":39,"end_time":77.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":75.06,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Is this gonna be everybody today?","index":40,"end_time":78.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":77.58,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Is Ozzy gonna be joining us?","index":41,"end_time":79.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":78.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Can''t hear you.","index":42,"end_time":83.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":82.58,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"L. You''re mute.","index":43,"end_time":84.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":83.26,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"He''s.","index":44,"end_time":85.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":84.74,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"He''s working on an RFP that''s due tomorrow, so he''s going to be a little occupied today.","index":45,"end_time":89.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":85.3,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So you just get.","index":46,"end_time":90.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":89.64,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"You just have me, Matt, and S. All right, Sounds good.","index":47,"end_time":94.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":90.56,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"I think he''s here.","index":48,"end_time":95.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":94.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh.","index":49,"end_time":97.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":97.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, there he is.","index":50,"end_time":99.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":98.36,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Hey, ozzy.","index":51,"end_time":105.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":104.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":52,"end_time":112.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":111.72,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Good afternoon.","index":53,"end_time":112.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":112.08,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I apologize.","index":54,"end_time":113.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":112.72,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I''m going to have to be mob on this reschedule during pickup, so no worries.","index":55,"end_time":119.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":113.36,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"All right, can everyone see my screen?","index":56,"end_time":123.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":121.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":57,"end_time":124.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":123.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":58,"end_time":124.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":124.22,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"All right.","index":59,"end_time":126.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":125.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So great to see everyone.","index":60,"end_time":129.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":127.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you again for making the time for this.","index":61,"end_time":130.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":129.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So today we''re going to walk through some stuff that will feel familiar to you guys as experts in your industry, but will also feel new at the same time.","index":62,"end_time":140.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":131.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Over the past few weeks of us working together, some of the information that you guys have shared, the conversations we''ve had, the deep research analysis that we''ve run, we''ve translated that into what we call a marketing roadmap, and it''s designed specifically for how your business actually operates.","index":63,"end_time":155.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":140.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I want to frame this a little bit as, you know, during a lot of conversations.","index":64,"end_time":162.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":157.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Matt, mainly that you had with Tristan, but even early on in our kickoff and alignment meetings that we''ve had, I know you guys have tried some different things from marketing approach.","index":65,"end_time":170.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":162.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Haven''t always had a, you know, a great scenario or great output from those things.","index":66,"end_time":176.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":170.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it wasn''t that you just needed more strategy.","index":67,"end_time":180.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":178.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You need marketing execution to align with that strategy and ultimately to align with business priorities.","index":68,"end_time":185.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":180.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I like to toss analogies out there.","index":69,"end_time":188.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":185.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If this one is too on the nose, please let me know.","index":70,"end_time":191.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":188.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I say think of this as building like a tower infrastructure project.","index":71,"end_time":196.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":191.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you''re not going to start by pouring the concrete everywhere and just hoping that it works.","index":72,"end_time":200.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":196.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re going to start with, you know, your site analysis.","index":73,"end_time":202.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":200.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You need to understand the terrain, you have to identify the right locations and then you''re able to execute with more precision.","index":74,"end_time":207.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":202.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hopefully I nailed that with you guys as ACT experts in that space.","index":75,"end_time":210.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":207.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Get nods.","index":76,"end_time":214.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":213.91,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":77,"end_time":217.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":216.79,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"10 out of 10.","index":78,"end_time":218.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":217.27,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":79,"end_time":220.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":219.43,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So how, how we''ll spend our time today is going through five main areas.","index":80,"end_time":224.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":220.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll do a quick overview going through your guys target market, your positioning, a bit of the competitive landscape, more to set the context for the rest of our conversation.","index":81,"end_time":234.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":224.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We always want to make sure we''re on the same page about who we''re talking to and what makes you guys different.","index":82,"end_time":239.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":234.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Second, we''ll dive into the roadma itself.","index":83,"end_time":242.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":240.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the annual goal that we''ve put together, the first quarter''s initiatives and the actual plan, we''ve put together a line item by line item of the first three months of the work that we want to accomplish if we do move forward.","index":84,"end_time":253.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":242.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll also go through the research document.","index":85,"end_time":256.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":253.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s 121 pages of competitive intelligence, customer psychology, market analysis.","index":86,"end_time":263.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":257.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not going to read you every page of that report today.","index":87,"end_time":266.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":263.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t read that fast.","index":88,"end_time":267.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":266.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But instead think of it as like the foundation that we''ve poured.","index":89,"end_time":271.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":268.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to be building on top of this.","index":90,"end_time":273.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":271.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So any questions before we get started here?","index":91,"end_time":276.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":274.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":92,"end_time":279.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":279.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so you know, we''ve talked a little bit about how we deliver in our relationships.","index":93,"end_time":287.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":281.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just to quickly go back over this, we work in a six phase process.","index":94,"end_time":292.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":287.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Phase one through three is what we''ve just done.","index":95,"end_time":296.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":292.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re actually familiar guys.","index":96,"end_time":298.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":296.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, they just went through eos.","index":97,"end_time":300.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":298.59,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So you got to have your proven process.","index":98,"end_time":302.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":300.83,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":99,"end_time":304.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":303.95,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I''m sure you''ve seen things that look very similar to this.","index":100,"end_time":307.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.51,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You know Wickman.","index":101,"end_time":309.79,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":308.75,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Yeah, no, you know G, we, we do try to run EOS basically by the book here.","index":102,"end_time":318.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":310.27,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''ve worked with three implementers over the course of my career and we find that rolling them out, rolling that system out not only for the way that we work as a leadership team, but also the way that we work with our clients tends to be very successful.","index":103,"end_time":334.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":319.39,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So working in quarterly segments, revisiting things on monthly and weekly basis, so on and so forth.","index":104,"end_time":340.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":334.58,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But sorry to jump in there, Colin.","index":105,"end_time":342.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":340.78,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"No, no, you''re, you''re, you''re all good.","index":106,"end_time":344.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":342.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":107,"end_time":344.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":344.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So definitely mirrors the EOS framework you guys are familiar with.","index":108,"end_time":348.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":344.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, quarterly rocks and annual goals and how everything ladders up to each other.","index":109,"end_time":351.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":348.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I was saying is we are right now in step three and wrapping up step three at the conclusion of this call.","index":110,"end_time":358.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":352.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So phases one through three, that''s where I asked you guys a bunch of questions.","index":111,"end_time":362.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":359.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys gave us some data, we conducted a bunch of research, and now we''re entering into this roadmap.","index":112,"end_time":368.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":362.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Phases 5 and 6, 4, 5 and 6 are really where we write.","index":113,"end_time":372.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":368.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, here''s the, the approach for abm, for example, of what we would do.","index":114,"end_time":375.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":372.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or here''s the approach for paid media.","index":115,"end_time":377.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":375.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then on a regular basis executing so creating new landing pages, creating content and then analyzing how that''s performing on a regular bas, and tweaking the actual outputs that we''re creating based on that data that''s coming back to us.","index":116,"end_time":389.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":377.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions about how we work or are structured?","index":117,"end_time":394.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":391.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I do want to touch a little bit on the marketing research overview.","index":118,"end_time":402.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":398.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like I said, I''m not going to read through everything, but we''ll send this over for you guys to have.","index":119,"end_time":406.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":402.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s got a table of contents so you can quickly distill where you want to dive into.","index":120,"end_time":412.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":407.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''ve got market overviews, industry dynamics, customer insights, competitive landscape, and then we also do a very deep competitor analysis going through how they perform on SEO social media, how their brand positions themselves, what they''re doing from a paid perspective, and their overall content strategy.","index":121,"end_time":433.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":412.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All very useful for building what should be done for milestone at a high level.","index":122,"end_time":440.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":433.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve used multiple AI models.","index":123,"end_time":442.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":441.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We actually use four LLMs to scrape websites and do a bunch of research and pull all of these into a framework that we''ve developed in house.","index":124,"end_time":451.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":442.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, analyzing paid LinkedIn presence, anything that they''re doing really out in the market.","index":125,"end_time":457.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":451.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ve also studied your customer psychology.","index":126,"end_time":459.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":457.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what''s motivating?","index":127,"end_time":461.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":460.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s say a facility director in a school district, what''s keeping them up at night?","index":128,"end_time":465.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":461.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or how are carriers making their site acquisition decisions?","index":129,"end_time":468.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":466.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we found some pretty open holes as far as the competitive landscape.","index":130,"end_time":475.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":470.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All three of your major competitors, so Tower Co, diamond and Everest they actually have a 1 out of 10 on our metrics for paid advertising.","index":131,"end_time":484.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":475.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They are very, very minimally present if present at all in most B2B markets.","index":132,"end_time":491.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":484.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys want to run ads you guys are playing with a lot of kids in the sandbox.","index":133,"end_time":495.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":491.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re paying a lot more money per whatever that conversion is.","index":134,"end_time":498.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":495.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there is a large opportunity there as well from the customer psychology standpoint.","index":135,"end_time":505.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":499.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So found that municipal decision makers aren''t really waking up thinking I need a tower developed today.","index":136,"end_time":510.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":505.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re thinking their budget is in a shortfall.","index":137,"end_time":513.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":510.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They have community pressure and that is really where we can tie into your guys value proposition of connecting to those deeper concerns.","index":138,"end_time":521.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":513.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So where they''re worried about is this going to blow up in my face?","index":139,"end_time":524.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":522.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your guys community, your transparent community engagement approach really fits in well here.","index":140,"end_time":530.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":525.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you''re not just selling the infrastructure but you''re selling how we can mitigate that potential risk.","index":141,"end_time":534.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":530.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Third, you guys have a very strong positioning advantage.","index":142,"end_time":538.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":535.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Tower co positions himself as coast to coast diamond positions themselves as mainly with school districts working with programmatic scale.","index":143,"end_time":547.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":538.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you guys are a little bit more positioned as the municipal partnership specialist handling very difficult or complex projects and then everything else is really going to be in here.","index":144,"end_time":560.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":547.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what this all culminates into is this is giving us our roadmap.","index":145,"end_time":564.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":560.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can be a mover in the paid media space.","index":146,"end_time":567.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":564.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s not a lot of competition there.","index":147,"end_time":568.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":567.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There are things that we can take advantage of and then building case studies that prove how you deliver, getting a presence across social media, making sure that your guys brand and positioning is out there.","index":148,"end_time":577.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":568.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s just a lot of opportunities in the market that we''ve uncovered.","index":149,"end_time":580.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":578.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know, I just went on like a five minute monologue there so I''ll take a break.","index":150,"end_time":585.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":581.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions?","index":151,"end_time":586.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":585.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no question.","index":152,"end_time":591.92,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":591.2,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"It''s not surprising that you know our competitors have a, a low ranking on, on ad spend and presence on I guess whatever channels you may have researched, Google Ads or LinkedIn.","index":153,"end_time":603.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":591.92,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Um, I think it you know if there''s space for us to participate in that I think that''s great.","index":154,"end_time":610.52,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":604.44,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"But it also validates that the, the industry just operates just in a very old legacy world of, of getting business done.","index":155,"end_time":619.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":610.52,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"You know it''s like their, their visibility on LinkedIn is just you know we built this tower or like it''s, it''s Christmas, you know.","index":156,"end_time":628.92,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":619.72,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Here you go, here''s a picture of our team.","index":157,"end_time":630.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":628.92,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So yeah, that''s not surprising but could be a good avenue to explore further.","index":158,"end_time":636.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":632.37,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":159,"end_time":637.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":636.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the really cool show up more.","index":160,"end_time":638.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":637.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly, exactly.","index":161,"end_time":640.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":638.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You Just hit the nail on the head Matt.","index":162,"end_time":641.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":640.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s cheaper.","index":163,"end_time":642.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":641.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can play around in that sandbox and see kind of what structure we can build, what we''re able to grab out of that for prospects and engagement and everything like that for, for very low spend compared to most B2B companies.","index":164,"end_time":655.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":642.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean we had somebody during project management technology space came to us and they''re like we want to do paid ads.","index":165,"end_time":665.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":657.42,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like you know your competitors.","index":166,"end_time":668.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":666.54,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"First off they''re heavily funded.","index":167,"end_time":670.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":668.46,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Second off they lose money every month because they''re funded and just are trying to drive users and they spend like $2 million a month on paid ads.","index":168,"end_time":678.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":670.02,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So maybe you go a different approach with you all.","index":169,"end_time":681.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":678.78,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It is nice and when we run into these very niche industries, not project management technology, there are more things that we can do that will have more impact for less spend like Colin said.","index":170,"end_time":695,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":681.86,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So it does put you in a unique, a unique position and a good one where we can try some things out.","index":171,"end_time":701.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":695.16,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And Colin is going to break down.","index":172,"end_time":704.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":703.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You were taught, you were saying, Matt, you know which channels you, you kind of looked into.","index":173,"end_time":708.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":705.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Colin is going to break down, you know what the different.","index":174,"end_time":711.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":708.64,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"What he saw on these competitors as well.","index":175,"end_time":714.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":711.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, absolutely.","index":176,"end_time":715.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":714.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Before we get there though, I do want to dive into the target market.","index":177,"end_time":719.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":716.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ve put together icp so starting with target account and then also an individual that we build.","index":178,"end_time":726.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":719.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They are not a real person but they are something that we build a empathy map for based on people in their space with their job titles, etc.","index":179,"end_time":734.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":726.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So starting out with the ideal target account.","index":180,"end_time":738.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":735.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So these are national and regional wireless characters or carriers with your guys main location presence being along the east coast obviously have a strong foothold or in the Virginia area.","index":181,"end_time":750.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":738.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But looking to spread a bit further down.","index":182,"end_time":752.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":750.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Want to confirm the revenue levels and employee counts here.","index":183,"end_time":756.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":753.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Based on the research that we conducted.","index":184,"end_time":758.019,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":756.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you feel like these fall into who you would like to work with from this perspective?","index":185,"end_time":762.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":758.019,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, actually it''s, you know we just have three, three customers so they''re pretty easy to find.","index":186,"end_time":771.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":765.38,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Right.","index":187,"end_time":772.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":772.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, it''s three.","index":188,"end_time":774.94,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":773.34,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"The ideal target account would, I mean from a, from a business perspective it''s, yeah, it''s T Mobile AT and T and Verizon but each market has their own set of leadership that we need to connect to.","index":189,"end_time":791.82,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":775.18,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So I would, I would consider each one of those regional directors or real estate managers that represent that particular market to be the target account.","index":190,"end_time":801.14,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":791.82,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"But yeah, that''s, that''s where we get in a little bit more here.","index":191,"end_time":803.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":801.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, cool.","index":192,"end_time":804.58,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":803.94,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":193,"end_time":805.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":804.58,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"And so yeah, we have Our, our empathy map broken out here as well.","index":194,"end_time":809.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":805.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So broken down into what this person is thinking, seeing, saying the pain points they''re experiencing, etc, and ultimately what their goals are.","index":195,"end_time":816.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":809.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, I''ll send all of this over for you guys to review.","index":196,"end_time":821.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":818.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t want to read through a bunch of text on a slide, but this is the empathy map that we''ve put in place for that target account type.","index":197,"end_time":827.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":821.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The next one being focus on municipal governments and public school systems.","index":198,"end_time":832.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":829.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Again, another one of the major areas that you guys work in.","index":199,"end_time":836.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":833.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Want to verify the parameters that we have here for revenue and employee count or if you guys have any other insight into like why that would be different?","index":200,"end_time":847.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":837.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, this looks, that''s looks right?","index":201,"end_time":855.82,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":853.9,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":202,"end_time":856.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":855.82,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":203,"end_time":858.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":857.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then similar for this we do have David Martinez.","index":204,"end_time":861.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":858.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He is a fictional facilities director for Prince George''s County Public Schools.","index":205,"end_time":865.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":861.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what he''s, you know, he''s seeing budget cuts, deferred maintenance, community connectivity problems.","index":206,"end_time":871.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":866.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s worried about opposition from the community derailing projects.","index":207,"end_time":876.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":872.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s concerned about picking developers.","index":208,"end_time":878.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":876.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He just wants to generate some meaningful recurring revenue, improve connectivity, maintain trust in the community and really ultimately, how can milestone towers help him achieve that?","index":209,"end_time":887.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":878.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then lastly, more of the fire departments and emergency management agencies.","index":210,"end_time":895.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":891.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that you guys have done some deals in this space as well.","index":211,"end_time":899.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":896.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s been a little bit of a smaller cut of historical business, but didn''t want to leave that out as a target audience either.","index":212,"end_time":907.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":900.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is fictional Fire chief Robert Thompson for Anne Arundel County Fire Departments.","index":213,"end_time":913.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":907.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Matt, I saw your head kind of move a little bit when you read that one.","index":214,"end_time":917.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":914.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think, I think it''s a good call out.","index":215,"end_time":920.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":917.82,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I mean, technically this person would still fall into the previous bucket.","index":216,"end_time":926.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":921.98,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I mean, this guy does just straight up work for the county.","index":217,"end_time":931.58,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":926.98,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So we don''t typically target, you know, I guess the police chief or the fire chief.","index":218,"end_time":940.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":932.3,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"It would just be directly reaching out to the county itself and then that would lend itself to a conversation.","index":219,"end_time":946.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":942.44,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"A lot of these guys don''t have a lot of decision making power.","index":220,"end_time":950.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":947,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"That was just my, my immediate reaction.","index":221,"end_time":952.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":950.76,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"But it''s still a good call out.","index":222,"end_time":955,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":953.48,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I think they, they would be definitely, maybe not a customer, but definitely an ideal, Like support for, for the project.","index":223,"end_time":965.49,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":955.08,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Yeah, and that''s exactly why I have it in here, is because a lot of what we need to build is also advocacy for you guys.","index":224,"end_time":971.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":965.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need more brand awareness and we need to, you can''t just immediately get a conversation with someone working for the county right away.","index":225,"end_time":979.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":971.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of times we''re going to see that we need to kind of elevate that information.","index":226,"end_time":983.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":979.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to start with someone who''s a little bit more accessible, give them some things to talk to their team about, and then ultimately that leads into a decision being made.","index":227,"end_time":990.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":983.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":228,"end_time":991.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":991.66,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":229,"end_time":994.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":993.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, What I want to jump into next is the brand canvas, brand positioning and messaging that we''ve put together.","index":230,"end_time":1000.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":995.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you guys ever worked with storybrand framework before?","index":231,"end_time":1004.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1000.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":232,"end_time":1007.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1007.1,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"For previous.","index":233,"end_time":1008.14,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1007.62,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Maybe not story brand.","index":234,"end_time":1013.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1012.38,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"No, I''m not familiar with StoryBrand.","index":235,"end_time":1014.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.42,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, no worries.","index":236,"end_time":1016.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1015.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just always like to ask, because it depends kind of like how I.","index":237,"end_time":1019.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1017.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How I present it.","index":238,"end_time":1021.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1020.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is your brand positioning.","index":239,"end_time":1023.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1021.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we use the story brand framework here.","index":240,"end_time":1024.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1023.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s really based on one single premise, and that is Evergreat Story has a hero.","index":241,"end_time":1030.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1025.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That hero is not Milestone Towers.","index":242,"end_time":1032.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1030.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That hero is your customer.","index":243,"end_time":1034.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1032.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You are actually the guide that helps them succeed in their journey.","index":244,"end_time":1038.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1034.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So their customer being all of the SCPs that we just walked through, municipal leaders, carriers who want reliable infrastructure.","index":245,"end_time":1046.659,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1039.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But they face, you know, complex issues.","index":246,"end_time":1048.539,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1046.659,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They are the hero they''re dealing with.","index":247,"end_time":1051.099,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1049.179,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be a villain from several different points.","index":248,"end_time":1054.379,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1051.819,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This could be unreliable developers they''ve worked with in the past.","index":249,"end_time":1057.899,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1055.099,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be community opposition.","index":250,"end_time":1059.899,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1058.459,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be regulatory complexity.","index":251,"end_time":1061.978,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1059.899,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, these all stem from actual conversations that have happened and things that you guys have shared with us in our first few calls, as well as I navigate through, they find you guys.","index":252,"end_time":1071.899,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1063.019,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that is, you know, from the landing pages, the campaigns, everything that we''re running, the educational resources that we''re putting together, direct mailers, everything like that, they understand that you have an understanding of what they''ve navigated through.","index":253,"end_time":1085.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1072.619,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys have been in this business for over 25 years.","index":254,"end_time":1088.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1085.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re bringing expertise that commodity builders just can''t match.","index":255,"end_time":1092.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1088.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys have a lot of experience, even in some of the local municipalities that we can point to, like working with Fairfax County.","index":256,"end_time":1097.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1092.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ultimately, that leads into you giving them a plan that is your transparent process.","index":257,"end_time":1102.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1099.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is not changing anything that you guys do.","index":258,"end_time":1104.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1102.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is just really bringing it to fruition.","index":259,"end_time":1107.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1104.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So identifying the sites, managing community engagement, going to town halls.","index":260,"end_time":1111.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1107.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys told a great story about that last time as well.","index":261,"end_time":1113.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1111.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And really bringing them to ultimately a call to action.","index":262,"end_time":1117.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1114.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They need to make a decision, and that should be to partner with Milestone for their next infrastructure project.","index":263,"end_time":1123,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1117.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would have them schedule a conversation, but we also always have sort of a fallback cta.","index":264,"end_time":1130.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1124.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a.","index":265,"end_time":1131.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1130.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if they don''t fill out a form directly, they still have some form to convert.","index":266,"end_time":1135.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1132.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do just see kind of across the industries, form fills dying down a bit.","index":267,"end_time":1139.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1136.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"People consider their information to be their currency, their time is their currency.","index":268,"end_time":1143.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1139.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we need to give them a lot of reason to actually start that conversation or raise their hand.","index":269,"end_time":1148.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1144.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions around this story?","index":270,"end_time":1151.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1149.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Brand framework, Awesome.","index":271,"end_time":1159.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1151.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ultimately, you''re helping them transform from uncertainty and frustration to confidence and improving partner that''s able to deliver with any complex infrastructure.","index":272,"end_time":1168.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1159.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Transparent engagement and genuine community commitment.","index":273,"end_time":1172.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1169.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys are very aware of the services and products that you offer.","index":274,"end_time":1179.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1175.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I don''t think that we need to spend a lot of time.","index":275,"end_time":1181.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1179.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We kind of just have a, a matrix breakdown of this.","index":276,"end_time":1184.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1181.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll send this over.","index":277,"end_time":1185.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1184.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys have any changes, please let us know.","index":278,"end_time":1187.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1185.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I feel like we don''t need to spend a lot of time here.","index":279,"end_time":1189.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1187.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys know what you, you do and what you sell.","index":280,"end_time":1191.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1189.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So getting into more of the competitive analysis, this is what Justin was alluding to before.","index":281,"end_time":1200.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1196.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is where we dive in a little bit deeper, Matt, into what the competitors are doing.","index":282,"end_time":1207.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1202.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have this kind of chart here to represent where they sit on this map.","index":283,"end_time":1210.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1207.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the spider chart is showing really how, how you guys stack up.","index":284,"end_time":1215.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1211.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys pop up in a few slides after your competitors for Tower Co. Again, their whole thing is about being coast to coast.","index":285,"end_time":1223.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1215.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They do have 91 employees.","index":286,"end_time":1225.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1224.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They have several partnerships that they like to talk about a lot.","index":287,"end_time":1228.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1225.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Their biggest presence is really on organic social media.","index":288,"end_time":1232.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1229.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They have over 6,000 followers there.","index":289,"end_time":1234.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1232.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Excuse me, that is about 10 and a half times what you guys have and almost 40% more than what diamond has as well.","index":290,"end_time":1241.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1235.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They do not have a very strong domain authority and not very many links back to their site and they have actually zero paid advertising that we''re able to find through several tools such as spyfu but also Meta Ads Manager and Google Ads.","index":291,"end_time":1256.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1241.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Their brand voice is really more about the professional and how they can emphasize customer centric partnerships.","index":292,"end_time":1263.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1258.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think that there''s a lot of opportunity here.","index":293,"end_time":1267,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1265.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Again, another one that''s not operating in the paid space at all and really promotes most of themselves through organic social.","index":294,"end_time":1272.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1267,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Matt, I think this is more of those posts that you were talking about of like, hey, look at this project, we got it before Christmas.","index":295,"end_time":1277.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1273.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The next one is Diamond.","index":296,"end_time":1281.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1280.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for diamond they did have the highest domain authority out of everyone that we analyzed, but again, a very low actually backlink count to the site.","index":297,"end_time":1290.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1282.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They do have a lot of video content.","index":298,"end_time":1293.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1291.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, it''s really, it''s forward or four videos that they''ve produced, but it''s more than we''ve seen kind of across the board for the industry and we feel pretty strongly that video is a great source for a lot of content to come out of.","index":299,"end_time":1308.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1294.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know Matt, if you and I hop on a call for 30 minutes, I just ask you a bunch of questions.","index":300,"end_time":1312.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1308.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We turn all of that into an engine to create blog posts, create newsletters, white papers, all of these things just from taking 30 minutes of your time and creating it into a bunch of different mediums and formats for people to consume wherever they are, whenever they''re there.","index":301,"end_time":1327.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1312.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, this really highlights the they, they also have a strangely high LinkedIn follower count, over 4400.","index":302,"end_time":1336.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1328.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But again really that is where they, they kind of stick their flag.","index":303,"end_time":1340.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1336.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re not really trying many other channels, just kind of dedicating to social media for Everest.","index":304,"end_time":1349.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1340.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Zero LinkedIn followers, zero employees actually tied to their company page on LinkedIn.","index":305,"end_time":1354.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1349.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Very low domain authority.","index":306,"end_time":1356.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1355.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This company does not really seem to care about any sort of digital presence.","index":307,"end_time":1360.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1356.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably operating much more in the oldboy network traditionally I would imagine based on all of our research.","index":308,"end_time":1367.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1361.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then for milestone.","index":309,"end_time":1372.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1371.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you guys do have out of the companies that actually had followers the lowest count 586.","index":310,"end_time":1378.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1373.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your domain authority is a 27.","index":311,"end_time":1381.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1379.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You have 135 links going back to your site.","index":312,"end_time":1384.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1381.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You do have stronger brand positioning than some of the other competitors that we''ve seen.","index":313,"end_time":1389.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1384.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think there are still some tweaks we can make to that and some tests that we would like to run across landing pages before say changing the homepage.","index":314,"end_time":1397.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1389.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys haven''t run really any paid advertising and there''s not much of an organic presence to the website from what we''re able to scrape.","index":315,"end_time":1404.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1398.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But there''s a lot of diamond in the rough I think is a good way to put it.","index":316,"end_time":1409.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1405.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean there''s the stories that you guys have told just in our first few meetings.","index":317,"end_time":1413.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1409.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to get that on the website.","index":318,"end_time":1415.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1413.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is what is going to drive more engagement.","index":319,"end_time":1417.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1415.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions with this high level overview of the competitive analysis?","index":320,"end_time":1423.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1419.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":321,"end_time":1429.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1428.66,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"All right, so we''ve laid the context out so we''ll get into the actual roadmap and we will start by diving into goals.","index":322,"end_time":1437.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1429.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So EOs, OKRs, objectives and key results is how we like to set our goals.","index":323,"end_time":1443.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1437.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so what we''ve come up with for our annual goal alignment is to increase qualified pipeline from target accounts.","index":324,"end_time":1451.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1443.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Matt, the, the benchmarks that we were looking at were more of, you know, things coming into your email.","index":325,"end_time":1457.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1452.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You said that they''re, they''re kind of a few a month.","index":326,"end_time":1459.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1457.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not really super consistent or predictable.","index":327,"end_time":1461.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1459.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there wasn''t much of a benchmark to operate off of there from a purely imperial standpoint from data.","index":328,"end_time":1467.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1462.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what we wanted to put forward is gathering qualified baseline inquiries.","index":329,"end_time":1474.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1468.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s with actual decision makers from wireless carriers, any expansion markets you guys are working in, municipalities or school districts in the target geos that we''ve outlined.","index":330,"end_time":1485.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1474.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what makes them qualified is that they are a decision maker.","index":331,"end_time":1489.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1486.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They have active coverage needs or are looking in property development and then scheduling that discovery call with you guys.","index":332,"end_time":1496.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1489.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we would shoot for is getting to 12 qualified inquiries per month.","index":333,"end_time":1500.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1496.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But there''s a scale.","index":334,"end_time":1502.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1501.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a lot of infrastructure that we need to build a lot of foundation.","index":335,"end_time":1505.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1502.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m not saying that in February we''re going to get 12, but we''re going to scale up to that 12 per month number.","index":336,"end_time":1511.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1505.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we would build all of that to if you guys are okay with us making some updates to Salesforce to capture all of that information so you.","index":337,"end_time":1519.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1512.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can have all of that.","index":338,"end_time":1520.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1519.8,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Other times, clients would prefer us to build like a free HubSpot or something and then just package up leads when they''re ready and send them over.","index":339,"end_time":1527.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1521.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So whatever preference you guys have there any questions on these goals.","index":340,"end_time":1534.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1527.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Coming into this?","index":341,"end_time":1544.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1544.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was there any numbers that you guys had in your head?","index":342,"end_time":1546.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1544.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think, I think 12 is a good number to get to like a consistent and predictable.","index":343,"end_time":1557.38,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1548.58,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Flow.","index":344,"end_time":1559.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1559.46,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I mean, I think that''s kind of.","index":345,"end_time":1561.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1559.94,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"That aligns with what we need.","index":346,"end_time":1563.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1561.86,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"You could assume if we''re getting that many and they''re qualified, those will actually translate into real projects.","index":347,"end_time":1569.7,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1563.86,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So I, I think I''m okay with that number.","index":348,"end_time":1574.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1570.34,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I think that''s fairly realistic and aligns with what we''ve kind of come up with internally.","index":349,"end_time":1579.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1574.35,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So I like that.","index":350,"end_time":1580.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1579.71,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"No, I don''t have any questions.","index":351,"end_time":1586.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1585.31,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"It looks good.","index":352,"end_time":1587.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1586.63,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Okay, so you''re saying assuming 3 to 5,000 minimum paid advertising spend plus the cost to create the content.","index":353,"end_time":1594.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1587.47,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Yeah, so our agency plus ad spend.","index":354,"end_time":1598.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1595.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":355,"end_time":1599.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1599.34,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"All right.","index":356,"end_time":1600.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.74,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And then the choices of places where we invest would be our customers or potential municipal owners, those being the two buckets.","index":357,"end_time":1612.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1600.3,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And we can allocate accordingly.","index":358,"end_time":1613.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1612.02,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Correct.","index":359,"end_time":1614.499,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1613.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And typically we see this kind of ebb and flow based on the business that we''re seeing come in.","index":360,"end_time":1618.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1614.499,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you guys are seeing one side of the business really tick up and you want to dive into the other, that''s where we can put more of the investment.","index":361,"end_time":1623.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1619.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":362,"end_time":1624.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1624.64,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And then with respect to messaging.","index":363,"end_time":1626.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1624.96,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So let''s say we say, okay, look, we don''t think it''s a good investment to do that to our wireless customers.","index":364,"end_time":1634.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1626.96,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"But if we wanted to target specific municipal environments.","index":365,"end_time":1639.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1634.96,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Then you would work with us on creating kind of our target list and then find the ways in which we get to the eyeballs of the people that we care about.","index":366,"end_time":1650.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1640.72,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":367,"end_time":1651.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1650.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":368,"end_time":1651.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1651.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re soup to nuts.","index":369,"end_time":1652.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1651.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":370,"end_time":1653.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1652.98,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"And that targeting could be for.","index":371,"end_time":1656.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1653.86,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"New.","index":372,"end_time":1659.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1658.98,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Opportunities, but also potentially maintaining existing opportunities.","index":373,"end_time":1662.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1659.3,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Correct.","index":374,"end_time":1663.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1663.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, all right, great.","index":375,"end_time":1665.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1664.5,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":376,"end_time":1667.82,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1667.46,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I would say to second that.","index":377,"end_time":1670.26,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1667.82,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I think the, the ad spend idea, I think what we really need now is in the immediate future is the content.","index":378,"end_time":1680.61,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1670.26,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"And whether it''s case studies or if it''s, you know, pitch decks, whatever the ad spend, at least for the wireless carriers, I don''t see that being very effective.","index":379,"end_time":1692.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1682.53,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I think it''s more effective, to be honest, even more so.","index":380,"end_time":1696.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1692.89,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"A third bucket, which would be.","index":381,"end_time":1698.37,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1696.69,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I.","index":382,"end_time":1700.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1700.53,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"Would just call it a private landowner bucket.","index":383,"end_time":1703.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1700.77,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So that could be master plan developers, that could be private landowners that just happen to have a lot of land in a given area.","index":384,"end_time":1711.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1704.13,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I do think those should be part of this list in some capacity.","index":385,"end_time":1717.12,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1712.32,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I don''t know if I want to flood them with investment, but.","index":386,"end_time":1720.16,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1717.12,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m just curious to see where, where, where the, how, how the ad spend.","index":387,"end_time":1731.6,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1725.36,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"If, if in which case, in the, in the history of our competitors, they, they did dedicate real investment to paid advertising, I wonder if it actually yielded them any results.","index":388,"end_time":1743.26,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1732.32,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Yeah, And I don''t think we see paid.","index":389,"end_time":1745.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1743.98,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So first off, I think the paid could be a little bit lower than that and we''re not even going to come out of the gates spending that amount of money.","index":390,"end_time":1754.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1745.9,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''ll test, test into it.","index":391,"end_time":1756.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1754.34,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But I want to be clear that the paid that''s in here and Colin, you can correct me where I''m wrong, but really is supplemental to outreach that we''re going to be doing.","index":392,"end_time":1770.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1758.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s not necessarily so.","index":393,"end_time":1772.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1770.87,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like we''re not suggesting go and have a big Google Ads budget which is essentially a slot machine, and hopefully you land a big deal and if not, the money is flushed.","index":394,"end_time":1783.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1772.43,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"What we''re hoping to do, and Colin''s going to get into this is have paid ads as a layer of retargeting where the people who we''re conducting outreach to are also then seeing milestone towers ads across the Internet, whether that''s on ESPN.com, cNN, Fox Business, whatever it may be.","index":395,"end_time":1805.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1784.31,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So it''s not a traditional advertising layer where we''re like, we hope that they''re searching, we hope that they click it, we hope they submit a contact form, we hope they.","index":396,"end_time":1813.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1805.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That turns into thousands of dollars of business for you.","index":397,"end_time":1816.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1813.32,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''m with you there, Matt.","index":398,"end_time":1818.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1817,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I Don''t.","index":399,"end_time":1818.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1818.36,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That is not the approach, Colin, if you go to the next slide, I know you wanted to stay on this slide because it''s important to talk to, but if you go to the next slides, I mean really what you see here, the first thing that Colin wants to do is to launch the educational content and case study library.","index":400,"end_time":1831.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1818.92,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So aside from the marketing infrastructure and measurement capabilities and then on the next slide is that account based marketing approach where we''re going to run this dual track approach of the people that we''re going to be targeting.","index":401,"end_time":1843.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1831.72,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Colin, we could probably lower those paid campaigns to like $1,000 a month.","index":402,"end_time":1848.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1843.57,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We can even test at like 500 to $1,000 a month for each one.","index":403,"end_time":1853.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1848.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So don''t want that to scare you away.","index":404,"end_time":1855.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1853.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s more.","index":405,"end_time":1855.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1855.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If you go to the next slide, Colin, it''s more of a layer.","index":406,"end_time":1860.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1855.97,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So what we are trying to do here is we are trying to have an omnichannel approach where you are reaching out to people via email.","index":407,"end_time":1869.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1860.37,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You have ads that are being shown to them.","index":408,"end_time":1871.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1869.6,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We are tracking them where they go around the Internet and then giving signals to you all as to what they engage with, whether it''s emails, advertising, et cetera.","index":409,"end_time":1881.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1871.68,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And Colin, I know you kind, I kind of skipped forward here for you, but I think it''s important that they see the vision of where this is going versus just us saying, hey, you guys should run some ads and we''ll see what comes in.","index":410,"end_time":1891.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1881.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That is not the intention here.","index":411,"end_time":1893.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1891.84,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It is much more of kind of that flywheel approach of content and then omnichannel marketing and then tracking it.","index":412,"end_time":1903.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1894.03,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"All those I think are the three most important things that we have laid out.","index":413,"end_time":1906.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1903.03,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So Colin, you can go back or forward.","index":414,"end_time":1909.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1906.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":415,"end_time":1910.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1909.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You did not mean to steal your thunder here.","index":416,"end_time":1912.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1910.51,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Good.","index":417,"end_time":1913.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1912.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The things that I want to underline that he said is 1 99% chance we''re not spending a dollar of advertising in month one.","index":418,"end_time":1920.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1913.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Matt, to your point, we need to get the content on the website.","index":419,"end_time":1923.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1920.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to get case studies, we need to get.","index":420,"end_time":1925.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1923.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I actually just had a LinkedIn post about this earlier this week.","index":421,"end_time":1927.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1925.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t want to set.","index":422,"end_time":1928.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1927.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re not going to pay thousands of dollars to send someone to a page that we actually don''t feel confident in converting them.","index":423,"end_time":1934.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1928.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we need to get a lot of that infrastructure in place.","index":424,"end_time":1936.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1934.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I do think we can go lower.","index":425,"end_time":1938.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1936.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like to have numbers in here of like, hey, maybe we see the opportunity coming back, right?","index":426,"end_time":1944.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1938.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we''re seeing the return on ad spend, we''re seeing the return on investment from that channel, I want to say that might be something we dive into a bit more and then I typically don''t include much of Google Ads in these types of campaigns, but I didn''t want to completely eliminate it either.","index":427,"end_time":1958.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1944.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just wanted to underline a few of those things.","index":428,"end_time":1960.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1958.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I appreciate that.","index":429,"end_time":1962.78,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1961.26,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I''m glad I threw.","index":430,"end_time":1963.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1962.78,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"You guys already kind of worked through this stuff, so I''ll stop.","index":431,"end_time":1966.54,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1963.74,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"No, you''re questions are awesome.","index":432,"end_time":1969.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1967.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we, we appreciate it.","index":433,"end_time":1971.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1970.3,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We want, I mean we''re talking about the goals and the tactics.","index":434,"end_time":1976.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1971.94,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I mean I know we talked to you at you what have you about what we have seen in our homework of why we put this together in the way that we did.","index":435,"end_time":1985.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1976.93,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And that''s great.","index":436,"end_time":1986.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1985.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But now is where rubber meets the road.","index":437,"end_time":1988.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1986.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And it''s like these are the goals and I won''t bury the lead.","index":438,"end_time":1993.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1988.85,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I mean what we have laid out is $6,000 for us to roll all of this out.","index":439,"end_time":1999.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1993.01,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If you just go to the pricing.","index":440,"end_time":2000.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1999.17,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And I''ll go back.","index":441,"end_time":2001.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2000.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So $6,000, it''s going to take a little bit more investment than that.","index":442,"end_time":2004.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2001.91,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But we''re going to put.","index":443,"end_time":2005.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2004.91,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we work off of this points system.","index":444,"end_time":2009.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2005.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"One point equals $100.","index":445,"end_time":2011.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2009.43,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We have an entire plan on the next slide.","index":446,"end_time":2013.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2011.27,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You don''t need to go to that yet, Colin.","index":447,"end_time":2015.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2013.55,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But the point I''m making is it''s $6,000 a month and then if we say 500 1,000 to $2,000 in ad spend.","index":448,"end_time":2024.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2015.19,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So don''t want to go too high there and that probably won''t start until month two or three.","index":449,"end_time":2029.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2024.15,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But the reason I bring this up is what I want to know is based on, based on the numbers that we put together at $6,000 a month, let''s just say plus 2,000 in ad spend.","index":450,"end_time":2042.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2031.25,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And now Colin, if you go back to the goals, if these goals were to come true, 12 qualified inquiries per month by month 12, 144 annually, 6 per month by month 6 and then the remainder from months 7 through 12.","index":451,"end_time":2059.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2043.01,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Is that a good use of your money on the marketing side?","index":452,"end_time":2064.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2060.39,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That is the equation that we are trying to build.","index":453,"end_time":2067.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2064.95,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Here is something that''s why we call it alignment.","index":454,"end_time":2071.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2067.67,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like this entire thing is called the aligned growth engine.","index":455,"end_time":2073.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2071.35,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We are trying to align on if X spend and Y results, does that equal success?","index":456,"end_time":2082.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2073.47,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If yes, then we need to understand, we need to roll out for you what the tactics are to get us there.","index":457,"end_time":2090.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2083.2,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so what our tactics are that we have to get there are the marketing operations and infrastructure that we need to build out to make sure that we''re tracking appropriately and then we need to launch the educational content and case study library as well as the two track account based marketing campaign that includes email, some light advertising.","index":458,"end_time":2108.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2090.72,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And that is what we have, that is what we have put together.","index":459,"end_time":2113.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2109.51,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so the question goes back to you all is like, is that something that you feel good about, that you feel comfortable with?","index":460,"end_time":2120.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2113.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If no.","index":461,"end_time":2121.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2120.47,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Where, where was it missing something?","index":462,"end_time":2123.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2121.35,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Was the, you know, the, the equation, was there anything we missed?","index":463,"end_time":2130.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2123.75,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I mean we feel pretty good about it.","index":464,"end_time":2131.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2130.07,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So I just want to pass that back to you.","index":465,"end_time":2132.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2131.11,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Now that you have the information, we can answer any question under the sun.","index":466,"end_time":2135.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2132.67,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"This is the part that should be very collaborative.","index":467,"end_time":2138.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2135.59,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":468,"end_time":2140.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2140.51,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So my two cents on this are that we''ve got two, we''ve got two ways to generate, we''ve only got one way to generate new opportunities and that''s direct engagement with our customers, you know, in house with each of the carrier customers and with the, the teams that they outsource the work to.","index":469,"end_time":2165,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2140.95,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So that, that is the, that''s where the, that''s where opportunities flow to us.","index":470,"end_time":2173.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2166.28,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"However, in order to be able to stay top of mind with those relationships, we have to continue to introduce opportunities that, that resonate with them in terms of their most challenging and most difficult environments.","index":471,"end_time":2195.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2174.92,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"If they need a cell tower built and, and they, they can hand it to a Towerco or a diamond and they can get that site done by working with an existing private property owner, then we''re never going to hear from them.","index":472,"end_time":2213.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2196.33,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"If they get shot down because the city of Homestead, Florida wouldn''t return their phone calls or told them that they have no interest in working with them, then it would, it may come, it would come back to us and say hey, we see that you guys have a contract with the city of Homestead.","index":473,"end_time":2233,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2214.92,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"We''ve tried all the private property owners in city Homestead.","index":474,"end_time":2236.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2233.8,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"None of them said yes.","index":475,"end_time":2237.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2236.44,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So the only place left is the park.","index":476,"end_time":2239.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2237.36,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Can you guys, can we, can you guys call the city and see if we can put on the park and let you guys work on it?","index":477,"end_time":2244.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2239.71,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So, so you have to understand that the low hanging fruit is always going to be the easiest site to get and they''re going to pick the, their favorite tower developers to go get the easiest site because they get bulk pricing, they get discounts and they, they, they prefer for those companies to give them the volume because they get the best, best pricing from them and they''re the easiest sites and they''re the ones that are not char, not difficult to be able to obtain entitlements for when what resonates with them is when we can deliver something that those guys can''t.","index":478,"end_time":2280.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2244.71,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So if they have a, if they believe that there''s a high probability that Vertical Bridge or Towercom or Darko or Skyway or, you know, all these companies are gonna, don''t have the team, don''t have the skills, don''t have the ability to be able to solve the problem, or that that ring has been unfulfilled for several years.","index":479,"end_time":2302.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2281.46,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Then, then they give us a call and say, hey, give us a one to try.","index":480,"end_time":2306.889,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2303.17,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Most of the rings we''ve got have been from property owners that we have the advantage because there''s no other choices or they trust us to be able to go open that door because we have experience in doing that for them.","index":481,"end_time":2321.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2306.889,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And so when it comes to the ads, we can target ads to the folks at Verizon, we can target ads to the folks at the site acquisition teams, although I''m not sure where to find them.","index":482,"end_time":2335.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2321.86,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Although I guess they''re in LinkedIn, right?","index":483,"end_time":2337.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2335.78,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So if you focus on LinkedIn, that''s where you probably find them.","index":484,"end_time":2340.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2337.7,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"But so the, the, it''s the combination of having, as Matt Forkas has said many times over, it''s the combination of having new relationships, new municipalities.","index":485,"end_time":2354.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2342.11,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So when we call Verizon in Florida, say, hey, by the way, we just onboarded Marianna county and we''ve got, you know, six really great school sites that weren''t, did not exist a month ago or two months ago, or we just onboarded XYZ owner, we just doubled the number of Lakewood Ranch, which is a second fastest growing master plan community in the United States.","index":486,"end_time":2375.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2354.35,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So those are the things that get their attention.","index":487,"end_time":2378.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2375.96,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And, and then we have to be prepared to share with them the opportunities and locations so they can put them in their database.","index":488,"end_time":2384.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2378.84,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So, so again, when it comes to the ads for our customers, I think the conversion rate for the investment, I''m skeptical, but I''m not, I''m not a, I''m not an absolute.","index":489,"end_time":2400.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2385.32,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"No.","index":490,"end_time":2401.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2400.82,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"But when it comes to future property owners where we, they hear us, they see a drum beat from us in different ways in different places, where they see a testimonial from someone they trust or they, they, they see, you know, a case study summary or something that you know, would want them to click on, say, hey, how did they do?","index":491,"end_time":2423.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2402.18,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"How did, you know, how did, how did Richland 2 county schools get that deal done?","index":492,"end_time":2429.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2423.86,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Because that, that looks like a pretty, that''s like something interesting to me and so forth.","index":493,"end_time":2433.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2429.3,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So, so those are, I think those are the the places where investing capital would, would be, would be more interesting to us to pivot.","index":494,"end_time":2446.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2433.62,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"We do have a upcoming political PR issue that''s, that''s looming that we''re going to need to get ahead of.","index":495,"end_time":2454.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2446.95,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"But I want to let you guys get through this, this, this presentation first before we talk about that.","index":496,"end_time":2458.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2454.31,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Oh, go ahead, Matt.","index":497,"end_time":2462.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2460.95,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, I have questions on that because I, I want to make sure we''re talking about the same thing related to I.","index":498,"end_time":2470.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2462.03,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"The.","index":499,"end_time":2471.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2471.11,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Could you, could you, could you pull up the, that points thing you just showed?","index":500,"end_time":2475.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2472.15,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Yeah, because I think the short answer, the simplest answer to the question is yes.","index":501,"end_time":2481.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2475.97,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I think that budget, if it aligns to getting a consistent 12 inquiries a month, if that ends up being the result, if it''s more, if it''s slightly less, I think that we would take that deal day in, day out.","index":502,"end_time":2495.41,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2482.21,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So that would be my answer to that question.","index":503,"end_time":2498.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2495.97,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I think the concern about ad spend is almost, shouldn''t necessarily be the heart of this conversation.","index":504,"end_time":2509.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2498.85,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I mean, we''re onboarding you as a marketing agency to do more than just spending dollars and creating content for, for ads.","index":505,"end_time":2515.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2509.13,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So regarding the point system, you know, you have this full list of tasks and deliverables.","index":506,"end_time":2522.37,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2516.13,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I think that''s where, at least from my end, in my perspective, where I''m, you know, if we''re paying this retainer, I just want to make sure we''re getting the, the value out of there so I, I get the result.","index":507,"end_time":2537.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2524.37,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I think that''s, that''s great.","index":508,"end_time":2538.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2537.47,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I would, I would.","index":509,"end_time":2539.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2538.67,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Six thousand bucks a month if it takes us six months to get the 12 consistent inquiries a month.","index":510,"end_time":2544.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2539.63,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I would, I would take that, I would take that deal every day.","index":511,"end_time":2548.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2545.55,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I don''t know if Lena Rousey would agree with that either.","index":512,"end_time":2552.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2548.71,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"But one, I have a question on clarification.","index":513,"end_time":2559.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2552.71,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"Are the 12 inquiries, what are they new sites or are they inquiries, including landowner inquiries that are coming in?","index":514,"end_time":2569.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2559.56,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"Yeah, great question, Ozzy.","index":515,"end_time":2571.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2570.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s broken down.","index":516,"end_time":2572.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2571.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure if you can see the slide.","index":517,"end_time":2573.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2572.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s broken down here with a split of.","index":518,"end_time":2575.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2573.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re looking for 60% carrier sourced and 40% municipal sourced.","index":519,"end_time":2579.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2576.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"40.","index":520,"end_time":2579.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2579.52,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"And you''re in, you''re considering them qualified based on them being them having an actual validated need.","index":521,"end_time":2588.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2581.73,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Correct.","index":522,"end_time":2589.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2589.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":523,"end_time":2590.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2590.05,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"And being in an area that you guys service.","index":524,"end_time":2592.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2590.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":525,"end_time":2593.57,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2592.85,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Was there a follow up to that?","index":526,"end_time":2600.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2598.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":527,"end_time":2604.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2603.89,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"I mean, I think I''m a little bit reluctant.","index":528,"end_time":2606.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2604.21,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"I think if I thought about 12 inquiries.","index":529,"end_time":2609.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2606.68,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"Yeah, I think I would be with Matt.","index":530,"end_time":2611.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2609.36,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"With a split, it''s a little less than.","index":531,"end_time":2613.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2611.6,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":532,"end_time":2616,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2615.2,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"You know, but that''s.","index":533,"end_time":2617.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2616.24,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"Don''t let that bother you.","index":534,"end_time":2618.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2617.6,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"Just keep going.","index":535,"end_time":2619.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2618.72,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"I think it''s.","index":536,"end_time":2619.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2619.32,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"Yeah, you know, to be clear, is 12 per month, by month, 12 split, with US having to have some ramp time to be able to make sure that we hone in on exactly how we''re targeting these people, who we''re targeting, etc, because, I mean, they''re, they''re.","index":537,"end_time":2638.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2619.96,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I mean, of course, you guys are all like, if you could do that tomorrow, we''ll sign up instantly.","index":538,"end_time":2643.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2639.07,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We don''t have a silver bullet.","index":539,"end_time":2644.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2643.31,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I wish we did.","index":540,"end_time":2645.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2644.83,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It is.","index":541,"end_time":2646.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2645.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I understand, I understand.","index":542,"end_time":2647.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2646.35,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"A little bit of time to get up to speed.","index":543,"end_time":2649.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2647.51,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But we, you know, we do have faith in what it is we''re doing.","index":544,"end_time":2653.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2649.75,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And that was some of the stuff lens.","index":545,"end_time":2657.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2653.87,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I. I don''t want.","index":546,"end_time":2658.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2657.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We have 15 minutes.","index":547,"end_time":2660.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2659.4,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I want to discuss some of the stuff that you.","index":548,"end_time":2665.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2661.24,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You''re bringing up.","index":549,"end_time":2666.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2665.64,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So some of these municipalities and school districts, and I know that there are private landowners that we probably won''t be able to target, but are there the school districts?","index":550,"end_time":2682.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2666.76,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So you, you were saying you reach out to them, you show.","index":551,"end_time":2685.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2682.48,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"They sniff around or they find a case study or what have you.","index":552,"end_time":2690.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2685.71,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You don''t need to pull this up just yet.","index":553,"end_time":2694.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2693.27,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Colin.","index":554,"end_time":2695.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2694.55,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Talk to me a little bit about that.","index":555,"end_time":2698.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2697.67,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So how does that happen?","index":556,"end_time":2699.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2698.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So you, you said somebody''s sniffing around, they run into a case study, they get excited about it, they reach out.","index":557,"end_time":2706.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2699.91,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Or how does it work?","index":558,"end_time":2707.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2706.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Well, I mean, I think that it really doesn''t work.","index":559,"end_time":2712.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2710.15,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"We''re talking about creating the, Creating the activity.","index":560,"end_time":2715.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2712.31,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Right now what we''re doing is we''re prioritizing.","index":561,"end_time":2717.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2715.18,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Matt''s leading this.","index":562,"end_time":2718.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2718.1,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"We''re prioritizing our target list and we''re cold calling them to see if we can get meetings.","index":563,"end_time":2723.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2718.98,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Yeah, and we''ve had some success with that.","index":564,"end_time":2726.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2723.62,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So.","index":565,"end_time":2726.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2726.02,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"And then during the meeting and we explain the program and we share our references, who are people they typically may know and, and see if we can''t move to the next step.","index":566,"end_time":2734.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2726.3,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So that''s kind of the process we''re doing right now is a very specific and directed based on the research we''ve done on the right people in the organizations that we''re targeting.","index":567,"end_time":2744.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2734.98,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So.","index":568,"end_time":2744.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2744.01,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So I guess the question is, for people that would see an ad, if that person saw the ad before the phone call, would that validate the phone call or would that, you know, cause them to call us?","index":569,"end_time":2756.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2744.61,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So that''s, I guess, the question.","index":570,"end_time":2758.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2756.85,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Right.","index":571,"end_time":2758.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2758.29,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So there we go.","index":572,"end_time":2760.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2758.69,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So now this is exactly to the cold calling.","index":573,"end_time":2763.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2760.21,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We don''t always get the cold calling level.","index":574,"end_time":2766.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2764.13,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"To it.","index":575,"end_time":2767.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2766.63,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"The amount of sophistication, of attribution may or may not be.","index":576,"end_time":2773.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2768.43,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"There may be something that we have to have conversations about.","index":577,"end_time":2775.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2773.47,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If somebody cold calls someone and they''re like, oh, yeah, I''ve actually seen a couple of your ads.","index":578,"end_time":2778.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2775.87,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But one of the things that we can do, Len, and this, this is where I wanted to go with this.","index":579,"end_time":2783.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2778.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So the ads that we''re talking about.","index":580,"end_time":2785.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2783.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So basically what we could do is if there are people who you''re calling into, we can run email campaigns to those people.","index":581,"end_time":2792.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2785.47,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We can show ads to those people.","index":582,"end_time":2793.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2792.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Those ads can be case studies.","index":583,"end_time":2795.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2793.93,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like, I think there''s a.","index":584,"end_time":2797.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2795.93,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"There''s a misconception that every ad needs to be a.","index":585,"end_time":2799.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2797.05,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Be a direct response ad and somebody should send you an RFP after they see your ad.","index":586,"end_time":2804.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2799.65,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s not the case.","index":587,"end_time":2805.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2804.65,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We can run content as ads for very low dollar spend.","index":588,"end_time":2810.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2805.69,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then we''re at.","index":589,"end_time":2811.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2810.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If you pull up, Colin, your marketing infrastructure, I want to just like work through this.","index":590,"end_time":2816.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2811.45,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So I want to make sure everybody''s on the same page here as to what we''re prepared posing.","index":591,"end_time":2819.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2816.37,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So Clay here, you may or may not have contact information.","index":592,"end_time":2824.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2820.92,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I don''t know if you''re cold calling by just cold calling the directory and starting to ask for people that you see on LinkedIn, but we can actually pull their contact information.","index":593,"end_time":2833.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2824.76,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We can pull people from these municipalities.","index":594,"end_time":2836.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2834.28,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We have the ability to build these lists for you using Clay, which is an AI tool.","index":595,"end_time":2841.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2836.84,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We can get all of their information.","index":596,"end_time":2842.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2841.56,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We can then send them emails, we can show them ads.","index":597,"end_time":2847.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2843.48,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then these other two tools are B2B and factors are actually de anonymization tools where I can say Len, Ozzy, Matt, Naz, whoever.","index":598,"end_time":2857.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2847.34,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I want to let you know that, you know, the somebody at the Fairfax county school district that we''ve been targeting has actually been clicking on your ads.","index":599,"end_time":2866.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2857.82,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And you maybe you should call them a couple times and see if you can get through.","index":600,"end_time":2869.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2866.26,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Our B2B actually goes down to the contact level.","index":601,"end_time":2872.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2870.63,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I can tell you specifically, hey, this person has clicked two ads.","index":602,"end_time":2877.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2872.75,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"They''ve been to your website.","index":603,"end_time":2878.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2877.07,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"They have, you know, read a case study.","index":604,"end_time":2882.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2879.03,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"They just haven''t filled out a form or responded to an email.","index":605,"end_time":2884.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2882.51,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You guys should probably reach out to this person.","index":606,"end_time":2886.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2884.87,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Sometimes we don''t have the ability to track down to the contact level.","index":607,"end_time":2890.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2887.11,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That''s factors.","index":608,"end_time":2891.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2890.55,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Factors is the account level.","index":609,"end_time":2892.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2891.59,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Maybe we see that a bunch of people in Fairfax county are clicking ads and doing things, and you''re like, all right, we need to reach out.","index":610,"end_time":2899.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2892.95,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We need to.","index":611,"end_time":2900.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2899.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We need to talk to somebody.","index":612,"end_time":2902.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2900.81,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Over there because clearly they are engaging with our stuff and we need to have those conversations.","index":613,"end_time":2906.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2902.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So these are not just like big, I don''t want to use the term billboard, but like big digital billboard ads trying to get people to work with you.","index":614,"end_time":2914.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2906.85,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s ways to get you continually seen.","index":615,"end_time":2916.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2914.33,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And what we are trying to draw down are signals.","index":616,"end_time":2919.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2916.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We are trying to draw down signals from people of how they''re engaging with the content, how they''re engaging with emails, ads, whatever other content that we put out there we can see when they go to your website and that''s what we report back to you on.","index":617,"end_time":2931.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2919.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So you see Supabase and Salesforce.","index":618,"end_time":2933.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2931.37,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Supabase is where we''re actually going to take all of that.","index":619,"end_time":2936.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2933.57,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So all that information is going to flow through N8N.","index":620,"end_time":2938.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2936.17,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''m not trying to get too technical here, but you guys are pretty technical.","index":621,"end_time":2941.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2938.69,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Guys, enough.","index":622,"end_time":2942.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2941.73,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"All that information runs into N8N, which is a workflow tool, an AI workflow tool that will then spit out into Supabase and everyone who''s engaging and at what accounts.","index":623,"end_time":2952.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2942.77,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then we determine what goes into Salesforce as a lead.","index":624,"end_time":2955.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2952.85,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Does it have to be that they respond?","index":625,"end_time":2957.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2955.97,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Maybe you say that it is, maybe it''s that they''ve scored well enough because they''ve engaged with enough stuff.","index":626,"end_time":2963.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2957.73,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We put it into Salesforce and give someone a task to call them.","index":627,"end_time":2966.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2963.57,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we need to have those conversations.","index":628,"end_time":2968.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2967.09,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We haven''t locked in exactly what you know.","index":629,"end_time":2971.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2968.93,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Matt, you asked what is a qualified lead.","index":630,"end_time":2973.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2971.21,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We do have to come up with that very specific definition.","index":631,"end_time":2976.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2973.09,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But we know that based on previous criteria this would be what you''re looking for is getting to that 12amonth for that spend and that is what we are going to have to do.","index":632,"end_time":2988.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2977.22,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So just want to make sure we''re all clear on what''s being proposed here.","index":633,"end_time":2993.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2988.18,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"This isn''t like just running, you know, direct response ads to the broader public and seeing what rolls in.","index":634,"end_time":3001.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2993.38,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t think, I don''t think we doubt the effort.","index":635,"end_time":3006.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3002.83,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I think it''s clear.","index":636,"end_time":3008.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3007.63,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I think what we''re trying to figure out, quite honestly, Justin, is how do they all.","index":637,"end_time":3014.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3009.15,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"How it actually connects.","index":638,"end_time":3016.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3015.15,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Right.","index":639,"end_time":3016.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3016.67,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"And how it all works together.","index":640,"end_time":3018.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3016.91,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So I mean, I think that''s, you know, what you''re hearing Len say, hey, you know, our traditional approach has been, you know, and that''s going to continue to exist with the carriers and that''s really the hardest.","index":641,"end_time":3031.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3019.55,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Right.","index":642,"end_time":3031.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3031.23,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"That''s for customers.","index":643,"end_time":3032.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3031.91,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Carries are, in a sense, you heard us say this before, it''s a hand to hand combat.","index":644,"end_time":3037.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3032.95,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So we''re Just trying to figure out really how it all kind of pieces together.","index":645,"end_time":3042.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3039.51,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I''m not, quite honestly, I''m not interested in the looking at the marketing stack.","index":646,"end_time":3047.669,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3043.43,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I know you guys have it and it''s great.","index":647,"end_time":3049.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3047.669,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"You got.","index":648,"end_time":3050.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3049.51,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"You guys are a marketing agency.","index":649,"end_time":3051.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3050.03,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So every marketing agency will have it.","index":650,"end_time":3053.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3051.75,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"All the technology.","index":651,"end_time":3054.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3054.15,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I think it''s a matter of how do we, you know, get all the softer stuff together and deliver on the results.","index":652,"end_time":3062.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3055.51,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Right.","index":653,"end_time":3063.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3062.76,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So the question about, you know, the, the inquiries, I think, yeah, I mean it''s not going to be day one.","index":654,"end_time":3070.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3063.24,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I get that.","index":655,"end_time":3071.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3070.44,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"That goes without saying.","index":656,"end_time":3073.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3072.04,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I think it''s more of me reflecting on, you know, our initial internally, whether we believe what is the right, what is the right number.","index":657,"end_time":3083.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3073.24,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I don''t think we have it.","index":658,"end_time":3084.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3083.32,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I don''t think we have one.","index":659,"end_time":3085.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3084.87,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So that''s, you know, that was just my reaction to it.","index":660,"end_time":3089.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3087.19,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"It''s not what you''re presenting.","index":661,"end_time":3091.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3089.79,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"It''s more about internally what we believe.","index":662,"end_time":3094.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3091.55,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"How do we value these things?","index":663,"end_time":3096.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3094.63,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Because we haven''t in the past.","index":664,"end_time":3097.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3096.27,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":665,"end_time":3099.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3099.43,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":666,"end_time":3100.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3099.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So what could.","index":667,"end_time":3101.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3100.19,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"This is actually how the workflow works, not just technology tools.","index":668,"end_time":3109.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3105.03,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So how could we better explain what the proposed engagement is?","index":669,"end_time":3118.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3109.15,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"My immediate reaction to this, I mean, this whole infrastructure I feel is almost overkill.","index":670,"end_time":3130.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3123.75,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I mean I use Clay, I use Apollo every day, at least from municipal perspective.","index":671,"end_time":3136.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3131.35,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Everything''s already on these counties websites.","index":672,"end_time":3139.52,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3137.4,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"It''s maybe three or four people you''re trying to get in contact with.","index":673,"end_time":3143.16,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3139.52,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"They typically pick up the phone.","index":674,"end_time":3146.04,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3144.44,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"They, they more often than not do respond to emails, even if it takes a couple times.","index":675,"end_time":3152.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3147.16,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So this vast approach using these agent tools like NAN and Supabase is just, it''s just, it''s just overkill.","index":676,"end_time":3163.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3153.56,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s completely necessary now.","index":677,"end_time":3168.33,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3165.01,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"If it was more for like a broad approach at scale.","index":678,"end_time":3171.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3168.33,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"If you''re targeting hundreds, if not thousands of potential leads, I could see this being very useful.","index":679,"end_time":3178.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3171.65,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"But that would fall more into the realm of like a private landowners across the country, right.","index":680,"end_time":3187.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3179.33,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"That may have a piece of property that lands up with a, an area where there''s a coverage gap regarding the municipal.","index":681,"end_time":3194.26,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3187.13,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I mean the carrier is even smaller than that.","index":682,"end_time":3196.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3194.42,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I mean you could count that on a couple hands how many people you actually need to talk to that matter.","index":683,"end_time":3201.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3196.3,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"That''s very small, very small list.","index":684,"end_time":3205.54,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3202.98,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"And for the municipal side, there are a lot of municipalities in the country, especially where we do business, but each organization really only has two, three people that we need to speak to.","index":685,"end_time":3216.34,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3205.78,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So that list is also pretty small.","index":686,"end_time":3218.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3216.87,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I mean I have a master list of a couple hundred Right now for the markets that we''re currently doing business with, and we''re slowly rolling that out.","index":687,"end_time":3230.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3218.15,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"And that''s just cold outreach.","index":688,"end_time":3232.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3230.47,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I think the methodology of how we track those prospects is pretty cool.","index":689,"end_time":3239.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3233.35,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Not cool is pretty basic, but I think it works.","index":690,"end_time":3245.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3239.59,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"But we haven''t really approached the scale that I''m trying to tackle quite yet.","index":691,"end_time":3250.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3246.05,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So maybe there could be some implementation there.","index":692,"end_time":3253.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3250.77,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"But what I''m looking for more and maybe less so with the ads too, is just the general marketing services that you guys.","index":693,"end_time":3262.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3253.25,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"The.","index":694,"end_time":3262.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3262.01,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"That you guys provide.","index":695,"end_time":3263.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3262.77,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So there was a link on one of the pages with.","index":696,"end_time":3266.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3263.97,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I have it here from Tristan too.","index":697,"end_time":3268.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3267.25,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So if.","index":698,"end_time":3273.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3273.31,"speaker_name":"ozzie"},{"text":"Can we.","index":699,"end_time":3274.55,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3274.11,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Can you just.","index":700,"end_time":3275.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3274.55,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"While Ozzy and Leonard on the call, can you break down what those points are being used for monthly?","index":701,"end_time":3280.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3275.31,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":702,"end_time":3282.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3280.91,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Because Len mentioned some really very fresh recent pressure that''s going to get starting to build up from the federal level that''s going to potentially affect our business model.","index":703,"end_time":3300.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3286.03,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So that would be more a reaction in preparing certain things rather than kind of a different, almost a completely different strategy than what we talked about thus far.","index":704,"end_time":3310.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3300.17,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"And I don''t need to get into that now, but I know some of these points would get attributed to that.","index":705,"end_time":3315.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3311.29,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Okay, so we''ve got 60 points per month.","index":706,"end_time":3320.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3317.37,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":707,"end_time":3321.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3321.13,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So 6,000.","index":708,"end_time":3322.732,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3321.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"60.","index":709,"end_time":3323.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3322.857,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For 6,000.","index":710,"end_time":3324.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3323.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We would be giving you another 20 every month.","index":711,"end_time":3326.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3324.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you guys also get 60 from this engagement if you do sign on for the retainer.","index":712,"end_time":3330.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3326.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got.","index":713,"end_time":3331.34,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3330.98,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Okay, so you have a little bit more.","index":714,"end_time":3333.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3331.34,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we were going to really front load this thing in the first three months, resulting in a little bit over 100 points per month.","index":715,"end_time":3338.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3333.14,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So what you see here is the ABM plan, the content plan and the performance reporting plan here in month one.","index":716,"end_time":3346.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3340.02,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If you just skip to month three.","index":717,"end_time":3349.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3346.54,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Colin, We''ve got case studies, slide decks.","index":718,"end_time":3353.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3349.95,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re running abm.","index":719,"end_time":3354.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3353.71,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re.","index":720,"end_time":3355.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3355.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have in here that we would like to do some sort of video series.","index":721,"end_time":3359.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3355.63,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Something where you''re engaging with people in the space.","index":722,"end_time":3362.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3360.03,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Maybe some.","index":723,"end_time":3363.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3362.83,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Maybe you''re doing one episode a month with someone who works at a carrier.","index":724,"end_time":3367.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3363.59,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Maybe you''re doing one episode a month where you''re talking to someone in a municipality.","index":725,"end_time":3371.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3367.87,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re creating content around the people in your space in month two.","index":726,"end_time":3376.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3371.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And I''m working backwards because that sounds like that''s a lot more of the stuff that you guys want.","index":727,"end_time":3380.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3377.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We have web pages here that we would launch.","index":728,"end_time":3382.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3380.56,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We have an image ad creative package, developing outreach sequences and then setting up the paid media and abm.","index":729,"end_time":3390.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3382.84,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then from there we''d be running at a clip of 80 points per month ongoing, where we''re running content, ABM and performance reporting.","index":730,"end_time":3401.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3390.84,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Based on what we had laid out here, I''m curious, what is, what are the requirements that you''re going to be looking for for this PR situation that''s coming up?","index":731,"end_time":3413.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3401.01,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I feel free to elaborate or not as much as you feel comfortable, but I''m just curious.","index":732,"end_time":3420.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3413.73,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It seems like there''s this and you''re gonna, we''ll send all this over to you afterward, but it feels like there''s this elephant in the room that is slightly different from anything we''ve talked about that I''m curious how it impacts the engagement.","index":733,"end_time":3431.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3420.25,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll give you 90 seconds on it.","index":734,"end_time":3433.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3431.56,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So we''ve been for 25 years partnering with schools to build towers on their football fields and middle schools and so forth.","index":735,"end_time":3440.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3433.32,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And the positives and reasons that our partners do it is because we create better connectivity, which is safety, especially public safety.","index":736,"end_time":3448.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3441.08,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"With 911, it''s better to have a, it''s better for kids in schools, in the community to have better connectivity near the schools than have no connectivity.","index":737,"end_time":3456.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3448.16,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And oftentimes the school sites are the only places where we can solve the problem.","index":738,"end_time":3459.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3456.87,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"We''ve had health concerns come from parents and from an organization called the Environmental Health Trust who castigate towers near schools as harmful to children, especially EMF and wireless radio energy.","index":739,"end_time":3474.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3461.19,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And that the FCC is a captured organization that doesn''t protect families or children because the radio energy that''s emanating from the tower sites are not accurately, you know, aren''t, aren''t safe.","index":740,"end_time":3488.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3474.79,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And, and they also say the same thing with respect to WI fi routers too.","index":741,"end_time":3492.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3489.03,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"That organization was founded by RFK Jr and now, now that he''s gotten the food pyramid fixed, he''s in his next project is RF Safety in the Environment.","index":742,"end_time":3503.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3493.27,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And, and he''s taken the, the page off the, the FDA site that says cell towers are not harmful to people and that wireless energy is not harmful to people.","index":743,"end_time":3515.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3503.91,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And so following this organization he helped start, he''s now funded a study to look at radio energy impact to families, children and the populace as part of Maha.","index":744,"end_time":3529.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3515.53,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So we''re expecting a report to come out this spring from Maha saying cell towers in your schools is not a good idea.","index":745,"end_time":3537.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3530.41,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And they may just say that overall, they may say that there should be a one mile perimeter.","index":746,"end_time":3543.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3538.34,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"They should say that we can''t dictate what schools do or don''t do.","index":747,"end_time":3547.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3544.02,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"But just like vaccines, we think you should get eight vaccines for your baby instead of 16 based on what Denmark says.","index":748,"end_time":3553.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3547.3,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And that''s Our recommendation.","index":749,"end_time":3555.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3553.86,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So anybody that wants to fight towers at schools on our existing partnerships or any future partnerships is going to have some ammo coming from RFK Juniors, FDA within the next several months.","index":750,"end_time":3566.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3555.78,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So what we need to do is start thinking about how do we get ahead of this to our school partners to immunize them, no pun intended, for what''s coming.","index":751,"end_time":3576.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3567.67,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"And also they have really good, really good counterbalances in a professional way.","index":752,"end_time":3581.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3576.47,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"So those are the things that are front of mind for me is protecting our brand and protecting our home turf, which is about to be attacked in a federal level.","index":753,"end_time":3589.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3581.51,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":754,"end_time":3592.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3591.12,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Question for you.","index":755,"end_time":3593.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3592.56,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So is that more important?","index":756,"end_time":3597.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3593.76,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like, Matt, this might be a question for you in a perfect world, like, where would you want us to focus?","index":757,"end_time":3606.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3597.6,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It sounds like you''re doing some of the stuff that we presented, although maybe we presented it at, I don''t know, more in depth clip where we''re using other tools and you''re like, may, maybe that helps.","index":758,"end_time":3621.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3606.48,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Maybe it''s some of the stuff that I''m already doing is just spending 80 to 100 points a month on creating content.","index":759,"end_time":3631.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3621.78,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"A better use of your budget.","index":760,"end_time":3636.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3632.18,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like that''s what I''m trying to understand is because two things can''t be true.","index":761,"end_time":3641.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3636.58,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Well, I guess it''s three, right?","index":762,"end_time":3643.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3642.18,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s like a triangle.","index":763,"end_time":3644.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3643.46,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s like we can''t do everything, which is content plus outbound campaigns, all for, you know, our entry level service offering.","index":764,"end_time":3661.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3644.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We can do a lot of.","index":765,"end_time":3663.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3662.43,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We could do a little bit of each, which is kind of what we have right now.","index":766,"end_time":3666.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3664.35,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We have like some case studies, we have some content that we''re going to be putting out and we''re running some performance marketing.","index":767,"end_time":3671.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3666.95,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We think we can do a pretty good job with that mixture.","index":768,"end_time":3674.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3672.14,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":769,"end_time":3675.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3675.26,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"If you want to level up how much we''re doing on the content side, then we have to lower what we''re doing on the performance side or we have to up the budget.","index":770,"end_time":3684.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3675.98,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Doesn''t feel like there''s an appetite there for increased budget.","index":771,"end_time":3687.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3684.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Maybe there is.","index":772,"end_time":3688.299,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3687.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''m open to it.","index":773,"end_time":3689.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3688.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But it doesn''t feel like we''re there yet.","index":774,"end_time":3691.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3689.58,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then there''s this other thing that''s coming forward.","index":775,"end_time":3695.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3692.3,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"The issue is, is the results.","index":776,"end_time":3696.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3695.18,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So if we don''t have the performance marketing and we become, it''s not reactive in creating content, but we are essentially supplying materials.","index":777,"end_time":3708.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3697.91,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like, I hope that they drive leads.","index":778,"end_time":3711.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3708.83,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I hope if we make case studies, if we write blog posts, ebooks, we can create like a big report.","index":779,"end_time":3718.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3711.07,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Maybe we go survey and interview people about, I don''t know, not saying we do this Len, but like maybe we go interview 15 scientists and they can tell us what they think about radio waves.","index":780,"end_time":3729.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3718.15,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You know, I''m not saying we do that, but it is something we could do.","index":781,"end_time":3732.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3729.55,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"However, if we do those things, I''m definitely not comfortable saying that we''re gonna get you 12 new appointments or 12 new leads per month.","index":782,"end_time":3742.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3733.27,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s a different engagement.","index":783,"end_time":3744.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3742.87,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Neither is right nor wrong.","index":784,"end_time":3745.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3744.47,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s what''s in the best interest of your business.","index":785,"end_time":3748.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3745.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So do you, it''s like do you want us going out and trying to hunt the new while creating some materials for the organization?","index":786,"end_time":3755.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3748.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That''s what we have right now.","index":787,"end_time":3756.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3755.45,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Or do you want to say, hey, we really think, you know, we''ve got Matt out there, he''s pounding the pavement.","index":788,"end_time":3762.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3757.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If you could provide him with more content and then we can also fight this impending war that we''re going to have.","index":789,"end_time":3769.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3762.69,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Maybe war probably isn''t the right word to use about our federal government.","index":790,"end_time":3773.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3770.33,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"This impending situation with what''s coming, maybe that''s a better use of the funds that we have available.","index":791,"end_time":3784.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3773.85,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And I think that is, I''m open to iterating on it.","index":792,"end_time":3787.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3784.34,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"There is not a right answer.","index":793,"end_time":3788.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3787.26,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Businesses change all the time.","index":794,"end_time":3789.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3788.22,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"This is why we have points.","index":795,"end_time":3790.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3789.18,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We move points around for our clients all the time.","index":796,"end_time":3792.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3790.26,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"The big thing is, are those points directly equating to performance goals or are they.","index":797,"end_time":3798.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3792.34,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Are the goals to help and enable the people within the business?","index":798,"end_time":3804.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3799.7,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Neither''s right or wrong.","index":799,"end_time":3806.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3805.46,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I just think that''s something that we have to make a decision on.","index":800,"end_time":3808.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3806.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, and I think you just articulated, I mean, pretty clearly.","index":801,"end_time":3812.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3809.38,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I think that''s where maybe we''re all gonna getting a little bit hung up.","index":802,"end_time":3816.42,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3812.22,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So I''d have to look at what you guys put together in terms of point structure and the three month program.","index":803,"end_time":3822.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3816.42,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I think on my end like a lot of the content that you''re talking about I think is really just one off stuff.","index":804,"end_time":3827.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3822.18,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I don''t think it''s going to be this, you know, we won''t need much touch points on like updating case studies or constantly getting new case studies.","index":805,"end_time":3836.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3827.74,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So I think once a lot of that content is created and we have it in our, in our database, that''ll be it.","index":806,"end_time":3842.55,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3836.55,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"And then we can kind of adjust points as, as needed and then.","index":807,"end_time":3847.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3843.19,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So I think the simple answer would just be the mixture.","index":808,"end_time":3851.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3848.23,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I think I''m the one implementing a lot of the outreach already.","index":809,"end_time":3854.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3851.03,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I definitely need more support and more creative thinking.","index":810,"end_time":3858.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3854.87,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"You know, I love, I''ve loved it from day one.","index":811,"end_time":3860.8,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3858.84,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"I love the idea of video, video work.","index":812,"end_time":3863.48,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3860.8,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"You Know, obviously updates for just like baseline marketing stuff, like updates to a website, maybe a couple ebooks or downloadable material.","index":813,"end_time":3871.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3863.96,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Sure.","index":814,"end_time":3871.64,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3871.28,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"So that''s what we have in there right now.","index":815,"end_time":3874.559,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3872.52,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I think we''re.","index":816,"end_time":3875.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3874.559,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I think we''re on the same.","index":817,"end_time":3876.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3875.12,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"The same page with maybe some tweaks.","index":818,"end_time":3879,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3876.76,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So I''m five minutes late for another call.","index":819,"end_time":3881.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3879.16,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I just really wanted to hear the.","index":820,"end_time":3883.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3881.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I don''t know, whatever it was that was being talked around.","index":821,"end_time":3887.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3884.85,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Seems pretty important.","index":822,"end_time":3889.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3888.05,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So, Matt, I''m gonna send some time for us to.","index":823,"end_time":3893.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3890.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''ll have Colin just send some time for us to connect next week.","index":824,"end_time":3896.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3893.81,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''ll get you over the roadmap and let''s iterate on it.","index":825,"end_time":3898.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3896.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Let''s find something that everyone feels comfortable with and then.","index":826,"end_time":3901.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3898.97,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yes, Len, Ozzy, Matt, everybody, we''re here to help you when things come up and we need to make some content directly related to situations that arise.","index":827,"end_time":3912.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3901.73,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Just got off a call, actually.","index":828,"end_time":3914.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3913.17,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Colin and I right before this with a client who last year got absolutely crushed.","index":829,"end_time":3919.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3914.17,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"They''re in the warehousing and manufacturing space.","index":830,"end_time":3922.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3919.53,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"They got absolutely crushed by tariffs.","index":831,"end_time":3925.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3922.61,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we experience these things with our clients very regularly and we''re here to help you with it on the marketing side.","index":832,"end_time":3932.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3925.81,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we''ll send that stuff over.","index":833,"end_time":3933.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3932.45,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Colin, maybe find a time on Tuesday.","index":834,"end_time":3936.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3934.61,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''ll just throw a time out there, Matt, just because everybody has to jump and I don''t want to coordinate calendars if the time doesn''t work.","index":835,"end_time":3941.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3936.61,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Just counter with something that does.","index":836,"end_time":3942.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3941.6,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I really appreciate everybody jumping on the call, giving your insights and I think, you know, we''ll have a chance to work together on some of these things.","index":837,"end_time":3950.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3943.04,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":838,"end_time":3952.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3951.6,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"And Colin, just really quick.","index":839,"end_time":3953,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3952.04,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Wednesday would be much better next week.","index":840,"end_time":3954.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3953,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Okay.","index":841,"end_time":3956.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3956.239,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wednesday would not work for us.","index":842,"end_time":3958.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3957.52,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Matt, if you''re looking to Thursday.","index":843,"end_time":3962,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3958.96,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"No, for now.","index":844,"end_time":3965.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3963.76,"speaker_name":"lenforkas"},{"text":"If you want, Len and I, once.","index":845,"end_time":3967.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3965.36,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"It won''t work.","index":846,"end_time":3968.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3967.84,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":847,"end_time":3970.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3969.87,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Well, I''ll get back to you then, Colin.","index":848,"end_time":3972.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3970.63,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll send something over and then.","index":849,"end_time":3974.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3972.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can.","index":850,"end_time":3975.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3974.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can play calendar around then.","index":851,"end_time":3977.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3975.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":852,"end_time":3977.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3977.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you guys so much.","index":853,"end_time":3979.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3977.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":854,"end_time":3979.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3979.31,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Take care.","index":855,"end_time":3980.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3979.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":856,"end_time":3980.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3980.31,"speaker_name":"matt f"},{"text":"Bye.","index":857,"end_time":3981.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3981.07,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"}],"dateString":"2026-02-04T20:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86761224184?pwd=6XHa7isEgCFC6vLLbNwKiA78umTD9e.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,justin.brown@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,matthew@milestonetowers.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","justin.brown@marketersindemand.com","matthew@milestonetowers.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KG58N6PWHZ5SKC534HYEKMYP","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Outlined a growth roadmap aiming for 12 qualified leads per month by month twelve.","Identified weak digital presence among competitors; paid ads offer low-cost opportunity to compete.","Agreed initial focus on content creation, including case studies and empathy-based messaging.","Discussed shifting point allocation to address emerging federal policy PR risk this spring.","Matt confirmed contact lists exist and outreach underway; content support seen as high-value."],"highlights":[{"quote":"If these goals were to come true... Is that a good use of your money?","speaker":"Justin Brown"},{"quote":"We need to get ahead of this to our school partners to immunize them.","speaker":"lenforkas"},{"quote":"Yeah, I mean, I would take that deal every day.","speaker":"matt f"}],"topics":["delivery","content","risk","strategy"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-02-05T17:41:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Strategy and Competitive Positioning**\n\nThe team agreed on a tailored marketing roadmap leveraging the low competitive presence in paid advertising to build brand and lead generation momentum. (02:05)\n\n- **Colin Costigan** highlighted that major competitors **Tower Co, Diamond, and Everest** score a **1 out of 10** in paid advertising presence, creating a strong opportunity to capture market share with a strategic paid media approach focused on LinkedIn and targeted digital channels.\n- Competitors rely heavily on organic social media, with Tower Co having over **6,000 followers**, about **10.5 times** Milestone Towers’ **586 followers**, but lack paid ads, signaling an untapped area to reach decision makers.\n- Milestone Towers’ positioning as a **municipal partnership specialist** with over **25 years of experience** and transparent community engagement offers a key differentiator to leverage in marketing content and messaging.\n- The customer psychology insight showed municipal decision makers focus on **budget shortfalls and community opposition**, not just infrastructure needs, aligning well with Milestone’s value proposition to mitigate risk through transparent engagement.\n\n## **Target Market and Ideal Customer Profiles**\n\nThe team confirmed clear target accounts and personas focusing on wireless carriers, municipal governments, and public school systems, with a split of qualified leads expected from these segments. (11:54)\n\n- Target accounts primarily include **national and regional wireless carriers** like **T-Mobile, AT&T, and Verizon**, with focus on east coast markets and regional leadership teams as primary contacts.\n- The municipal segment targets **municipal governments and public school systems**, represented by personas such as **David Martinez, a fictional facilities director** facing budget cuts and community opposition.\n- A smaller but important segment includes **fire departments and emergency management agencies**, acting more as project supporters than decision makers.\n- The team agreed on a **60% carrier-sourced and 40% municipal-sourced split** for qualified inquiries, emphasizing decision makers with active coverage or property development needs.\n\n## **Annual Goals and Lead Generation Targets**\n\nThe agreed annual goal is to build a predictable pipeline reaching **12 qualified inquiries per month by month 12**, focusing on decision makers within the defined target accounts. (24:51)\n\n- These inquiries must represent **validated needs** from wireless carriers, municipalities, or school districts in the service areas, with discovery calls scheduled as a key conversion step.\n- The ramp-up expects gradual growth, targeting **6 inquiries per month by month 6**, scaling to **12 per month by month 12**, with flexibility based on business flow.\n- The team viewed **12 inquiries per month** as realistic and aligned with internal expectations, assuming that qualified leads will convert to real projects.\n- The split of inquiries includes both new business development and maintaining existing customer relationships, addressing both wireless customers and municipal owners.\n\n## **Marketing Tactics and Budget Allocation**\n\nThe marketing approach involves phased content creation, account-based marketing (ABM), and light paid advertising as a retargeting layer, with a monthly budget of **$6,000 for agency services plus $500 to $2,000 for ad spend**, starting cautiously in month two or three. (30:31)\n\n- Content production includes launching an **educational content and case study library**, web page updates, pitch decks, and potentially a monthly video series featuring carriers and municipal contacts.\n- Paid media will serve primarily as a **retargeting and brand awareness layer** supporting direct outreach rather than broad direct response ads, focusing on LinkedIn and targeted digital platforms.\n- The agency will build and manage marketing infrastructure using tools like **Clay, B2B, Factors, Supabase, and N8N** to collect engagement data, track lead signals, and integrate with Salesforce for lead management.\n- The team prioritized content creation and ABM over heavy ad spend initially, agreeing on testing lower ad budgets and scaling based on return on investment.\n\n## **Sales and Outreach Integration**\n\nDirect engagement and cold calling by internal teams remain the primary lead generation method, with marketing efforts designed to support and validate outreach through content and targeted ads. (44:54)\n\n- Lenforkas emphasized that **new opportunities come from hard-to-get sites and municipalities where competition is weak**, making trust and expertise critical selling points.\n- Ads and email campaigns will target prospects pre- and post-outreach to build familiarity and improve conversion rates, creating a “drum beat” of consistent brand presence.\n- Using AI tools, the agency can provide **contact-level engagement data** to prioritize follow-up calls and tailor outreach efforts based on prospect behavior.\n- Matt expressed that the marketing tech stack might be **overkill for the small, focused municipal and carrier contact lists**, suggesting the infrastructure is better suited for scaling to larger private landowner audiences.\n\n## **Emerging PR Challenge and Content Strategy**\n\nThe team identified an urgent need to prepare for an upcoming **federal-level PR challenge related to health concerns over cell towers near schools**, requiring proactive content and communication support. (57:11)\n\n- Lenforkas explained that the **Environmental Health Trust**, funded by **RFK Jr.**, will release a report this spring potentially restricting tower siting near schools due to alleged health risks.\n- This poses a risk to Milestone Towers’ core market and brand, necessitating early education and advocacy to “immunize” school partners against misinformation.\n- The marketing agency was asked to allocate points toward **reactive content creation and PR support** focused on countering negative narratives and protecting existing partnerships.\n- Matt prioritized a flexible point allocation between **content production, ABM outreach, and reactive PR efforts**, emphasizing the need to balance ongoing lead generation with emergent brand defense without increasing overall budget.","outline":null,"keywords":["Marketing roadmap","account-based marketing","paid media strategy","municipal targeting","competitive analysis","content creation"],"overview":"- **Marketing Opportunity:** Major competitors score low in paid ads, creating a chance for Milestone Towers to capture market share.\n\n- **Target Accounts:** Focus on wireless carriers, municipal governments, and public schools, with a lead split of 60% carriers and 40% municipalities.\n\n- **Annual Goal:** Aim for 12 qualified inquiries per month by month 12, starting with 6 by month 6 to ensure steady growth.\n\n- **Marketing Tactics:** Initial budget of $6,000 monthly for agency services, plus up to $2,000 for targeted ads, focusing on content and ABM.\n\n- **PR Challenge:** Urgent preparation needed for potential federal PR issues related to health concerns over cell towers near schools. \n\n- **Engagement Strategy:** Direct outreach supported by ads, with AI tools to enhance follow-up with prospects based on engagement data.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend marketing research document and roadmap overview to Milestone Towers for review (07:13)\nPrepare and share detailed marketing roadmap and points system breakdown for client feedback (55:30)\nSchedule follow-up meeting to discuss roadmap iterations and next steps, proposing times and accommodating participants'' availability (01:05:57)\n\n**Justin Brown**\nSupport preparation of content infrastructure including case studies, video series, outreach sequences, and marketing operations (31:00)\nClarify marketing engagement approach focusing on combined outreach, retargeting ads, and tracking engagement signals (48:26)\nCoordinate sending follow-up meeting invitations and ensure agenda includes iterative planning on content vs performance marketing balance (01:05:57)\n\n**Matt Forkas**\nReview and assess proposed point system deliverables and three-month marketing plan detailing content creation, outreach, and ABM activities (54:40)\nProvide feedback on priority areas including potential emphasis on content creation to support ongoing outreach and prepare for political/PR concerns (01:02:35)\nShare additional insight into internal lead generation practices, contacting relevant municipal and carrier decision makers (45:26)\n\n**Len Forkas**\nContinue prioritizing direct engagement and cold calling with carriers and municipalities and provide target lists as needed for marketing targeting (45:10)\nAlert the marketing team about upcoming political/PR issues and work collaboratively on messaging and educational content to prepare partners (57:00)\n\n**Oswaldo Reyes-Chica**\nCollaborate on validating qualified lead criteria and helping structure key performance indicators for inquiry quality and conversion (42:50)\nParticipate in roadmap review and contribute perspective on internal expectations and alignment on lead targets (50:02)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"8ea33157-4750-4188-8bd1-75072eea09c1","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
