    '{"id":"01KG3W4NEWYM8HV7R7S67VMT5W","title":"MiD//Rezku POS: Reconnect","summary":{"notes":"## **Contract and Onboarding**\n\nThe team agreed to start work immediately upon signing an updated Statement of Work (SOW).\n\n- **Justin Brown confirmed** they have enough information to begin work and will send the updated **SOW this afternoon** to Paul for review (02:01)  \n    - The existing Master Service Agreement (MSA) is already in place, speeding contract finalization  \n    - Justin emphasized the importance of starting execution over prolonged planning to drive results  \n    - Once the **SOW is signed via DocuSign**, onboarding materials will be sent to Georgi as the main contact  \n    - This approach aims to accelerate project launch and early delivery milestones  \n\n- **Paul Katsch expressed trust** despite prior skepticism about vendors, highlighting the team''s different, practical approach (02:15)  \n    - Paul noted past experiences with overpromising companies, valuing this team’s straightforwardness  \n    - He committed to recommending the team publicly if outcomes meet expectations  \n    - This sets a high bar for execution quality and transparency to build ongoing partnership  \n    - Georgi will coordinate communications, streamlining workflow between teams  \n\n## **Project Roadmap and Execution Strategy**\n\nLaunching work immediately aligns with a pragmatic roadmap focused on iterative progress.\n\n- **Justin Brown outlined** that Colin, Tristan, and he spent many hours crafting a detailed roadmap to guide initial efforts (01:09)  \n    - The roadmap is a living document, expected to evolve with real-time insights and results  \n    - The team prioritizes action over endless discussion to maintain momentum  \n    - This iterative approach supports quick adjustments based on early data and feedback  \n    - It ensures the project remains flexible yet focused on measurable outcomes  \n\n- The decision to start \"rolling sleeves up\" reflects a shift from planning paralysis to execution urgency (01:17)  \n    - This mindset aims to reduce time-to-market and accelerate value delivery  \n    - It underscores a results-driven culture preferred by Paul and his team  \n    - The strategic choice supports rapid validation of marketing ideas and tactics  \n    - It mitigates risks of delayed launches common in cautious vendor engagements  \n\n## **Communication and Coordination**\n\nClear points of contact and streamlined communication channels were established for efficient collaboration.\n\n- **Georgi Funtarov confirmed** he will be the primary contact for all project-related communications (02:48)  \n    - This ensures a single communication funnel, reducing confusion and delays  \n    - Justin will send all onboarding and project documents directly to Georgi  \n    - Centralized communication supports faster issue resolution and decision-making  \n    - This structure facilitates smoother coordination across internal and external teams  \n\n- The use of DocuSign for contract execution was highlighted to speed administrative processes (02:51)  \n    - This reduces paperwork bottlenecks and enables immediate project starts  \n    - Digital signing supports remote collaboration and quicker approvals  \n    - It fits the overall plan for rapid onboarding and rollout  \n    - This choice reflects a modern, efficient operational approach preferred by both sides  \n\n## **Partnership Outlook and Business Impact**\n\nThere is a mutual commitment to building a long-term partnership based on trust and results.\n\n- **Paul Katsch emphasized** the importance of tangible results to justify ongoing collaboration and referrals (02:15)  \n    - He conveyed cautious optimism based on the team’s practical approach and prior work  \n    - Successful execution could lead to expanding business and formal recommendations  \n    - This sets expectations for measurable impact and accountability  \n    - It reflects a strategic alignment to grow both businesses through shared success  \n\n- Justin expressed enthusiasm about the partnership, reinforcing a positive, forward-looking attitude (02:02)  \n    - This tone aims to build confidence and motivate the team for early wins  \n    - It signals readiness to adapt and scale based on initial project outcomes  \n    - The attitude supports a culture of collaboration and mutual growth  \n    - It lays the foundation for ongoing innovation and joint business development","outline":null,"keywords":["Statement of Work","Roadmap Document","Onboarding","Marketing Strategy","Trust","Collaboration"],"overview":"- **Contract Signing:** Team begins work upon signing updated SOW; existing MSA simplifies contract process for a quicker start.\n\n- **Trust in Team:** Paul''s trust built on team''s practical, straightforward approach despite past vendor skepticism; potential for public recommendations.\n\n- **Project Roadmap:** Detailed roadmap created for iterative progress; prioritizes actionable insights over prolonged planning for flexibility and momentum.\n\n- **Communication Structure:** Georgi designated as primary contact to streamline communications; reduces confusion and enables faster decision-making.\n\n- **Digital Processes:** DocuSign for contracts accelerates project initiation; allows for quick approvals and supports remote collaboration.\n\n- **Partnership Commitment:** Focus on tangible results to justify ongoing collaboration; successful execution could lead to business expansion and referrals.","action_items":"\n**Justin Brown**\nSend updated Statement of Work (SOW) document this afternoon to Paul Katsch and Georgi Funtarov (01:50)\nSend DocuSign agreement to Paul immediately following the meeting (02:51)\n\n**Georgi Funtarov**\nServe as main point of contact for the project going forward (02:48)\n\n**Paul Katsch**\nReview and sign the DocuSign agreement after receipt from Justin (02:51)\n"},"duration":3.4000000953674316,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Justin Brown"},{"id":1,"name":"paulkatsch"},{"id":2,"name":"Justin Brown"},{"id":3,"name":"georgifuntarov"},{"id":4,"name":"Justin Brown"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Gentlemen.","index":0,"end_time":5.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.28,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"George.","index":1,"end_time":7.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.72,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"Hello, sir.","index":2,"end_time":17.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":16.16,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Hello.","index":3,"end_time":17.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.44,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"Hello.","index":4,"end_time":18.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.84,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"How are you guys doing?","index":5,"end_time":19.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":18.32,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":6,"end_time":20.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":19.84,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Some of us better than others.","index":7,"end_time":24.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":22.72,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I think the, the cold weather is starting to take a toll on some.","index":8,"end_time":28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.32,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Some hell healths, but doing okay.","index":9,"end_time":31.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":28.49,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We are.","index":10,"end_time":32.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":32.01,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re not doing our offensive setup today, so on our way.","index":11,"end_time":37.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":32.49,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"No worries.","index":12,"end_time":38.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":38.01,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Well, we had a chance to send over some materials and wanted to just touch base today and see, you know, what the next step is and if.","index":13,"end_time":48.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":38.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''Re ready to move forward.","index":14,"end_time":49.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":48.33,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So how do we.","index":15,"end_time":51.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":50.41,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"What.","index":16,"end_time":51.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.53,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"Tell me if we want to move forward.","index":17,"end_time":53.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":52.49,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"What.","index":18,"end_time":54.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.93,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"What do we do if we want to move forward?","index":19,"end_time":57.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.17,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"I send over an SOW for us to start work and we start work tomorrow.","index":20,"end_time":62.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.42,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Okay.","index":21,"end_time":63.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.42,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"And do you feel like you have enough information to start work?","index":22,"end_time":68.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.82,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"I definitely feel like we have enough.","index":23,"end_time":72.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":69.74,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Information to start work.","index":24,"end_time":73.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.14,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Colin, Tristan and me, we spent many hours putting together that roadmap document.","index":25,"end_time":80.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":74.06,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Right.","index":26,"end_time":81.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":80.82,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"There will be iterations to it, updates, adjustments, but we''ve got to start rolling our sleeves up and we can sit here until the sun comes up and.","index":27,"end_time":89.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":81.3,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Talk about ideas for doing marketing and then you got to go out and actually do it.","index":28,"end_time":96.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":89.98,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so we''re.","index":29,"end_time":97.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":96.42,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we''re going to put our trust in you and that''s a big deal.","index":30,"end_time":100.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":97.46,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"So send me that document.","index":31,"end_time":102.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.02,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"Do you have my email specifically?","index":32,"end_time":104.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.86,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"I.","index":33,"end_time":106.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":105.94,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"I''ll put in the chat for you.","index":34,"end_time":109.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":108.44,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Just.","index":35,"end_time":110.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":109.72,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You can put that in there and.","index":36,"end_time":112.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.84,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, we already have the.","index":37,"end_time":113.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":112.32,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"The MSA in place, so it''s just an updated sow.","index":38,"end_time":117.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":114.84,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I can put that together this afternoon.","index":39,"end_time":119.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":117.8,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And we get going.","index":40,"end_time":121,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":119.6,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Let''s do it.","index":41,"end_time":122.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":121.4,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"All right, well, I appreciate you putting.","index":42,"end_time":124.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":122.68,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Your trust in us, Paul.","index":43,"end_time":125.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":124.12,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re really excited to move forward, so.","index":44,"end_time":128.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":125.64,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''Ll, we''ll be excited to see how this goes and upwards and onwards.","index":45,"end_time":135.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.56,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"All right.","index":46,"end_time":136.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":135.58,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"If, if this works out well, we''ll be happy to, you know, recommend you and help you build your business, because you''re helping us build ours.","index":47,"end_time":143.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":136.3,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"But, you know, we, we''ve.","index":48,"end_time":145.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":143.18,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"We were a little gun shy when it comes to this stuff.","index":49,"end_time":147.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":145.42,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"We''ve talked to a lot of companies and, you know, most of them are just a bunch of hot air.","index":50,"end_time":151.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.54,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"And almost the better the presentation is though, the worse the company is.","index":51,"end_time":155.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":151.22,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"So, you know, you guys have a very different approach and so we''re going to give it a try.","index":52,"end_time":159.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.06,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"All right, well, I appreciate that.","index":53,"end_time":161.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":159.91,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''ll get that stuff over to you and then I''ll coordinate with Georgie.","index":54,"end_time":167.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.47,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, send everything to me.","index":55,"end_time":169.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":168.15,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I''ll be your main point of contact.","index":56,"end_time":170.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":169.39,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":57,"end_time":171.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":170.75,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"Okay.","index":58,"end_time":171.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.35,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And I''m going to send Paul the docusign after this once that comes back, I''ll send all the onboarding materials to.","index":59,"end_time":178.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You, Georgie, and we''re ready to go.","index":60,"end_time":180.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":178.51,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Let''s do it, gentlemen.","index":61,"end_time":181.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":180.47,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"All right.","index":62,"end_time":182.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.07,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"Sounds pretty cool.","index":63,"end_time":183.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.47,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"All right, thanks, everybody.","index":64,"end_time":184.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":183.43,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":65,"end_time":185.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":184.75,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"},{"text":"See ya.","index":66,"end_time":186.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Bye.","index":67,"end_time":187.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":186.79,"speaker_name":"paulkatsch"}],"dateString":"2026-02-04T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82392934130?pwd=xxtZrvkx73x0YgLxakrgjPXYJF0AI9.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,justin.brown@marketersindemand.com,gfuntarov@rezku.com,brett.martin@rezku.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","justin.brown@marketersindemand.com","gfuntarov@rezku.com","brett.martin@rezku.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KG3W4NEWYM8HV7R7S67VMT5W","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
