WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '965b21f3-8748-420c-aaf3-b3fdcaa2f504',
    '2026-02-04 15:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KGFKHM7XB134Y0N9M65JDVN2',
    'iCorps + New North Weekly',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Samuel Bagnall","Ruby Pontbriand","Nathalie Mintjens"}'::text[],
    1691,
    'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_NWVjNDBkODktN2I3OS00ZWQ0LTgzMDEtMWNkNDk5OGVlYjQ2@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"0188564a-93de-489c-bf54-1927d4a9ed28","Oid":"bdae9fd3-d481-4c5e-aeea-7272e37b7d07"}',
    '{"id":"01KGFKHM7XB134Y0N9M65JDVN2","title":"iCorps + New North Weekly","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Performance and Lead Quality**\n\nThe team decided to **pause all paid ads** temporarily, focusing instead on analyzing lead quality and funnel performance in January, which yielded **47 MQLs and 10 SQLs**, maintaining a strong conversion rate (05:53).\n\n- **Nathalie Mintjens** highlighted that all current **three active opportunities** originated from **SEO** sources, signaling the channel’s strength.\n- They are developing a detailed report tracing leads from **MQL to customer stage** to identify exact drop-off points and reasons, distinguishing between marketing quality issues and sales disqualifications.\n- **Ruby Pontbriand** shared preliminary findings from closed-lost deals, noting most losses were to competitors due to **fit or price**, followed by non-responsiveness and scope changes.\n- Ruby also emphasized the need to track leads by **company counts rather than individual contacts** to align better with sales priorities.\n- Both Ruby and Nathalie agreed to compare their analyses for a fuller picture on where leads stall or fail to convert.\n\n## **Sales Enablement and Competitive Positioning**\n\nStrengthening sales enablement emerged as a key priority to address lost deals due to price sensitivity and competitive fit concerns (11:21).\n\n- Ruby explained that the company’s **white glove, relationship-focused, and experienced service** justifies a higher price, but prospects need clearer proof of this value.\n- They discussed enhancing sales enablement materials so sales reps can better communicate the company’s unique value, including **consultant tenure and personalized account management**.\n- Nathalie suggested reviewing assets from **Kirk’s team** to improve post-meeting sales collateral aligned with the brand story and competitive positioning.\n- Ruby framed the sales enablement push as essential to turning strong leads into customers, referencing past AI readiness sales enablement efforts as a model.\n\n## **SEO and Website Optimization Strategy**\n\nSEO remains the top-performing channel, with plans to prioritize ongoing content and site improvements to boost leads and engagement (15:32).\n\n- Nathalie confirmed the **Microsoft page updates** are ready for review and that they are comparing new site SEO performance against the old site.\n- They will create a monthly plan allocating resources toward **new blog posts and page optimizations** to capitalize on SEO momentum.\n- Location pages will be linked more prominently, potentially added as a **nav dropdown and homepage call-out**, improving user visibility and local SEO.\n- Ruby recommended researching competitors and MSPs to find the best ways to showcase multiple office locations as a trust signal without diluting SEO.\n\n## **Content Optimization and Blog Update Project**\n\nA new project aims to systematically update the **top five performing blog posts** to meet **2026 SEO and AI search standards**, while enhancing conversion potential (19:45).\n\n- Ruby proposed using **AI tools like ChatGPT or Copilot** to analyze existing content for accuracy and SEO gaps before content expert Jeff reviews updates.\n- Nathalie agreed and offered to provide **Ahrefs data on pages ranking between 10th and 15th positions** to prioritize which posts to optimize first.\n- They plan to cross-reference rankings from multiple tools, including Google Search Console and Ahrefs, to ensure accuracy and avoid misleading data.\n- Colin suggested starting with a small **proof of concept** on one blog post to validate the workflow before scaling.\n\n## **Sales Team Update and Lead Follow-up**\n\nA new salesperson, **Jeremy**, recently joined and is being trained to handle follow-up on **highly engaged leads**, with no immediate changes to existing campaigns except paused ads (26:16).\n\n- Ruby and Sam are leading Jeremy’s onboarding, focusing on encompassing leads and developing his follow-up skills.\n- Paid ads remain paused, but **email and LinkedIn outreach campaigns continue** under Ruby’s management to maintain engagement.\n- This approach balances resource allocation by freeing up management time from ad optimization to strengthen sales enablement efforts.","outline":null,"keywords":["MQL","SQL","sales enablement","SEO performance","blog post optimization","paid advertising pause"],"overview":"- **Ad Strategy:** All paid ads paused to analyze lead quality and funnel performance; 47 MQLs and 10 SQLs noted in January.\n- **Lead Tracking:** Developing a report tracing leads from MQL to customer stage to identify drop-off reasons effectively.\n- **Sales Enablement Focus:** Improving sales materials to show unique value; emphasize service quality and account management.\n- **SEO Strategy:** SEO remains top channel; Microsoft page updates ready for review; plans for ongoing content and site improvements.\n- **Blog Updates:** Aim to optimize top five blog posts using AI tools; prioritizing based on Ahrefs data and existing rankings.\n- **New Salesperson Training:** Jeremy onboarded to follow up on engaged leads; email and LinkedIn outreach campaigns continue despite ad pause.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nSend updated Microsoft page draft for review post-meeting (15:30)\nProvide report and executive summary comparing new vs. old website SEO performance (19:00)\nConduct research on competitor MSP sites’ location page practices and recommend enhancements (18:55)\nAnalyze Google Search Console impressions drop from Aug-Sept to identify cause (19:00)\nGenerate Ahrefs report showing pages ranked 10-15 for prioritizing SEO optimization (23:30)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nPull ranking data from both Google Search Console and Ahrefs for comparison, focusing on top 5 blog posts as MVP (25:15)\n\n**Sam Bagnall**\nShare Jeff’s feedback on AI landing pages as soon as available (26:05)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nContinue managing email and LinkedIn outreach campaigns despite paused ads; train new salesperson Jeremy on lead follow-up (27:20)\n"},"duration":28.190000534057617,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"id":2,"name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"id":3,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Sam.","index":0,"end_time":14.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":15.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.2,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":16.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.6,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":16.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.64,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":4,"end_time":18.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":16.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Good, Doing good.","index":5,"end_time":20.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":18.64,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''m in my car, so hopefully this isn''t too weird.","index":6,"end_time":26.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":21.52,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"If it gets weird, I''ll turn off my camera, but yeah, it works.","index":7,"end_time":30.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.32,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Couldn''t tell.","index":8,"end_time":33.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":32.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Really?","index":9,"end_time":34.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":34.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nope.","index":10,"end_time":35.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":35.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, I shouldn''t have said anything.","index":11,"end_time":37.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":35.96,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"My bad.","index":12,"end_time":38.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":37.84,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"You guys have any plans for the super bowl or this weekend or anything?","index":13,"end_time":48.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.68,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Probably just trying to relax at home as much as possible.","index":14,"end_time":54.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":51.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":15,"end_time":57.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.08,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":16,"end_time":58.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.96,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How about you?","index":17,"end_time":59.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, same thing.","index":18,"end_time":60.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.88,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Hanging out.","index":19,"end_time":62.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":61.4,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I don''t even know who''s playing in the Super Bowl.","index":20,"end_time":71.479,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":69.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do you usually watch or have you ever or.","index":21,"end_time":74.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":72.6,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Okay.","index":22,"end_time":76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.56,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I didn''t.","index":23,"end_time":76.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":76,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I didn''t.","index":24,"end_time":76.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":76.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I didn''t know.","index":25,"end_time":77.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":76.64,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Actually.","index":26,"end_time":79.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":79.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just this year was my first time, I think sitting down and watching a full football game because the Bears were doing well and so the whole city was involved, but other than that, I don''t know anything about football.","index":27,"end_time":94.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":80.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, well.","index":28,"end_time":97.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.84,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, Mike''s going to the game.","index":29,"end_time":98.759,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":97.68,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"The Patriots and the Patriots are playing in it.","index":30,"end_time":101.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.759,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So Mike''s going.","index":31,"end_time":102.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.68,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":32,"end_time":103.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":103.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":33,"end_time":104.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.28,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So he''s heading out Friday and come back Monday.","index":34,"end_time":106.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.72,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"He''s excited, so.","index":35,"end_time":109.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.08,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, up here it''s a big deal.","index":36,"end_time":110.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.36,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Home team''s playing, so.","index":37,"end_time":113.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":112.36,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":38,"end_time":154.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":154.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hey.","index":39,"end_time":155.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.41,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":40,"end_time":157.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":156.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Good.","index":41,"end_time":159.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":159.17,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":42,"end_time":161.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":159.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":43,"end_time":161.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":161.21,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"How are you doing, Sam?","index":44,"end_time":164.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":163.49,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Good, good.","index":45,"end_time":166.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.65,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"How''s George?","index":46,"end_time":167.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":166.97,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"He''s good.","index":47,"end_time":168.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":168.29,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"He went back, so I figured I would.","index":48,"end_time":171.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":168.81,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, I figured I would just take it.","index":49,"end_time":172.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.49,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":50,"end_time":175.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":172.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Cool.","index":51,"end_time":175.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":175.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How''s the week been, Ruby?","index":52,"end_time":180.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":178.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Less snow.","index":53,"end_time":183.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":182.13,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''s good than previous weeks.","index":54,"end_time":187.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":185.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Weather wise.","index":55,"end_time":191.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":190.54,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Sunny and bright and nice and not melting, but that''s okay.","index":56,"end_time":196.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":191.58,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"How about you?","index":57,"end_time":199.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":199.02,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s been a good week.","index":58,"end_time":203.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":202.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I. I''m in Hong Kong now.","index":59,"end_time":206.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":203.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I came for another trip, so it was a weekend of a lot of travel.","index":60,"end_time":209.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":206.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m just trying to get adjusted.","index":61,"end_time":211.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":210.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, wow.","index":62,"end_time":213.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":212.36,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"How long have you been there?","index":63,"end_time":214.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":213.8,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I just got in on Sunday evening.","index":64,"end_time":219,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":215.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":65,"end_time":219.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":219.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, That''s a lot.","index":66,"end_time":222.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":220.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"What''s that?","index":67,"end_time":223.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"How long is that trip?","index":68,"end_time":224.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":223.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s a 16 hour flight if it''s direct from Chicago.","index":69,"end_time":230.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":225.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":70,"end_time":231.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":230.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But a lot of the times though, they don''t have that flight.","index":71,"end_time":234.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":232.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You have to go like through New York or la.","index":72,"end_time":237.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":234.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I was looking at this time.","index":73,"end_time":239.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":238.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They had it though.","index":74,"end_time":240.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":239.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, that''s good.","index":75,"end_time":241.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.33,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, I was looking at.","index":76,"end_time":242.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":241.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I was looking at trying to get like do a vacation or something or go to go to Mexico and the flights are outrageously expensive.","index":77,"end_time":251.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":244.25,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I don''t know what is going on, but it''s probably because I''m looking at like school vacation week and that''s not.","index":78,"end_time":257.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":251.25,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Going to happen because it''s spring break.","index":79,"end_time":259.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":257.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":80,"end_time":260.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":260.09,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So much.","index":81,"end_time":261.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":260.97,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Or like even for February break, the kids have a week off and it''s just outrageous.","index":82,"end_time":266.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":261.45,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Even if I.","index":83,"end_time":267.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267.02,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I looked, I like tracked the flight, I started looking back in like the summer, and even then it was really exciting.","index":84,"end_time":274.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267.62,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s just, they''re not.","index":85,"end_time":274.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":274.02,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''re not budging on the price, so.","index":86,"end_time":276.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":274.86,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Oh, well.","index":87,"end_time":277.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":277.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And are you gonna stay local then for that week?","index":88,"end_time":283.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":281.179,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m gonna.","index":89,"end_time":284.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":283.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s nothing.","index":90,"end_time":286.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":284.9,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I can''t.","index":91,"end_time":286.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":286.3,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I can''t.","index":92,"end_time":287.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":286.86,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''m not gonna go anywhere because even going somewhere domestic would be cheaper.","index":93,"end_time":290.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":287.22,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But I don''t know, I kind of really like the idea of doing the all inclusive thing, which would be what I would do if we went to Mexico, because I have that, like, that all inclusive place that I go to or whatever.","index":94,"end_time":304.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":290.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I don''t know.","index":95,"end_time":305.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.77,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We''ll see.","index":96,"end_time":306.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":305.49,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s fine.","index":97,"end_time":306.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.01,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I was just saying like that flights are crazy and Hong Kong is a really long flight.","index":98,"end_time":312.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.61,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":99,"end_time":315.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":314.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Actually, I was able to get it very cheap, like compared to usual because we have like, there''s a lot of students that come from this part of the world to US colleges.","index":100,"end_time":325.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":315.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So January and August, it''s like triple the price, what it is right now because everyone''s flying back to school.","index":101,"end_time":332.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":325.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But yeah, I was shocked.","index":102,"end_time":334.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":332.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I saw the flight for February.","index":103,"end_time":335.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":334.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It was super cheap, so I had to do it.","index":104,"end_time":338.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":335.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m glad you did.","index":105,"end_time":340.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":339.7,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''s cool.","index":106,"end_time":341.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":340.7,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":107,"end_time":341.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.38,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"All right, so we can get started.","index":108,"end_time":346.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":343.9,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I know that.","index":109,"end_time":347.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":346.3,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":110,"end_time":351.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":351.02,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":111,"end_time":351.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":351.38,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":112,"end_time":354.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":353.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So just looking at abm, so we paused all of the paid ads.","index":113,"end_time":360.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":355.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I know we maybe wanted to discuss or just.","index":114,"end_time":365.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":361.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It looks like that.","index":115,"end_time":366.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":365.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, they''d like us to pause it for the time being, which is fine.","index":116,"end_time":369.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":366.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So all of the channels are not spending anything right now and just wanted to look back on January.","index":117,"end_time":376.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":369.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we had 47 MQLs come in, 10 of which became SQLs.","index":118,"end_time":382.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":377.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So still quite a high conversion rate to SQL.","index":119,"end_time":385.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":383.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then some other metrics from the executive dashboard.","index":120,"end_time":389.139,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":386.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right now we have three active opportunities that came from marketing sources and all of those were SEO.","index":121,"end_time":396.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":389.139,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep.","index":122,"end_time":397.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":397.18,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then something else that we''re working on from our side is that report that we talked about last week that shows.","index":123,"end_time":405.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":399.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, we had a good number of those top of funnel MQLs come in for the year.","index":124,"end_time":409.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":405.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But where are they getting stuck?","index":125,"end_time":411.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":410.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Where they''re not getting to that customer stage.","index":126,"end_time":414.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":411.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''re running a report on that right now.","index":127,"end_time":416.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":414.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''ll see like the MQL to SQL conversion and then the conversion to opportunities and then to customers and then through the Lead detail, we''ll be able to see what''s the reason that they''re not going through.","index":128,"end_time":428.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":416.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Is it a marketing issue that it''s the quality that''s coming in or is it that it''s another reason why they''re unqualified?","index":129,"end_time":436.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":428.3,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like they didn''t get past the first sales meeting.","index":130,"end_time":439.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":436.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''ll be able to see more of that as we get that report.","index":131,"end_time":443.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":439.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":132,"end_time":444.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":443.82,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That sounds great.","index":133,"end_time":446.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":445.34,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''m interested to see what you guys come back with because I''ve done some, like last week and into this week I did some uncovering of stuff and it''s based like baseline.","index":134,"end_time":462.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":446.06,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"What I''ve uncovered is that the reason for losing the deals is the majority were like lost to competitor either on fit or price, followed by like them not being responsive, followed by them staying with their current provider or keeping work in house or I don''t know, there was a couple that were like change of scope companies too small or they didn''t want to spend the money for the invest for the assessment.","index":135,"end_time":500.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.35,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So Those are like 2025 closed, lost by reason and that.","index":136,"end_time":505.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":501.01,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So that may basically means like they came in through marketing sources, they were in SQL, they made it to opportunity, a deal was created, but they did not actually convert to customer.","index":137,"end_time":516.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":505.13,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So.","index":138,"end_time":517.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":517.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, but I''m interested to see like what you guys pull up too, especially for like the numbers because.","index":139,"end_time":523.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":517.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Or like the count of, count of companies is kind of what I''m basing a lot of these on for Mike and Jeff and Cook, so that the number like.","index":140,"end_time":536.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":525.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because I know when we look at MQL numbers we''re usually looking at like the total of individual contacts.","index":141,"end_time":542.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.4,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I''m doing it based on companies because they''re really looking at like number of actual customers, which means we only get a customer out of a company, if that makes sense.","index":142,"end_time":557.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":143,"end_time":558.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":557.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":144,"end_time":559.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":559.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":145,"end_time":561.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":561.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":146,"end_time":563.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.65,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I ran stuff for like closed one reason also see like, okay, why are we winning deals?","index":147,"end_time":568.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":563.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Number one reason is expertise.","index":148,"end_time":570.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569.21,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then I did uncover that there were, I mean like we had talked about before that there were a number.","index":149,"end_time":581.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.81,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Of.","index":150,"end_time":581.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":581.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"SQLs that moved backwards in the.","index":151,"end_time":586.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":584.49,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Funnel.","index":152,"end_time":587.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":586.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You know, just like based on sales qualification.","index":153,"end_time":592.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":590.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So.","index":154,"end_time":592.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":592.35,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I put those things together.","index":155,"end_time":599.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":598.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But like I said, I''m really excited and thankful that you guys are running some of these things too so we can compare notes and yeah.","index":156,"end_time":607.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":599.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"See what, what, what we need to do next.","index":157,"end_time":610.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":608.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I did do one slide on kind of like funnel ownership and accountability to kind of explain the story that this is what marketing controls and this is what sales controls and like what the primary KPI is for success on each of those sides.","index":158,"end_time":630.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":610.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And again, that''s.","index":159,"end_time":634.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.88,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''s for.","index":160,"end_time":635.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":634.88,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"For.","index":161,"end_time":635.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":635.44,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"What is the word?","index":162,"end_time":638.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":637.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s the.","index":163,"end_time":640.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":640,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"The approach or like the.","index":164,"end_time":642.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.28,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"The philosophy, I guess, that I have that is a little different than.","index":165,"end_time":647.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":642.76,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Than what theirs is.","index":166,"end_time":648.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":647.52,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So.","index":167,"end_time":649.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":648.72,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":168,"end_time":650.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":649.76,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":169,"end_time":652.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":652.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But that''s.","index":170,"end_time":656.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":655.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You mentioned looking at the closed.","index":171,"end_time":658.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":656.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"One reason that''s a good stat to know as well.","index":172,"end_time":661,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":658.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I feel like from that we can also see, like, if expertise is one of the top reasons, maybe we focus on creating content that leans into that more and sales enablement content too.","index":173,"end_time":673.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":661,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So they''re on the calls.","index":174,"end_time":675.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":674.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do they have assets that speak to the expertise?","index":175,"end_time":678.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":675.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That could be something we help with as well.","index":176,"end_time":681.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":679.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think you''re absolutely right.","index":177,"end_time":683.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":681.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I know, like.","index":178,"end_time":685.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":684.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And that also ties into.","index":179,"end_time":687,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":685.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"The last reason is that we''re losing on price or to competitors because we aren''t cheap.","index":180,"end_time":694.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":687,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":181,"end_time":695.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":694.97,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We are white glove.","index":182,"end_time":697.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":695.33,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We are kind of fancy.","index":183,"end_time":699.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":697.17,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":184,"end_time":699.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":699.25,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But we are also very people focused, relationship focused and still, you know, very humble and grounded in those.","index":185,"end_time":705.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":699.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"In those areas of, you know, business consulting and, you know, the actual bottom line of your business and things like that.","index":186,"end_time":713.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":706.09,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So that''s why we''re not cheap, is that we really do present a greater value than our competitors.","index":187,"end_time":719.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":713.61,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And that is definitely an area where I think we could do more to showcase that to prospects and to, you know, a potential deal.","index":188,"end_time":732.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":719.44,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because we''re doing a good job getting them in.","index":189,"end_time":733.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":732.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":190,"end_time":734.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":733.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because at the top of the funnel, the website looks legit, our content looks legit.","index":191,"end_time":738.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":734.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''re seeing good stuff from us.","index":192,"end_time":740.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":738.96,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We do look like, you know, we''re worth going with, which is why they booked the call.","index":193,"end_time":745.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.96,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''re just not totally convinced that it''s worth the full investment.","index":194,"end_time":750.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":746.88,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And maybe that''s the missing piece where we need more materials that continue to drive that point.","index":195,"end_time":756.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":751.68,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":196,"end_time":758.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":757.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If it would be beneficial, like if Kirk''s team has a deck that they use or any of the assets that they send out after meetings, we can take a look at that and see if there''s any improvements that we can make.","index":197,"end_time":773.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":759.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think it goes a lot of it goes back to the brand story that we have in your strategy document.","index":198,"end_time":779.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":773.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I don''t think we had tied in, like, how prospects compare I core to competitors.","index":199,"end_time":787.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":781.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But I think that is an important piece, especially if we''re losing a lot of deals because of price.","index":200,"end_time":792.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":787.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"What is it about the increased price with I core?","index":201,"end_time":797.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":794.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"What did they get that you don''t get with competitors?","index":202,"end_time":799.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":797.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, and we do some of that in the brand story and on the website.","index":203,"end_time":804.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":800.46,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And it''s like us based Right.","index":204,"end_time":806.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.14,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And it''s over 30 years of experience and you''re going to get somebody on the phone no matter what.","index":205,"end_time":813.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":806.86,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"If you call us, somebody''s going to answer.","index":206,"end_time":815.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":813.66,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You''re going to get your person, this person knows you.","index":207,"end_time":818.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":815.9,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They know your business like it''s, you know, the 10 year.","index":208,"end_time":823.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":818.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You know, the fact that your, your account manager is going to be the same one.","index":209,"end_time":827.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":823.67,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You''re.","index":210,"end_time":828.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":827.99,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''re not going to be like cycling through a bunch of different consultants if they become a client.","index":211,"end_time":834.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":828.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s.","index":212,"end_time":834.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":834.35,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think that''s a big piece for a lot of prospects, is they don''t want a revolving door if they''re going to make the investment.","index":213,"end_time":840.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":835.67,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They want it to really, truly be something that''s going to stick and stay and stand the test of time.","index":214,"end_time":845.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":840.95,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And our data on our employee tenure and our consultant tenure and experience backs that up.","index":215,"end_time":851.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":845.99,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like, and that''s again like on the About Us page and why we did some of those differentiators in the brand story.","index":216,"end_time":857.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":851.63,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But to your point.","index":217,"end_time":860.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":859.47,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":218,"end_time":860.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":860.35,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think we just need to kind of Sales enablement is probably the missing piece here.","index":219,"end_time":865.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":860.75,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I know that''s come up, you know, in like fits and starts with even just with the AI readiness.","index":220,"end_time":871.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":866.27,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":221,"end_time":871.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":871.63,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It was a big focus on sales enablement.","index":222,"end_time":874.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":871.99,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":223,"end_time":874.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":874.55,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Let''s make sure that they can sell it.","index":224,"end_time":876.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":874.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Um, let''s make sure they''re trained, let''s make sure they understand this so that, sure, we''ll get a lead, but if they can''t sell it, then that lead is kind of not set up for success.","index":225,"end_time":887.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":877.04,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I think leaning into that sales enablement thing would be definitely a great strategy starting point.","index":226,"end_time":898.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":890,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I agree.","index":227,"end_time":901.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":899.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And just looking at your point, so I, with the paid media paused, I actually removed that from your monthly management tasks here.","index":228,"end_time":913.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":902.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''re not going to charge you to be like optimizing the campaign.","index":229,"end_time":917.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":914.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that opened up eight more points for us throughout the month that we can then put back into some of those sales enablement content pieces.","index":230,"end_time":925.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":917.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":231,"end_time":929.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":925.66,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All right.","index":232,"end_time":932.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":932.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for SEO, so we have the Microsoft page updated, ready for your review from Jeff''s feedback.","index":233,"end_time":939.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":932.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I''ll send that over right after this meeting.","index":234,"end_time":942.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":939.31,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then looking at performance.","index":235,"end_time":947.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":946.07,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So another report that we''re creating right now is we''re going to look.","index":236,"end_time":951.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":947.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''re looking at the performance of the new site versus the previous one.","index":237,"end_time":954.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":951.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So like we mentioned last week, organic and SEO was the best channel last year.","index":238,"end_time":959.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":955.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So just looking at how the new or how that compares to what the website was doing before, what are some of the key pages that are Bringing in new form fills, and then on top of that, we''re bringing in the data, but then also creating an executive report that kind of outlines what''s the plan for that going forward.","index":239,"end_time":979.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":960.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So kind of putting more of a priority on SEO and seeing like, okay, per month we can allocate a certain number of points to developing a new blog post or optimizing an existing page.","index":240,"end_time":991.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":980.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So just creating a plan for how we''re going to lean into this channel more going forward.","index":241,"end_time":996.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":992.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then, so I got your note about the location pages, and I think that''s a good idea.","index":242,"end_time":1007.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1000.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We can link them to the locations that we have over here, definitely.","index":243,"end_time":1014.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1007.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then I also, we can put them in a more prominent place on the homepage, like just a small call out that you do have local offices in these locations.","index":244,"end_time":1023.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1014.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then one of the highest traffic pages is also the encompass page.","index":245,"end_time":1028.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1024.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that could be another place that we insert it.","index":246,"end_time":1035.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1030.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":247,"end_time":1036.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1035.7,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":248,"end_time":1037.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1037.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right.","index":249,"end_time":1040.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1039.62,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":250,"end_time":1041.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1040.1,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And that''s.","index":251,"end_time":1042.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1041.3,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Do you think it makes sense to put it in the nav or just homepage?","index":252,"end_time":1049.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1045.39,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we could put our locations drop down here.","index":253,"end_time":1057.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1054.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":254,"end_time":1064.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1063.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Because right now the only place that they see it is if they click onto.","index":255,"end_time":1068.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1064.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, the Contact Us page.","index":256,"end_time":1071.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1068.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":257,"end_time":1071.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1071.61,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I also wonder maybe, does it belong.","index":258,"end_time":1078.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1072.97,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"On the about page on this one?","index":259,"end_time":1081.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1078.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":260,"end_time":1082.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1081.93,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think it would make sense.","index":261,"end_time":1086.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1085.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Maybe do some research on how other our competitors do it or how other MSPs are showcasing their locations.","index":262,"end_time":1095.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1087.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because, I mean, it''s a selling point.","index":263,"end_time":1098.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1097.06,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right?","index":264,"end_time":1098.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1098.34,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like, it''s, people like to have that, like, local thing or that they know, oh, they''ve got more than just one office.","index":265,"end_time":1105.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1098.62,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''re legit.","index":266,"end_time":1106.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1105.54,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And like, how to, how do we capitalize on that?","index":267,"end_time":1111.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.9,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because we know it''s, it''s a hot topic.","index":268,"end_time":1114.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1111.46,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":269,"end_time":1114.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1114.42,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We know people are searching for location stuff and performing well.","index":270,"end_time":1118.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1114.62,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I just want to, no, I don''t want to flood it and I don''t want to compete against ourselves, but I think there''s definitely some, some stuff we could do there.","index":271,"end_time":1130.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1120.18,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":272,"end_time":1134.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1133.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":273,"end_time":1137.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1136.75,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''ll, I''ll do some research on other MSP sites.","index":274,"end_time":1139.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1137.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":275,"end_time":1140.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1140.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":276,"end_time":1142.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1142.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":277,"end_time":1145.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1144.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then lastly, we''re also taking a look at the Google search console impressions from August to September.","index":278,"end_time":1152.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1145.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''re going to look at if there were, for example, if we had any campaigns running at that time that we then paused, which caused the drop.","index":279,"end_time":1161.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1153.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If there were any organic pages that lost their rankings.","index":280,"end_time":1164.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1161.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''ll take a look and see what caused that drop.","index":281,"end_time":1166.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1164.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":282,"end_time":1168.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1167.5,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":283,"end_time":1170.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1169.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, that sounds good.","index":284,"end_time":1172.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1171.26,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I''ll send all of These reports over once they''re done.","index":285,"end_time":1179.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1176.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Was there anything else you wanted to discuss?","index":286,"end_time":1181.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1180.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I have one thing just to just so you are up to speed is where is that?","index":287,"end_time":1195.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1185.61,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So it''s along the topic of SEO and it''s along the topic of how I landed in Google Search console yesterday and it has to do with blog posts and blog content.","index":288,"end_time":1209.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1197.93,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So when I was in Google Google Search Console, I was looking at the blog property also in that disaster recovery sites blog is like top performing, like so many.","index":289,"end_time":1222.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1210.45,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s like ranked really high in position.","index":290,"end_time":1224.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1222.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Tons of impressions, tons of.","index":291,"end_time":1227.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1225.49,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s like.","index":292,"end_time":1227.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1227.17,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And it always has been like I''ve known about this one for a while and we did update it a little bit a couple years ago because we realized, wow, like a lot of people come to this page.","index":293,"end_time":1238.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1228.77,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I just kind of like, kind of reopened that project, but on like a larger scale where we could systematically go through these like top.","index":294,"end_time":1250.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1240.91,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Maybe like the top five performing blog posts that are, you know, obviously outdated, right?","index":295,"end_time":1257.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1250.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because unless they were written today, they''re outdated.","index":296,"end_time":1259.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1257.35,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But to what degree are they outdated and what content needs to get updated to bring them into 2026 standards?","index":297,"end_time":1266.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1260.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then what content can be optimized for SEO and for AI search?","index":298,"end_time":1272.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1268,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And more importantly, and most importantly is how do we optimize the content for conversions, for leads, for people to like book a meeting or do the contact Us page.","index":299,"end_time":1284,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1272.72,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I ran that idea by Sam and I put together kind of like an idea for a project plan of like how to systematically do it and go through them.","index":300,"end_time":1298.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1286.88,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And we would use like a prompt with chatgpt or Copilot to help us with that, like analysis of each of the blog posts.","index":301,"end_time":1307.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1298.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then we would share our findings with Jeff for his expertise in terms of the content updates and accuracy.","index":302,"end_time":1317.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1308.14,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then we would run it by you guys for your insights on the SEO best practices and AI search best practices.","index":303,"end_time":1325.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1317.9,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And also the focus on.","index":304,"end_time":1329.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1325.58,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We know it''s doing well, it''s been doing well.","index":305,"end_time":1332.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We don''t want to undo any of that accidentally, you know, by any changes that we make.","index":306,"end_time":1338.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1332.09,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So anyway, that was kind of a small little project idea that I thought would be low hanging, low hanging fruit, not a, not a huge lift, not like a massive amount of points on your end or at all.","index":307,"end_time":1354.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1340.57,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It would just, I think we would just ask you for if you could review some stuff.","index":308,"end_time":1359.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1354.93,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that sounds good.","index":309,"end_time":1363.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1361.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We could even.","index":310,"end_time":1364.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1364.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I know we''ve, in the past we did it the other way where we did the writing for SEO and then Jeff reviewed after and then his Review kind of changes the content itself.","index":311,"end_time":1378.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1366.3,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I think doing it your way is best.","index":312,"end_time":1380.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1378.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Where we have Jeff write the content and then you can send it over to us and we can do the task of optimizing it for a specific keyword.","index":313,"end_time":1386.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1380.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":314,"end_time":1389.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1387.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":315,"end_time":1389.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1389.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And a lot of these, like I said, they''re written already.","index":316,"end_time":1391.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1389.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We already have like performance metrics on them.","index":317,"end_time":1396.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1393.68,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So it makes it.","index":318,"end_time":1400.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1399.2,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s a little easier because it''s not like we''re.","index":319,"end_time":1401.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1400.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s not like a blank slate.","index":320,"end_time":1402.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1401.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s just optimizing existing stuff.","index":321,"end_time":1406.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1402.96,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":322,"end_time":1411.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1410.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then I can also pull a report from Ahrefs that shows you current rankings of sites.","index":323,"end_time":1419.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1411.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So maybe if there''s like, if we have a group of pages that are ranking between 10th to 15th place, those are the ones that we want to prioritize first to see if we can move them up a bit.","index":324,"end_time":1430.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1419.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I can send you a report that shows all the pages within that range.","index":325,"end_time":1434.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1430.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, that''d be helpful.","index":326,"end_time":1435.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1434.51,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then I have a question with ranking.","index":327,"end_time":1439.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1436.19,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like when I go into Google Search Console and I look for like that, the New York page, the location based SEO page that you said was ranking like whatever it was, the rank that I see in Google Search Console is.","index":328,"end_time":1457.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1441.64,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Seems different.","index":329,"end_time":1457.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1457.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And is that just because I''m using the wrong program or like Ahrefs is the better one to use or it''s like a.","index":330,"end_time":1465.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1459.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"How does that work?","index":331,"end_time":1466.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1465.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Ahrefs specifically?","index":332,"end_time":1469.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1468.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I was gonna say it also more depends on where their servers are pulling from because Google rankings will be in different spots based on location.","index":333,"end_time":1476.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1469.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so what''s the best tool to use then?","index":334,"end_time":1481.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1477.42,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s actually a mix.","index":335,"end_time":1484.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1483.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We like having several tools, pull them and then find the truth in between.","index":336,"end_time":1487.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1484.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I see.","index":337,"end_time":1488.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1488.06,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, So I wonder if, if maybe we need your help then on that ranking thing for the blog posts.","index":338,"end_time":1505.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1488.82,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because what I''m pulling, if we pull it from just from Google Search Console alone for the rank, it may not be accurate.","index":339,"end_time":1514.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1506.28,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we should at least pull from both sources and have like a comparison column.","index":340,"end_time":1518.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1514.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":341,"end_time":1519.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1518.78,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, so that''d be cool if you guys could do that.","index":342,"end_time":1524.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1520.94,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Just a top.","index":343,"end_time":1524.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1524.18,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You don''t have to do.","index":344,"end_time":1527.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1526.38,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You don''t have to do the ranking of like every single blog post you''ve ever done.","index":345,"end_time":1530.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1528.22,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because like I said, I think we''re just going to focus on like top five to start or open to your thoughts.","index":346,"end_time":1538.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1532.54,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Do you think top five is too small?","index":347,"end_time":1539.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1538.34,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Should we do top ten?","index":348,"end_time":1540.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1539.5,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like, I don''t know.","index":349,"end_time":1541.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1540.5,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think we also need kind of an MVP here.","index":350,"end_time":1543.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I want to establish some proof of concept of like this flow that we''re working on and then we can scale it.","index":351,"end_time":1550.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1545.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, makes sense.","index":352,"end_time":1552.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1551.19,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All right, so maybe just go with the one we know for sure.","index":353,"end_time":1556.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1553.35,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":354,"end_time":1557.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1556.55,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":355,"end_time":1560.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1560.23,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then the AI landing pages.","index":356,"end_time":1564.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1563.35,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Natalie, Jeff has feedback, but I just need to get it from him.","index":357,"end_time":1567.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1564.79,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So I''m working on that.","index":358,"end_time":1568.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1567.79,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll send it over as soon as I get it.","index":359,"end_time":1571.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1569.43,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":360,"end_time":1573.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1572.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":361,"end_time":1574.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1573.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, and then another update.","index":362,"end_time":1578,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1576.76,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We did have a new, A new salesperson start with us a couple weeks back.","index":363,"end_time":1586,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1578,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"His name''s Jeremy.","index":364,"end_time":1586.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1586,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"He''s pretty cool.","index":365,"end_time":1587.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1586.88,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And so he''s on the sales team and he''s, you know, getting up to speed.","index":366,"end_time":1593.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1588.2,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"His number one focus is encompassing and Sam and I are.","index":367,"end_time":1599.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1593.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Or we, we''ve, you know, like trained him and stuff and he is going to take over some of the highly engaged leads for follow up.","index":368,"end_time":1607.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1599.87,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I know we''ve like paused ads, so like, I don''t know if that means.","index":369,"end_time":1612.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1608.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That doesn''t mean like the, the others if we paused.","index":370,"end_time":1615.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1612.91,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, wait, sorry.","index":371,"end_time":1616.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1615.87,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"He''s going to work on lead follow up.","index":372,"end_time":1618.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1617.31,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''m going to train him how to do it.","index":373,"end_time":1621.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1619.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That was the update, just so you guys know.","index":374,"end_time":1623.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1621.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But nothing else needs to like change or whatever.","index":375,"end_time":1626.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1624.15,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I know we paused ads.","index":376,"end_time":1629.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1627.27,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Does that also mean.","index":377,"end_time":1630.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1629.43,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That doesn''t mean that.","index":378,"end_time":1632.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1631.03,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Does that mean the AI readiness campaign entirely is paused or that just means the ads related to it?","index":379,"end_time":1639.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1632.47,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, just the ads are paused.","index":380,"end_time":1641.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1640.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We still have the emails going out and the LinkedIn messages from you.","index":381,"end_time":1645.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1641.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":382,"end_time":1647.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1645.99,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Cool.","index":383,"end_time":1647.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1647.03,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So all that can continue to come from me.","index":384,"end_time":1649.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1647.91,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We don''t need to switch it to Jeremy by any means.","index":385,"end_time":1651.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1649.55,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think that''d be insane to do at this point.","index":386,"end_time":1653.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1651.27,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Let''s just get him to do some follow up and see how that that goes.","index":387,"end_time":1656.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1653.27,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":388,"end_time":1658.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1657.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":389,"end_time":1660.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1658.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Thank you guys.","index":390,"end_time":1661.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1661.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":391,"end_time":1662.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1662.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":392,"end_time":1663.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1662.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Bye.","index":393,"end_time":1664.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1664.45,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Bye.","index":394,"end_time":1665.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1664.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"}],"dateString":"2026-02-04T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"rpontbriand@icorps.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_NWVjNDBkODktN2I3OS00ZWQ0LTgzMDEtMWNkNDk5OGVlYjQ2@thread.v2/0?context={\"Tid\":\"0188564a-93de-489c-bf54-1927d4a9ed28\",\"Oid\":\"bdae9fd3-d481-4c5e-aeea-7272e37b7d07\"}","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,rpontbriand@icorps.com,sbagnall@icorps.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","sbagnall@icorps.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KGFKHM7XB134Y0N9M65JDVN2","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Paused all paid ads; reallocated eight points to sales enablement content development.","Nathalie reported 47 MQLs in January with strong conversion to 10 SQLs, mostly from SEO.","Ruby identified top deal loss reasons: competitor price/fit, unresponsiveness, and staying with current vendor.","Team aligned on revamping high-performing blog posts for SEO, AI search, and conversion optimization.","New hire Jeremy will lead follow-up on highly engaged leads for the Encompass product line."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Flights are crazy and Hong Kong is a really long flight.","speaker":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"quote":"We paused all of the paid ads.","speaker":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"quote":"Number one reason is expertise.","speaker":"Ruby Pontbriand"}],"topics":["SEO","conversion","sales enablement","hiring","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-02-04T17:37:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Performance and Lead Quality**\n\nThe team decided to **pause all paid ads** temporarily, focusing instead on analyzing lead quality and funnel performance in January, which yielded **47 MQLs and 10 SQLs**, maintaining a strong conversion rate (05:53).\n\n- **Nathalie Mintjens** highlighted that all current **three active opportunities** originated from **SEO** sources, signaling the channel’s strength.\n- They are developing a detailed report tracing leads from **MQL to customer stage** to identify exact drop-off points and reasons, distinguishing between marketing quality issues and sales disqualifications.\n- **Ruby Pontbriand** shared preliminary findings from closed-lost deals, noting most losses were to competitors due to **fit or price**, followed by non-responsiveness and scope changes.\n- Ruby also emphasized the need to track leads by **company counts rather than individual contacts** to align better with sales priorities.\n- Both Ruby and Nathalie agreed to compare their analyses for a fuller picture on where leads stall or fail to convert.\n\n## **Sales Enablement and Competitive Positioning**\n\nStrengthening sales enablement emerged as a key priority to address lost deals due to price sensitivity and competitive fit concerns (11:21).\n\n- Ruby explained that the company’s **white glove, relationship-focused, and experienced service** justifies a higher price, but prospects need clearer proof of this value.\n- They discussed enhancing sales enablement materials so sales reps can better communicate the company’s unique value, including **consultant tenure and personalized account management**.\n- Nathalie suggested reviewing assets from **Kirk’s team** to improve post-meeting sales collateral aligned with the brand story and competitive positioning.\n- Ruby framed the sales enablement push as essential to turning strong leads into customers, referencing past AI readiness sales enablement efforts as a model.\n\n## **SEO and Website Optimization Strategy**\n\nSEO remains the top-performing channel, with plans to prioritize ongoing content and site improvements to boost leads and engagement (15:32).\n\n- Nathalie confirmed the **Microsoft page updates** are ready for review and that they are comparing new site SEO performance against the old site.\n- They will create a monthly plan allocating resources toward **new blog posts and page optimizations** to capitalize on SEO momentum.\n- Location pages will be linked more prominently, potentially added as a **nav dropdown and homepage call-out**, improving user visibility and local SEO.\n- Ruby recommended researching competitors and MSPs to find the best ways to showcase multiple office locations as a trust signal without diluting SEO.\n\n## **Content Optimization and Blog Update Project**\n\nA new project aims to systematically update the **top five performing blog posts** to meet **2026 SEO and AI search standards**, while enhancing conversion potential (19:45).\n\n- Ruby proposed using **AI tools like ChatGPT or Copilot** to analyze existing content for accuracy and SEO gaps before content expert Jeff reviews updates.\n- Nathalie agreed and offered to provide **Ahrefs data on pages ranking between 10th and 15th positions** to prioritize which posts to optimize first.\n- They plan to cross-reference rankings from multiple tools, including Google Search Console and Ahrefs, to ensure accuracy and avoid misleading data.\n- Colin suggested starting with a small **proof of concept** on one blog post to validate the workflow before scaling.\n\n## **Sales Team Update and Lead Follow-up**\n\nA new salesperson, **Jeremy**, recently joined and is being trained to handle follow-up on **highly engaged leads**, with no immediate changes to existing campaigns except paused ads (26:16).\n\n- Ruby and Sam are leading Jeremy’s onboarding, focusing on encompassing leads and developing his follow-up skills.\n- Paid ads remain paused, but **email and LinkedIn outreach campaigns continue** under Ruby’s management to maintain engagement.\n- This approach balances resource allocation by freeing up management time from ad optimization to strengthen sales enablement efforts.","outline":null,"keywords":["MQL","SQL","sales enablement","SEO performance","blog post optimization","paid advertising pause"],"overview":"- **Ad Strategy:** All paid ads paused to analyze lead quality and funnel performance; 47 MQLs and 10 SQLs noted in January.\n- **Lead Tracking:** Developing a report tracing leads from MQL to customer stage to identify drop-off reasons effectively.\n- **Sales Enablement Focus:** Improving sales materials to show unique value; emphasize service quality and account management.\n- **SEO Strategy:** SEO remains top channel; Microsoft page updates ready for review; plans for ongoing content and site improvements.\n- **Blog Updates:** Aim to optimize top five blog posts using AI tools; prioritizing based on Ahrefs data and existing rankings.\n- **New Salesperson Training:** Jeremy onboarded to follow up on engaged leads; email and LinkedIn outreach campaigns continue despite ad pause.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nSend updated Microsoft page draft for review post-meeting (15:30)\nProvide report and executive summary comparing new vs. old website SEO performance (19:00)\nConduct research on competitor MSP sites’ location page practices and recommend enhancements (18:55)\nAnalyze Google Search Console impressions drop from Aug-Sept to identify cause (19:00)\nGenerate Ahrefs report showing pages ranked 10-15 for prioritizing SEO optimization (23:30)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nPull ranking data from both Google Search Console and Ahrefs for comparison, focusing on top 5 blog posts as MVP (25:15)\n\n**Sam Bagnall**\nShare Jeff’s feedback on AI landing pages as soon as available (26:05)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nContinue managing email and LinkedIn outreach campaigns despite paused ads; train new salesperson Jeremy on lead follow-up (27:20)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"7951bc7c-6a7a-4bb9-a026-f0140e3692d3","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
