INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: iCorps + New North Weekly',
  '## **Marketing Performance and Lead Quality**

The team decided to **pause all paid ads** temporarily, focusing instead on analyzing lead quality and funnel performance in January, which yielded **47 MQLs and 10 SQLs**, maintaining a strong conversion rate (05:53).

- **Nathalie Mintjens** highlighted that all current **three active opportunities** originated from **SEO** sources, signaling the channel’s strength.
- They are developing a detailed report tracing leads from **MQL to customer stage** to identify exact drop-off points and reasons, distinguishing between marketing quality issues and sales disqualifications.
- **Ruby Pontbriand** shared preliminary findings from closed-lost deals, noting most losses were to competitors due to **fit or price**, followed by non-responsiveness and scope changes.
- Ruby also emphasized the need to track leads by **company counts rather than individual contacts** to align better with sales priorities.
- Both Ruby and Nathalie agreed to compare their analyses for a fuller picture on where leads stall or fail to convert.

## **Sales Enablement and Competitive Positioning**

Strengthening sales enablement emerged as a key priority to address lost deals due to price sensitivity and competitive fit concerns (11:21).

- Ruby explained that the company’s **white glove, relationship-focused, and experienced service** justifies a higher price, but prospects need clearer proof of this value.
- They discussed enhancing sales enablement materials so sales reps can better communicate the company’s unique value, including **consultant tenure and personalized account management**.
- Nathalie suggested reviewing assets from **Kirk’s team** to improve post-meeting sales collateral aligned with the brand story and competitive positioning.
- Ruby framed the sales enablement push as essential to turning strong leads into customers, referencing past AI readiness sales enablement efforts as a model.

## **SEO and Website Optimization Strategy**

SEO remains the top-performing channel, with plans to prioritize ongoing content and site improvements to boost leads and engagement (15:32).

- Nathalie confirmed the **Microsoft page updates** are ready for review and that they are comparing new site SEO performance against the old site.
- They will create a monthly plan allocating resources toward **new blog posts and page optimizations** to capitalize on SEO momentum.
- Location pages will be linked more prominently, potentially added as a **nav dropdown and homepage call-out**, improving user visibility and local SEO.
- Ruby recommended researching competitors and MSPs to find the best ways to showcase multiple office locations as a trust signal without diluting SEO.

## **Content Optimization and Blog Update Project**

A new project aims to systematically update the **top five performing blog posts** to meet **2026 SEO and AI search standards**, while enhancing conversion potential (19:45).

- Ruby proposed using **AI tools like ChatGPT or Copilot** to analyze existing content for accuracy and SEO gaps before content expert Jeff reviews updates.
- Nathalie agreed and offered to provide **Ahrefs data on pages ranking between 10th and 15th positions** to prioritize which posts to optimize first.
- They plan to cross-reference rankings from multiple tools, including Google Search Console and Ahrefs, to ensure accuracy and avoid misleading data.
- Colin suggested starting with a small **proof of concept** on one blog post to validate the workflow before scaling.

## **Sales Team Update and Lead Follow-up**

A new salesperson, **Jeremy**, recently joined and is being trained to handle follow-up on **highly engaged leads**, with no immediate changes to existing campaigns except paused ads (26:16).

- Ruby and Sam are leading Jeremy’s onboarding, focusing on encompassing leads and developing his follow-up skills.
- Paid ads remain paused, but **email and LinkedIn outreach campaigns continue** under Ruby’s management to maintain engagement.
- This approach balances resource allocation by freeing up management time from ad optimization to strengthen sales enablement efforts.',
  '2026-02-04 15:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Send updated Microsoft page draft for review post-meeting (15:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide report and executive summary comparing new vs. old website SEO performance (19:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Conduct research on competitor MSP sites’ location page practices and recommend enhancements (18:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Analyze Google Search Console impressions drop from Aug-Sept to identify cause (19:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Generate Ahrefs report showing pages ranked 10-15 for prioritizing SEO optimization (23:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Pull ranking data from both Google Search Console and Ahrefs for comparison, focusing on top 5 blog posts as MVP (25:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Share Jeff’s feedback on AI landing pages as soon as available (26:05)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue managing email and LinkedIn outreach campaigns despite paused ads; train new salesperson Jeremy on lead follow-up (27:20)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Techmode+New North (2026-02-03 20:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'b1f3ae44-0316-492e-aef1-bb260b814482',
    '2026-02-03 20:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KGDNQZXTYSZFM3Q7ZET4JTFB',
    'Techmode+New North',
    '{"Matthew Look","Colin Costigan","Ryan Fisher","Lindsay Hall","Christopher Quigley"}'::text[],
    1763,
    'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_ODBmZWFjMWYtMWIxYi00NmZmLTgyMDEtOWFiZWJhYWEwYzVh@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"3801011d-e732-48ee-be2a-e499b1a29ba4","Oid":"e804fbe9-a623-4d26-a887-992e62fb92d1"}',
    '{"id":"01KGDNQZXTYSZFM3Q7ZET4JTFB","title":"Techmode+New North","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Strategy and Keyword Optimization**\n\nThe team decided to refocus campaigns toward broader, generic UCAS terms and consolidate landing pages to capture a larger audience likely searching for RingCentral alternatives, leveraging its **60% market share** as a key driver (02:36).\n\n- **Matthew Look** argued that redirecting generic UCAS traffic to a centralized RingCentral alternative page could capture up to **60% of relevant searches**, mitigating the lack of direct RingCentral replacement keywords.\n- Colin agreed and committed to building the necessary campaign infrastructure to support this approach, including form integrations with HubSpot (06:30).\n- The RingCentral questionnaire is confirmed built in Gravity Forms and will be linked on the new landing page to qualify leads better (16:34).\n- Keyword shifts include moving away from low-volume \"move\" or \"switch\" terms toward broader alternatives that show rising search interest, approved by Matthew (13:10).\n- Negative keywords such as Google Voice will be added to refine targeting, with landing pages adjusted accordingly to improve relevance and click-through rates (17:46).\n- Microsoft Ads campaigns will focus on targeted keywords like \"cloud phone system\" and \"small business cloud phone systems,\" avoiding irrelevant terms like AWS or \"set up,\" per Matthew’s guidance (21:15).\n\n## **Campaign Performance Evaluation and Decision Framework**\n\nA clear evaluation framework was established to assess campaign viability through staged criteria, focusing on lead tracking, cost efficiency, and conversion quality over a **2–3 week initial run plus a 10–14 day optimization period** before final decisions (23:19).\n\n- Colin outlined this phased approach for campaign launch, monitoring, and decision-making, emphasizing lead qualification via HubSpot as a critical metric (23:19).\n- Applying this framework, the Amazon Connect campaign, despite a **4.83% click-through rate**, lacks conversions over **90 days**, leading to a consensus to pause or kill the campaign pending further discussion between Ryan and Matthew (18:54, 20:25).\n- The Price Offer campaign showed a **click-through rate increase from 2.6% to 3.1%** with **3–4 clicks daily** on a limited budget, prompting a rewrite of the landing page to better align with top queries like Zoom Phone and Google Voice (17:20).\n- The PMAX campaign will be paused, with its budget reallocated to search campaigns to improve ROI (18:39).\n\n## **Website and Form Integration Enhancements**\n\nThe team prioritized improving form data quality and website content to support better lead management and user experience, focusing on HubSpot integration and testimonial authenticity (05:54).\n\n- Lindsay confirmed the need to split the existing single name field into **first and last name fields** in forms to cleanly integrate with HubSpot, but the team agreed to defer this fix until campaign success justifies the effort (07:08).\n- Colin committed to replacing existing testimonial sections with real Google Reviews to increase credibility, as current testimonial images appear fake, which Matthew flagged as a concern (10:41).\n- Blog templates were categorized into four clear types—trends, MSP-focused, technical features, and competitor comparisons—with user-friendly category selection via checkboxes planned for Lindsay to manage content layouts easily (11:42).\n- Colin will build the category system and walk Lindsay through the content tagging process once ready, simplifying content management workflows (12:48).\n\n## **Lead Follow-up and Account Management**\n\nActive tracking and follow-up on leads generated from campaigns were reviewed, highlighting some overdue tasks and outreach challenges (26:08).\n\n- Christopher Quigley reported difficulties verifying the legitimacy of a contact, **Leo Suo from State College Area School District**, lacking phone and LinkedIn presence despite a valid email domain, highlighting potential lead quality issues (26:08).\n- Follow-up for **J Troop from iTrue Security**, a potential MSP partner, is overdue by two weeks; Michael Lewis had trouble leaving a voicemail due to a full inbox, and a reminder will be sent to Michael to prompt re-engagement (27:01, 28:10).\n- The team maintains manual cleaning of HubSpot records, including capitalization and data normalization, to support efficient qualification and outreach by Christopher (08:04).\n\n## **Market and Competitive Insights**\n\nThe discussion revealed insights into competitor behavior and market positioning that influence campaign decisions and product focus (14:06).\n\n- Matthew shared a unique anecdote about receiving a **$44,000 monthly fake RingCentral invoice** for **2,000 phantom users** on a demo system, highlighting potential competitor reporting tactics and market opacity (14:06).\n- The team acknowledged that RingCentral’s large market share requires creative marketing approaches since direct replacement keywords are restricted or ineffective (03:05).\n- Microsoft Ads keyword targeting showed promising performance around Avaya-related terms, implying a competitive opportunity among users still relying on legacy systems (21:43).\n- The hosting of legacy software downloads like Equinox drives traffic despite irrelevance to current sales, prompting a suggestion to gate downloads behind email capture for lead generation (22:21).\n\n## **Timeline and Next Steps**\n\nThe team aligned on key next steps and deliverables to implement campaign and website updates promptly (24:56).\n\n- Colin will share the detailed campaign evaluation criteria document with the team for reference and ongoing use (24:51).\n- Campaigns for RingCentral generic terms will launch with the updated form and landing page elements once the questionnaire is linked (25:17).\n- Blog template categories will be built, and Lindsay will be trained on their use soon (12:38).\n- Michael Lewis will be reminded to follow up on overdue leads, ensuring no missed opportunities (28:33).\n- The Amazon Connect campaign will be paused or killed based on Matthew and Ryan’s final discussion within the next week (20:25).","outline":null,"keywords":["RingCentral","Campaign Evaluation","Website Updates","HubSpot Integration","Keyword Strategy","Testimonial Management"],"overview":"- **Campaign Focus Shift:** Redirect to broader UCAS terms and consolidate landing pages for better audience capture. \n- **Keyword Strategy Updates:** Move towards high-interest keywords and add negative keywords like Google Voice for better targeting.\n- **Evaluation Framework:** New criteria for campaign viability includes a 2–3 week initial run and a 10–14 day optimization period.\n- **Lead Tracking Challenges:** Issues noted with verifying leads; overdue follow-ups need addressing to improve engagement.\n- **Market Insights:** Competitor behavior impacts strategy; explore opportunities within legacy systems and current traffic sources. \n- **Next Steps Defined:** Implement campaign elements, train on new blog templates, and follow up on overdue leads soon.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nPut together campaign infrastructure for RingCentral landing page that routes generic UCaaS terms there (06:50)\nFix broken website link animations on SMB page (09:53)\nReplace synthetic testimonials on website with authentic Google reviews plugin (10:35)\nBuild blog templates with assigned categories and backend checks; show Lindsay how to select categories once completed (12:38)\nImplement new keywords and headlines for campaigns based on increased search volume and remove irrelevant terms (16:21)\nAdd RingCentral questionnaire link on RingCentral landing page (16:39)\nSend campaign evaluation criteria document to team (24:51)\nContinue cleaning and monitoring HubSpot lead contacts and campaign results (25:56)\n\n**Matthew Look**\nPromote the idea of routing broad UCaaS traffic to RingCentral alternative page (02:36)\nFor now, defer reformatting form fields into first and last name; rely on manual cleaning (07:48)\nConfirm pause or kill decision on Amazon Connect campaign after discussion with Ryan Fisher (20:25)\n\n**Lindsay Hall**\nPrepare RingCentral questionnaire example for inclusion on site (16:43)\nAssist in setting reminders and notify Michael Lewis about overdue follow-ups with leads (28:33)\n\n**Christopher Quigley**\nContinue managing HubSpot contacts follow-up efforts, including sending outreach emails and cleaning data entries (26:08)\n"},"duration":29.389999389648438,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Matthew Look"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"id":3,"name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"id":4,"name":"Christopher Quigley"}],"sentences":[{"text":"All right, There''s Lindsay.","index":0,"end_time":10.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Everyone have a good weekend?","index":1,"end_time":15.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":14.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s pretty good.","index":2,"end_time":17.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.88,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":3,"end_time":20.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Went snowboarding, played some golf, watched Bridgerton.","index":4,"end_time":27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.96,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So, you know, it was a good weekend.","index":5,"end_time":28.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.16,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That is a good weekend.","index":6,"end_time":29.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You actually did all those things?","index":7,"end_time":31.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":29.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I did.","index":8,"end_time":31.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.32,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Nice.","index":9,"end_time":32.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I had two out of three of those things.","index":10,"end_time":36.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":34.92,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Oh, you didn''t go golfing?","index":11,"end_time":39.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":38.68,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You watched Bridgerton too?","index":12,"end_time":41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.88,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s like my guilty pleasure.","index":13,"end_time":44.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.16,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s just nonsense that I enjoy.","index":14,"end_time":45.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.28,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That doesn''t have any stress to it.","index":15,"end_time":47.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":45.8,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Ryan.","index":16,"end_time":47.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.12,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I was shocked that Drew didn''t want to watch it last night, but she didn''t want to watch it.","index":17,"end_time":52.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":48.6,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Maybe she just likes watching.","index":18,"end_time":53.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":52.57,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"I have some of those.","index":19,"end_time":60.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":58.97,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It''s a good storyline this season.","index":20,"end_time":62.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.49,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Do you not know how to leisure?","index":21,"end_time":65.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.17,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That was said last night a few times.","index":22,"end_time":67.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.25,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Leisure.","index":23,"end_time":69.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.49,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Do you not know how to leisure?","index":24,"end_time":70.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.37,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Sit down and relax.","index":25,"end_time":72.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.05,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You have to learn how to leisure.","index":26,"end_time":74.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.49,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Said a leisure.","index":27,"end_time":75.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.25,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"People don''t know.","index":28,"end_time":75.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":75.01,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''m like, I gotta learn how to say that.","index":29,"end_time":77.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.17,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And then we''ve decided we''re calling when we go to the dock.","index":30,"end_time":80.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.74,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''re going to the pro.","index":31,"end_time":81.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":80.7,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''re going to the promenade is what we''re saying from now on, Ryan.","index":32,"end_time":84.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":81.38,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We.","index":33,"end_time":86.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have to be fancier at the lookout.","index":34,"end_time":88.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":86.62,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Look, household.","index":35,"end_time":89.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":88.34,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Would you like to go to the promenade?","index":36,"end_time":90.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":89.22,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Indeed.","index":37,"end_time":92.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":91.46,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Let''s go promenading.","index":38,"end_time":94.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.82,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t know that that''s a word.","index":39,"end_time":95.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":94.18,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"The promenade in Sheboygan.","index":40,"end_time":96.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":95.3,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":97.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.06,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":42,"end_time":99.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With Britishers, I always get thrown off with schedule and diary.","index":43,"end_time":104.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Diary.","index":44,"end_time":106.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.81,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"How do they say diary?","index":45,"end_time":107.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":106.29,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That''s like their calendar is their diary.","index":46,"end_time":109.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I see.","index":47,"end_time":111.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":110.05,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Huh?","index":48,"end_time":111.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":111.05,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I gotcha.","index":49,"end_time":113.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":112.77,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"All right, well, got a lot to go through today.","index":50,"end_time":117.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":115.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh.","index":51,"end_time":118.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":118.13,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So we got a bunch of website updates.","index":52,"end_time":122.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wanted to talk through the blog templates, Lindsay, just to see if we''re lined up on what we want those categories to be.","index":53,"end_time":127.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":122.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a bunch of campaign recommendations.","index":54,"end_time":129.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":127.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Matt, I put together the campaign criteria you were talking about for how we''re going to grade current and ongoing and future campaigns.","index":55,"end_time":137.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Love it.","index":56,"end_time":138.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":137.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Look at that.","index":57,"end_time":138.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.39,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I forgot I even asked for that.","index":58,"end_time":139.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.79,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But good thing someone''s paying attention.","index":59,"end_time":141.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So looking at the Ringcentral landing page.","index":60,"end_time":145.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":143.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is all set up in markup for any additional feedback that you guys may have, but this has been fully written out and designed and for this.","index":61,"end_time":155.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":145.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, good.","index":62,"end_time":156.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s my thought on this one.","index":63,"end_time":158.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":156.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I know we can''t get on, like, Ringcentral sucks or Ringcentral replacement, stuff like that, but if we follow the numbers, they all.","index":64,"end_time":166.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158.35,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They have, like, 60% of the market.","index":65,"end_time":168.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":166.73,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Somebody looking 50% of the time is likely to be a Ringcentral Customer.","index":66,"end_time":176.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.21,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So should we just dump Everybody to our RingCentral alternative page?","index":67,"end_time":180.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":176.33,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Or in worst case, let''s say they don''t, but they know of.","index":68,"end_time":183.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":180.33,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s almost as good.","index":69,"end_time":185.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.33,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right?","index":70,"end_time":186.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":185.93,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Right, Yeah.","index":71,"end_time":187.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":186.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, what we could do is like take all of the Ring Central information we''ve put across several different pages and make like one base page that they land at and then have links for them to go to all the other pages we''ve created.","index":72,"end_time":200.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess.","index":73,"end_time":202.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.78,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":74,"end_time":203.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":202.9,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I.","index":75,"end_time":203.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":203.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe I didn''t make myself.","index":76,"end_time":205.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":203.38,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":77,"end_time":206.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":205.62,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And I don''t.","index":78,"end_time":206.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":206.06,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I wasn''t going that deep yet.","index":79,"end_time":207.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":206.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Colin.","index":80,"end_time":208.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.94,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I guess my point was being, let''s say if we''re going to run a campaign, like, we can''t get on the terms we want, we can''t get on the terms of, like, you can''t like RingCentral replacement, things like that, because they just don''t exist.","index":81,"end_time":217.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.3,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But what if we just took our general terms that we go for, like ucas.","index":82,"end_time":222.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.04,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay, I''m following Hosted.","index":83,"end_time":224.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":223,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ucas.","index":84,"end_time":225.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Hosted.","index":85,"end_time":226.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We just have that and then we.","index":86,"end_time":227.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.04,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Instead of sending that to a generic page of us, you know, that talks about us, maybe we just send those to the RingCentral alternative page, knowing that 60% of the time these people could be people looking for Ring Central replacement.","index":87,"end_time":239.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.72,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s an interesting theory.","index":88,"end_time":241.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":239.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t hate it, Matt.","index":89,"end_time":242.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like that you don''t hate it.","index":90,"end_time":244.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":243.33,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I just always have the fear of, like, they land there and they''re not ring central and they''re like, obviously this isn''t for me.","index":91,"end_time":251.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":92,"end_time":252.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.81,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So the other side of that is, is we''ve been doing that and it''s not.","index":93,"end_time":254.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.21,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s still not for them.","index":94,"end_time":255.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.65,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I don''t know that we have much to lose on the other side of that, Colin.","index":95,"end_time":260.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.61,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a very valid point.","index":96,"end_time":261.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":260.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, if we would have done that out of the gate, I would think it was a terrible idea.","index":97,"end_time":266.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.25,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But based on the experience we have, I don''t know that we got much to lose on that side.","index":98,"end_time":270.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.01,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right.","index":99,"end_time":270.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.06,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":100,"end_time":271.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":270.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, you can keep going.","index":101,"end_time":274.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.34,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Just something to think about on this is, you know, maybe we try something like that.","index":102,"end_time":278.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.46,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And is.","index":103,"end_time":279.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.54,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Is that what''s her name from Always Sunny?","index":104,"end_time":282.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.06,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I think it looks like her.","index":105,"end_time":284.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It also looks like.","index":106,"end_time":285.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":284.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you guys watched Pluribus?","index":107,"end_time":287.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I have not.","index":108,"end_time":288.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":287.74,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Almost looks like the main character from that show.","index":109,"end_time":291.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":110,"end_time":292.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.22,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":111,"end_time":293.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Brian, you''ve seen Pluribus yet or not yet?","index":112,"end_time":296.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.86,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I thought you had.","index":113,"end_time":297.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.74,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Or maybe not.","index":114,"end_time":298.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I watched the first episode and I watched any more of it.","index":115,"end_time":304.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":299.38,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"It''s on my list.","index":116,"end_time":304.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.02,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"It''s really good.","index":117,"end_time":307.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.42,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Lindsay.","index":118,"end_time":307.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.1,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I like it.","index":119,"end_time":308.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.54,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s no Landman.","index":120,"end_time":309.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.58,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s.","index":121,"end_time":311.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s on my list as well.","index":122,"end_time":312.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I. I don''t have Paramount.","index":123,"end_time":313.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":312.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tired of all these different services.","index":124,"end_time":316.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":314.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You got to get that Paramount.","index":125,"end_time":318.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":317.14,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Plus it''s worth it.","index":126,"end_time":319.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":318.46,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"There''s enough good stuff on that one to make it worth it.","index":127,"end_time":322.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":319.68,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"We just finished season one of Landman.","index":128,"end_time":324.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":322.96,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"We started season two last night.","index":129,"end_time":326.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":324.88,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It''s very good.","index":130,"end_time":327.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":326.32,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, my brother in law talks about it all the time.","index":131,"end_time":329.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":327.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And earlier, or I guess late last year, I argued with DirecTV to get a bunch of streaming services through them for free.","index":132,"end_time":337.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Paramount wasn''t included, unfortunately.","index":133,"end_time":339.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But maybe I can argue with them again.","index":134,"end_time":340.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":135,"end_time":342.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay.","index":136,"end_time":343.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.44,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We also created some rotational banners to start testing on these ads.","index":137,"end_time":347.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":343.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have those designed in here and then the blog character sell as well.","index":138,"end_time":351.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lindsay.","index":139,"end_time":352.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":140,"end_time":353.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":352.78,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So displaying these at the bottom like that.","index":141,"end_time":356.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":354.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, I like that.","index":142,"end_time":357.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":356.78,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"All right, let''s get the RingCentral page.","index":143,"end_time":359.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.98,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But here let''s going back to that RingCentral page.","index":144,"end_time":361.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.54,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I love the RingCenter page idea.","index":145,"end_time":363.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.74,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We.","index":146,"end_time":363.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.46,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"How there''s no search unless we do a generic UCAS search.","index":147,"end_time":367.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.78,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s going to get people to this page.","index":148,"end_time":369.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.78,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Am I right?","index":149,"end_time":371.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":370.54,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Because of the market share that Ring Central has.","index":150,"end_time":373.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, that.","index":151,"end_time":373.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s been the.","index":152,"end_time":374.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the fact we can''t get on the term.","index":153,"end_time":376.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.86,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"The terms don''t tend to exist.","index":154,"end_time":377.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.22,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right.","index":155,"end_time":377.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":156,"end_time":378.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.86,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I don''t know how we get anybody to this page if we don''t just do our generic UCAS stuff.","index":157,"end_time":384.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.82,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"To this page.","index":158,"end_time":385.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.86,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":159,"end_time":386.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Am I selling this or do you really agree with me?","index":160,"end_time":390.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.5,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I do agree.","index":161,"end_time":390.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":162,"end_time":391.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.42,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''m a pretty good salesman, so I can.","index":163,"end_time":397.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.74,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I can.","index":164,"end_time":397.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397.14,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I got these markers for my whiteboard, but they''re like half the size of my hand, so I feel like very strange writing.","index":165,"end_time":405.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":399.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":166,"end_time":406.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":406.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I like the idea.","index":167,"end_time":407.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":406.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll put together that campaign infrastructure.","index":168,"end_time":410.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":407.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":169,"end_time":411.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.77,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We also built the form in HubSpot, so that''s connected to the gravity forms.","index":170,"end_time":416.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lindsay.","index":171,"end_time":417.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One thing I did want to ask there, Matt.","index":172,"end_time":419.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":417.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The way that you built the tool, at least in the recordings I was watching from our calls, was one name for field.","index":173,"end_time":424.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can we do a first and last name just so it plays Nice with HubSpot.","index":174,"end_time":428.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do I have to redo?","index":175,"end_time":429.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.69,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''ll have to update the fields and you''ll have to change the field number accordingly.","index":176,"end_time":435.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":430.75,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Wait, wait, wait, wait.","index":177,"end_time":436.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.63,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I thought I had it.","index":178,"end_time":438.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.39,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Did I have it as one field or two fields?","index":179,"end_time":440.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.23,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"One.","index":180,"end_time":440.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":440.51,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So I have to re.","index":181,"end_time":442.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.95,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I have to redo it to change it as two fields.","index":182,"end_time":445.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.71,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I got to go back into Claude and Ask it to switch into two fields.","index":183,"end_time":451.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.51,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s correct.","index":184,"end_time":453.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":452.51,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"What.","index":185,"end_time":454.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.79,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"What''s the downside if I don''t?","index":186,"end_time":455.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.11,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Then they just both go into first name and it''s just a.","index":187,"end_time":458.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":456.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s messy in HubSpot.","index":188,"end_time":459.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if you''d rather the team just correct that when the form comes in, you can do that.","index":189,"end_time":463.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s just do that for the moment.","index":190,"end_time":466.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay.","index":191,"end_time":467.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":466.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s going to be Chris anyways.","index":192,"end_time":470.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, I don''t want to.","index":193,"end_time":471.959,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.84,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I could.","index":194,"end_time":472.439,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.959,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Problem is is you touch anything and you break something so crazy.","index":195,"end_time":476.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.84,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I could be dicking with this thing for a whole day for something that is not even going to take off.","index":196,"end_time":480.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":476.68,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":197,"end_time":481.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":481.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if this thing takes off.","index":198,"end_time":482.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":481.71,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry.","index":199,"end_time":484.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":484.03,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"If it takes off and we end up starting getting a ton of people in it, then it would be worth my time to fix up till that.","index":200,"end_time":490.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"If it''s like three for the next Crystal''s got to do one every three months or something, then.","index":201,"end_time":494.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.15,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You know what?","index":202,"end_time":495.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.75,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''ll deal with it.","index":203,"end_time":496.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.39,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, I got no problem with being able to because usually when I''m gathering intel and whatever and trying to find out as much as I can about it before we, you know, start reaching out, I try to clean up the HubSpot record anyways.","index":204,"end_time":508.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":496.59,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Something, you know, capitalize the proper nouns and stuff like that.","index":205,"end_time":511.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":508.11,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So I got no problem with that.","index":206,"end_time":513.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":511.5,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":207,"end_time":514.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":513.58,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So that''s what we''re going to do for now.","index":208,"end_time":515.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":514.06,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":209,"end_time":515.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":515.5,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Everybody go with that?","index":210,"end_time":516.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.9,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Sounds good to me.","index":211,"end_time":518.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":517.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be a simple command change or I could be dicking with it for a day.","index":212,"end_time":522.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.26,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, I know.","index":213,"end_time":524.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":522.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll run out a lot.","index":214,"end_time":526.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.46,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Did I run out of Claude points?","index":215,"end_time":530.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":528.86,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They''re almost as bad as New north points.","index":216,"end_time":532.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.54,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I think Claude points are worse.","index":217,"end_time":536.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we also have the SMB page.","index":218,"end_time":540.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":538.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we got rid of Enterprise in the HERO or header area and went with UCAS for SMB.","index":219,"end_time":546.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right size for growing teams.","index":220,"end_time":548.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we think everybody knows what SMB means?","index":221,"end_time":554.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.23,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I think the SMBs do okay.","index":222,"end_time":559.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":557.27,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It''s often much more searched than Small to Medium Business.","index":223,"end_time":564.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, good enough.","index":224,"end_time":565.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.87,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":225,"end_time":566.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.86,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It was a legit question.","index":226,"end_time":568.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.82,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I didn''t know.","index":227,"end_time":569.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.78,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Oh, I gotta fix these.","index":228,"end_time":571.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":570.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These just broke just a second ago.","index":229,"end_time":573.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":571.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I probably broke it when I was updating links.","index":230,"end_time":577.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":575.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, I will fix that.","index":231,"end_time":579.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":578.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are in a four column or a four square and they have links to phone systems, the Premiere launch, the Techmode Go page, and the best voip page.","index":232,"end_time":589.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good with that.","index":233,"end_time":593.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":593.15,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Some nice animation there.","index":234,"end_time":600.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":598.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the amazing testimonials that you guys have that are definitely real.","index":235,"end_time":605.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":600.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What if I Had some real testimonials that I wanted to swap out.","index":236,"end_time":610.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":607.07,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Is that something that I can add into the back end of the website?","index":237,"end_time":614.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":610.35,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Because I''d see that they''re saved as individual entities in the back end of the site.","index":238,"end_time":618.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":614.43,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So is that something like I can create, you know, like clone them and like create a new one?","index":239,"end_time":622.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":618.77,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Will they load in there automatically or is that something that will have to be manually adjusted?","index":240,"end_time":628.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":623.37,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, check this real quick.","index":241,"end_time":629.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":628.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":242,"end_time":630.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":630.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or are we just replacing that with our Google one?","index":243,"end_time":633.329,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":631.05,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I want to do.","index":244,"end_time":634.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.329,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s the other.","index":245,"end_time":636.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s the other option.","index":246,"end_time":637.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":636.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":247,"end_time":638.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":637.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it is just the testimonial field that it''s loading from Lindsay.","index":248,"end_time":641.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":249,"end_time":641.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":641.21,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"The custom post type that''s in there.","index":250,"end_time":643.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":641.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":251,"end_time":644.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":643.7,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m not a big fan of those.","index":252,"end_time":646.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.82,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They look fake.","index":253,"end_time":646.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.06,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Even the pictures look fake.","index":254,"end_time":648.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":647.06,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Well, the pictures are definitely fake.","index":255,"end_time":651.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":649.06,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"To your point though, Matt, we could just fully replace the testimonial section with the review.","index":256,"end_time":662.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":655.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the Google Reviews plugin.","index":257,"end_time":665.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":663.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I want to do.","index":258,"end_time":666.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665.22,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":259,"end_time":667.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.58,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s top of my list of things I want to do.","index":260,"end_time":669.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":667.7,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I liked that on another website I saw.","index":261,"end_time":671.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.74,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":262,"end_time":673.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":672.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Colin, can you go in and give us a good review though.","index":263,"end_time":676.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.65,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Colin in our mailing list of technical clients so that he can.","index":264,"end_time":683.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":679.37,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"We''re doing a drawing for $500 gift card.","index":265,"end_time":685.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":683.29,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"If you give us a good review then I''ll put enter you in the drawing.","index":266,"end_time":687.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":685.25,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":267,"end_time":688.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.49,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And then Lindsey, I know we shared the blog templates and you guys looked at those designs and we talked through having categories we can use the different designs.","index":268,"end_time":699.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you had a chance to think through what those categories would be?","index":269,"end_time":702.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":699.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I did.","index":270,"end_time":703.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":702.55,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Let me find my thingy here.","index":271,"end_time":706.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":703.35,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So it was kind of hard to choose like the individual tags, I guess.","index":272,"end_time":714.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":706.79,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"But I did say I have notes here.","index":273,"end_time":717.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":714.95,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So like the list type ones kind of.","index":274,"end_time":719.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":717.51,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"We''ve done a couple of those in the past two weeks.","index":275,"end_time":722.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":719.47,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Kind of like 20, 26.","index":276,"end_time":723.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":722.43,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Like top things and trends.","index":277,"end_time":726.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":724.32,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":278,"end_time":727.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":727.12,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And then like the MSP focused ones can do the.","index":279,"end_time":730.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":727.56,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Like the.","index":280,"end_time":731,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":730.48,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Where all the controls are on the right side, all the navigation stuff''s on the right side.","index":281,"end_time":735.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":731,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And then product features, technical stuff like the call routing, the stir shaken attestation.","index":282,"end_time":743.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":735.84,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And then also competitor comparisons should be the ones with the navigation on the left side.","index":283,"end_time":749.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":744.32,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Okay.","index":284,"end_time":750.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":749.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then essentially everything else would keep the current template.","index":285,"end_time":753.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":750.09,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Okay.","index":286,"end_time":755.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":755.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":287,"end_time":755.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":755.49,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Love it.","index":288,"end_time":759.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice and easy.","index":289,"end_time":761.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":760.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, we''ll build out all those categories then.","index":290,"end_time":763.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":761.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":291,"end_time":764.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":764.33,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And then once those are built, can you show me how to choose them?","index":292,"end_time":768.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":764.73,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":293,"end_time":769.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":768.97,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So we''re going to make it a checkbox that you''ll just have to click and then it''ll update the design and everything that''s being laid out.","index":294,"end_time":777.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":769.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":295,"end_time":777.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":777.29,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And then I should check that checkbox obviously before I start entering any content or making any changes to them.","index":296,"end_time":782.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":777.73,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Actually.","index":297,"end_time":786.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, you really shouldn''t have to.","index":298,"end_time":787.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":786.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we can walk through all that when it''s.","index":299,"end_time":788.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":787.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When the functionality is fully built in.","index":300,"end_time":790.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":301,"end_time":791.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":790.65,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":302,"end_time":791.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":791.09,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":303,"end_time":792.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":791.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":304,"end_time":793.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":793.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then looking at.","index":305,"end_time":794.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":793.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we''re talking about the looking to move ad group and not driving results.","index":306,"end_time":798.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":794.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know, keywords are very low search volume there.","index":307,"end_time":801.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":798.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did put together some new keyword suggestions.","index":308,"end_time":803.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":801.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can move the teams.","index":309,"end_time":806.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":804.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here we go.","index":310,"end_time":806.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":806.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we were running was a lot around literal switch from or move terminology.","index":311,"end_time":814.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":808.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what we''re suggesting is moving into some of the more alternative type language.","index":312,"end_time":821.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":815.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we are seeing some search volume pick up around these keywords, Matt.","index":313,"end_time":825.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we want to dive back into that.","index":314,"end_time":828.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":826.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe Ringcentral cut their budget for the new year.","index":315,"end_time":831.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":829.52,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Somebody doesn''t.","index":316,"end_time":839.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So no one''s paying that $40,000 a month bill they keep sending us, Ryan.","index":317,"end_time":843.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.96,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They had to cut back on their SEO.","index":318,"end_time":845.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They''ve been sending that bill for like six years.","index":319,"end_time":848.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":846.76,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Six years, man.","index":320,"end_time":850.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":849.16,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"What is that?","index":321,"end_time":851.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":850.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Every month?","index":322,"end_time":853.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":853,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, I don''t want to, I don''t want to bore you with central, but you know, a long time ago when we started to get into this hosted world, we sold Ring Central for briefly, for a brief time just to kind of get our feet wet, understand how it worked and kind of get some competitive information.","index":323,"end_time":867.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":853.6,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I think we sold two.","index":324,"end_time":868.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.62,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"RingCentral gave us a free demo system, you know, to basically demo in and play with and everything.","index":325,"end_time":875.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":869.06,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"At some point along the line, somebody added like 2000 users to that demo system.","index":326,"end_time":880.419,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.7,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Bills it out monthly for like.","index":327,"end_time":883.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.14,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"How much is it, Ryan?","index":328,"end_time":884.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":883.14,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"60 grand?","index":329,"end_time":884.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":884.18,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"40,000.","index":330,"end_time":887.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":887.06,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"It''s like $44,000 a month.","index":331,"end_time":889.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":887.78,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"$44,000.","index":332,"end_time":891.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":889.79,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They bill it out to a phony credit card, to a phony address every month.","index":333,"end_time":896.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":891.63,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Been doing it for probably six to eight years.","index":334,"end_time":898.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":896.83,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''ve been getting that bill.","index":335,"end_time":899.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.95,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Wow.","index":336,"end_time":900.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":900.19,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Somehow it''s the emails, me the invoice.","index":337,"end_time":910.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":903.63,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"For that and it''s all scammy.","index":338,"end_time":912.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.03,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s all scammy line number, Wall street stuff, you know.","index":339,"end_time":917.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":340,"end_time":919.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":917.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They''re reporting back to their shareholders, like, look, we have 2,000 users in this one.","index":341,"end_time":922.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":919.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but I mean that''s just us.","index":342,"end_time":925.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.19,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"How many more of those do they have going out?","index":343,"end_time":927.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right.","index":344,"end_time":927.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":927.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That are just ones like that.","index":345,"end_time":928.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.35,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right.","index":346,"end_time":929.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":928.91,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"You know, think about it.","index":347,"end_time":932.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.03,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s half a million dollars a year, Colin.","index":348,"end_time":935.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s phony.","index":349,"end_time":935.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.23,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Just to us.","index":350,"end_time":939.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":938.27,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I know.","index":351,"end_time":940.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":939.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wow.","index":352,"end_time":943.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":943.32,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"But, yeah, we laugh every time we get the bill.","index":353,"end_time":947.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":944.12,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"At one time, I actually did call on the bill and I''m like, what this?","index":354,"end_time":950.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":947.88,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I want it canceled.","index":355,"end_time":952.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":951.24,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They''re like, no, yeah, it''s fine.","index":356,"end_time":954.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.16,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Nothing to worry about.","index":357,"end_time":955.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"This isn''t anything is ever going to come back to you.","index":358,"end_time":957.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":955.44,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Wow, that is crazy.","index":359,"end_time":962.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":960.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s crazy.","index":360,"end_time":964.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay, sorry.","index":361,"end_time":968.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":967.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Back on my train of thought.","index":362,"end_time":969.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":968.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So how do we feel about these keywords?","index":363,"end_time":972.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":970.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have no problem with any of them.","index":364,"end_time":977.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":975.97,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":365,"end_time":979.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":979.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let''s do it.","index":366,"end_time":981.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.37,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":367,"end_time":982.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re just going to add in some new headlines and everything too, when we do that, so.","index":368,"end_time":987.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":984.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I do have a question.","index":369,"end_time":988.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.73,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We have the Ringcentral questionnaire.","index":370,"end_time":991.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":989.57,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Do I not?","index":371,"end_time":992.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":991.85,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Lindsey, is that built.","index":372,"end_time":993.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":992.45,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yes.","index":373,"end_time":994.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":993.99,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Should we.","index":374,"end_time":995.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.63,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That should go on that Ringcentral page too.","index":375,"end_time":996.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":995.15,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Is that already built like into Gravity Forms, Lindy, or something you guys need to send over?","index":376,"end_time":1003.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":999.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s built into Gravity Forms and it''s a standalone page that you would just like put a link in for that.","index":377,"end_time":1012.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1003.03,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So I can just send you the example of what I did on the MSP page.","index":378,"end_time":1016.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1012.23,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That''d be great.","index":379,"end_time":1017.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1016.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or even just.","index":380,"end_time":1017.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can even check the id.","index":381,"end_time":1020.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, we want to spot in on that Ringcentral page, basically, like, you know, are we a good fit for you or not?","index":382,"end_time":1030.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1023.05,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Or some like that?","index":383,"end_time":1031.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1030.65,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Is that ID number 22, Lindsay?","index":384,"end_time":1034.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1032.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to say yes, but let me confirm.","index":385,"end_time":1037.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1035.529,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Okay.","index":386,"end_time":1038.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1037.93,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":387,"end_time":1041.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1040.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll update that and then looking through.","index":388,"end_time":1043.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1041.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the price offer campaign, we did see a nice improvement to the click through rate, jumping from 2.6 to 3.1, getting three to four clicks a day based on the actual budget that''s assigned to it.","index":389,"end_time":1058.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1043.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The top queries have more been around Zoom Phone or Cloud phone or Google Voice, which isn''t matching the landing page.","index":390,"end_time":1063.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But Google Voice also isn''t matching what you guys.","index":391,"end_time":1065.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1063.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Google Voice.","index":392,"end_time":1066.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1066.32,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"We should restrict.","index":393,"end_time":1067.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1066.96,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, so I have that over in here for adding into negative keywords as well.","index":394,"end_time":1072.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I wanted to re approach the landing page here and have some more language around these things.","index":395,"end_time":1079.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1074.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m fine with it.","index":396,"end_time":1083.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.81,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":397,"end_time":1084.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1083.93,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Do we.","index":398,"end_time":1085.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1084.73,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Hang on.","index":399,"end_time":1085.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1085.25,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Are we willing to change the page on one week?","index":400,"end_time":1087.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1085.65,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"On how much data?","index":401,"end_time":1088.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1087.37,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"How much data do we have on that?","index":402,"end_time":1090.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1088.73,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, we''ve got probably.","index":403,"end_time":1093.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1091.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, how much?","index":404,"end_time":1094.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1093.69,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, do we want to give it a little bit more or do we feel strongly it''s worth rewriting the page for that?","index":405,"end_time":1100.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1096.17,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I think it''s worth rewriting the page.","index":406,"end_time":1102.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1100.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I actually have my criteria baked in here as well that we can go over.","index":407,"end_time":1105.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1102.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, I think we''ve run it.","index":408,"end_time":1107.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1105.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":409,"end_time":1107.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1107.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then for the PMAX campaign I think fully pause.","index":410,"end_time":1111.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1108.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we redistribute that budget to search campaigns.","index":411,"end_time":1116.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Agreed.","index":412,"end_time":1117.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.77,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"For the Amazon campaign, Amazon Connect as a term is driving the most spend and has a very strong click through rate of 4.83 over the last three months.","index":413,"end_time":1127.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1119.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":414,"end_time":1128.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1128.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s the conversion factor of once they go to the landing page.","index":415,"end_time":1131.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1128.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So want to make more changes to that page as well?","index":416,"end_time":1134.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1131.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean do I, do we want to make changes or do we want to kill this?","index":417,"end_time":1137.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1134.69,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"This is more of a Ryan and Matt question.","index":418,"end_time":1141.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1139.41,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Ryan, I feel done.","index":419,"end_time":1145.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1141.17,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I feel like we.","index":420,"end_time":1146.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.65,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I kind of thought that was our plan to do that.","index":421,"end_time":1148.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1146.41,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"But what can you just, can you clarify a little bit Colin, on what you meant about it being a good performing.","index":422,"end_time":1155.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1148.65,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"I guess I was.","index":423,"end_time":1157.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1156.83,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Didn''t understand that part of it.","index":424,"end_time":1159.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1157.87,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":425,"end_time":1159.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1159.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As far as the keywords.","index":426,"end_time":1160.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1159.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So where you guys are popping up for the results when someone''s searching Amazon Connect they are clicking on your guys ad.","index":427,"end_time":1165.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1160.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s just that they''re not converting when they get to the landing page.","index":428,"end_time":1168.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1165.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean yeah.","index":429,"end_time":1173.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1171.15,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I kind of thought we were moving on.","index":430,"end_time":1178.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1176.83,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yeah, I kind of feel like we should pause it too but give it.","index":431,"end_time":1181.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.48,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Ask us again next week.","index":432,"end_time":1182.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1181.6,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Let Ryan and I have a discussion because we put a lot, we put a lot of time into learning this product and we''re hoping to get something out of it.","index":433,"end_time":1188.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1182.64,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But I mean here''s the thing.","index":434,"end_time":1192.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1189.32,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''m not writing blog posts around it.","index":435,"end_time":1193.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1192.2,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''re not actively trying to improve that page and we''re not getting any conversions.","index":436,"end_time":1199,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1193.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And we''ve had that going for how long?","index":437,"end_time":1200.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1199,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"About 90 days.","index":438,"end_time":1202.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1201.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No Amazon campaign has been going way longer than that.","index":439,"end_time":1205.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1202.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Sorry, that was just in the last 90 days of performance I was looking at.","index":440,"end_time":1208.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1206.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ve had that.","index":441,"end_time":1209.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1208.7,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":442,"end_time":1211.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1211.1,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s been at least six months if not more I think.","index":443,"end_time":1214.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1212.06,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yeah, I would agree.","index":444,"end_time":1216.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1215.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I think it was in November or October.","index":445,"end_time":1219.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1217.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so I''ll let you guys talk.","index":446,"end_time":1224.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1221.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":447,"end_time":1225.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1224.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''m feeling like killing it.","index":448,"end_time":1226.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.18,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean I hate to kill it because we''ve kind of abandoned it but I don''t feel it''s a strong focus.","index":449,"end_time":1230.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1226.18,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''ve had it going, we''re doing well on the page.","index":450,"end_time":1233.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1230.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''re just not getting any conversions.","index":451,"end_time":1235.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1233.68,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So this kind of comes back to Colin, like what''s the recipe for when we kill something?","index":452,"end_time":1239.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1235.44,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right.","index":453,"end_time":1240.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1239.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep.","index":454,"end_time":1240.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1240.24,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"And that''s what I have on the next slide and real quick on the Microsoft ad stuff.","index":455,"end_time":1244.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1240.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re seeing some good efficiency as far as the reach for spend, we want to just.","index":456,"end_time":1249.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to run a few more keywords by you to see how you feel about them.","index":457,"end_time":1255.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the great thing about Microsoft ads is again, less people playing in the sandbox and we can continue splitting out for the budget that we have some more keywords.","index":458,"end_time":1264.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1255.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So some that I pulled up were like cloud phone system, small business cloud phone systems, hosted phone systems.","index":459,"end_time":1269.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1265.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we could even go with competitor based like Avaya or aws.","index":460,"end_time":1274.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1270.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, AWS isn''t going to be a competitor, so I mean that''s definitely not one we probably want to be in.","index":461,"end_time":1279.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1275.42,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Avaya phone system is fine.","index":462,"end_time":1281.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1279.82,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"A buy a phone system set up is probably not fine.","index":463,"end_time":1283.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1281.38,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay.","index":464,"end_time":1284.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1284.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Set up means they already have it.","index":465,"end_time":1286.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1285.5,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They''re trying to fix something likely.","index":466,"end_time":1288.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.86,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right.","index":467,"end_time":1291.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How do I feel about everything else?","index":468,"end_time":1293.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1292.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m fine with.","index":469,"end_time":1294.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1293.51,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, good with those.","index":470,"end_time":1295.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.07,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":471,"end_time":1295.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1295.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":472,"end_time":1298.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1297.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and they had some other weird ones like Equinox downloads that I don''t think are relevant at all.","index":473,"end_time":1302.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1298.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Dude, it''s funny that the best performers over there are Abaya shit.","index":474,"end_time":1307.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1303.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Ryan.","index":475,"end_time":1308.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1307.75,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It tells a little bit about who''s on that Avaya stuff, doesn''t it?","index":476,"end_time":1310.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.15,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That they''re using edge.","index":477,"end_time":1312.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1310.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That is comical.","index":478,"end_time":1315.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1314.31,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, it does.","index":479,"end_time":1316.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1315.43,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"It does.","index":480,"end_time":1316.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1316.19,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"You know.","index":481,"end_time":1317.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1316.55,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":482,"end_time":1321.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1320.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":483,"end_time":1321.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1321.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I had my Internet Explorer back and my.","index":484,"end_time":1323.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1321.53,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I would have the answer to my IP office questions.","index":485,"end_time":1326.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1323.77,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"All right, so we''ll load.","index":486,"end_time":1329.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1328.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t get to altavista to look up my ip.","index":487,"end_time":1331.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1329.97,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s funny when you.","index":488,"end_time":1332.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1331.97,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"It''s funny when you host.","index":489,"end_time":1334.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1332.89,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"We lost your.","index":490,"end_time":1337.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.93,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s funny when you host a download like that.","index":491,"end_time":1340.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1337.61,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"What''s that?","index":492,"end_time":1341.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1340.69,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"No, we lost you for a second.","index":493,"end_time":1342.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1341.81,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Go ahead.","index":494,"end_time":1343.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.89,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You guys not hear me?","index":495,"end_time":1343.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1343.13,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yeah, we got you.","index":496,"end_time":1344.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1344.26,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Oh, sorry.","index":497,"end_time":1345.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1345.14,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"It''s funny when you, when you host a download like that that''s kind of out of date that people still want to get and that.","index":498,"end_time":1353.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1346.42,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"That drives traffic.","index":499,"end_time":1354.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.54,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Right.","index":500,"end_time":1355.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1354.9,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Like we''re the only ones out there hosting that version of aviation Equinox.","index":501,"end_time":1359.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1355.26,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"You can''t get it anywhere else and it drives traffic to our site.","index":502,"end_time":1362.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1359.62,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"We should put it behind something.","index":503,"end_time":1363.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1362.58,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":504,"end_time":1364.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1364.02,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"We should put it behind a.","index":505,"end_time":1365.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1364.5,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Give me your email address.","index":506,"end_time":1368.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1366.98,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":507,"end_time":1368.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1368.02,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We should like Wall Street.","index":508,"end_time":1371.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1368.94,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s.","index":509,"end_time":1372.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1372.03,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It''s one of our visited website.","index":510,"end_time":1375.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1372.67,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And.","index":511,"end_time":1379.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1378.83,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"They would be a prime candidate to try to get on board.","index":512,"end_time":1382.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1379.11,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Well, I should say that maybe not.","index":513,"end_time":1386.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Maybe they''re on a prime candidate, but they can have a use for what we''re selling.","index":514,"end_time":1389.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1386.31,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Keep going.","index":515,"end_time":1392.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1391.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t want to get off track.","index":516,"end_time":1393.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1392.07,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I find it interesting, that''s all.","index":517,"end_time":1397.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1395.63,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry.","index":518,"end_time":1398.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1397.42,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So this is what I put together for Our evaluation criteria, Matt.","index":519,"end_time":1402.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1399.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So walking through from prior to launch to the initial launch and then optimization and then our decision point.","index":520,"end_time":1409.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1403.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all the things that we need to make sure that we have, you know, everything is enabled as far as lead tracking, the systems are all connected and communicating to each other.","index":521,"end_time":1418.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1409.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have, you know, AB testing going on.","index":522,"end_time":1420.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1418.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The landing page is nice and focused.","index":523,"end_time":1422.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1420.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The initial run span is two to three weeks.","index":524,"end_time":1425.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1422.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But also looking at the cost that is going into that campaign vers the delivery of results.","index":525,"end_time":1431.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1425.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So leaving it in that learning mode, see how the behavior is going.","index":526,"end_time":1436.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1432.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then doing our first check.","index":527,"end_time":1438.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1436.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are leads coming in?","index":528,"end_time":1439,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1438.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If leads are coming in, are they qualified?","index":529,"end_time":1440.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1439,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which thankful to Chris''s work in HubSpot is very quick to see.","index":530,"end_time":1446.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if they are qualified, is the cost per lead reasonable or is it causing more bleeding there?","index":531,"end_time":1454.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1447.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If it''s required, we can make some small tweaks.","index":532,"end_time":1457.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1454.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tighten landing page or keyword targeting, run it for another 10 to 14 days and then after that, that is when we reach our decision point.","index":533,"end_time":1466.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1457.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we use this formula, the Amazon Connect page should be long dead.","index":534,"end_time":1472.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1467.87,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We should have killed that like two, three months ago.","index":535,"end_time":1474.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1472.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Correct.","index":536,"end_time":1476.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1476.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":537,"end_time":1477.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1476.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Well, then we kill it.","index":538,"end_time":1478.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1477.35,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Noted.","index":539,"end_time":1480.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1479.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any other questions or anything around this?","index":540,"end_time":1491.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1489.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I like it.","index":541,"end_time":1492.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1491.28,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Let''s make sure we.","index":542,"end_time":1493,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1492.04,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Can you get this over to us too so we can have this, please?","index":543,"end_time":1496.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1493,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":544,"end_time":1496.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1496.08,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"No problem.","index":545,"end_time":1496.999,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1496.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":546,"end_time":1504.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1502.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, developing campaign to send Traffic to the RingCentral page for the more generic terms.","index":547,"end_time":1509.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1504.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going with one field on the forms.","index":548,"end_time":1512.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1510.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll give you guys a review on Google as well.","index":549,"end_time":1516.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1513.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":550,"end_time":1518.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1517.54,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"The RingCentral categories.","index":551,"end_time":1519.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1518.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have trends, MSP product, technical and competitor.","index":552,"end_time":1522.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1519.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then killing the AWS campaign.","index":553,"end_time":1525.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1523.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll send over this criteria.","index":554,"end_time":1527.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1525.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is all from my side now.","index":555,"end_time":1530.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1527.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Over to you guys.","index":556,"end_time":1531.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1530.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t have a list.","index":557,"end_time":1534.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1533.94,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Lindsey, I think you have the items I have, and I don''t know that we have any open ones we can talk about.","index":558,"end_time":1539.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1534.7,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Nope.","index":559,"end_time":1540.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1540.09,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"I think that covers everything that I have written down here.","index":560,"end_time":1543.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1540.29,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yep.","index":561,"end_time":1549.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1548.49,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Google campaigns.","index":562,"end_time":1550.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1549.13,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yep.","index":563,"end_time":1552.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1551.93,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I think that covered everything that we had for today.","index":564,"end_time":1555.929,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1552.37,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":565,"end_time":1557.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1556.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was looking.","index":566,"end_time":1557.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1557.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve been following these two HubSpot contacts that Chris is working.","index":567,"end_time":1562.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1557.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have Leo Suo from State College area School District.","index":568,"end_time":1566.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1562.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":569,"end_time":1568.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1568.29,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I just got it this morning, so.","index":570,"end_time":1571.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1568.93,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Yeah, and I tried to find Leo.","index":571,"end_time":1573.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1571.61,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"He''s nowhere to be found on LinkedIn or Seamless.","index":572,"end_time":1577.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1574.37,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So I sent a boilerplate email and we''ll see if I''ve not gotten a reply yet.","index":573,"end_time":1582.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1577.89,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":574,"end_time":1584.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1583.089,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No phone number?","index":575,"end_time":1584.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1584.25,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"No phone number.","index":576,"end_time":1586.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1585.97,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":577,"end_time":1590.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1590.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The web address is legit.","index":578,"end_time":1592.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1590.65,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t know if the person''s legit.","index":579,"end_time":1594.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1593.18,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right.","index":580,"end_time":1594.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1594.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, as we talked about, people can get college IDs, email addresses pretty easy.","index":581,"end_time":1599.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1594.86,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":582,"end_time":1600.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1600.14,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So I took it a step further and I.","index":583,"end_time":1602.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1600.7,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So I pulled up the business on Seamless and I pulled down a couple of IT contacts or like the director or whatever.","index":584,"end_time":1612.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1602.54,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"And so I''ve also reached out to them with the emails.","index":585,"end_time":1615.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1612.54,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So it was.","index":586,"end_time":1616.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1615.14,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"I was.","index":587,"end_time":1617.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1616.66,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"I mean, that was this morning, so I haven''t heard anything yet, but.","index":588,"end_time":1619.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1617.34,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"And then this other one, this is actually Michael''s contact.","index":589,"end_time":1628.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1621.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"J troop from iTrue Security.","index":590,"end_time":1630.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1629.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Having a hard time.","index":591,"end_time":1633.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1633.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looks like it''s like a partner program.","index":592,"end_time":1635.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1634.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m having a hard time.","index":593,"end_time":1636.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1635.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If this was someone that you guys were talking to before that clicked on an ad also.","index":594,"end_time":1641.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1637.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":595,"end_time":1642.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1642.58,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":596,"end_time":1643.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1642.9,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"I think he had clicked on a.","index":597,"end_time":1645.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1643.62,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Let me see how it came in.","index":598,"end_time":1647.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1646.49,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Came in from a Google Ad.","index":599,"end_time":1651.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1649.45,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Better 3cx support.","index":600,"end_time":1654.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1652.73,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"And he is looking, you know, to be an msp, I guess, essentially they provide security, but they want to be able to provide, you know, telecom for their customers potentially.","index":601,"end_time":1670.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1655.29,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"And so Michael Lewis, we had the initial meeting or whatever, and so, yeah, the ball''s in Michael''s court there.","index":602,"end_time":1678.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1670.65,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"It looks like he''s had it scheduled to follow up, but it''s maybe a little overdue by a few.","index":603,"end_time":1684.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1679.55,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Couple weeks.","index":604,"end_time":1684.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1684.19,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So.","index":605,"end_time":1686.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1685.79,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Yeah, it was due on January 14.","index":606,"end_time":1690.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1687.869,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But he''s trying to send him a reminder.","index":607,"end_time":1692.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1690.59,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Well, he called on the 21st of January, and the guy, he wasn''t able to leave him voicemail because the.","index":608,"end_time":1699.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1693.79,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"The voicemail, yeah, it said it''s not accepting new messages.","index":609,"end_time":1705.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1700.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh.","index":610,"end_time":1706.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1706,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So he did follow up recently?","index":611,"end_time":1709.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1708.56,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, he just didn''t update the task.","index":612,"end_time":1712.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1710.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can we still let him know that, Lindsay?","index":613,"end_time":1715.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1713.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Sure thing.","index":614,"end_time":1716.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1715.679,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":615,"end_time":1720.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1720.16,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you all very much.","index":616,"end_time":1723.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1721.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, guys and girls, thanks.","index":617,"end_time":1725.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1724.64,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":618,"end_time":1726.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1725.76,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Have a good one.","index":619,"end_time":1727.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1726.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":620,"end_time":1727.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1727.52,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Bye.","index":621,"end_time":1728.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1727.88,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"You too.","index":622,"end_time":1728.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1728.08,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It.","index":623,"end_time":1728.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1728.63,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"}],"dateString":"2026-02-03T20:00:00.000Z","host_email":"lhall@techmode.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_ODBmZWFjMWYtMWIxYi00NmZmLTgyMDEtOWFiZWJhYWEwYzVh@thread.v2/0?context={\"Tid\":\"3801011d-e732-48ee-be2a-e499b1a29ba4\",\"Oid\":\"e804fbe9-a623-4d26-a887-992e62fb92d1\"}","participants":["cquigley@techmode.com,michael.lewis@techmode.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,lhall@techmode.com,mlook@techmode.com,rfisher@techmode.com","cquigley@techmode.com","michael.lewis@techmode.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","mlook@techmode.com","rfisher@techmode.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KGDNQZXTYSZFM3Q7ZET4JTFB","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Aligned on campaign pivot to promote RingCentral alternative using broad UCAS-related search terms.","Agreed to maintain single-name field temporarily; low volume doesn''t justify rework in form logic.","Decided to sunset Amazon Connect campaign due to sustained low conversions over six months.","Established campaign evaluation criteria to support data-driven pause or scale decisions.","Highlighted blog template category strategy; Lindsay to finalize and apply variable layouts."],"highlights":[{"quote":"If we use this formula, the Amazon Connect page should be long dead.","speaker":"Matthew Look"},{"quote":"So I''ll put together that campaign infrastructure.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I love the RingCenter page idea.","speaker":"Matthew Look"}],"topics":["campaign","delivery","ads","evaluation","forms","RingCentral"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-02-04T18:35:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Strategy and Keyword Optimization**\n\nThe team decided to refocus campaigns toward broader, generic UCAS terms and consolidate landing pages to capture a larger audience likely searching for RingCentral alternatives, leveraging its **60% market share** as a key driver (02:36).\n\n- **Matthew Look** argued that redirecting generic UCAS traffic to a centralized RingCentral alternative page could capture up to **60% of relevant searches**, mitigating the lack of direct RingCentral replacement keywords.\n- Colin agreed and committed to building the necessary campaign infrastructure to support this approach, including form integrations with HubSpot (06:30).\n- The RingCentral questionnaire is confirmed built in Gravity Forms and will be linked on the new landing page to qualify leads better (16:34).\n- Keyword shifts include moving away from low-volume \"move\" or \"switch\" terms toward broader alternatives that show rising search interest, approved by Matthew (13:10).\n- Negative keywords such as Google Voice will be added to refine targeting, with landing pages adjusted accordingly to improve relevance and click-through rates (17:46).\n- Microsoft Ads campaigns will focus on targeted keywords like \"cloud phone system\" and \"small business cloud phone systems,\" avoiding irrelevant terms like AWS or \"set up,\" per Matthew’s guidance (21:15).\n\n## **Campaign Performance Evaluation and Decision Framework**\n\nA clear evaluation framework was established to assess campaign viability through staged criteria, focusing on lead tracking, cost efficiency, and conversion quality over a **2–3 week initial run plus a 10–14 day optimization period** before final decisions (23:19).\n\n- Colin outlined this phased approach for campaign launch, monitoring, and decision-making, emphasizing lead qualification via HubSpot as a critical metric (23:19).\n- Applying this framework, the Amazon Connect campaign, despite a **4.83% click-through rate**, lacks conversions over **90 days**, leading to a consensus to pause or kill the campaign pending further discussion between Ryan and Matthew (18:54, 20:25).\n- The Price Offer campaign showed a **click-through rate increase from 2.6% to 3.1%** with **3–4 clicks daily** on a limited budget, prompting a rewrite of the landing page to better align with top queries like Zoom Phone and Google Voice (17:20).\n- The PMAX campaign will be paused, with its budget reallocated to search campaigns to improve ROI (18:39).\n\n## **Website and Form Integration Enhancements**\n\nThe team prioritized improving form data quality and website content to support better lead management and user experience, focusing on HubSpot integration and testimonial authenticity (05:54).\n\n- Lindsay confirmed the need to split the existing single name field into **first and last name fields** in forms to cleanly integrate with HubSpot, but the team agreed to defer this fix until campaign success justifies the effort (07:08).\n- Colin committed to replacing existing testimonial sections with real Google Reviews to increase credibility, as current testimonial images appear fake, which Matthew flagged as a concern (10:41).\n- Blog templates were categorized into four clear types—trends, MSP-focused, technical features, and competitor comparisons—with user-friendly category selection via checkboxes planned for Lindsay to manage content layouts easily (11:42).\n- Colin will build the category system and walk Lindsay through the content tagging process once ready, simplifying content management workflows (12:48).\n\n## **Lead Follow-up and Account Management**\n\nActive tracking and follow-up on leads generated from campaigns were reviewed, highlighting some overdue tasks and outreach challenges (26:08).\n\n- Christopher Quigley reported difficulties verifying the legitimacy of a contact, **Leo Suo from State College Area School District**, lacking phone and LinkedIn presence despite a valid email domain, highlighting potential lead quality issues (26:08).\n- Follow-up for **J Troop from iTrue Security**, a potential MSP partner, is overdue by two weeks; Michael Lewis had trouble leaving a voicemail due to a full inbox, and a reminder will be sent to Michael to prompt re-engagement (27:01, 28:10).\n- The team maintains manual cleaning of HubSpot records, including capitalization and data normalization, to support efficient qualification and outreach by Christopher (08:04).\n\n## **Market and Competitive Insights**\n\nThe discussion revealed insights into competitor behavior and market positioning that influence campaign decisions and product focus (14:06).\n\n- Matthew shared a unique anecdote about receiving a **$44,000 monthly fake RingCentral invoice** for **2,000 phantom users** on a demo system, highlighting potential competitor reporting tactics and market opacity (14:06).\n- The team acknowledged that RingCentral’s large market share requires creative marketing approaches since direct replacement keywords are restricted or ineffective (03:05).\n- Microsoft Ads keyword targeting showed promising performance around Avaya-related terms, implying a competitive opportunity among users still relying on legacy systems (21:43).\n- The hosting of legacy software downloads like Equinox drives traffic despite irrelevance to current sales, prompting a suggestion to gate downloads behind email capture for lead generation (22:21).\n\n## **Timeline and Next Steps**\n\nThe team aligned on key next steps and deliverables to implement campaign and website updates promptly (24:56).\n\n- Colin will share the detailed campaign evaluation criteria document with the team for reference and ongoing use (24:51).\n- Campaigns for RingCentral generic terms will launch with the updated form and landing page elements once the questionnaire is linked (25:17).\n- Blog template categories will be built, and Lindsay will be trained on their use soon (12:38).\n- Michael Lewis will be reminded to follow up on overdue leads, ensuring no missed opportunities (28:33).\n- The Amazon Connect campaign will be paused or killed based on Matthew and Ryan’s final discussion within the next week (20:25).","outline":null,"keywords":["RingCentral","Campaign Evaluation","Website Updates","HubSpot Integration","Keyword Strategy","Testimonial Management"],"overview":"- **Campaign Focus Shift:** Redirect to broader UCAS terms and consolidate landing pages for better audience capture. \n- **Keyword Strategy Updates:** Move towards high-interest keywords and add negative keywords like Google Voice for better targeting.\n- **Evaluation Framework:** New criteria for campaign viability includes a 2–3 week initial run and a 10–14 day optimization period.\n- **Lead Tracking Challenges:** Issues noted with verifying leads; overdue follow-ups need addressing to improve engagement.\n- **Market Insights:** Competitor behavior impacts strategy; explore opportunities within legacy systems and current traffic sources. \n- **Next Steps Defined:** Implement campaign elements, train on new blog templates, and follow up on overdue leads soon.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nPut together campaign infrastructure for RingCentral landing page that routes generic UCaaS terms there (06:50)\nFix broken website link animations on SMB page (09:53)\nReplace synthetic testimonials on website with authentic Google reviews plugin (10:35)\nBuild blog templates with assigned categories and backend checks; show Lindsay how to select categories once completed (12:38)\nImplement new keywords and headlines for campaigns based on increased search volume and remove irrelevant terms (16:21)\nAdd RingCentral questionnaire link on RingCentral landing page (16:39)\nSend campaign evaluation criteria document to team (24:51)\nContinue cleaning and monitoring HubSpot lead contacts and campaign results (25:56)\n\n**Matthew Look**\nPromote the idea of routing broad UCaaS traffic to RingCentral alternative page (02:36)\nFor now, defer reformatting form fields into first and last name; rely on manual cleaning (07:48)\nConfirm pause or kill decision on Amazon Connect campaign after discussion with Ryan Fisher (20:25)\n\n**Lindsay Hall**\nPrepare RingCentral questionnaire example for inclusion on site (16:43)\nAssist in setting reminders and notify Michael Lewis about overdue follow-ups with leads (28:33)\n\n**Christopher Quigley**\nContinue managing HubSpot contacts follow-up efforts, including sending outreach emails and cleaning data entries (26:08)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"78464100-f110-46a4-bc5e-cf1b3800c5b9","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
