    '{"id":"01KGDEY0JE8341D06CGCJBZ55P","title":"KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Launch and Brand Alignment**\n\nThe **KTC Search website is nearly complete**, pending final review on one page before going live, reflecting the new brand identity (02:53).  \n- The team will resend all website links to Kristen for detailed feedback on layout and content placement.  \n- Michael clarified the decision to retain the current website build instead of switching to the Richie May site, preserving previous work and brand consistency.  \n- Final edits on the intro and outro voiceover scripts will be reviewed by Kristen with a target to finalize by end of day for a **$500 voiceover** recording.  \n- Completion of the website launch is critical as it aligns with the campaign infrastructure already set up, enabling synchronized go-live of marketing efforts.\n\n## **Content and Slide Deck Strategy**\n\nThe **slide deck will be rebranded for KTC Search** using internal Richie May RPO case study data, showcasing presence in **5 countries, 14 offices, and 115 employees** as a proof point of capability (06:00).  \n- Michael will provide additional sample proposal templates to customize future client presentations based on his Stanton Chase experience.  \n- The deck is designed to support both internal education and external sales proposals, with flexibility to rearrange and reword content for clarity.  \n- Colin’s team will handle design tweaks and wordsmithing to polish the deck ahead of wider usage.  \n- This rebranding effort is intended to reinforce KTC Search’s multi-country operational scale and RPO expertise in sales conversations.\n\n## **Lead Generation and Trade Show Targeting**\n\nMichael shared insights on **Distribucon, a major utilities trade show in San Diego**, as a strategic networking opportunity to acquire qualified leads in the utility space (08:00).  \n- While not currently sponsoring or attending, the team discussed options to acquire attendee lists close to the event to enable targeted outreach.  \n- Colin proposed email campaigns and geo-targeted ads around the event location to maximize engagement within budget constraints.  \n- Trade shows remain a key channel for lead generation, with the potential for sponsorship or booth presence evaluated based on ROI and client interest.  \n- The approach reflects a focus on targeted, industry-specific prospecting to drive higher quality pipeline development.\n\n## **Marketing Automation and CRM Integration**\n\nThe **ABM campaign automation system is fully built**, integrating email and LinkedIn outreach workflows directly into HubSpot with notifications for timely follow-up (10:55).  \n- Colin demonstrated automated alerts that notify Michael when prospects engage, improving sales responsiveness and pipeline management.  \n- The system supports granular tracking of campaign touchpoints, streamlining lead qualification and follow-up efficiency.  \n- This setup underpins a data-driven engagement strategy designed to maximize conversion rates from marketing outreach.  \n- Continuous monitoring and iterative improvements are planned to keep automation aligned with evolving campaign goals.\n\n## **Email Infrastructure and Domain Management**\n\nMichael requested assistance to configure email systems for KTC after transferring domains to **GoDaddy**, preferring **Google Workspace over Microsoft 365** for better integration and ease of use (11:10).  \n- Colin confirmed in-house capability to set up and manage Google accounts, including domain linking and DNS configuration critical for deliverability and compliance.  \n- Michael emphasized the need to avoid document access issues typically encountered when sending Google files to Microsoft Office users, with Colin advising simple file downloads as Office-compatible formats to prevent client friction.  \n- Action assigned: Michael and Kristen to share GoDaddy and Google admin access with Colin for setup, targeting a seamless migration and operational readiness.  \n- This infrastructure work is vital for compliance, brand consistency, and smooth outbound communications from KTC.\n\n## **Advertising and Social Media Setup**\n\nInitial **LinkedIn ad creatives in multiple sizes and formats** are ready and were reviewed last week, awaiting ad account setup and connection to the business manager (17:53).  \n- Michael committed to creating the ad account and sharing access by end of day to enable campaign launch.  \n- Colin’s team will provide setup instructions and ongoing support to optimize social media advertising.  \n- This step completes the marketing funnel from brand presence to targeted lead outreach, feeding the ABM system.  \n- The coordinated rollout of website, ads, and automation aims to create momentum for lead generation and brand awareness in the coming weeks.","outline":null,"keywords":["Website launch","marketing automation","email platform","LinkedIn ads","trade show","ATS migration"],"overview":"- **Website Launch Progress:** KTC Search site nearly complete; final review pending before launching with new brand identity.  \n- **Slide Deck Rebranding:** New slide deck showcases presence in 5 countries, 14 offices, 115 employees, supporting sales and internal education.  \n- **Trade Show Strategy:** Distribucon trade show discussed for potential lead generation; exploring attendee outreach and targeted ad campaigns.  \n- **ABM Automation System:** Fully built, integrating email and LinkedIn workflows; enhances lead qualification and follow-up efficiency.  \n- **Email Setup Request:** Need to configure email with Google Workspace after domain transfer; focus on compliance and operational readiness.  \n- **Social Media Ads Ready:** LinkedIn ad creatives prepared; account setup underway to launch targeted advertising campaigns for lead generation.","action_items":"\n**Michael Kersten**\nSend Google admin account access with super admin permissions to Colin for setup (14:58)\nProvide GoDaddy credentials and domain access for email and domain configuration (15:07)\nComplete LinkedIn ad account creation and share access with marketing team (18:25)\n\n**Kristen Baller**\nReview voiceover intro/outro scripts and provide feedback by end of day (18:59)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend website links and gather detailed review comments for final edits prior to launch (03:16)\nRework slide deck content with branding changes and await additional proposal templates from Michael (06:35)\nPresent automation setup for ABM campaign and integrate communications with HubSpot (10:55)\nProceed with domain setup and Google email configuration upon receipt of admin credentials (14:50)\nProvide draft ads and campaign creatives to Michael and Kristen and assist with LinkedIn setup (17:53)\nFollow up on ATS data cleanup and prepare for final handover from Columbia team (20:24)\n\n**Paula Ocampo**\nLog and track action items related to Google/GoDaddy access and requests for Michael and Kristen (14:48)\n"},"duration":21.700000762939453,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Kristen Baller"},{"id":3,"name":"Michael Kersten"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Kristen.","index":0,"end_time":139.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":140.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Didn''t want to scare you.","index":2,"end_time":141.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to come in quietly.","index":3,"end_time":142.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":141.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I appreciate that because I had you hidden.","index":4,"end_time":145.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":143.09,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I''m nothing like a little chat GPT.","index":5,"end_time":150.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":147.57,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I''m writing a job description right now.","index":6,"end_time":153.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":151.73,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"There we go.","index":7,"end_time":154.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":153.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One.","index":8,"end_time":155.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":9,"end_time":156.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":155.66,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":10,"end_time":158.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":158.06,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And.","index":11,"end_time":159.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I keep like I keep going back.","index":12,"end_time":162.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":161.02,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Nope, that''s not what it is.","index":13,"end_time":164.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":162.7,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Nope, that''s not what it is.","index":14,"end_time":165.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":164.18,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":166.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":165.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Before Michael hops on, do I have.","index":16,"end_time":170.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":168.54,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Does he have anything outstanding for you or.","index":17,"end_time":172.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":170.38,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Well, he sent over a few things last week.","index":18,"end_time":175.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I want to just talk through like the slide deck and everything like that.","index":19,"end_time":178.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":175.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Other than that, the website is nearly complete, so we''re just finishing one page and then it''s just on your guys review for us to go live.","index":20,"end_time":185.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":21,"end_time":186.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":186.23,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So.","index":22,"end_time":191.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":190.63,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And we can just review the website where we reviewed it prior.","index":23,"end_time":195.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":191.19,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Okay.","index":24,"end_time":196.389,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":195.91,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":25,"end_time":196.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":196.389,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We can send over all the links again if you need them.","index":26,"end_time":198.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":196.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":27,"end_time":198.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":198.39,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And then just do what I did last time on like this goes here or this goes here.","index":28,"end_time":205.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":198.91,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"This looks good.","index":29,"end_time":206.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":205.67,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":30,"end_time":207.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":206.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And how granular should I get?","index":31,"end_time":208.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":207.07,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Or this would be the version that we would take live.","index":32,"end_time":211.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So any edits that you want made.","index":33,"end_time":213.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":34,"end_time":214.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":213.29,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Oh, hey, Colin.","index":35,"end_time":216.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":215.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''re going to stay status cool the way we are so you don''t have to worry about the other conversation we.","index":36,"end_time":219.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":216.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Had on the switch.","index":37,"end_time":222.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":38,"end_time":223.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":222.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":39,"end_time":225.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":223.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":40,"end_time":226.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I said it doesn''t make sense to throw away everything we''ve done.","index":41,"end_time":231.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":227.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":42,"end_time":232.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":43,"end_time":233.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":44,"end_time":233.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":233.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Paula, what he''s referring to is the switch of what the website on the Richie May rather than the.","index":45,"end_time":237.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The website we''ve been building now.","index":46,"end_time":241.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, I do have a quick question for you.","index":47,"end_time":243.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":241.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, Colin is.","index":48,"end_time":244.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":243.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I.","index":49,"end_time":244.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":244.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I''ll do this myself.","index":50,"end_time":245.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":244.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I will send this as soon as we''re done.","index":51,"end_time":247.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":245.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is if in our HubSpot.","index":52,"end_time":251.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":247.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Can you guys.","index":53,"end_time":253.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":252.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You obviously can see what Richie May''s website looks like, but is there a chance that you can set me up a. I don''t know, a landing page that if we, you know, we post jobs, we can post the Richie May stuff or a redirect.","index":54,"end_time":268.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":253.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if I give me a link.","index":55,"end_time":270,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":268.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if they put something up on the Richie web, Richie May sub is our postings that are redirect to that one.","index":56,"end_time":275.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":270,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then I can get you hooked up with Lauren and then that way if I need to post those Richie Mae jobs, they''re being posted, but they''re not being posted on ktc.","index":57,"end_time":286.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":275.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They''re posted obviously under, you know, Richie May''s stuff.","index":58,"end_time":289.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":286.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":59,"end_time":290.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a few ways we could do that.","index":60,"end_time":291.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could just have like even a link on a page or like a button or in the navigation where they just go directly to the Richie May site, or we can even have a listing of those jobs on your site and.","index":61,"end_time":300.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But as soon as they click, they go to the Richie May site.","index":62,"end_time":303.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":63,"end_time":303.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":303.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I don''t want any of the Richie May stuff on my KTC stuff, so it''d be totally separate.","index":64,"end_time":307.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":303.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So, yeah, from that standpoint, just what I''m trying to do is from a compliance standpoint.","index":65,"end_time":311.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":307.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if somebody, you know, where.","index":66,"end_time":313.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":311.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t know where you''re sitting here, but some of these.","index":67,"end_time":315.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":313.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"These states, they''re, you know, all big about posting roles and stuff like that.","index":68,"end_time":318.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":315.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So it''s more of a compliance thing than anything else.","index":69,"end_time":321.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":318.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That if somebody, you know, especially when I were hiring some of these HR roles, well, I don''t see it posted.","index":70,"end_time":326.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":321.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Well, you know, do you know the rules are blah, blah, blah.","index":71,"end_time":329.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":326.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"A, It''s a.","index":72,"end_time":330.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":330.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''s a confidential search, so that''s why.","index":73,"end_time":332.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":330.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We don''t post it.","index":74,"end_time":332.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":332.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, whatever.","index":75,"end_time":333.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":332.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":76,"end_time":333.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":77,"end_time":334.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":78,"end_time":334.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":79,"end_time":335.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":80,"end_time":336.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":81,"end_time":339.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":82,"end_time":340.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to go through the slide deck, Michael.","index":83,"end_time":347.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have that pulled up here.","index":84,"end_time":349.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So from a content perspective, I think you''ve said that we''re.","index":85,"end_time":352.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is all your content.","index":86,"end_time":353.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s pretty much just switching this to the.","index":87,"end_time":355.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":353.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The brand that we''ve created for KTC Search.","index":88,"end_time":357.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct?","index":89,"end_time":358.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":90,"end_time":358.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":91,"end_time":359.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything else?","index":92,"end_time":359.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, quick things.","index":93,"end_time":361.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":360.29,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If you go down, go to that slide.","index":94,"end_time":362.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":361.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I think it''s slide three.","index":95,"end_time":363.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":362.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Or is it slide three?","index":96,"end_time":364.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":363.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":97,"end_time":366.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":366.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":98,"end_time":367.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":366.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This, this.","index":99,"end_time":368.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Go back up to slide three real quick.","index":100,"end_time":370.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":368.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This would be where we say the internal one.","index":101,"end_time":375.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":371.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys could probably want to re.","index":102,"end_time":376.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":375.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Reword this or re.","index":103,"end_time":377.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":376.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Spit this.","index":104,"end_time":378.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This would be what.","index":105,"end_time":378.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":378.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It would be considered an RPO example, meaning that this is what we, you know, however you want, but this is what we do internally for Richie and May.","index":106,"end_time":386.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":378.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But.","index":107,"end_time":386.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if we''re going to brand, you know, rebrand this under ktc, what we''re using, this is.","index":108,"end_time":391.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":386.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This is a case study of an rpo, what we can bring with an RPO type service.","index":109,"end_time":395.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":391.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":110,"end_time":396.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":111,"end_time":396.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":396.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And you can move it around or whatever.","index":112,"end_time":400.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":399.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But that''s basically what that slide was showing is what we''ve done internally.","index":113,"end_time":404.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":400.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"There''s, you know, we''re in five countries, we have 14 offices, and, you know, we finished the year with 115 people or whatever.","index":114,"end_time":411.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":404.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, you can.","index":115,"end_time":412.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":411.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You get the logistics.","index":116,"end_time":413.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":412.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But basically what we were trying to.","index":117,"end_time":415.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":413.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This was a slide being showed to the other offices as to what we do.","index":118,"end_time":418.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":415.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Right.","index":119,"end_time":419.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":419.2,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":120,"end_time":420.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":121,"end_time":422.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":421.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I don''t think we had any other questions coming through here.","index":122,"end_time":424.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And like I said, you can do as you want or whatever, and I can, I have other data we can send to you or whatever, but that''s.","index":123,"end_time":431.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":426.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That was kind of the general one.","index":124,"end_time":432.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":431.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I can send you a couple.","index":125,"end_time":434.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":432.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Couple other.","index":126,"end_time":435.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":434.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because we kind of have this as the overall practice.","index":127,"end_time":438.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":436.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But then when we do a proposal, I wouldn''t mind having you guys build out the proposal template, which is usually a PowerPoint where somebody calls up and says, hey, they want to do something.","index":128,"end_time":447.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":438.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''re kind of customizing it, and I''ll send you a sample.","index":129,"end_time":450.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":448.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''ll send you a couple of my samples from my Stanton Chase days, and you can kind of see how we laid it out once again.","index":130,"end_time":456.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":451.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t like the way we kind of did it there, but you''ll get a general idea of what we''re trying to accomplish.","index":131,"end_time":460.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":456.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s good.","index":132,"end_time":462.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":133,"end_time":464.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":134,"end_time":466.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That all seems pretty straightforward.","index":135,"end_time":467.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":466.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, we''ll tack this one from a design perspective, and then we can tweak your wordsmith as needed.","index":136,"end_time":471.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":137,"end_time":471.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":138,"end_time":472.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":139,"end_time":474.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":473.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you also sent me over this trade show.","index":140,"end_time":476.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":474.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":141,"end_time":478.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":477.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That was.","index":142,"end_time":478.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":478.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I was sent that over to you.","index":143,"end_time":479.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":478.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is.","index":144,"end_time":480.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a big utilities trade show that a lot of my clients, you know, that''s where a lot of clients go for the utility space.","index":145,"end_time":488.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":480.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''s a big.","index":146,"end_time":488.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":488.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''s distribicon in San Diego.","index":147,"end_time":493,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":488.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So when you guys are working list and stuff like that, you know, I.","index":148,"end_time":497.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":493.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This was more of an example.","index":149,"end_time":498.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":497.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This would be an audience.","index":150,"end_time":499.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":498.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Some of the people going to the show would be an audience of the people I''d want to chase because they''re in the space and they''re, they would be looking for the type of talent that I have.","index":151,"end_time":507.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":499.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So it''s more of an example of stuff like this that''s out there in the industry.","index":152,"end_time":512.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":507.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That might make sense to try to find a list from.","index":153,"end_time":515.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":512.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Or maybe, you know, does it make sense a couple of these, you know, big ones.","index":154,"end_time":519.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":515.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Does it make sense to maybe be a sponsor or stuff like that?","index":155,"end_time":522.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":519.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":156,"end_time":523.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So are you planning.","index":157,"end_time":524.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you just planning to attend or are you sponsoring?","index":158,"end_time":526.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not doing anything.","index":159,"end_time":527.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":526.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This is just an example right now.","index":160,"end_time":529.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":528.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This is happening right now.","index":161,"end_time":530.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":529.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Oh, right.","index":162,"end_time":531.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":530.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":163,"end_time":532.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":531.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m not going to it.","index":164,"end_time":533.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":532.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But normally what you would see sometimes is in this type of space, sometimes you''ll see retained search firms.","index":165,"end_time":538.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":533.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They''ll, they''ll, they''ll.","index":166,"end_time":540.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":538.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They''ll go on the floor and present, or sometimes they''ll sponsor and maybe, you know, or they use it as a network thing where I would go and get the list and then try to set up meetings with appropriate people.","index":167,"end_time":551.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":540.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So it''s, you know, not necessarily setting a booth up, not necessarily sponsoring, but, you know, using as an opportunity for networking.","index":168,"end_time":558.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":551.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But it was more also just to give you, hey, here''s some different players.","index":169,"end_time":562.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":558.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":170,"end_time":563.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That we would want to potentially go after because they would, they would want my type of services for the type of people.","index":171,"end_time":569.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":563.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":172,"end_time":569.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":173,"end_time":570,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s awesome.","index":174,"end_time":570.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think trade shows are an awesome thing to tap into.","index":175,"end_time":574.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s always up to budget as well and then kind of across the board.","index":176,"end_time":579.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Honestly, industry wise, we''ve seen that they''re not really willing to share contact lists until like a week or two before the event just to limit the amount of emailing and everything that people are doing.","index":177,"end_time":589.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":579.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, we can do email campaigns, we can do even like GEO targeted advertising, like around the, the actual location of the event, all sorts of things like that.","index":178,"end_time":598.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":590,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, perfect, perfect.","index":179,"end_time":601.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":599.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":180,"end_time":602.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":601.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or even, you know, we help to trade booth designs and give away ideas and all sorts of stuff like that as well.","index":181,"end_time":607.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":182,"end_time":608.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":608.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":183,"end_time":610.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":610.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Feel pretty good on those two then.","index":184,"end_time":612.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, we''re all good.","index":185,"end_time":614.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":186,"end_time":614.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just wanted to see if there''s any feedback.","index":187,"end_time":616.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":614.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re.","index":188,"end_time":618.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":617.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I built out the entire automation system for the ABM campaign.","index":189,"end_time":622.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the email, the LinkedIn outreach, and it all automatically filters into HubSpot.","index":190,"end_time":627.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Michael, I want to know if you may have gotten some email notifications.","index":191,"end_time":629.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":627.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all of that is built.","index":192,"end_time":634.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can even just show you a quick preview.","index":193,"end_time":635.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is my nerdy side because I love this stuff.","index":194,"end_time":638.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":636.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s really cool what AI has allowed us to automate from a process standpoint.","index":195,"end_time":646.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So here when I talk about like the ABM program that we''re building, it is every single one of these is a separate automation that''s happening.","index":196,"end_time":654.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know, anything from emails that we''re sending, getting captured and all going into a database, sending Michael, you a email notification of like, hey, this person did this.","index":197,"end_time":664.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":655.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s time to follow up with XYZ.","index":198,"end_time":666.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":664.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s automatically being filtered into HubSpot.","index":199,"end_time":669.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everything like that.","index":200,"end_time":669.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool question for you on this.","index":201,"end_time":673.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":670.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Are you guys in your world, Are you guys a 365 environment or are you guys a Google?","index":202,"end_time":678.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":673.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Google.","index":203,"end_time":679.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":678.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You are Google.","index":204,"end_time":680.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so let me ask a question.","index":205,"end_time":682.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":680.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So we have those domains, the kt.","index":206,"end_time":684.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":682.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So our developer guy, good, better and different.","index":207,"end_time":689.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":685.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s good and you can come back and tell me because you guys will Obviously have to connect stuff to it but he transferred the KTC and those other three other domains over to GoDaddy.","index":208,"end_time":698.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":689.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So they sit now with GoDaddy.","index":209,"end_time":700.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":698.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We obviously have to procure new emails and we need to do stuff.","index":210,"end_time":706.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":702.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So my question is is if we decide to do it in, in, in Gmail do you guys have the services?","index":211,"end_time":715.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":706.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If I give you access in there you guys can kind of set all that stuff up.","index":212,"end_time":718.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":715.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Or am I better to use 365 environments for this?","index":213,"end_time":723.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":718.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean I think it''s some we certainly can do.","index":214,"end_time":726.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":724.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We haven''t, we don''t do a lot of that type of work but I mean we have the capability in house to do it.","index":215,"end_time":731.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":726.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay cool.","index":216,"end_time":732.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":731.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I might have you guys do that then.","index":217,"end_time":733.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":732.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"The other question is when you''re sending out the messages and Kristen and I always have this conversation is I''m not opposed to Google.","index":218,"end_time":743.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":733.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean a lot of large corporations have switched to Google.","index":219,"end_time":746.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":743.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I always get paranoid is when you''re sending documents out with Google it always immediately goes to somebody tries to connect to their personal email and I have the nightmares of sending a proposal or sending something to a PE firm and they can''t open it up because it''s not in, in Microsoft.","index":220,"end_time":764.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":747.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I guess I''ve been tendency leaning a little bit more to buying 365 licenses because then I know we won''t have that problem.","index":221,"end_time":772.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":764.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But Kristen''s done a pretty good job of walking me off the ledge.","index":222,"end_time":776.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":772.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But what is your guys''s take since you''re a Google shop?","index":223,"end_time":780.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":776.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I personally have a strong preference towards Google for the ease of integrations and connections.","index":224,"end_time":786.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":780.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"365 puts a lot of what I would even call like a fake firewall in front of things.","index":225,"end_time":792.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s that is kind of like that''s why we''re a Google shop.","index":226,"end_time":796.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We build a lot of these tools, we integrate a lot of things together.","index":227,"end_time":799.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":796.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Microsoft just makes it a lot more complicated.","index":228,"end_time":801.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that being said I mean we work with both sides we can really build anything that we need.","index":229,"end_time":805.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":801.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay so if, if we now if it''s with it setting over at GoDaddy those domains if I give you guys access can you guys help us set all that up?","index":230,"end_time":817.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":805.439,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because we have another consultant.","index":231,"end_time":820.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":817.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"His name, I forget what his name is but he kind of goes off the reservation a little bit and.","index":232,"end_time":824.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":820.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I.","index":233,"end_time":827.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Don''T this is too critical just to throw it over the fence and hope sure.","index":234,"end_time":830.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":827.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That he doesn''t.","index":235,"end_time":830.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":830.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah yeah let us help you out.","index":236,"end_time":832.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":830.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah I rather, I rather if you guys can entertain that I''d Rather have you just do it.","index":237,"end_time":837.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":832.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then that way, I mean, I can give you access into our.","index":238,"end_time":840.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":837.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I have an enterprise version of, of.","index":239,"end_time":842.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":840.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Of.","index":240,"end_time":843.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":843.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of Google Suite or Google, whatever the hell it''s called.","index":241,"end_time":846.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":843.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":242,"end_time":847.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":846.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is connecting them and then getting the appropriate emails situated and stuff like that.","index":243,"end_time":851.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":847.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because we did procure Apollo just because we were looking for another way to get contact information to our sourcers in India for, you know, phone numbers and stuff.","index":244,"end_time":862.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":851.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And they kind of did a little bit of a bait and switch where they''re only presenting work emails, not personal, which is kind of a problem.","index":245,"end_time":869.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":862.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I have a conversation with them.","index":246,"end_time":871.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":869.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But if we''re able to resolve some of that, if we want to use that for messaging outbound once again, is that a service that I could come back to you guys and ask you to help us set that up?","index":247,"end_time":882.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":871.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because obviously there''s, you know, stuff that has to be put in the DNS and everything else.","index":248,"end_time":886.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":882.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, yeah, 100%.","index":249,"end_time":888.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":886.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":250,"end_time":888.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":888.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So Paul, let''s mark down just some action items for Michael and Kristen to get back to us with GoDaddy and Google account access and then we can work through the next steps there.","index":251,"end_time":897.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":888.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":252,"end_time":898.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":897.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I can do is I can just sign a Google account to you, Colin, an admin one with super Admin, and then you can get in the platform, do whatever you want.","index":253,"end_time":905.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":898.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":254,"end_time":906.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":255,"end_time":906.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":256,"end_time":907.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll send you the credentials over for GoDaddy.","index":257,"end_time":911.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":907.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All my domains are there, but we''ll obviously need to procure.","index":258,"end_time":915.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":911.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What?","index":259,"end_time":916.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":916.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Well, all we have to do is.","index":260,"end_time":917.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":916.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Connect it to Google.","index":261,"end_time":918.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":917.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So once I give you access, I guess you guys can do what you need to.","index":262,"end_time":921.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":918.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":263,"end_time":922.379,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":921.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":264,"end_time":923.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":922.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we have our.","index":265,"end_time":923.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":923.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We set up domains for these campaigns as well.","index":266,"end_time":925.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":923.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have like go to get KTC Search, start KTC Search and go KTC Search or something like that.","index":267,"end_time":931.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":268,"end_time":932.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":932.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"For the domains we''re sending from.","index":269,"end_time":934.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":270,"end_time":934.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":934.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then when we''re sending stuff out, will you guys be able to.","index":271,"end_time":940.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":934.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Once everything is set up or can you help me make sure that when I am sending stuff out, I never get something set to a client in automatics.","index":272,"end_time":949.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":941.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It wants to go to their personal Gmail and a client can''t open up our proposals.","index":273,"end_time":952.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":949.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is there ways to set stuff up in the back behind the scenes?","index":274,"end_time":955.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":952.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So when you do send stuff out, regardless if the person is a Google user or not, it''s not going to make them do all this crazy stuff to open up a document.","index":275,"end_time":963.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":955.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m not sure I''m following what you mean.","index":276,"end_time":967.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so for example, if Kristen sends me a Google Sheet, and she just sends it, emails it to me.","index":277,"end_time":974.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":967.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What it wants to do is it immediately wants to try to attach to my personal account, my personal Gmail account.","index":278,"end_time":983.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":974.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Unless she goes in there and shares my email address as, you know, putting this as somebody I share it to, I can''t open the attachment.","index":279,"end_time":992.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":984.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It wants me.","index":280,"end_time":993.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":992.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It says I don''t have rights to it, then I have to send something back.","index":281,"end_time":996.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":993.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So my question being is, is probably 8 out of 10 of the PE clients that I work with, they''re all on Office, Right.","index":282,"end_time":1005.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":996.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So what I don''t want to do is send something, you know, through Google, you know, if we switch that route, and then all of a sudden they can''t open up a document and they''re like, what the hell am I working with here?","index":283,"end_time":1015.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1005.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that.","index":284,"end_time":1015.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1015.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That''s my question is, is how do.","index":285,"end_time":1017.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1015.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You need a live document?","index":286,"end_time":1019.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1017.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or, like, could you just.","index":287,"end_time":1021.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because in Google, I mean, you can Download as a PowerPoint, you can download as an Excel.","index":288,"end_time":1024.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1021.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":289,"end_time":1025.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1024.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you just do it.","index":290,"end_time":1025.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1025.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":291,"end_time":1026.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1025.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if I. Yeah, like, for example, like, I could hit file download and Download as Microsoft PowerPoint.","index":292,"end_time":1031.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1026.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":293,"end_time":1032.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1031.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if I do it that way, then we''re fine.","index":294,"end_time":1033.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1032.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":295,"end_time":1033.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1033.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":296,"end_time":1034.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1033.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That is just a file that you''re attaching to your email.","index":297,"end_time":1036.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1034.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, got it.","index":298,"end_time":1036.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1036.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":299,"end_time":1037.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1036.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":300,"end_time":1037.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1037.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":301,"end_time":1038.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1037.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":302,"end_time":1038.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1038.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I''m diarsing here.","index":303,"end_time":1040.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1038.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So Kristen has to listen to me talk about this all the time, so no worries.","index":304,"end_time":1044.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1040.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So, yeah, like I said, we''re wrapping up some.","index":305,"end_time":1047.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1045.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just final things on the website, but we''ll send over.","index":306,"end_time":1049.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1047.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve got most of this whole thing built out.","index":307,"end_time":1051.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1049.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":308,"end_time":1052.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1051.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Very excited about it.","index":309,"end_time":1055.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1053.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Michael, did we end up creating a vanity email for, like, recruitingtc.com or.","index":310,"end_time":1064.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1056.55,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"That would all have to be.","index":311,"end_time":1066.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1065.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Once we set the KTC up, the email, they can set all those up.","index":312,"end_time":1071.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1066.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They could set up whatever we need.","index":313,"end_time":1072.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1071.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":314,"end_time":1074.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":315,"end_time":1075.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1075.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve also got the first series of ads that we''ve created, so we can send these over to you.","index":316,"end_time":1081.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1076.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a bunch of different sizes and formats for LinkedIn and ad roles, and we went over the.","index":317,"end_time":1088.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1081.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The captions and everything or the text on them last week.","index":318,"end_time":1090.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1088.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":319,"end_time":1091.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1090.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":320,"end_time":1092.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1091.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Michael, I know we talked on the phone, so we just need the LinkedIn account set up, and then after that, you can share it with us so we.","index":321,"end_time":1102.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1093.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can share these instructions with you.","index":322,"end_time":1104.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1103.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":323,"end_time":1105.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1105.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If you have any questions, just feel free to give me a call.","index":324,"end_time":1107.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1105.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":325,"end_time":1108.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1107.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I hooked up the one.","index":326,"end_time":1109.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1108.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I just have to do the other one.","index":327,"end_time":1110.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1109.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, you did the page.","index":328,"end_time":1111.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1110.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now you just need to create an ad account, connect it to your business manager and share that.","index":329,"end_time":1114.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1111.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":330,"end_time":1115.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1114.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, I have that.","index":331,"end_time":1116.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1115.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''ll take care of that today for you and if I have questions, I''ll pester you.","index":332,"end_time":1119.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1116.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":333,"end_time":1120.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1119.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then last week we talked about you guys just doing a final review of the intro and outro.","index":334,"end_time":1125.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1120.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think that we''re all good on that.","index":335,"end_time":1127.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1125.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The one thing that we wanted to make sure is that we''re all aligned on the intro outro text that they''re actually reading.","index":336,"end_time":1134.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1127.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s probably been a little bit since you''ve looked at this.","index":337,"end_time":1136.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1134.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kristen.","index":338,"end_time":1137.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1136.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just wanted to bring this back up and make sure before we.","index":339,"end_time":1139.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1137.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because we''re going to pay like $500 for someone to do a voiceover, so.","index":340,"end_time":1142.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1139.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, do you want me to just send this over to you so you have a chance to review it and then maybe get back to us end of day?","index":341,"end_time":1149.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1143.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be perfect.","index":342,"end_time":1150.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1149.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":343,"end_time":1151.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1150.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":344,"end_time":1152.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1151.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, I think that''s pretty much everything, Paula.","index":345,"end_time":1154.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1152.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anything else that I''m missing?","index":346,"end_time":1156,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1154.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we kind of flew through a lot.","index":347,"end_time":1157.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1156,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I''m good on my end.","index":348,"end_time":1160.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1158.68,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":349,"end_time":1160.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1160.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so we''ll send over all the follow up items there and then.","index":350,"end_time":1163.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1161.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, just keep us updated on the Google access and setting up the domains and all of that stuff.","index":351,"end_time":1172.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll send all that stuff over to you.","index":352,"end_time":1174.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1172.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then the Columbia folks should be almost done.","index":353,"end_time":1178.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1174.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I think I have a call with.","index":354,"end_time":1179.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1178.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Them Friday or Monday or Tuesday.","index":355,"end_time":1182.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1179.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They''re almost done.","index":356,"end_time":1183.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1182.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Once they''re done with that hooking the our ATS up with there.","index":357,"end_time":1188.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1184.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So it''s supposed to be sending back.","index":358,"end_time":1189.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1188.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I want to cut them loose.","index":359,"end_time":1191.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1189.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Right.","index":360,"end_time":1191.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1191.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we can maybe set up a separate call just to have you guys go in there, see where status is and we can kind of talk about what else I may want to change.","index":361,"end_time":1199.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1191.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And that sounds like you guys can take all that over then so I can cut them loose.","index":362,"end_time":1202.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1199.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Correct.","index":363,"end_time":1202.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1202.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":364,"end_time":1202.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1202.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"100%.","index":365,"end_time":1203.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1202.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":366,"end_time":1204.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1203.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, I was in there.","index":367,"end_time":1206.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1205,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I, I deleted any contacts that I auto generated last night when I was testing it out.","index":368,"end_time":1209.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1206.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, everything is working smoothly from all the systems that we''ve built and connected.","index":369,"end_time":1213.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1209.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":370,"end_time":1215.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1214.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":371,"end_time":1215.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1215.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I.","index":372,"end_time":1216.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1215.879,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You would know better than that.","index":373,"end_time":1217.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1216.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, it seems like they''re doing a decent job.","index":374,"end_time":1219.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1217.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"There''s not a lot of data in there.","index":375,"end_time":1220.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1219.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I just figured I would wait till they''re all done and then we can go in there and do what we want to do, so.","index":376,"end_time":1224.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1220.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, I do see some.","index":377,"end_time":1226.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1224.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Things of like there''s SMS numbers in here as contact names.","index":378,"end_time":1229.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1226.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So maybe some things we can do to clean that up.","index":379,"end_time":1230.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1229.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But.","index":380,"end_time":1231.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1230.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But yeah, other than that, I mean, it hasn''t been super messy.","index":381,"end_time":1233.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1231.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":382,"end_time":1234.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1234.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, let me know once you guys.","index":383,"end_time":1236.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1234.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You see that, come back and let me know it needs to be fixed.","index":384,"end_time":1238.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1236.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then, like I said, we''ll switch all that stuff over to you guys.","index":385,"end_time":1240.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1238.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":386,"end_time":1241.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1240.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":387,"end_time":1242.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1242.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything else from your guys end?","index":388,"end_time":1243.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1242.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nope, that''s it.","index":389,"end_time":1244.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1243.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":390,"end_time":1245.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1244.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll start working through the slide decks and all the other things that we talked about.","index":391,"end_time":1248.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1245.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, yeah, Kristen, whenever you have a chance to review just the voiceover script, then we can move forward with securing that and we''re in a really good spot.","index":392,"end_time":1256.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1248.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As soon as it''s like, it''s all coming together at once, almost like we.","index":393,"end_time":1260.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1256.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We said a month ago.","index":394,"end_time":1261.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1260.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So got the website coming together.","index":395,"end_time":1262.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1261.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All the infrastructure for the campaigns have been set up and everything.","index":396,"end_time":1265.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1262.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So once we''re all good to go on, like, the website, for example, I mean, everything''s good to go.","index":397,"end_time":1270.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1265.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":398,"end_time":1271.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1270.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":399,"end_time":1272.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1272.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you, guys.","index":400,"end_time":1274.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1272.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Talk soon.","index":401,"end_time":1274.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1274.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":402,"end_time":1275.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1274.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":403,"end_time":1276.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1275.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2026-02-03T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83519004309?pwd=JvKSZR6BzSlyNxK5WTgZHYayMsLSKi.1&jst=2","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,michael@kerstentalentcapital.com,kristen@kerstentalentcapitals.co,paula.ocampo@marketersindemand.com,kristen.baller@richeymay.com","michael@kerstentalentcapital.com","kristen@kerstentalentcapitals.co","paula.ocampo@marketersindemand.com","kristen.baller@richeymay.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KGDEY0JE8341D06CGCJBZ55P","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.93,"bullets":["Confirmed website is nearly complete pending client review before going live.","Colin built automation for ABM outreach integrating LinkedIn and HubSpot alerts for tracking.","Team aligned on maintaining current tech stack and not switching platforms mid-project.","Michael requested Colin''s support to configure domains, email, and Apollo integration for outreach.","Ad creative and voiceover prep finalized; leadership review of script due by end of day."],"highlights":[{"quote":"The website is nearly complete, so we''re just finishing one page.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I built out the entire automation system for the ABM campaign.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"You guys can... set all that stuff up... I''d rather have you just do it.","speaker":"Michael Kersten"}],"topics":["delivery","infrastructure","automation","tech stack"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-0613","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-02-03T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Website Launch and Brand Alignment**\n\nThe **KTC Search website is nearly complete**, pending final review on one page before going live, reflecting the new brand identity (02:53).  \n- The team will resend all website links to Kristen for detailed feedback on layout and content placement.  \n- Michael clarified the decision to retain the current website build instead of switching to the Richie May site, preserving previous work and brand consistency.  \n- Final edits on the intro and outro voiceover scripts will be reviewed by Kristen with a target to finalize by end of day for a **$500 voiceover** recording.  \n- Completion of the website launch is critical as it aligns with the campaign infrastructure already set up, enabling synchronized go-live of marketing efforts.\n\n## **Content and Slide Deck Strategy**\n\nThe **slide deck will be rebranded for KTC Search** using internal Richie May RPO case study data, showcasing presence in **5 countries, 14 offices, and 115 employees** as a proof point of capability (06:00).  \n- Michael will provide additional sample proposal templates to customize future client presentations based on his Stanton Chase experience.  \n- The deck is designed to support both internal education and external sales proposals, with flexibility to rearrange and reword content for clarity.  \n- Colin’s team will handle design tweaks and wordsmithing to polish the deck ahead of wider usage.  \n- This rebranding effort is intended to reinforce KTC Search’s multi-country operational scale and RPO expertise in sales conversations.\n\n## **Lead Generation and Trade Show Targeting**\n\nMichael shared insights on **Distribucon, a major utilities trade show in San Diego**, as a strategic networking opportunity to acquire qualified leads in the utility space (08:00).  \n- While not currently sponsoring or attending, the team discussed options to acquire attendee lists close to the event to enable targeted outreach.  \n- Colin proposed email campaigns and geo-targeted ads around the event location to maximize engagement within budget constraints.  \n- Trade shows remain a key channel for lead generation, with the potential for sponsorship or booth presence evaluated based on ROI and client interest.  \n- The approach reflects a focus on targeted, industry-specific prospecting to drive higher quality pipeline development.\n\n## **Marketing Automation and CRM Integration**\n\nThe **ABM campaign automation system is fully built**, integrating email and LinkedIn outreach workflows directly into HubSpot with notifications for timely follow-up (10:55).  \n- Colin demonstrated automated alerts that notify Michael when prospects engage, improving sales responsiveness and pipeline management.  \n- The system supports granular tracking of campaign touchpoints, streamlining lead qualification and follow-up efficiency.  \n- This setup underpins a data-driven engagement strategy designed to maximize conversion rates from marketing outreach.  \n- Continuous monitoring and iterative improvements are planned to keep automation aligned with evolving campaign goals.\n\n## **Email Infrastructure and Domain Management**\n\nMichael requested assistance to configure email systems for KTC after transferring domains to **GoDaddy**, preferring **Google Workspace over Microsoft 365** for better integration and ease of use (11:10).  \n- Colin confirmed in-house capability to set up and manage Google accounts, including domain linking and DNS configuration critical for deliverability and compliance.  \n- Michael emphasized the need to avoid document access issues typically encountered when sending Google files to Microsoft Office users, with Colin advising simple file downloads as Office-compatible formats to prevent client friction.  \n- Action assigned: Michael and Kristen to share GoDaddy and Google admin access with Colin for setup, targeting a seamless migration and operational readiness.  \n- This infrastructure work is vital for compliance, brand consistency, and smooth outbound communications from KTC.\n\n## **Advertising and Social Media Setup**\n\nInitial **LinkedIn ad creatives in multiple sizes and formats** are ready and were reviewed last week, awaiting ad account setup and connection to the business manager (17:53).  \n- Michael committed to creating the ad account and sharing access by end of day to enable campaign launch.  \n- Colin’s team will provide setup instructions and ongoing support to optimize social media advertising.  \n- This step completes the marketing funnel from brand presence to targeted lead outreach, feeding the ABM system.  \n- The coordinated rollout of website, ads, and automation aims to create momentum for lead generation and brand awareness in the coming weeks.","outline":null,"keywords":["Website launch","marketing automation","email platform","LinkedIn ads","trade show","ATS migration"],"overview":"- **Website Launch Progress:** KTC Search site nearly complete; final review pending before launching with new brand identity.  \n- **Slide Deck Rebranding:** New slide deck showcases presence in 5 countries, 14 offices, 115 employees, supporting sales and internal education.  \n- **Trade Show Strategy:** Distribucon trade show discussed for potential lead generation; exploring attendee outreach and targeted ad campaigns.  \n- **ABM Automation System:** Fully built, integrating email and LinkedIn workflows; enhances lead qualification and follow-up efficiency.  \n- **Email Setup Request:** Need to configure email with Google Workspace after domain transfer; focus on compliance and operational readiness.  \n- **Social Media Ads Ready:** LinkedIn ad creatives prepared; account setup underway to launch targeted advertising campaigns for lead generation.","action_items":"\n**Michael Kersten**\nSend Google admin account access with super admin permissions to Colin for setup (14:58)\nProvide GoDaddy credentials and domain access for email and domain configuration (15:07)\nComplete LinkedIn ad account creation and share access with marketing team (18:25)\n\n**Kristen Baller**\nReview voiceover intro/outro scripts and provide feedback by end of day (18:59)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend website links and gather detailed review comments for final edits prior to launch (03:16)\nRework slide deck content with branding changes and await additional proposal templates from Michael (06:35)\nPresent automation setup for ABM campaign and integrate communications with HubSpot (10:55)\nProceed with domain setup and Google email configuration upon receipt of admin credentials (14:50)\nProvide draft ads and campaign creatives to Michael and Kristen and assist with LinkedIn setup (17:53)\nFollow up on ATS data cleanup and prepare for final handover from Columbia team (20:24)\n\n**Paula Ocampo**\nLog and track action items related to Google/GoDaddy access and requests for Michael and Kristen (14:48)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"fb2fdaa5-c1dc-42d1-9621-a2d72b1e78f2","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
