-- Meeting: Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync (2026-02-02 16:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '059db008-bde9-43e2-b5ea-2d8080194a92',
    '2026-02-02 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFXMD0YJD60T1CF0V5S6EWKD',
    'Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync',
    '{"victor garcia","Colin Costigan","christinazanca"}'::text[],
    1853,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85439302813?pwd=qMBHtkNo4lURIrnTCVFhLG0k15ZQca.1',
    '{"id":"01KFXMD0YJD60T1CF0V5S6EWKD","title":"Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Access and Account Management**\n\nThe team resolved critical access issues by granting multiple users super admin rights on the **Ponce Bank Sandbox** environment to enable app development and testing (12:00).\n\n- **Christina** confirmed that **Ashley and Gabe** received super admin access in the Sandbox to build the private app connection.\n- This access is strictly limited to the Sandbox, ensuring the main production environment remains secure and unaffected.\n- **Colin** clarified that multiple super admins are allowed, correcting initial confusion about single-admin limits.\n- This setup allows development without risking changes on the live site, enabling smoother testing and iteration.\n\nGoogle account access remains problematic due to a **lockout triggered by flagged ad activity and suspected fraudulent login attempts** (13:20).\n\n- **Victor** is actively submitting an appeal to Google, using detailed documentation and screenshots provided by the team.\n- The account lock affects both the Google Business Manager and Ads Manager, with Ads Manager access fully deactivated despite password resets.\n- **Christina** highlighted confusion caused by multiple individual employee logins rather than a unified main account, complicating management and recovery.\n- **Colin** noted that larger organizations typically use individual logins for accountability, while smaller ones share a single login, suggesting a need for clearer account structure.\n\nThe team acknowledged the **risk of Google blacklisting Ponce Bank**, stressing the importance of a successful appeal (18:30).\n\n- The ad account suspension stems from running ads for Mortgage World Bankers under Ponce Bank’s account, likely violating Google''s ad policies.\n- Consolidation of Mortgage World Bankers under Ponce Bank Direct is planned, which may simplify future compliance.\n- The team plans to present the appeal from a Ponce Bank email to increase credibility.\n- They are awaiting a direct human review rather than automated rejections to clarify the exact policy issues.\n\n## **Marketing List Expansion and Postcard Campaign**\n\nThe team plans to **expand the direct mail list by including households near closing competitor branches** to capture potential new customers (20:00).\n\n- **Wanda** reported two Banco Popular branches and two or more Capital One branches are closing nearby.\n- The new list will extend a **half-mile radius** around these closing branches to attract displaced customers.\n- **Jane** will provide specific branch addresses to the list vendor for this expansion today.\n- **Colin** will coordinate with Data Axle to identify new contacts while avoiding duplicate charges for existing names.\n\nThis targeted expansion aims to leverage competitor closures to increase lead volume and improve mail campaign ROI.\n\n## **Website and Creative Updates**\n\nThe team is progressing with **website updates and creative materials**, aiming to deliver improved samples by **Friday** for executive review (22:00).\n\n- **Colin** shared the design team is implementing feedback to increase white space and adjust navigation styling based on recent discussions.\n- Email and page templates in HubSpot are also being updated alongside website pages.\n- Retail sales and banking leadership provided positive feedback on brochures and placemats, with plans to extend creative assets to include **acting services**.\n- Further tweaks or new versions may be developed to support additional product lines, expanding marketing reach.\n\nThe focus is on delivering polished, versatile creative assets that align with leadership expectations and prepare for upcoming executive presentations.\n\n## **Contract Structure and Resource Planning**\n\nThe team agreed to transition to **one master contract** covering all marketing, creative, and website work for flexibility and budget clarity (24:00).\n\n- **Christina** emphasized the need to consolidate multiple ancillary contracts into a single, larger agreement for easier management.\n- This approach will support fluid budget allocation across website updates, campaigns, and creative work without rigid line items.\n- The current website contract runs through **April**, with campaign and creative contracts renewing in **June**, making timely planning essential.\n- The team is considering onboarding a **creative specialist FTE** to handle smaller design tasks and serve as an agency liaison, relieving workload from existing staff.\n\n**Colin** explained their typical approach uses fixed-price deliverables rather than hourly billing, improving cost predictability.\n\n- Work is planned quarterly with line-item forecasts but allows adjustments month to month.\n- This model helps avoid budget overruns and supports agile response to shifting marketing needs.\n\n## **Budget Tracking and Forecasting**\n\nThe team is actively monitoring spending, noting they are currently **over budget and borrowing from future months** (29:00).\n\n- Christina requested a clear forecast from now until June to understand net budget impacts.\n- This will inform how much can be allocated toward the potential new FTE and ongoing marketing efforts.\n- Colin confirmed close coordination with Tristan to schedule contract discussions and refine budget planning.\n- The goal is to ensure stable funding for website enhancements, campaigns, and creative support through the second quarter.\n\n## **Team Collaboration and Next Steps**\n\nThe relationship between the agency and client teams has improved, enabling smoother communication and alignment on priorities (29:50).\n\n- Christina acknowledged progress past initial creative misalignments and expressed confidence in continuing the partnership.\n- Upcoming meetings will focus on contract renewal, resource planning, and finalizing campaign and creative roadmaps.\n- Victor will finalize the Google appeal and share email threads with the team for transparency.\n- Jane will send competitor branch location data to facilitate mail list expansion.\n\nColin will coordinate scheduling with Tristan and Christina to keep key initiatives on track and ensure deadlines are met.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot Access","Google Ads Suspension","Mailing List Update","Website Redesign","Contract Renewal","Creative Specialist"],"overview":"- **Access Management:** Multiple users granted super admin rights in the Ponce Bank Sandbox for secure app development and testing.  \n- **Google Account Issues:** Ongoing appeal to regain access after lockout due to suspected fraud; concerns over ad compliance highlighted.  \n- **Mail List Expansion:** Targeting homes near closing competitor branches to attract new customers; expanding radius to half a mile.  \n- **Website Updates:** Progressing on website and creative updates for an executive review by Friday; improving design and templates.  \n- **Contract Structure:** Transitioning to one master contract for better flexibility and management of marketing and creative work.  \n- **Budget Forecasting:** Team over budget; needs clear forecasts to manage funding for new FTE and ongoing marketing efforts.","action_items":"\n**Christina Zanca**\nGrant super admin access to Ashley and Gabe in HubSpot Sandbox account as per instructions (12:13)\nProvide feedback and confirm next steps related to website and creative material progress (22:00)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nSubmit Google appeal based on provided documentation and screenshots; hold sending until further discussion and share all email trails with the team (13:24)\n\n**Jane Trachet**\nProvide addresses and details of closing Banco Popular and Capital One branches to Colin for mailing list enhancement (20:04)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nCoordinate with Data Axle to verify and run deduplication on mailing list additions from branch closings (21:41)\n\n**Agency Team (Colin and Tristan)**\nContinue working on website and HubSpot email template updates; aim to provide revised samples by Friday to align with executive meeting scheduling (22:23)\n\n**Christina Zanca & Colin Costigan**\nSchedule a meeting to discuss upcoming contract renewal, budgeting, and potential onboarding of a creative specialist FTE (24:04)\n\n**Victor Garcia and Colin Costigan**\nFollow up internally on Google Business accounts access and password reset inconsistencies offline (16:03)\n"},"duration":30.889999389648438,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"victor garcia"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"christinazanca"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, what''s going on?","index":0,"end_time":218.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.6,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good afternoon.","index":1,"end_time":218.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.4,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Oh, good morning.","index":2,"end_time":219.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.96,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":3,"end_time":220.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.6,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":4,"end_time":223.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":222.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":5,"end_time":224.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.76,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"How are you?","index":6,"end_time":224.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.08,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I think you shouldn''t.","index":7,"end_time":225.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.8,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"The box that you lastly did.","index":8,"end_time":230.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.92,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I feel.","index":9,"end_time":230.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":230.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t feel good.","index":10,"end_time":232.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":230.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And what I''m saying is you''re.","index":11,"end_time":246.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.68,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You''re keep on printing out the blank, blank sheet of paper.","index":12,"end_time":249.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.2,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Is Christina back in today or.","index":13,"end_time":319.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, she''s in today.","index":14,"end_time":321.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.15,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"She should be joining in like a few minutes.","index":15,"end_time":323.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.11,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Hello.","index":16,"end_time":339.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":339.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hello.","index":17,"end_time":340.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":339.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":18,"end_time":341.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you?","index":19,"end_time":342.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":341.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just another day in paradise, Christina.","index":20,"end_time":345.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":343.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":21,"end_time":345.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":22,"end_time":347.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":346.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Although I wouldn''t say it''s.","index":23,"end_time":350.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":349.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s always paradise.","index":24,"end_time":351.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":350.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m ready for it not to be like a foot of snow on the ground.","index":25,"end_time":355.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''d be great.","index":26,"end_time":356.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What?","index":27,"end_time":357.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":357.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No more snow?","index":28,"end_time":358.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":357.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m ready for the snow to be gone.","index":29,"end_time":360.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, yeah, Please, no.","index":30,"end_time":361.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":360.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No more snow.","index":31,"end_time":362.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":361.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There''s so many water, mean breaks, and just like ice walls in my neighborhood.","index":32,"end_time":368.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":362.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m just.","index":33,"end_time":368.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m so over it.","index":34,"end_time":369.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":35,"end_time":370.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":369.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then my husband this morning tells me how, you know, he had to literally hold his kind of frustration and anger because I guess a mom hit his car squeezing through.","index":36,"end_time":383.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And before he can get out and, you know, tell her off, my daughter had to remind him, you can''t say anything because that''s my crush''s mother.","index":37,"end_time":393.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So my husband was, you know, giving me an earful this morning, so he''s just like, I''m over it.","index":38,"end_time":399.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":394.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s crazy.","index":39,"end_time":401.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":399.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, my God.","index":40,"end_time":402.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":401.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I''m sure I''m gonna hear all about that later.","index":41,"end_time":405.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":402.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But anywho.","index":42,"end_time":406.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":405.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":43,"end_time":408.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We got a ton to cover, I guess, right?","index":44,"end_time":412.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":408.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":45,"end_time":413.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Guilla is having some Internet issues, so it''s just me today.","index":46,"end_time":418.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":413.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Christine, I know you were out sick on Friday, so one, I hope you''re feeling better to wanted to see if you saw our conversation around, like, you giving super admin access.","index":47,"end_time":427.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, so I did.","index":48,"end_time":431.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":429.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The problem is.","index":49,"end_time":433.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":431.899,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And Victor, chime in here, because I know you think you tried, is that we are locked.","index":50,"end_time":438.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":433.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, we are locked out.","index":51,"end_time":440.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":439.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And it''s saying that on HubSpot.","index":52,"end_time":441.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No, no, no.","index":53,"end_time":442.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.86,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Not HubSpot.","index":54,"end_time":443.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.42,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Oh, on HubSpot.","index":55,"end_time":444.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":443.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":56,"end_time":444.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":444.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Why did I think it was on the Google thing?","index":57,"end_time":447.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":445.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Are we talking about two different.","index":58,"end_time":448.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":447.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That was a separate.","index":59,"end_time":448.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, also.","index":60,"end_time":449.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that was another thing.","index":61,"end_time":450.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, crap.","index":62,"end_time":451.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":451.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":63,"end_time":452.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":451.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":64,"end_time":454.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What is super.","index":65,"end_time":455.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":454.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I guess I didn''t see it on the HubSpot.","index":66,"end_time":458.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":456.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Give me.","index":67,"end_time":459.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":458.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":459.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you right now, since you''re the only super admin on the account you have to give our seat and the seat that Victor.","index":69,"end_time":469.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sorry, that Ashley and Gabe are sharing super admin access so they can build the private app.","index":70,"end_time":473.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":469.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m trying to log into Hubs.","index":71,"end_time":477.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":475.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, now my 2fa is taking.","index":72,"end_time":478.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A while.","index":73,"end_time":478.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":478.39,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So I''ll probably just, I''ll resend you the invite.","index":74,"end_time":483.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":480.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I imagine maybe that''s been buried.","index":75,"end_time":484.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":483.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hold on.","index":76,"end_time":486.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":485.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I, I, I''m pretty sure I already accepted it and logged in.","index":77,"end_time":489.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":486.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I thought you could only have one super admin, though.","index":78,"end_time":497.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":494.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No, you could have several.","index":79,"end_time":499.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These multifactor authentications.","index":80,"end_time":505.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I, I, I sometimes just want to just shoot them.","index":81,"end_time":507.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":505.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, it just made me do it on my phone and then once I got past that, it said.","index":82,"end_time":510.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":507.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, now we have to check your email.","index":83,"end_time":512.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":510.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Remember me?","index":84,"end_time":517.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":516.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How long?","index":85,"end_time":518.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":517.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hold on.","index":86,"end_time":534.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":534.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I guess I gotta go to.","index":87,"end_time":536.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":534.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, it shows that your invite''s still pending for the Sandbox account, so I can resend that.","index":88,"end_time":545.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wait, what do you mean the invite''s still pending for the Sandbox account?","index":89,"end_time":549.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":546.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh, so this is not for our main account.","index":90,"end_time":554.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":549.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m supposed to have two accounts.","index":91,"end_time":556.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":554.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, so we have two instances.","index":92,"end_time":557.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have the Sandbox and then the regular.","index":93,"end_time":559.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":557.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, all right.","index":94,"end_time":561.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":560.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, send me that.","index":95,"end_time":562.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":561.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I don''t think I''ve ever logged in.","index":96,"end_time":568.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":566.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is it two separate logins or two separate emails?","index":97,"end_time":571.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":568.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No, it''d be one login, but when you, like, log in, it would say like Ponce bank or Ponce Bank Sandbox.","index":98,"end_time":576.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":571.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can actually click on this link that I''m putting in the Zoom Chat.","index":99,"end_time":581.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":577.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":100,"end_time":582.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":581.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because when I click.","index":101,"end_time":585.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":582.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t see, I don''t see Sandbox.","index":102,"end_time":587.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":585.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, wait a minute.","index":103,"end_time":588.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh, hold on.","index":104,"end_time":589.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":588.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh, wait, no, I have it.","index":105,"end_time":591.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":590.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just didn''t, I just wasn''t looking in the right place.","index":106,"end_time":593.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":591.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":107,"end_time":594.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":594.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh, good.","index":108,"end_time":595.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.12,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, so standard Sandbox.","index":109,"end_time":606.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":600.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Now I have to go Account, I guess.","index":110,"end_time":610.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Where would I change that?","index":111,"end_time":613.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":612.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if you hit the settings cog in the top of the screen and then Users and teams on the left menu.","index":112,"end_time":618.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, hold on.","index":113,"end_time":619.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"See, I see account.","index":114,"end_time":634.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":632.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I see how many pages.","index":115,"end_time":637.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":634.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t see users in teams.","index":116,"end_time":638.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":637.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Do you want to share your screen?","index":117,"end_time":640.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":639.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it might be just be just Monday morning.","index":118,"end_time":644,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, totally get following.","index":119,"end_time":645.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":644.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hold on.","index":120,"end_time":646.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I have to figure out how I even get back to the Zoom.","index":121,"end_time":649.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hold on.","index":122,"end_time":650.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":649.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Jesus.","index":123,"end_time":651.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":650.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":124,"end_time":654.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":653.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No, don''t tell me to update my computer.","index":125,"end_time":656.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh, my God, Kelly.","index":126,"end_time":657.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":656.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hopefully I don''t get kicked off.","index":127,"end_time":660.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":659.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Guys, it''s, I just, I''m getting this update now alert.","index":128,"end_time":663.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":660.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":129,"end_time":663.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":663.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":130,"end_time":664.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":664.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh, God.","index":131,"end_time":665.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":664.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":132,"end_time":666.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":666.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, so here, correct.","index":133,"end_time":669.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":667.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No, so hit the X and then there''s like a Settings.","index":134,"end_time":673.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you see like where in the top right, it says Ponte Bank Sandbox with a drop down.","index":135,"end_time":677.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":674.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, a little bit to the left of that, there''s like a settings icon.","index":136,"end_time":681.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":678.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, this thing?","index":137,"end_time":682.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":681.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":138,"end_time":683.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Jesus.","index":139,"end_time":683.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":683.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":140,"end_time":684.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":684.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No, you''re good.","index":141,"end_time":685.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":684.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then under account management, it says users and teams on the left menu.","index":142,"end_time":692.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":143,"end_time":692.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":692.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":144,"end_time":693.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":692.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":145,"end_time":693.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":693.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Why is it so slow?","index":146,"end_time":704.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":703.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":147,"end_time":705.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.11,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, so once there''s Ashley, once she loads, so you can hover over her and hit actions.","index":148,"end_time":717.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":713.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then make super admin at the top.","index":149,"end_time":723.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":722.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if you could do the same for our user, that would be great.","index":150,"end_time":733.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":730.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":151,"end_time":734.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":733.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yes.","index":152,"end_time":737.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":737.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":153,"end_time":737.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":154,"end_time":745.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":744.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, Victor, then Ashley and Gabe should be all good to build the private app connection that they were asking about.","index":155,"end_time":753,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":745.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":156,"end_time":754.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What is this?","index":157,"end_time":756.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Deactivated.","index":158,"end_time":757.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":756.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh, is that the one that we changed the.","index":159,"end_time":760.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":757.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yes.","index":160,"end_time":760.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":760.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":161,"end_time":761.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":761.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":162,"end_time":762.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":761.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so this is temporary.","index":163,"end_time":763.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":762.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This is just for the temporary page, right?","index":164,"end_time":765.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":763.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so, like, it''s not going to give super admin access to the main page.","index":165,"end_time":769.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":765.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No, this is just the sandbox.","index":166,"end_time":770.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":769.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is just for us to build, like, everything and test it all out and then transfer it over to the actual environment.","index":167,"end_time":775.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":770.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, yeah, that.","index":168,"end_time":776.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":775.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s good because I know there''s like, other things and I''m not sure, like, would.","index":169,"end_time":781.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":776.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They''d want access.","index":170,"end_time":782.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":781.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":171,"end_time":784.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":783.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Now, just on the subject of access, so I think I replied back on the Google, so I believe I saw Victor tried and it''s.","index":172,"end_time":796.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":785.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"He''s getting the.","index":173,"end_time":797.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":796.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The alert to say that you know where our accountant is deactivated.","index":174,"end_time":801.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":797.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Victor and I talked about that on Friday.","index":175,"end_time":803.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":802.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":176,"end_time":804.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":804.05,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So what I''m doing right now, literally right now, to check it off my list, he already sent us what we should say to Google right now.","index":177,"end_time":812.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So I''m already on their website so that I could send that appeal right now.","index":178,"end_time":816.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":812.45,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"He already sent out the full layout on what we should say, adding screenshots, et cetera.","index":179,"end_time":821.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":817.6,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So I''m taking care of that right now.","index":180,"end_time":822.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.52,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, so you''re.","index":181,"end_time":824.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":823.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So let me just take one step back and I want everybody to understand what happened.","index":182,"end_time":829.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":825.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think that we had two different issues with this account.","index":183,"end_time":833,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":829.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We had one issue where we were trying our team to get access to the Google page Business manager for the locations page.","index":184,"end_time":843.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":833,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And at the same time as we got flagged for the MWB ad, Victor and I were trying to reset passwords at the same time.","index":185,"end_time":852.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":843.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And the emails that we got noted that where our account was locked because they thought it was fraudulent activity.","index":186,"end_time":860.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":852.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so I was supposed to get 30 days from whatever day they gave me.","index":187,"end_time":869.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":860.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They said to me, oh, we''re going to send you a reactivation kind of email that would get your access after we review it, coincidentally enough, and the reason why I thought it was the same thing is that the same day that I was supposed to get the email to get access to our account, we also got the email saying that our account was suspended due to the ad.","index":188,"end_time":892.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":869.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So what I was thinking happened is that when Google went back and looked at our account because of the fraudulent login activity or attempts to log in, they flagged our account also for the ad on mwb.","index":189,"end_time":907.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":892.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so I just want to make sure that as we''re approaching them, we not only reference that we are maintaining the, you know, the policies for, you know, advertising guidelines, but we are locked out, totally out of our account.","index":190,"end_time":926.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":907.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Even just to, you know, manage anything.","index":191,"end_time":928.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":926.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":192,"end_time":931.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":930.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Portion of that.","index":193,"end_time":933.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":932.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry, go ahead.","index":194,"end_time":933.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":933.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, yeah, I''m sorry, Colin.","index":195,"end_time":935.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.77,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m able to log in, but we''re just not able to do anything.","index":196,"end_time":938.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, no, our login.","index":197,"end_time":940.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":938.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Our login works, but we''re not able to do anything.","index":198,"end_time":943.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But the login only works for the Google business manager.","index":199,"end_time":949.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":943.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The login for the Ads Manager is totally deactivated.","index":200,"end_time":952.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":949.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Well, Victor''s able to get into Hats Manager.","index":201,"end_time":955.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":952.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":202,"end_time":955.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":955.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s what I''m in right now to send out the appeal.","index":203,"end_time":959.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":957.55,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"How are you in Ads Manager if our passwords were reset?","index":204,"end_time":967.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":963.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And that''s the.","index":205,"end_time":968.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":967.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let''s talk about.","index":206,"end_time":971.829,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":971.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let''s talk about it offline, because I got to show you what emails I got because we were resetting our passwords because we couldn''t get in when we were trying to explore the issue with the location pages for Uberall.","index":207,"end_time":982.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":971.829,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sure.","index":208,"end_time":984.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":984.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":209,"end_time":985.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":985.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I want to see what you see, because we should have one main account, not like employee specific.","index":210,"end_time":994.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":985.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And Colin, for.","index":211,"end_time":995.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":994.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For, for your kind of, I guess, insights, do you see clients having individual employee logins or one main account?","index":212,"end_time":1003.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":995.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because that''s part of my, my problem right now.","index":213,"end_time":1006.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1003.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I feel like we all had separate accounts and that''s how Jen was able to do things under her account that we never even headlined a site.","index":214,"end_time":1014.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1006.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, yeah, Typically larger organizations do have like, one account per person just for tracking of, like, who''s done what.","index":215,"end_time":1021.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1015.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Smaller organizations tend to have, like, one main login that everyone uses.","index":216,"end_time":1026.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":217,"end_time":1028.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1027.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just one.","index":218,"end_time":1028.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1028.36,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right.","index":219,"end_time":1030.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1030.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Victor?","index":220,"end_time":1031,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1030.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":221,"end_time":1033.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1033,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"When you send those, those appeals or cases or whatever it is.","index":222,"end_time":1037.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1033.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll hold until we speak.","index":223,"end_time":1040.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1039.69,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":224,"end_time":1041.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1041.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And forward us to all of the, the, the, the email trails.","index":225,"end_time":1045.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1041.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I''m just, I''m just, like, so confused because right now my account, I can''t get in at all on either of them.","index":226,"end_time":1053.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1045.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I don''t know.","index":227,"end_time":1055.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1054.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, how long do you Do.","index":228,"end_time":1059.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1056.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Did it take you for the appeal to go through when you appealed it originally for the person versus the AI agent?","index":229,"end_time":1067.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1059.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Me?","index":230,"end_time":1067.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1067.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I appealed about four times.","index":231,"end_time":1069.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Each time it was like three days before I got anything back.","index":232,"end_time":1072.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":233,"end_time":1074.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1074.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"With, with actual like pro.","index":234,"end_time":1076.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1074.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean I use Google search console to run.","index":235,"end_time":1077.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1076.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like, I''m using Google Tools and sending them proof that it''s showing no issues on the site.","index":236,"end_time":1082.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1077.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Victor, if you read through like the sip it I gave, it''s all about how the relationship between Ponse and MSW is.","index":237,"end_time":1089.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1082.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or Mortgage World Bankers is.","index":238,"end_time":1090.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1089.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is all clear.","index":239,"end_time":1092.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1091.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":240,"end_time":1093.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1092.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s in the logo.","index":241,"end_time":1093.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s all throughout the page.","index":242,"end_time":1094.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":243,"end_time":1096.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1096.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But in, in all, in all reality, we should have had a separate ads manager for Mortgage World Bankers.","index":244,"end_time":1101.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1096.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":245,"end_time":1102.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1102.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that, that''s going to be their, their whatever.","index":246,"end_time":1105.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1102.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if they really want to be stickler about it, we did violate their ad policy then.","index":247,"end_time":1109.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1105.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":248,"end_time":1109.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just, I don''t.","index":249,"end_time":1113.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1110.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I guess we would have to submit an appeal because not being able to ever run ads on Google going forward would be a significant.","index":250,"end_time":1122.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1114.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Detrimental.","index":251,"end_time":1124.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1124.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":252,"end_time":1124.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1124.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are they going to like blacklist Pon?","index":253,"end_time":1127.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1125.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s, that''s what we keep submitting documentation for.","index":254,"end_time":1130.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1128.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because they will like if we just try to stand up another ad account right now, they would block it immediately.","index":255,"end_time":1134.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1130.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lord have mercy.","index":256,"end_time":1137.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1136.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, more to come then.","index":257,"end_time":1142.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1137.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I did ask Betty if she had a, a point of contact for Pon Bank Direct because I know she said there was a back, a back and forth when she was trying to do something for Pon Bank Direct.","index":258,"end_time":1153.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1142.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll ask her again.","index":259,"end_time":1154.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1153.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''ll, we''ll see.","index":260,"end_time":1156.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1155.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But okay.","index":261,"end_time":1157.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1156.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":262,"end_time":1157.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1157.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think the most frustrating part of it is I just need someone to say like what an actual issue is and not just an auto reply from their AI of like.","index":263,"end_time":1164.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1157.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s just this policy.","index":264,"end_time":1165.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1164.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like this policy list a million things.","index":265,"end_time":1167.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1165.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve checked against all of them.","index":266,"end_time":1169.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1167.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re not in violation.","index":267,"end_time":1170.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1169.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can a human actually just look at this?","index":268,"end_time":1173.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1171.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":269,"end_time":1174.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1174.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And also too, we''re going to be consolidating everything from Mortgage World under Ponc Bank Direct anyways.","index":270,"end_time":1180.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1174.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":271,"end_time":1181.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1180.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you know, we can always build the case that, you know, an employee that''s no longer with us went rogue and you know, unfortunately, if we need to go that route.","index":272,"end_time":1191.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1182.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":273,"end_time":1193.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1193.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":274,"end_time":1193.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1193.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m hoping also that the appeal coming from a Ponce bank email may carry a little bit more weight.","index":275,"end_time":1198.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1193.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":276,"end_time":1199.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1199.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":277,"end_time":1202.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1199.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For the postcard you mentioned, you said heads up.","index":278,"end_time":1207.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1204.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We may need to add a secondary list.","index":279,"end_time":1208.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1207.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You said Wanda shared that two popular branches are closing So I wanted to talk through that.","index":280,"end_time":1213.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Jane will provide you more information offline.","index":281,"end_time":1216.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1213.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But just quick summary.","index":282,"end_time":1218.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1216.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So 207 branch manager Wanda came to us and said, hey, we''re getting word that two Banco Popular branches are closing in their area and they''re getting I guess some traction.","index":283,"end_time":1229.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1218.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then now it''s even further to two or more Capital One branch locations.","index":284,"end_time":1235.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1229.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So because the postcard took God awful time, you know, we have the original list that we purchased which is going to have people half mile radius.","index":285,"end_time":1246.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1235.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What I would like you guys to do is if you can just look at the addresses of the branch locations that Jeanne''s going to send you and determine, you know, how far they are from the branch.","index":286,"end_time":1258.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1247.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If they''re, you know, only a half mile, then odds are we already picked up those clients.","index":287,"end_time":1263.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1259.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But what I would like to do is go half mile from each of those branch locations and add them to our mail list so we can hopefully you know, attract some of those, those clients because we know that their odds are looking for a new bank closer to home.","index":288,"end_time":1282.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1264.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we can also even take more of the position of like hey, Ponce bank doesn''t leave you.","index":289,"end_time":1288.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1283.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s part of our mission, blah blah, blah.","index":290,"end_time":1290.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1288.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Jane, if you could just follow up with some of those details after, you know, or somewhat today, I think that would just be connecting with the list service.","index":291,"end_time":1300.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1290.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":292,"end_time":1301.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1301.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what I''ll do when I talk to Mike over at Data Axle is see if he can like with the new list or like new names that we would get.","index":293,"end_time":1307.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1301.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See if we can run like a negative and see how much of an increase that actually is.","index":294,"end_time":1311.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1307.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":295,"end_time":1313.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1312.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And maybe just like it''s like an add on versus like a dupe because I don''t think they would double charge us for, you know, for names.","index":296,"end_time":1319.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1313.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":297,"end_time":1319.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1319.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Contacts you already bought.","index":298,"end_time":1320.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1319.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":299,"end_time":1320.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1320.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":300,"end_time":1321.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1320.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then just quick, cause I know we took a lot of time on the Google thing, the website.","index":301,"end_time":1329.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1322.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I want to get to the executives hopefully this week or early next.","index":302,"end_time":1335.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1330.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So let me know if the feedback that I shared makes sense and if you have anything to share or when you''ll have.","index":303,"end_time":1343.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1336.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, we got the team working through the updates now.","index":304,"end_time":1344.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1343.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I went back and added even more notes just across all the pages based on everything we talked about of like let''s get some more white space in here, maybe some floating objects.","index":305,"end_time":1352.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1344.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t need a background on everything having the super nav in there, not the blue bar across every screen like several times.","index":306,"end_time":1359.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1352.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they''re working through all of those changes right now.","index":307,"end_time":1361.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1359.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, do you have any Ta on when you think that we''re gonna see a new sample, just because it''s hard for me to get on their calendar.","index":308,"end_time":1369.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1361.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I want to give Betty a heads up if, you know, if it''s by Friday, then, you know, I can hopefully get on their calendar for the Monday exec meeting, which is after.","index":309,"end_time":1381.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1369.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, so we have several pages being updated this week as well as HubSpot, email templates and page templates.","index":310,"end_time":1389.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1382.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, by Friday.","index":311,"end_time":1390.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1389.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":312,"end_time":1391.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1391.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, that sounds good.","index":313,"end_time":1392.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1391.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then just so you know, the brochures and the placemats, I had a meeting with the team.","index":314,"end_time":1399.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1393.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They liked the direction.","index":315,"end_time":1401.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1399.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There''s a couple things that may, you know, be missing.","index":316,"end_time":1404.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1401.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So they''re going to meet.","index":317,"end_time":1406.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1404.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And this is retail sales and retail banking.","index":318,"end_time":1409.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1406.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The leaders for those areas are going to meet.","index":319,"end_time":1411.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1409.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then today she mentioned it on our like, kind of leadership call.","index":320,"end_time":1416.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1412.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then both the heads of kind of EA lending and then another area said, hey, like, we would love to have something like that for actings.","index":321,"end_time":1426.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1416.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I let them know that we kind of are.","index":322,"end_time":1428.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1426.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Are building it a little bit more than just deposits, but we have.","index":323,"end_time":1433.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1428.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We might have to just make some tweaks or maybe even make an additional version.","index":324,"end_time":1436.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1433.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So more to come there.","index":325,"end_time":1439.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1438.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":326,"end_time":1440.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1439.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, but that''s exciting.","index":327,"end_time":1441.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And yeah, that was the last thing that I wanted to ask about.","index":328,"end_time":1444.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1442.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, cool.","index":329,"end_time":1445.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1444.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":330,"end_time":1446.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1445.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just said the last thing for me and it''s probably more of a me, you, Tristan conversation, Colin, but we are, before we know it, gonna come up to the contract, like resigning.","index":331,"end_time":1459.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1446.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So wanted to talk through that.","index":332,"end_time":1461.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1459.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think there''s some need to instead of have like a lot of miscellaneous ancillary contracts, like dedicated to the website or dedicated to whatever.","index":333,"end_time":1472.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1462.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think the consensus is, is that we''d rather just have like one master agreement, like bigger budget, and we could just be fluid for whatever.","index":334,"end_time":1480.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1472.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because we were talking about budgets the other day and I realized that like we have the website covered under the build, but we really don''t going forward understand kind of how or where we''re going to build in the website from like just a programming creative update or whatever.","index":335,"end_time":1499.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1481.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think that rather than dedicate budget to campaigns or creative or whatever, it''s probably just going to be one big thing.","index":336,"end_time":1507.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1499.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So hopefully you guys could set that up and there may just be a slight shift.","index":337,"end_time":1515.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1507.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re trying to figure out if it makes sense for us to onboard an additional FTE that is going to help support some of the work that you''re doing from a creative perspective.","index":338,"end_time":1528.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1515.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, for example, like all of the versioning, right all of the flyers, like, miscellaneous little things that we get internally that are not at the kind of the level for an agency to support because of budgets and all that kind of stuff.","index":339,"end_time":1542.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1528.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Also, like, you know, you guys are just already kind of working on a lot of.","index":340,"end_time":1546.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1542.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We are getting inundated with all of these just miscellaneous little things, and Gene is the only one on the team that supports those.","index":341,"end_time":1553.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1546.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''re trying to figure out, you know, how we manage that going forward.","index":342,"end_time":1558.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1553.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so we may be thinking about bringing on a.","index":343,"end_time":1561.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1559.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"A different resource.","index":344,"end_time":1563.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1562.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s going to be like a creative specialist or something that could help us with that, but that person, if it gets approved, would be pretty much like the agency liaison, which is going to be like, how do we take the templates that you guys helped us build and kind of push that forward across all the other little things supporting, like, external affairs and, you know, miscellaneous little campaigns that may cut.","index":345,"end_time":1592.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1563.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Come up also, too, like, how do.","index":346,"end_time":1595.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1592.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How do they help to set a little bit more of the creative direction as a backup to me, Jane.","index":347,"end_time":1603.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1596.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":348,"end_time":1604.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1603.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":349,"end_time":1604.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1604.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And you guys.","index":350,"end_time":1605.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1604.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":351,"end_time":1605.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1605.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so that''s just a couple of little updates.","index":352,"end_time":1608.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1606.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So let''s schedule some time maybe in the next week or so to just start to get in.","index":353,"end_time":1612.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1608.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In front of that, because those contracts and everything like that will have to go through for approval.","index":354,"end_time":1617.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1612.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I think.","index":355,"end_time":1618.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1617.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think April takes us through for the website, but then campaigns was supposed to start in June, and then the creative, I think, is up in June.","index":356,"end_time":1627.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1618.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":357,"end_time":1627.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1627.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I think so.","index":358,"end_time":1628.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1627.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which.","index":359,"end_time":1629.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1628.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":360,"end_time":1629.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1629.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it all logically just makes sense to say, what is the next six months of the year look like holistically?","index":361,"end_time":1637.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1629.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I''m assuming, like a lot of the ongoing stage, phrase phase two, website updates, programming and all that would be part of, like, what we maybe didn''t budget for, because it''s not really within, like, campaigns.","index":362,"end_time":1654.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1637.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":363,"end_time":1655.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1654.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":364,"end_time":1656.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1655.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that is.","index":365,"end_time":1656.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1656.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Honestly, Christine, typically how we do our contracts is like a.","index":366,"end_time":1660.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1656.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because marketing changes so much.","index":367,"end_time":1661.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1660.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":368,"end_time":1661.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1661.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we can''t.","index":369,"end_time":1662.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1661.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can''t predict at the beginning of the year, like, we''re going to need this much for this and this much for that.","index":370,"end_time":1666.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1662.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we have one contract and it''s like, okay, well, this month let''s pull from this area that we normally do some stuff and let''s put it here.","index":371,"end_time":1672.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1666.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, okay, perfect.","index":372,"end_time":1673.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1672.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":373,"end_time":1673.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1673.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll talk to Tristan.","index":374,"end_time":1674.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1673.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll get a meeting set pretty quick.","index":375,"end_time":1675.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1674.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":376,"end_time":1676.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1675.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And, you know, we''re definitely going to continue the relationship.","index":377,"end_time":1678.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1676.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think, you know, we.","index":378,"end_time":1680.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1678.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''ve made some, you know, really Good, good progress.","index":379,"end_time":1682.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1680.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, so far, once we kind of got past a little bit of a creative kind of just misalignment, but I think, you know, go forward.","index":380,"end_time":1688.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1682.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Websites coming good, you know, and.","index":381,"end_time":1691.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1688.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And all that.","index":382,"end_time":1692.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1691.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The one thing I''ll need you to tell me is if your hourly billing rates are different versus, like, designer versus programming versus account.","index":383,"end_time":1701.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1692.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s the great thing about the contracts that we typically do is we don''t.","index":384,"end_time":1703.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1701.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t go hourly.","index":385,"end_time":1704.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1703.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we tell you, like, a fixed price of, like, this landing page will cost this much.","index":386,"end_time":1708.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1704.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we run into, like, 18 hours of issues, you don''t pay for that.","index":387,"end_time":1710.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1708.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"18 hours average.","index":388,"end_time":1712.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1710.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":389,"end_time":1713.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1712.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":390,"end_time":1713.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1713.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":391,"end_time":1714.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1713.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":392,"end_time":1714.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1714.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, like, everything is much more predictable.","index":393,"end_time":1716.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1714.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s almost like a la carte.","index":394,"end_time":1717.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1716.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":395,"end_time":1718.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1718.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":396,"end_time":1719.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1719.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":397,"end_time":1720.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1719.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, we put a points plan together.","index":398,"end_time":1721.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1720.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s two hours or whatever it is.","index":399,"end_time":1723.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1721.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":400,"end_time":1724.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1723.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":401,"end_time":1724.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1724.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so every.","index":402,"end_time":1725.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1724.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Every three months, we sit down and we say, like, here''s the next three months of work, like, line item by line that we''re predicting to do.","index":403,"end_time":1731.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1725.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re fluid, though, we can take for the next month.","index":404,"end_time":1733.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1731.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can do whatever we need to do.","index":405,"end_time":1735.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1733.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can cancel the whole, like, campaign if we needed to, but that''s how we like to look at these.","index":406,"end_time":1740.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1735.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":407,"end_time":1741.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1740.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":408,"end_time":1741.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1741.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, that.","index":409,"end_time":1741.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1741.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s.","index":410,"end_time":1742.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1741.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s fine because I know we set it up a little bit.","index":411,"end_time":1744.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1742.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just a little bit different.","index":412,"end_time":1745.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1744.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":413,"end_time":1746.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1746.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The kickoff also, too, I think we''re currently over and we''ve been borrowing consistently from the next month, so we''re just going to want to figure out how are we looking from now until June and where if we''re going to be netting out anytime soon.","index":414,"end_time":1766.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1746.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I understand, like, where I can give you guys things also, you know, it''ll help me average out what the, you know, the budget is going to be right for, you know, for the new figure.","index":415,"end_time":1778.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1768.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Once we do that, then I''ll be able to figure out how much I can allocate towards a new fte.","index":416,"end_time":1784.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1778.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":417,"end_time":1785.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1784.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":418,"end_time":1786.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1785.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So awesome.","index":419,"end_time":1788.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1787.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds good.","index":420,"end_time":1789.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1788.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":421,"end_time":1791.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1790.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s really all that I had.","index":422,"end_time":1793.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1791.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, I think I''m getting better at giving time back.","index":423,"end_time":1797.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1795.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Unless.","index":424,"end_time":1797.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1797.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Well, I think our relationship, we''re also, like, we''re starting to read each other''s minds on these things.","index":425,"end_time":1801.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1798.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, yeah.","index":426,"end_time":1802.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1802.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No, it''s.","index":427,"end_time":1803.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1802.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s definitely.","index":428,"end_time":1804.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1803.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s definitely good, but.","index":429,"end_time":1805.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1804.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Cool.","index":430,"end_time":1806.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1806.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, so more.","index":431,"end_time":1808.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1807.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"More to come.","index":432,"end_time":1809.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1808.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Victor, I''ll come by in a minute and we talk about the Google thing, so you can get that email out.","index":433,"end_time":1815.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1810.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":434,"end_time":1816.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1815.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":435,"end_time":1816.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1816.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let me know if you guys have any questions.","index":436,"end_time":1817.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1816.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There.","index":437,"end_time":1817.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1817.71,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Jane will look out for an email from you with the items that we discussed, and then I''ll talk to get a meeting on for you, me, and Tristan, Christina.","index":438,"end_time":1824.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1817.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":439,"end_time":1825.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1825.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, thanks.","index":440,"end_time":1826.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1825.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":441,"end_time":1827.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1826.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a great rest of your day.","index":442,"end_time":1827.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1827.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You too.","index":443,"end_time":1828.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1828.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"}],"dateString":"2026-02-02T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85439302813?pwd=qMBHtkNo4lURIrnTCVFhLG0k15ZQca.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,jane.trachet@poncebank.net,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,victor.garcia@poncebank.net,rebecca.cruz@poncebank.net,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,christina.zanca@poncebank.net","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","jane.trachet@poncebank.net","victor.garcia@poncebank.net","rebecca.cruz@poncebank.net","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","christina.zanca@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFXMD0YJD60T1CF0V5S6EWKD","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.88,"bullets":["Resolved sandbox super admin access to enable private app setup by Ashley and Gabe.","Victor is submitting Google Ads appeal with screenshots to address account suspension issue.","Colin confirmed updated website samples will be ready by Friday for exec review.","Christina proposed consolidating contracts into a flexible master agreement before June renewals.","Retail leadership expressed interest in expanding brochure materials to include lending products."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We are definitely going to continue the relationship...we''ve made some really good, good progress.","speaker":"christinazanca"},{"quote":"He already sent out the full layout on what we should say, adding screenshots.","speaker":"victor garcia"},{"quote":"I''ll talk to Tristan. We''ll get a meeting set pretty quick.","speaker":"colin costigan"}],"topics":["access","ads","website","contract","collateral"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-02-02T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Access and Account Management**\n\nThe team resolved critical access issues by granting multiple users super admin rights on the **Ponce Bank Sandbox** environment to enable app development and testing (12:00).\n\n- **Christina** confirmed that **Ashley and Gabe** received super admin access in the Sandbox to build the private app connection.\n- This access is strictly limited to the Sandbox, ensuring the main production environment remains secure and unaffected.\n- **Colin** clarified that multiple super admins are allowed, correcting initial confusion about single-admin limits.\n- This setup allows development without risking changes on the live site, enabling smoother testing and iteration.\n\nGoogle account access remains problematic due to a **lockout triggered by flagged ad activity and suspected fraudulent login attempts** (13:20).\n\n- **Victor** is actively submitting an appeal to Google, using detailed documentation and screenshots provided by the team.\n- The account lock affects both the Google Business Manager and Ads Manager, with Ads Manager access fully deactivated despite password resets.\n- **Christina** highlighted confusion caused by multiple individual employee logins rather than a unified main account, complicating management and recovery.\n- **Colin** noted that larger organizations typically use individual logins for accountability, while smaller ones share a single login, suggesting a need for clearer account structure.\n\nThe team acknowledged the **risk of Google blacklisting Ponce Bank**, stressing the importance of a successful appeal (18:30).\n\n- The ad account suspension stems from running ads for Mortgage World Bankers under Ponce Bank’s account, likely violating Google''s ad policies.\n- Consolidation of Mortgage World Bankers under Ponce Bank Direct is planned, which may simplify future compliance.\n- The team plans to present the appeal from a Ponce Bank email to increase credibility.\n- They are awaiting a direct human review rather than automated rejections to clarify the exact policy issues.\n\n## **Marketing List Expansion and Postcard Campaign**\n\nThe team plans to **expand the direct mail list by including households near closing competitor branches** to capture potential new customers (20:00).\n\n- **Wanda** reported two Banco Popular branches and two or more Capital One branches are closing nearby.\n- The new list will extend a **half-mile radius** around these closing branches to attract displaced customers.\n- **Jane** will provide specific branch addresses to the list vendor for this expansion today.\n- **Colin** will coordinate with Data Axle to identify new contacts while avoiding duplicate charges for existing names.\n\nThis targeted expansion aims to leverage competitor closures to increase lead volume and improve mail campaign ROI.\n\n## **Website and Creative Updates**\n\nThe team is progressing with **website updates and creative materials**, aiming to deliver improved samples by **Friday** for executive review (22:00).\n\n- **Colin** shared the design team is implementing feedback to increase white space and adjust navigation styling based on recent discussions.\n- Email and page templates in HubSpot are also being updated alongside website pages.\n- Retail sales and banking leadership provided positive feedback on brochures and placemats, with plans to extend creative assets to include **acting services**.\n- Further tweaks or new versions may be developed to support additional product lines, expanding marketing reach.\n\nThe focus is on delivering polished, versatile creative assets that align with leadership expectations and prepare for upcoming executive presentations.\n\n## **Contract Structure and Resource Planning**\n\nThe team agreed to transition to **one master contract** covering all marketing, creative, and website work for flexibility and budget clarity (24:00).\n\n- **Christina** emphasized the need to consolidate multiple ancillary contracts into a single, larger agreement for easier management.\n- This approach will support fluid budget allocation across website updates, campaigns, and creative work without rigid line items.\n- The current website contract runs through **April**, with campaign and creative contracts renewing in **June**, making timely planning essential.\n- The team is considering onboarding a **creative specialist FTE** to handle smaller design tasks and serve as an agency liaison, relieving workload from existing staff.\n\n**Colin** explained their typical approach uses fixed-price deliverables rather than hourly billing, improving cost predictability.\n\n- Work is planned quarterly with line-item forecasts but allows adjustments month to month.\n- This model helps avoid budget overruns and supports agile response to shifting marketing needs.\n\n## **Budget Tracking and Forecasting**\n\nThe team is actively monitoring spending, noting they are currently **over budget and borrowing from future months** (29:00).\n\n- Christina requested a clear forecast from now until June to understand net budget impacts.\n- This will inform how much can be allocated toward the potential new FTE and ongoing marketing efforts.\n- Colin confirmed close coordination with Tristan to schedule contract discussions and refine budget planning.\n- The goal is to ensure stable funding for website enhancements, campaigns, and creative support through the second quarter.\n\n## **Team Collaboration and Next Steps**\n\nThe relationship between the agency and client teams has improved, enabling smoother communication and alignment on priorities (29:50).\n\n- Christina acknowledged progress past initial creative misalignments and expressed confidence in continuing the partnership.\n- Upcoming meetings will focus on contract renewal, resource planning, and finalizing campaign and creative roadmaps.\n- Victor will finalize the Google appeal and share email threads with the team for transparency.\n- Jane will send competitor branch location data to facilitate mail list expansion.\n\nColin will coordinate scheduling with Tristan and Christina to keep key initiatives on track and ensure deadlines are met.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot Access","Google Ads Suspension","Mailing List Update","Website Redesign","Contract Renewal","Creative Specialist"],"overview":"- **Access Management:** Multiple users granted super admin rights in the Ponce Bank Sandbox for secure app development and testing.  \n- **Google Account Issues:** Ongoing appeal to regain access after lockout due to suspected fraud; concerns over ad compliance highlighted.  \n- **Mail List Expansion:** Targeting homes near closing competitor branches to attract new customers; expanding radius to half a mile.  \n- **Website Updates:** Progressing on website and creative updates for an executive review by Friday; improving design and templates.  \n- **Contract Structure:** Transitioning to one master contract for better flexibility and management of marketing and creative work.  \n- **Budget Forecasting:** Team over budget; needs clear forecasts to manage funding for new FTE and ongoing marketing efforts.","action_items":"\n**Christina Zanca**\nGrant super admin access to Ashley and Gabe in HubSpot Sandbox account as per instructions (12:13)\nProvide feedback and confirm next steps related to website and creative material progress (22:00)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nSubmit Google appeal based on provided documentation and screenshots; hold sending until further discussion and share all email trails with the team (13:24)\n\n**Jane Trachet**\nProvide addresses and details of closing Banco Popular and Capital One branches to Colin for mailing list enhancement (20:04)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nCoordinate with Data Axle to verify and run deduplication on mailing list additions from branch closings (21:41)\n\n**Agency Team (Colin and Tristan)**\nContinue working on website and HubSpot email template updates; aim to provide revised samples by Friday to align with executive meeting scheduling (22:23)\n\n**Christina Zanca & Colin Costigan**\nSchedule a meeting to discuss upcoming contract renewal, budgeting, and potential onboarding of a creative specialist FTE (24:04)\n\n**Victor Garcia and Colin Costigan**\nFollow up internally on Google Business accounts access and password reset inconsistencies offline (16:03)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"a9efbc39-87f8-4b3a-b0ef-2ca4ecc26c53","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
    '2026-02-02 16:31:25.164323+00',
    '2026-02-02 16:31:25.164323+00'
  )
  RETURNING meeting_id, contract_id
)
INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync',
  '## **Access and Account Management**

The team resolved critical access issues by granting multiple users super admin rights on the **Ponce Bank Sandbox** environment to enable app development and testing (12:00).

- **Christina** confirmed that **Ashley and Gabe** received super admin access in the Sandbox to build the private app connection.
- This access is strictly limited to the Sandbox, ensuring the main production environment remains secure and unaffected.
- **Colin** clarified that multiple super admins are allowed, correcting initial confusion about single-admin limits.
- This setup allows development without risking changes on the live site, enabling smoother testing and iteration.

Google account access remains problematic due to a **lockout triggered by flagged ad activity and suspected fraudulent login attempts** (13:20).

- **Victor** is actively submitting an appeal to Google, using detailed documentation and screenshots provided by the team.
- The account lock affects both the Google Business Manager and Ads Manager, with Ads Manager access fully deactivated despite password resets.
- **Christina** highlighted confusion caused by multiple individual employee logins rather than a unified main account, complicating management and recovery.
- **Colin** noted that larger organizations typically use individual logins for accountability, while smaller ones share a single login, suggesting a need for clearer account structure.

The team acknowledged the **risk of Google blacklisting Ponce Bank**, stressing the importance of a successful appeal (18:30).

- The ad account suspension stems from running ads for Mortgage World Bankers under Ponce Bank’s account, likely violating Google''s ad policies.
- Consolidation of Mortgage World Bankers under Ponce Bank Direct is planned, which may simplify future compliance.
- The team plans to present the appeal from a Ponce Bank email to increase credibility.
- They are awaiting a direct human review rather than automated rejections to clarify the exact policy issues.

## **Marketing List Expansion and Postcard Campaign**

The team plans to **expand the direct mail list by including households near closing competitor branches** to capture potential new customers (20:00).

- **Wanda** reported two Banco Popular branches and two or more Capital One branches are closing nearby.
- The new list will extend a **half-mile radius** around these closing branches to attract displaced customers.
- **Jane** will provide specific branch addresses to the list vendor for this expansion today.
- **Colin** will coordinate with Data Axle to identify new contacts while avoiding duplicate charges for existing names.

This targeted expansion aims to leverage competitor closures to increase lead volume and improve mail campaign ROI.

## **Website and Creative Updates**

The team is progressing with **website updates and creative materials**, aiming to deliver improved samples by **Friday** for executive review (22:00).

- **Colin** shared the design team is implementing feedback to increase white space and adjust navigation styling based on recent discussions.
- Email and page templates in HubSpot are also being updated alongside website pages.
- Retail sales and banking leadership provided positive feedback on brochures and placemats, with plans to extend creative assets to include **acting services**.
- Further tweaks or new versions may be developed to support additional product lines, expanding marketing reach.

The focus is on delivering polished, versatile creative assets that align with leadership expectations and prepare for upcoming executive presentations.

## **Contract Structure and Resource Planning**

The team agreed to transition to **one master contract** covering all marketing, creative, and website work for flexibility and budget clarity (24:00).

- **Christina** emphasized the need to consolidate multiple ancillary contracts into a single, larger agreement for easier management.
- This approach will support fluid budget allocation across website updates, campaigns, and creative work without rigid line items.
- The current website contract runs through **April**, with campaign and creative contracts renewing in **June**, making timely planning essential.
- The team is considering onboarding a **creative specialist FTE** to handle smaller design tasks and serve as an agency liaison, relieving workload from existing staff.

**Colin** explained their typical approach uses fixed-price deliverables rather than hourly billing, improving cost predictability.

- Work is planned quarterly with line-item forecasts but allows adjustments month to month.
- This model helps avoid budget overruns and supports agile response to shifting marketing needs.

## **Budget Tracking and Forecasting**

The team is actively monitoring spending, noting they are currently **over budget and borrowing from future months** (29:00).

- Christina requested a clear forecast from now until June to understand net budget impacts.
- This will inform how much can be allocated toward the potential new FTE and ongoing marketing efforts.
- Colin confirmed close coordination with Tristan to schedule contract discussions and refine budget planning.
- The goal is to ensure stable funding for website enhancements, campaigns, and creative support through the second quarter.

## **Team Collaboration and Next Steps**

The relationship between the agency and client teams has improved, enabling smoother communication and alignment on priorities (29:50).

- Christina acknowledged progress past initial creative misalignments and expressed confidence in continuing the partnership.
- Upcoming meetings will focus on contract renewal, resource planning, and finalizing campaign and creative roadmaps.
- Victor will finalize the Google appeal and share email threads with the team for transparency.
- Jane will send competitor branch location data to facilitate mail list expansion.

Colin will coordinate scheduling with Tristan and Christina to keep key initiatives on track and ensure deadlines are met.',
  '2026-02-02 16:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Grant super admin access to Ashley and Gabe in HubSpot Sandbox account as per instructions (12:13)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide feedback and confirm next steps related to website and creative material progress (22:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Submit Google appeal based on provided documentation and screenshots; hold sending until further discussion and share all email trails with the team (13:24)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide addresses and details of closing Banco Popular and Capital One branches to Colin for mailing list enhancement (20:04)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Data Axle to verify and run deduplication on mailing list additions from branch closings (21:41)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue working on website and HubSpot email template updates; aim to provide revised samples by Friday to align with executive meeting scheduling (22:23)","completed":false},{"text":"Schedule a meeting to discuss upcoming contract renewal, budgeting, and potential onboarding of a creative specialist FTE (24:04)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up internally on Google Business accounts access and password reset inconsistencies offline (16:03)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: GSS // MID Weekly Meeting (2026-01-28 16:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '6061d0c2-de11-40b9-8824-1ccd80a970d6',
    '2026-01-28 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFGQSX3ZSPPEAH6FZ6SY82J3',
    'GSS // MID Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Will Fleming","Baylee Gunnell","Guille Santana","Nick S (GSS)"}'::text[],
    1219,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83236942727?pwd=NaLGKm3JEGM6umJeSVS9pHPmDfNAYN.1',
    '{"id":"01KFGQSX3ZSPPEAH6FZ6SY82J3","title":"GSS // MID Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Strategy and Updates**\n\nThe team finalized the **ebook content and landing page design** to launch by the **end of the month**, opting for an ungated format to reduce friction and improve user access (01:00).  \n- This approach leverages RB2B tracking to identify visitor company profiles and roles without requiring form fills.  \n- Guille emphasized this will improve lead quality by focusing on intent signals rather than form submissions.  \n- Baylee suggested producing content pieces that address outsourcing myths and competitor comparisons to build trust and generate leads.  \n- Will stressed the importance of framing pricing competitively without focusing solely on being the cheapest option, supporting long-term customer trust.\n\n## **Target Account List and Campaign Refinement**\n\nThe decision was made to **exclude franchise owners** from the ABM campaign due to their typically small scale and local reach, focusing instead on larger multi-unit operators and top company lists (02:00).  \n- Will explained that the **top 200 list** contains more relevant larger companies, often with CFO-level contacts, aligning better with accounting service prospects.  \n- Guille confirmed the top 200 list will be used for accounting services targeting while building separate lists for CFO services with larger company names.  \n- Nick highlighted the need to continuously target multi-unit franchise groups, confirming the list-building system can find similar contacts beyond the initial data set.\n\n## **Market Positioning and Competitive Differentiation**\n\nWill outlined a **market shift driven by inflation and recent service provider mergers**, creating an opportunity to win clients seeking cost-efficient, high-quality alternatives to large international firms (06:30).  \n- He shared a case of a prospect with over **100 fast food restaurants** unhappy with their current costly national provider, illustrating the demand for alternatives.  \n- Will advocated for content that delicately promotes the company’s **U.S.-aligned service model from Argentina**, addressing cultural fit and quality concerns without pushing offshore cost savings aggressively.  \n- Baylee supported this by proposing myth-busting and competitor comparison content to clarify benefits and overcome hesitation.\n\n## **Technology and Lead Tracking Integration**\n\nThe team is actively **configuring RB2B to connect with the client’s website** for real-time visitor tracking by page and service interest, aiming to deliver actionable lead intelligence (14:00).  \n- Guille plans to provide spreadsheets detailing visitor company names and insights, integrating alerts via Microsoft Teams as the preferred communication tool.  \n- This setup is expected to enhance sales responsiveness by highlighting high-intent visitors for accounting and CFO services.  \n- The integration will allow precise measurement of engagement with key website areas, improving targeting and follow-up quality.\n\n## **Campaign Execution Timeline and Messaging Development**\n\nMessaging updates and list refinement for the next campaign batch are targeted for completion by **next week**, with readiness to launch once finalized (19:30).  \n- Baylee noted that if an earlier launch is preferred, the team can deploy existing messaging and lists immediately to maintain momentum.  \n- Will emphasized willingness to wait for optimized messaging, prioritizing quality over speed to maximize campaign impact.  \n- Guille confirmed removal of unsuitable contacts such as former customers and franchise owners from updated lists based on client feedback.  \n- Nick expressed confidence in ongoing collaboration to refine targets and messaging for optimal outreach results.","outline":null,"keywords":["eBook","ABM campaign","franchise owners","RB2B tracking","outsourcing myths","competitor comparison"],"overview":"- **Ebook Launch:** Finalized ungated ebook and landing page by end of the month for improved user access.  \n- **Target Accounts:** Excluded franchise owners from ABM campaign, focusing on top 200 multi-unit operators for accounting services.  \n- **Market Opportunities:** Inflation and mergers create chances for cost-efficient alternatives to large firms, especially among dissatisfied prospects.  \n- **Lead Tracking:** Configuring RB2B for real-time website visitor tracking to enhance lead intelligence and sales responsiveness.  \n- **Campaign Readiness:** Messaging updates and list refinements due next week; can launch early with existing materials if needed.  \n- **Content Strategy:** Emphasizing trust-building through myth-busting and competitor comparisons to clarify benefits and address concerns.","action_items":"\n**Guille Santana**\nSend landing page and newsletter designs for review by end of day or next day (01:25)\nUse top 200 list to build accounting services target sequence and develop larger company name list for CFO services (05:40)\nRemove franchise owners and direct customers from list per GSS feedback and prepare updated outreach lists (18:10)\nComplete updated email messaging for campaigns and deliver new batch expected next week (19:35)\n\n**Will Fleming**\nProvide a list of current competitors for campaign targeting and content development (13:40)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nSchedule an interview with Will for gathering competitor insights and content creation (13:20)\n"},"duration":20.309999465942383,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Will Fleming"},{"id":1,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":2,"name":"Guille Santana"},{"id":3,"name":"Nick S (GSS)"}],"sentences":[{"text":"So.","index":0,"end_time":0.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Oh, cool.","index":1,"end_time":2.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s always a.","index":2,"end_time":3.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"A great thing to be busy with.","index":3,"end_time":4.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, it''s a current customer, so it''s.","index":4,"end_time":8.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.84,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Not like, oh, never mind.","index":5,"end_time":9.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, but anyways.","index":6,"end_time":13.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.24,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we should probably get started.","index":7,"end_time":18.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14.64,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Hey, you want to kick us off Guie?","index":8,"end_time":22.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":20.48,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yep.","index":9,"end_time":23.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":23.04,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"One second.","index":10,"end_time":25.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":24.56,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Zoom in.","index":11,"end_time":28.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There we go.","index":12,"end_time":30.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":30.07,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Alrighty.","index":13,"end_time":36.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":35.59,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So for today''s agenda, we''ll go over some content updates.","index":14,"end_time":41.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":37.35,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Updates on the new AVM campaign that we''re relaunching.","index":15,"end_time":45.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":42.149,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And just like let you know that how we''re setting up RB2B.","index":16,"end_time":50.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":45.83,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":17,"end_time":53.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.56,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"For the content updates, we incorporated your latest feedback wheel on the finalized ebook.","index":18,"end_time":62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":54.32,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s already done.","index":19,"end_time":63.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":62,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We have a landing page.","index":20,"end_time":64.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":63.52,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We''re designing a landing page and a newsletter.","index":21,"end_time":68.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":65.2,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I will probably send that over today or tomorrow for your review.","index":22,"end_time":72.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":69.12,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So we can send it over before the ebook end of the month.","index":23,"end_time":76.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":72.52,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"One thing I wanted to mention that it''s that the ebook will not be gated behind the form because we will have RB2B on our website.","index":24,"end_time":86.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":78.25,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And we''re doing that to reduce friction, like people filling out a form.","index":25,"end_time":92.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":86.97,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But RB2E will let us know and track who is visiting the landing page.","index":26,"end_time":98.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":92.73,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":27,"end_time":100.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.85,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So we know like clearly what companies and what roles they''re downloading the ebook.","index":28,"end_time":108.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.89,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":29,"end_time":109.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.22,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yep.","index":30,"end_time":111.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":110.5,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So that''s on content.","index":31,"end_time":113.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":111.54,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Now for the ABM campaign, we are going to exclude franchise owner because you guys mentioned that probably isn''t the role that we want to target because they probably just have one franchise.","index":32,"end_time":127.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":115.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And you sent over like the top 200 list to identify.","index":33,"end_time":133.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":129.95,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"You send over the top 200 list from 2024, I believe.","index":34,"end_time":139.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":134.59,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I think it''s a good idea, like we can take the company names from that list and use it to produce like lookalike companies on clay and on LinkedIn.","index":35,"end_time":153.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":139.71,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So, so we can refine our parameters but use that list like as a base to start building out the new list that we''re going to be targeting.","index":36,"end_time":163.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":154.11,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":37,"end_time":164.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":164.43,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So.","index":38,"end_time":165.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":164.91,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Let me just make a few comments on both areas and then Nick''s here, he can comment as well if he wants.","index":39,"end_time":176.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.429,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But the lists you sent over, I thought it was fine.","index":40,"end_time":182.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":176.07,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Uh, it''s mostly unique concept groups.","index":41,"end_time":186.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.82,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Some of them have quite a bit locations and some of them are in markets that in theory should.","index":42,"end_time":192.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":186.06,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Should be seeing issues and potentially we could help them.","index":43,"end_time":198.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.9,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I think that was good.","index":44,"end_time":200.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":199.54,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So in that first list, a franchise owner, those are not well known brands in that list.","index":45,"end_time":206.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.9,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And it''s not uncommon to see somebody that, that franchises kind of a local concept because maybe they have some success in a few restaurants and then they decide to franchise it, but they don''t really put any effort behind it and it never really goes anywhere.","index":46,"end_time":224.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.78,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And they may have like, you know, four or five franchisees, but they all have one store.","index":47,"end_time":231.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.65,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And that would be the less common, unique brands, very regional.","index":48,"end_time":236.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.29,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"The other, the 200, the top 200, you might see the same title because they are all going to be franchise franchise owners.","index":49,"end_time":246.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":236.94,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So but the idea that a franchise owner in Taco Bell is going to be large or even just.","index":50,"end_time":255.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.58,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s just a more.","index":51,"end_time":256.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.66,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They have 7,000.","index":52,"end_time":257.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.94,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"There''s 7,000 Taco Bells in the United States.","index":53,"end_time":260.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":257.86,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So therefore anybody that, that has a Taco Bell would be our target.","index":54,"end_time":264.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.18,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So just I just wanted to point out that the two different types of titles that you could see, I mean I don''t really see franchisees and Taco Bell calling themselves a franchise owner, but you never know.","index":55,"end_time":284.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.83,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But in general that, that''s.","index":56,"end_time":288.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.35,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And the other point is that not always, but sometimes in the, at least in the top 200 list is going to be more accounting services versus the other list.","index":57,"end_time":302.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.09,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"If somebody has 15 restaurants in New York City, they could be an accounting services customer and a CFO.","index":58,"end_time":310.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":302.49,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So it''s just less likely in the top 200 to be getting CFO services.","index":59,"end_time":316.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.29,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"That''s a more traffic area like just in terms of people selling the same services we''re trying to sell.","index":60,"end_time":326.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.38,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But yeah, I just wanted to point that out.","index":61,"end_time":331.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.46,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Got it, got it.","index":62,"end_time":334.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":333.14,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So we''ll use the top 200 list to build the accounting services for the accounting services sequence and we''ll definitely look more into building bigger company names for the CFO services.","index":63,"end_time":349.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":334.42,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"One.","index":64,"end_time":349.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":349.56,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":65,"end_time":353,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":352.44,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And I also think just in terms.","index":66,"end_time":355.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":353.32,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Of.","index":67,"end_time":355.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.52,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"When we talk about content, obviously we''re trying to get the attention of the marketplace and I mean, Nick can talk about this too, but I mean we have a customer from the top 200 list or not a customer, a prospect that we''re talking to right now.","index":68,"end_time":378.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.88,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And the basic message from them is that they''re with a big national firm that does the services from the United States and the costs are out of control and they need to look at a different scenario.","index":69,"end_time":393.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.03,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And they''re, you know, this is a group with more than 100 fast food restaurants.","index":70,"end_time":401.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.71,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s really the ideal scenario for us because when you, we believe, I mean both Nick and I and kind of what we see in the market that there is going to be in the next, you know, from now until two years, I mean people are just going to, there''s going to be a massive movement to get a more cost efficient solution.","index":71,"end_time":424.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.32,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"That is also has decent service because not everybody''s comfortable with the international model yet, but it''s.","index":72,"end_time":433.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.61,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Every year it changes.","index":73,"end_time":435.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.49,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So there was a merger between two firms recently that we compete with and there''s a lot of unhappy customers right now with either their cost or just their service.","index":74,"end_time":448.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.69,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And so it''d be.","index":75,"end_time":449.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.73,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And this group falls into that.","index":76,"end_time":451.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.65,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"That merger.","index":77,"end_time":453.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.44,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"That''s where they get their services.","index":78,"end_time":454.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.32,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So there''s.","index":79,"end_time":461.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.36,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Right now I think there should be a lot of people looking for a lower cost solution that they.","index":80,"end_time":467.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.88,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And that''s not India.","index":81,"end_time":468.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.24,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And so we should be present.","index":82,"end_time":470.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We may even want to.","index":83,"end_time":473.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.52,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Nick had brought this up a couple weeks ago.","index":84,"end_time":475.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.68,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We may want to do some content in the future that''s very specific about what''s going on in the market about.","index":85,"end_time":485.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":476.44,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And I''ll just give you a unrelated example.","index":86,"end_time":490.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":486.79,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I told Nick this five, 20 years ago I was.","index":87,"end_time":498.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.83,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We were at part of a call center business and we were trying to get call center work that was going to be managed from Latin America for usaa.","index":88,"end_time":512.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499.83,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"USAA is a premium insurance company in the United States and it''s for the military, former military.","index":89,"end_time":522.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":512.25,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I use it because my family''s from the military.","index":90,"end_time":525.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.53,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But.","index":91,"end_time":525.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":525.37,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And at the time USAA was saying they weren''t comfortable going to Latin America.","index":92,"end_time":532.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.37,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They needed lower cost, but they just didn''t feel that the service could be.","index":93,"end_time":536.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.13,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And right now USAA delivers their call center customer service from El Salvador.","index":94,"end_time":545.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":538.02,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So what has happened is what I think is somebody that''s really like at the top in terms of what their expectations are, the quality of service eventually like the cost just overtakes them and they just have no other option.","index":95,"end_time":561.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.94,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I''m sure they tested the market.","index":96,"end_time":562.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":561.38,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I''m sure they looked at a lot of different scenarios.","index":97,"end_time":565.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.98,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But eventually they went to the global marketplace because things just pushed in that way.","index":98,"end_time":570.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.81,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We''re going to see something similar.","index":99,"end_time":572.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.09,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We have seen it, but I think it''s going to be more rapid this year based on the inflation from the recent past.","index":100,"end_time":582.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.97,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And so we may want to think about some kind of story.","index":101,"end_time":585.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":582.53,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean I never wanted to sort of promote.","index":102,"end_time":587.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.41,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean we deliver the services from Argentina to be such a.","index":103,"end_time":592.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.61,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"An aggressive sort of push to pitch an offshore solution.","index":104,"end_time":599.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.82,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But maybe there''s a way to do it.","index":105,"end_time":601.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":599.46,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But I.","index":106,"end_time":603.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.5,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And so it''s not.","index":107,"end_time":604.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.38,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So it''s comfortable in a way or I''m not exactly sure.","index":108,"end_time":608.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.98,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But I think that that''s very relevant right now.","index":109,"end_time":610.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.5,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I heard some of the.","index":110,"end_time":612.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":611.22,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"From the conversations that Nick had over the last couple of days and it''s very important right now.","index":111,"end_time":620.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.98,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And if we can present ourselves as a U.S. centric or U.S. culturally aligned service provider.","index":112,"end_time":635.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":620.59,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think we can be very relevant.","index":113,"end_time":639.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.31,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like yay, you''re in Mexico and you, you''re culturally, I mean I can just tell you''re very aligned with the culture here.","index":114,"end_time":650.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.07,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And I mean maybe just your career.","index":115,"end_time":652.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":650.7,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I''m not exactly sure why, but that''s the way we are from Argentina.","index":116,"end_time":656.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":652.82,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So we have that same attachment.","index":117,"end_time":659.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.94,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And to the extent that we can promote that in a way that, you know, doesn''t, I don''t know, make people nervous about, you know, an international company and all that comes with it or like Argentina sometimes is that I think Mexico is, has a better perception in terms of like the business community than maybe Argentina.","index":118,"end_time":682.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":659.66,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Sometimes people think Argentina is like Banana Republic or something.","index":119,"end_time":686.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.62,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So we have to be a little bit.","index":120,"end_time":687.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.66,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But there I think it could be something I think should be something we should discuss in the content part.","index":121,"end_time":699.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.06,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So.","index":122,"end_time":700.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.48,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, I love, love, I love that idea, Will.","index":123,"end_time":704.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":701.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And that''s where my head was going as you were talking about that too.","index":124,"end_time":708.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":704.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Because we could do a couple pieces on that.","index":125,"end_time":710.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":708.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I was thinking like maybe one about myths of outsourcing your accounting, like debunking some of those myths.","index":126,"end_time":718.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":710.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We could also do one.","index":127,"end_time":720.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":719.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This is one that sometimes people are really excited about and some people are very hesitant about is like a comparison article of your competitors.","index":128,"end_time":731.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":721.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So essentially it''s just like outlining pros and cons of working with you versus like some of like your top competitors.","index":129,"end_time":740.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Some people really like doing that.","index":130,"end_time":742.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have some articles on our website like that and we honestly get the most leads from those articles.","index":131,"end_time":748.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":742.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"However, some people are hesitant because they''re like, oh, I''m just pointing to my competitors now and getting people on their website.","index":132,"end_time":755.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":748.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we, we can figure that out too.","index":133,"end_time":758.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":755.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But I, I definitely think we could make a couple pieces of content using that information.","index":134,"end_time":764.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I, I think we have to figure out a way.","index":135,"end_time":768.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":766.23,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean I don''t want to promote just like a race to the bottom on pricing, but we think our pricing is not like we don''t lead necessarily lead with that.","index":136,"end_time":778.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":768.63,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But people are definitely going to save money like our standard pricing.","index":137,"end_time":781.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.19,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They''re going to save money and if we can get them comfortable with the way we work from a service point of view, it''s, it''s just a no brainer.","index":138,"end_time":790.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.42,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So anyways.","index":139,"end_time":794.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.06,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, but it''s still your thunder.","index":140,"end_time":796.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.06,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Nick.","index":141,"end_time":797.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":796.86,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Let''s schedule a time for an interview.","index":142,"end_time":799.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":797.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Maybe sometime next week or this week if you''re available.","index":143,"end_time":803.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sure, absolutely.","index":144,"end_time":806.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":804.58,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Do we have a list of your current competitors or.","index":145,"end_time":812.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":807.68,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I don''t think so, but we can, we can.","index":146,"end_time":817.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.04,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I can send you one like, I can send you one that''s like people that we''re seeing right now that, that.","index":147,"end_time":824,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":817.92,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":148,"end_time":824.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":824,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That you''re competing with.","index":149,"end_time":825.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824.56,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be like, really useful for the campaigns.","index":150,"end_time":831.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":827.12,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":151,"end_time":831.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.32,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"All right.","index":152,"end_time":833.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":833.45,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"No, I think that''s a great idea.","index":153,"end_time":835.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":834.09,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And as Bailey said, we can see how we frame it so it doesn''t look like we''re being the cheapest option at the cost of like the service.","index":154,"end_time":847.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":837.85,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":155,"end_time":849.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":848.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":156,"end_time":851.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.41,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then last but not least, we''re currently configuring RB2B and connecting it to your website so that we can know like, who''s visiting GSS websites and just to know which are the pages that, where we see the highest intent.","index":157,"end_time":874.599,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":852.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Maybe it''s accounting services, maybe it''s CFO services.","index":158,"end_time":877.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":874.599,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And once that''s set up, we can get you like a spreadsheet of people that visit the website and including like relevant company names, like, and insights where, where they are available.","index":159,"end_time":892.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":878.2,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We can also set this up on, I believe, Slack or Microsoft Teams, so let us know which one is like the one.","index":160,"end_time":900.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":893.57,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, we kind of talked about this on Friday.","index":161,"end_time":903.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":901.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know.","index":162,"end_time":904.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":903.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t think you guys use slacker teams, so we can just send like.","index":163,"end_time":907.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, you use teams.","index":164,"end_time":909.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":908.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re heavy user teams.","index":165,"end_time":911.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":909.82,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":166,"end_time":912.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":911.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":167,"end_time":913.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":913.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":168,"end_time":915.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":915.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Would.","index":169,"end_time":915.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":915.66,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Do you want a teams like channel with us?","index":170,"end_time":920.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":915.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Would that be helpful or do you want to keep things on email?","index":171,"end_time":927.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":921.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I. I don''t know.","index":172,"end_time":930.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.26,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, Nick, I guess for me email is fine.","index":173,"end_time":934.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":930.54,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, I respond to both pretty quickly.","index":174,"end_time":944.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":941.35,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":175,"end_time":944.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, I mean, whatever is easier for you guys, I guess.","index":176,"end_time":948.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":945.99,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we can keep things on email if, if that''s cool.","index":177,"end_time":953.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":949.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":178,"end_time":955.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":954.71,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right.","index":179,"end_time":957.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":956.79,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And I would say that''s it.","index":180,"end_time":962.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":959.67,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Here''s your client portal.","index":181,"end_time":966.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":962.95,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I''m not sure if you''re seeing my screen.","index":182,"end_time":968.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":967.03,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, This is what we''re working on.","index":183,"end_time":976.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":970.31,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":184,"end_time":980.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.23,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"All right.","index":185,"end_time":988.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":988.24,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So just a quick question.","index":186,"end_time":992.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":991.44,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Oh, sorry, go ahead.","index":187,"end_time":993.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":992.72,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"No, go ahead, Nikki first.","index":188,"end_time":995.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.08,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Well, I don''t know if I missed any discussion about the list curating and the sources and stuff.","index":189,"end_time":1002.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":996.32,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I had just had the chance to read your email.","index":190,"end_time":1005.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1002.959,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Gay.","index":191,"end_time":1005.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1005.04,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And.","index":192,"end_time":1005.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1005.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''re going to be pulling similar contacts like the list you shared, which is good because they''re unique in what will said.","index":193,"end_time":1016.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1009.12,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"There''s opportunity there.","index":194,"end_time":1018.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1017.1,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"But then there''s also, you know, a large group of prospects that I continue to target as well within brands and multi unit franchise groups.","index":195,"end_time":1028.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1019.9,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Is that, is that something your list system can find or is that I.","index":196,"end_time":1037.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1031.42,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"You sent the email and you''re like, could you share the password or something like that.","index":197,"end_time":1041.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1038.3,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''m not sure what you''re asking for.","index":198,"end_time":1042.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1041.3,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"There.","index":199,"end_time":1043.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1042.78,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"What it''s like for password.","index":200,"end_time":1051.799,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1048.919,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, I think I''m a little.","index":201,"end_time":1055.639,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1054.199,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Little confused too.","index":202,"end_time":1057.239,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1055.959,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we should be able to find a lookalike list using what you sent us.","index":203,"end_time":1062.679,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.359,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it says, happy to review what we find with you once we have an updated pass.","index":204,"end_time":1069.039,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1065.479,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Is that.","index":205,"end_time":1069.559,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1069.039,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Maybe I misread that.","index":206,"end_time":1071.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1070.81,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like, oh, you need a password for me for this chain store guy thing.","index":207,"end_time":1074.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1071.73,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Maybe I misread that.","index":208,"end_time":1076.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1075.13,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"She''s saying pass through.","index":209,"end_time":1078.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1077.05,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Oh, gotcha.","index":210,"end_time":1080.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1079.13,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay, never mind.","index":211,"end_time":1082.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1080.01,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":212,"end_time":1082.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1082.49,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I was on a demo before this and I just read the email, like, real quick and.","index":213,"end_time":1087.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1082.77,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, we''ll send over the, like, the broader list once it''s ready.","index":214,"end_time":1092.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1087.13,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And with your comments, we''ll definitely take out like, the.","index":215,"end_time":1096.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1092.69,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"To customers and like the franchise owner.","index":216,"end_time":1101.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1096.93,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Because you said that''s probably not a good fit, but.","index":217,"end_time":1105.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1102.21,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re working on that.","index":218,"end_time":1107.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1105.65,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay, great, thanks.","index":219,"end_time":1109.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1107.97,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So in terms of the, like, we have this list.","index":220,"end_time":1116.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1112.29,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We had a couple customers in there that were former customers that would need to come out.","index":221,"end_time":1122.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1117.01,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then is.","index":222,"end_time":1123.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1122.81,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Is that.","index":223,"end_time":1124.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1123.77,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Will.","index":224,"end_time":1125.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1124.97,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Will you proceed with.","index":225,"end_time":1127.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1125.53,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"With that while you continue expanding the list?","index":226,"end_time":1131.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1127.21,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Is that the idea?","index":227,"end_time":1133.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.93,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Just want to get a sense of when we''ll get things sent out.","index":228,"end_time":1138.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1133.21,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We''re still working on, like, updated emails and messages from what we talked about on Friday, so that''s something we''re still working through.","index":229,"end_time":1149.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1139.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you want.","index":230,"end_time":1150.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1149.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If, like that list we sent over, if you want to use, like, the old stuff that was running, we could just hurry and launch.","index":231,"end_time":1156.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1150.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you want to get something at least.","index":232,"end_time":1158.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1156.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I just.","index":233,"end_time":1159.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1158.68,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I just want to get in whatever.","index":234,"end_time":1161.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.24,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like, use the time you need to.","index":235,"end_time":1163.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1161.16,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"To design it.","index":236,"end_time":1164.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.28,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"As we discussed, I was just getting.","index":237,"end_time":1166.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1164.44,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Wanted to get a sense of the timing.","index":238,"end_time":1167.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1166.12,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like, when do you anticipate the new batch getting sent?","index":239,"end_time":1171.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.12,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":240,"end_time":1175.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1174.68,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Or you got an answer?","index":241,"end_time":1177.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1176.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Da.","index":242,"end_time":1178.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1177.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Probably next week.","index":243,"end_time":1179.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1178.29,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We''re almost done with the messaging.","index":244,"end_time":1181.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1179.49,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":245,"end_time":1182.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1181.89,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"All right.","index":246,"end_time":1183.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1182.53,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"That''s helpful.","index":247,"end_time":1184.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1183.25,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay.","index":248,"end_time":1188.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1188.29,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"All right.","index":249,"end_time":1190.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1189.65,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That''s all I have.","index":250,"end_time":1191.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1190.37,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":251,"end_time":1194.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1193.33,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"See ya.","index":252,"end_time":1195.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1195.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Have a good day.","index":253,"end_time":1196.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1195.69,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Bye.","index":254,"end_time":1196.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1196.17,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Bye.","index":255,"end_time":1196.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1196.37,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"You too.","index":256,"end_time":1197.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1196.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2026-01-28T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83236942727?pwd=NaLGKm3JEGM6umJeSVS9pHPmDfNAYN.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,nstauff@gsslp.com,wfleming@gsslp.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","nstauff@gsslp.com","wfleming@gsslp.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFGQSX3ZSPPEAH6FZ6SY82J3","organizer_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Finalized ebook and landing page completed; aiming to release before end of month.","Guille confirmed ABM list will exclude single-location franchise owners to improve targeting.","Will emphasized timing risk if content doesn’t address current cost pressures in the market.","Baylee proposed myth-busting and competitor comparison articles to drive engaged traffic.","RB2B website tracking is being configured; Teams integration preferred over Slack."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Right now I think there should be a lot of people looking for a lower cost solution","speaker":"Will Fleming"},{"quote":"We could do a couple pieces on that... maybe one about myths of outsourcing your accounting","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"We''ll use the top 200 list to build the accounting services sequence","speaker":"Guille Santana"}],"topics":["content","targeting","launch","campaign","tracking"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-30T23:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content Strategy and Updates**\n\nThe team finalized the **ebook content and landing page design** to launch by the **end of the month**, opting for an ungated format to reduce friction and improve user access (01:00).  \n- This approach leverages RB2B tracking to identify visitor company profiles and roles without requiring form fills.  \n- Guille emphasized this will improve lead quality by focusing on intent signals rather than form submissions.  \n- Baylee suggested producing content pieces that address outsourcing myths and competitor comparisons to build trust and generate leads.  \n- Will stressed the importance of framing pricing competitively without focusing solely on being the cheapest option, supporting long-term customer trust.\n\n## **Target Account List and Campaign Refinement**\n\nThe decision was made to **exclude franchise owners** from the ABM campaign due to their typically small scale and local reach, focusing instead on larger multi-unit operators and top company lists (02:00).  \n- Will explained that the **top 200 list** contains more relevant larger companies, often with CFO-level contacts, aligning better with accounting service prospects.  \n- Guille confirmed the top 200 list will be used for accounting services targeting while building separate lists for CFO services with larger company names.  \n- Nick highlighted the need to continuously target multi-unit franchise groups, confirming the list-building system can find similar contacts beyond the initial data set.\n\n## **Market Positioning and Competitive Differentiation**\n\nWill outlined a **market shift driven by inflation and recent service provider mergers**, creating an opportunity to win clients seeking cost-efficient, high-quality alternatives to large international firms (06:30).  \n- He shared a case of a prospect with over **100 fast food restaurants** unhappy with their current costly national provider, illustrating the demand for alternatives.  \n- Will advocated for content that delicately promotes the company’s **U.S.-aligned service model from Argentina**, addressing cultural fit and quality concerns without pushing offshore cost savings aggressively.  \n- Baylee supported this by proposing myth-busting and competitor comparison content to clarify benefits and overcome hesitation.\n\n## **Technology and Lead Tracking Integration**\n\nThe team is actively **configuring RB2B to connect with the client’s website** for real-time visitor tracking by page and service interest, aiming to deliver actionable lead intelligence (14:00).  \n- Guille plans to provide spreadsheets detailing visitor company names and insights, integrating alerts via Microsoft Teams as the preferred communication tool.  \n- This setup is expected to enhance sales responsiveness by highlighting high-intent visitors for accounting and CFO services.  \n- The integration will allow precise measurement of engagement with key website areas, improving targeting and follow-up quality.\n\n## **Campaign Execution Timeline and Messaging Development**\n\nMessaging updates and list refinement for the next campaign batch are targeted for completion by **next week**, with readiness to launch once finalized (19:30).  \n- Baylee noted that if an earlier launch is preferred, the team can deploy existing messaging and lists immediately to maintain momentum.  \n- Will emphasized willingness to wait for optimized messaging, prioritizing quality over speed to maximize campaign impact.  \n- Guille confirmed removal of unsuitable contacts such as former customers and franchise owners from updated lists based on client feedback.  \n- Nick expressed confidence in ongoing collaboration to refine targets and messaging for optimal outreach results.","outline":null,"keywords":["eBook","ABM campaign","franchise owners","RB2B tracking","outsourcing myths","competitor comparison"],"overview":"- **Ebook Launch:** Finalized ungated ebook and landing page by end of the month for improved user access.  \n- **Target Accounts:** Excluded franchise owners from ABM campaign, focusing on top 200 multi-unit operators for accounting services.  \n- **Market Opportunities:** Inflation and mergers create chances for cost-efficient alternatives to large firms, especially among dissatisfied prospects.  \n- **Lead Tracking:** Configuring RB2B for real-time website visitor tracking to enhance lead intelligence and sales responsiveness.  \n- **Campaign Readiness:** Messaging updates and list refinements due next week; can launch early with existing materials if needed.  \n- **Content Strategy:** Emphasizing trust-building through myth-busting and competitor comparisons to clarify benefits and address concerns.","action_items":"\n**Guille Santana**\nSend landing page and newsletter designs for review by end of day or next day (01:25)\nUse top 200 list to build accounting services target sequence and develop larger company name list for CFO services (05:40)\nRemove franchise owners and direct customers from list per GSS feedback and prepare updated outreach lists (18:10)\nComplete updated email messaging for campaigns and deliver new batch expected next week (19:35)\n\n**Will Fleming**\nProvide a list of current competitors for campaign targeting and content development (13:40)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nSchedule an interview with Will for gathering competitor insights and content creation (13:20)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"4bb17917-5ef6-49a3-b533-b6af7e605e65","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
