INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect',
  '## **Lead Generation and Outreach Performance**

Lead generation via LinkedIn is growing rapidly, with outreach efforts focused on qualifying and engaging potential clients.

- **LinkedIn connection requests increased to 29 this week**, a **300% rise from 8 last week**, signaling strong new lead flow (02:00)  
    - Keenan is selectively following up on those who replied and filtering by role to prioritize quality conversations  
    - Shane noted it often takes multiple touch points on LinkedIn before engagement occurs, supporting a patient outreach approach  
    - Automated LinkedIn messaging sequences from Brad reduce manual workload, continuing follow-ups until prospects respond  
    - Keenan plans to call leads who submitted forms but did not respond, targeting early morning hours for better contact rates  

- **LinkedIn metrics reveal a 24% acceptance rate for billing organizations and 67% message reply rate on those connections**, while DSOs show lower engagement at 15% acceptance and 26% reply rates (08:29)  
    - Keenan questioned the 67% reply rate, finding only 7 replies out of 38 connections, suggesting data may be skewed or segmented differently  
    - Nathalie confirmed all replies appear in LinkedIn’s message section, indicating Keenan’s view might be limited to certain subsets  
    - Shane highlighted some promising prospects familiar with the company’s products, like Zanetta from E Assist, who may be valuable targets  

## **Email Campaigns and Website Engagement**

Renewed focus on email campaigns and website optimization is critical as organic engagement trends downward.

- **Website visits and email clicks are declining**, emphasizing the need to launch new ABM campaigns quickly to sustain traffic and lead flow (13:50)  
    - Historically, ABM campaigns have driven the largest share of website visits, so delays risk further traffic drops  
    - Nathalie shared updated outreach email sequences for DSOs and billing companies, awaiting Keenan’s feedback for launch  
    - January’s click data will be analyzed on January 31 to create a targeted list of prospects with 3+ clicks for lower-funnel nurture emails from Keenan  

- **Forms on the website and LinkedIn ads now require phone numbers**, improving lead quality and enabling better follow-up (14:58)  
    - This change supports more direct engagement efforts and helps prioritize leads with confirmed contact info  

## **Product and Feature Development**

Product updates focus on improving onboarding and internal task management to enhance client experience and operational efficiency.

- **Tiered onboarding feature development is complete, with pull requests merged and live updates across key website pages** (13:51)  
    - This includes guided onboarding messaging prominently placed on homepage and about page to set clear expectations  
    - Shane emphasized the team will lead launches and stay involved to ensure smooth adoption and customer success  

- **Upcoming internal tasking feature will allow team members to assign tasks within their own departments**, shifting from cross-team tasking only (17:30)  
    - Shane plans to release this within 1–2 weeks and will monitor adoption and feedback to guide further improvements  

- **Online self-signup with credit card payment is under consideration, requiring close collaboration between Shane and Keenan to set pricing and process details** (18:10)  
    - The feature will offer fixed pricing with no discounts online; volume discounts will require direct sales engagement  
    - Keenan suggested integrating scheduling so new signups can be onboarded promptly, potentially on Fridays when he is available  
    - This development is expected to take a couple of months, emphasizing the need for strategic planning  

## **Process Improvements and Operational Planning**

Operational adjustments aim to balance automation with targeted manual engagement to maximize efficiency without losing personalization.

- Keenan is experimenting with selective manual follow-ups on LinkedIn to gauge conversation quality before relying fully on automation (04:48)  
    - He plans to respond only to promising leads or those who reply, letting automated sequences handle the rest  
    - Shane recommended calling leads who fill forms but don’t answer messages, adjusting outreach timing based on time zones for better results (06:33)  

- Nathalie confirmed automated LinkedIn follow-ups continue until prospects respond, reducing Keenan’s messaging load (04:11)  
    - This system ensures persistent contact attempts without overburdening the outreach lead  
    - Keenan will review and approve updated email sequences today to accelerate campaign launches (20:50)  

## **Strategic Priorities and Next Steps**

The team is aligned on prioritizing lead nurturing via ABM campaigns and developing scalable onboarding and signup features to drive growth.

- Rapid approval and deployment of updated outreach emails is essential to reverse declining website traffic and maintain pipeline velocity (13:50)  
    - Keenan has time today to review sequences and will coordinate with Shane to finalize launch timing (20:50)  

- Product leadership sees online self-registration as a strategic growth lever but stresses the need to set clear pricing and onboarding workflows first (18:10)  
    - Close collaboration between Keenan and Shane is planned to define process and timeline for this multi-month development  

- Internal tasking improvements will enhance team efficiency and accountability, with initial rollout planned within the next two weeks (17:30)  
    - Monitoring adoption and feedback will inform further refinements to support operational scale  

- The team is leveraging detailed LinkedIn engagement data and website analytics to continuously refine targeting and messaging strategies for DSOs and billing organizations (08:29)  
    - Focusing on leads with multiple website interactions aims to improve conversion rates and sales efficiency by prioritizing warmer prospects',
  '2026-01-29 13:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Review updated outreach email sequences for DSOs and billing companies and provide feedback (07:58)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up with LinkedIn contacts who have responded and selectively engage others based on role and company fit (13:37)","completed":false},{"text":"Conduct early morning calls to leads who submitted forms but have not responded to messages, taking into account their possible time zones (06:33)","completed":false},{"text":"Investigate the discrepancy in LinkedIn reply rates compared to actual message replies seen (09:14)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Shane to strategize the upcoming online sign-up feature, deciding on pricing and onboarding support implications (18:23)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and approve email outreach sequences immediately after the meeting to enable campaign launch (20:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Send Keenan the updated outreach sequences after the meeting for review (15:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Prioritize launching new ABM email campaigns once the sequences are approved (13:58)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide Keenan with a list of people with three or more website clicks for January analysis, to be used in lower funnel nurturing (08:29)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up on LinkedIn ads and website form updates requiring phone numbers to improve lead quality (14:58)","completed":false},{"text":"Merge marketing updates and pull requests related to website and onboarding content (14:52)","completed":false},{"text":"Discuss online sign-up pricing and registration workflows with Keenan post-meeting (18:23)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor reception of the new internal tasking feature after launch and measure usage for billing and office teams separately (17:26)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
