-- Meeting: Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting (2026-01-30 17:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'bf57e936-b322-4b36-bf32-174d44c65e09',
    '2026-01-30 17:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFX1YFVPTDQ0YF278D89NADB',
    'Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Baylee Gunnell","Igor Zagradjanin","Gab"}'::text[],
    1776,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84418344570?pwd=Q4jwjvSlBFex6HPeIBY3JaK1RFchWb.1',
    '{"id":"01KFX1YFVPTDQ0YF278D89NADB","title":"Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Creative Refresh**\n\nThe team decided to refresh ad creatives mid-campaign to boost engagement and improve messaging clarity (10:09).\n\n- **White background creatives outperformed colored ones**, guiding the creative refresh for both ToFu and MoFu campaigns (10:39)  \n    - This choice was based on performance data showing clearer readability and stronger user response  \n    - Igor noted that ad viewers typically skim content quickly, making clarity crucial for engagement  \n    - The refreshed creatives are targeted for launch in the **second week of February** to optimize engagement leading into March  \n    - This refresh aligns with the strategy to build urgency ahead of the **March 4th enforcement deadline** for HR2808  \n\n- **Gab planned to draft updated copy ideas** for the refreshed creatives, focusing on urgency messaging (12:58)  \n    - Messaging for March will shift to enforcement status: “Is your house in order?” for mortgage lending audiences  \n    - Gab offered to collaborate with Jill to finalize copy before handing execution to the MIT team  \n    - This phased messaging supports a natural progression from awareness to enforcement readiness  \n    - The creative refresh aims to maintain momentum and improve campaign effectiveness through March  \n\n## **Content Strategy and Product Promotion**\n\nThe team outlined new content formats to support HR2808 awareness and Total IP Address product promotion (18:00).\n\n- **Baylee suggested creating a LinkedIn carousel checklist** from the HR2808 downloadable guide to tease key prep steps (18:10)  \n    - This format would start as an organic post with potential to boost if engagement is strong  \n    - The carousel will use white backgrounds consistent with the refreshed creative approach for brand cohesion  \n    - The goal is to drive guide downloads by offering bite-sized content that encourages deeper engagement  \n    - Gab committed to sharing the full ungated guide in Slack for easy access and content alignment  \n\n- **Gab introduced a new visual metaphor for the Total IP Address product** using an iceberg graphic to explain IP complexity (21:30)  \n    - The iceberg will contrast common IP misconceptions (tip) with deeper insights and solutions (below the surface)  \n    - This aims to simplify a technical concept to improve customer understanding and product appeal  \n    - Gab noted this is a departure from typical visuals, hoping it will stand out and educate marketers effectively  \n    - The design team was tasked with developing this concept, with Gab providing creative input  \n\n## **Podcast and Webinar Brand Strategy**\n\nThe team is preparing for a post-merger rebranding and clearer distinction between podcasts and webinars (24:50).\n\n- **Gab is working with her new direct supervisor to shift webinar editing and strategy** responsibilities to the MIT team (25:00)  \n    - This offloads time-consuming editing tasks from leadership to free her for strategic work  \n    - The supervisor supports differentiating the webinar content from the podcast to clarify their roles  \n    - Webinars will focus on product-heavy, exclusive content while podcasts emphasize thought leadership and brand awareness  \n    - Plans include repurposing webinar content into other formats to maximize reach and efficiency  \n\n- **A rebrand of the podcast visuals and naming is underway** due to the transition from Verisk to Active Prospect (27:30)  \n    - For now, the podcast will drop the Verisk logo and adopt a temporary “VMs” name while new branding is developed  \n    - Gab highlighted the need for clarity on whether branding will reflect Active Prospect or a division within it  \n    - The team plans a future kickoff to establish new graphics and deliverables tailored to the rebranded podcast and webinars  \n    - This transition reflects broader organizational changes and evolving brand identity post-merger  \n\n## **Operational and Technical Coordination**\n\nThe conversation covered file sharing improvements and vendor payment arrangements to support workflow efficiency (15:10).\n\n- **Baylee and Gab discussed new file upload workflows** leveraging Active Prospect’s move from Microsoft 365 to Google Drive (15:40)  \n    - A proposed workaround involves sharing upload links via Slack to bypass prior policy conflicts  \n    - This aims to accelerate asset sharing and reduce delays in creative production  \n    - Gab remains open to trying multiple approaches to ensure timely access to campaign materials  \n    - This change will support smoother collaboration as system migrations continue  \n\n- **Gab explained vendor payment challenges related to external designers** after Verisk’s decision to cut off third-party vendors (24:20)  \n    - She is exploring paying external designers through Justin’s system similar to other contractors like Mid, Dawson, and Vlad  \n    - This reflects a shift to internalize vendor payments and simplify financial processes  \n    - Baylee offered to sync with Don and Justin to clarify resource options and payment workflows  \n    - The resolution will help maintain creative capacity during the transition away from external vendors  \n\n## **Upcoming Priorities and Resource Focus**\n\nThe team agreed to deprioritize a 2025 episode compilation to concentrate on the March HR2808 launch (14:30).\n\n- **Gab recommended nixing the 2025 episodes compilation due to ongoing system migrations and resource limits** (14:33)  \n    - Focus will instead shift fully to creative development for the March enforcement campaign phase  \n    - This decision reflects pragmatic resource allocation to meet critical deadlines without overextension  \n    - Tim’s recording timeline remains flexible, with no pressure to accelerate delivery  \n    - The team will monitor progress and adjust priorities as campaign demands evolve  \n\n- **Baylee confirmed she had no new assets uploaded yet but will check and enable alternative upload methods** (15:27)  \n    - This proactive follow-up supports campaign asset flow without bottlenecks  \n    - The team remains aligned on timelines and open to iterative improvements in collaboration tools  \n    - This responsiveness helps maintain campaign momentum despite system transitions  \n    - Gab reaffirmed the intent to keep the campaign on track with fresh creatives launching mid-February  \n\n","outline":null,"keywords":["HR2808","campaign","creative refresh","LinkedIn carousels","Total IP Address","webinar branding"],"overview":"- **Creative Refresh Decision:** Mid-campaign refresh to boost engagement and clarity; new creatives launching second week of February.  \n- **Ad Performance Insight:** White backgrounds outperform colored ads for better readability; this drives creative direction for March campaigns.  \n- **Content Strategy Update:** New LinkedIn carousel from HR2808 guide planned to drive downloads; aligns with refreshed creative approach.  \n- **Podcast Rebranding Initiatives:** Temporarily renaming podcast to “VMs\"; focus on new visuals amid transition from Verisk to Active Prospect brand.  \n- **Vendor Payment Solutions:** Exploring internal payment processes for designers to maintain creative workflow amid external vendor cuts.  \n- **Resource Allocation Focus:** Deprioritizing the 2025 episode compilation to concentrate efforts on the critical March HR2808 campaign launch.","action_items":"\n**Gab Verzella**\nDraft LinkedIn paid social creative ideas for March HR2808 enforcement messaging and pass to marketing team for execution (12:00)\nUpload new creative assets using Slack link or try Google Drive folder upload to overcome portal access issues (15:30)\nShare HR2808 downloadable guide in Slack for marketing team reference to support social content development (18:40)\nCoordinate with new direct supervisor to formalize delegation of webinar editing to marketing team and continue to strategize brand differentiation between webinars and podcasts (25:30)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nCheck portal for new assets daily and share upload link for Gab to try file transfer (15:30)\nSync with Don and Justin regarding payment setup for external designers transitioning off Active Prospect (24:15)\n\n**Marketing Team (unassigned)**\nDesign ''iceberg'' style graphic explaining Total IP Address product''s technical value based on briefing from Gab and Jill (22:40)\nPlan and prepare new graphic packages and deliverables distinct for webinars and podcasts pending kickoff meeting (27:50)\n"},"duration":29.600000381469727,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"id":2,"name":"Gab"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey.","index":0,"end_time":227.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hello.","index":1,"end_time":229.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":229.28,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"How''s your Friday?","index":2,"end_time":233.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.3,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":3,"end_time":234.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":233.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":4,"end_time":235.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":234.66,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Hey, I love that we meet on Fridays.","index":5,"end_time":238.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":235.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s like, get to have a nice little chat, see all.","index":6,"end_time":243.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All the good things going on.","index":7,"end_time":244.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":243.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":8,"end_time":246.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":245.18,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I don''t know if Tim is coming.","index":9,"end_time":250.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":248.38,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I know Christina''s not.","index":10,"end_time":251.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":250.06,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"She has a doctor''s appointment.","index":11,"end_time":252.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":251.3,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I am happy to cover all the things if necessary, but.","index":12,"end_time":259.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":252.7,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":13,"end_time":259.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":259.39,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Happy Friday.","index":14,"end_time":260.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":259.59,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":260.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''ve been traveling a bunch.","index":16,"end_time":263.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How''s that been?","index":17,"end_time":263.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, just Vegas at the beginning of the month.","index":18,"end_time":269.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":264.87,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That it?","index":19,"end_time":270.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":269.51,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"What a place.","index":20,"end_time":271.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":270.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Did you get to go out and see anything?","index":21,"end_time":276.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I took a walk.","index":22,"end_time":278.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.19,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"At night.","index":23,"end_time":278.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":278.39,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"You would be surprised how, like, hard it is to find food that''s not like.","index":24,"end_time":283.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":279.43,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Like, over $40 in total for one person on the Strip.","index":25,"end_time":288.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":283.21,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Except for, like, Taco Bell or McDonald''s or whatever.","index":26,"end_time":292.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":288.45,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"One night I just, like, walked through all of the hotels up to the Bellagio, and I just, like, watched the fountain show.","index":27,"end_time":299.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":293.77,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":28,"end_time":300.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Because I had seen it during the day once before, and I was like, you know what?","index":29,"end_time":303.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":301.05,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Let me just go check it out at nighttime.","index":30,"end_time":305.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":303.93,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I went and I did that.","index":31,"end_time":306.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":305.61,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But it was fun.","index":32,"end_time":308.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":308.17,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It was fun, like, seeing everyone face to face and seeing Tim.","index":33,"end_time":313.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":308.97,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s always good to see that guy.","index":34,"end_time":315.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":313.73,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess so.","index":35,"end_time":317.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":315.17,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And were you on vacation last week?","index":36,"end_time":320.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Was I or something this week?","index":37,"end_time":323.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t even remember.","index":38,"end_time":324.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":323.89,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh, gosh.","index":39,"end_time":325.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.09,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":40,"end_time":326.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.65,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Me and some friends went up to the Pocono Mountains for a few days.","index":41,"end_time":332.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":328.13,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We came back early because of the snow, which, like, we were all bummed about.","index":42,"end_time":337.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":332.69,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But in the end, you know, we.","index":43,"end_time":340.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":337.81,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We come back and everything''s frozen.","index":44,"end_time":342.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":340.2,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s still frozen.","index":45,"end_time":343.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":342.32,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s not going to melt.","index":46,"end_time":345.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":344.12,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Temperatures are not getting higher.","index":47,"end_time":347.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.64,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s actually going to snow more in a week.","index":48,"end_time":349.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":347.52,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Is everybody just staying inside?","index":49,"end_time":352.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It was fun, though.","index":50,"end_time":353.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":353,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We went tubing.","index":51,"end_time":354.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":353.92,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh, fun.","index":52,"end_time":356.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, that''s.","index":53,"end_time":358.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ve never been tubing, so I was like, holy crap.","index":54,"end_time":360.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.04,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That''s so fun.","index":55,"end_time":363,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That was really fun because we got the 4 to 6pm slot, so it started at, like, sunset, and then they did the colorful lights one once.","index":56,"end_time":369.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":363,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It was dark.","index":57,"end_time":370.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":369.99,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh.","index":58,"end_time":372.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.99,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So we got the best of both worlds.","index":59,"end_time":373.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":372.43,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It was really fun.","index":60,"end_time":374.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Did they have those.","index":61,"end_time":375.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t know what the word is, but, like, it''ll lift you up the mountain so you don''t have to walk up.","index":62,"end_time":381.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, were you.","index":63,"end_time":382.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it was, like, a convenience.","index":64,"end_time":383.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":382.27,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"You did the good tubing.","index":65,"end_time":384.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":66,"end_time":385.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":67,"end_time":387.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":386.55,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I mean, it was like, 54 a ticket, and we were like, we''re gonna get our money''s worth.","index":68,"end_time":392.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":387.43,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We have to go up on that mountain at least five times.","index":69,"end_time":394.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":392.19,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, literally.","index":70,"end_time":396.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I did that with my family back during COVID So, like, everyone had to wear masks, but all of us were like soaked through, like within a few times going down just so our masks are like sopping wet.","index":71,"end_time":411.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":72,"end_time":413.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":412.94,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It was so fun, though, which isn''t.","index":73,"end_time":415.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":413.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"A bad problem to have.","index":74,"end_time":416.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.3,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It was really cold by the day we left.","index":75,"end_time":420.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":416.3,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It was like, nighttime was like negative one.","index":76,"end_time":424.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.46,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So it was nice to get out of there and come back.","index":77,"end_time":429.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":426.29,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, like a little one, but still very cold.","index":78,"end_time":432.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":429.33,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":79,"end_time":434.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m glad.","index":80,"end_time":435.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You gotta have a good fun, fun time.","index":81,"end_time":438.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And you two have been like on and off of vacation, right?","index":82,"end_time":443.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.77,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Like, one person''s gone, the other person stays.","index":83,"end_time":446.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":443.93,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":84,"end_time":448.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":446.17,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Well, I hope that time was good.","index":85,"end_time":450.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.18,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, I gotta go up the Pacific coast highway, so.","index":86,"end_time":456.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Gotta see the beautiful beach out there.","index":87,"end_time":458.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":456.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And it was really fun.","index":88,"end_time":459.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I love that.","index":89,"end_time":462.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":461.34,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that one there was like Shark Fin Cove.","index":90,"end_time":466.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.06,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I don''t remember where that was on the map, but it was really cool.","index":91,"end_time":470.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.98,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"There''s so many things we got this book in, like, I was like, we''re going to see 10% of this, but that''s okay.","index":92,"end_time":479.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, my gosh.","index":93,"end_time":481.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":480.2,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"What did you do, Igor?","index":94,"end_time":482.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":481.24,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, I just spent some time with my family.","index":95,"end_time":486.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":483.96,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Took a lot of rest actually.","index":96,"end_time":490.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.68,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":97,"end_time":491.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":490.52,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Enjoyed the snow because it was heavily snowing here in the beginning of January.","index":98,"end_time":495.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":491.16,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":99,"end_time":496.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":495.8,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, we haven''t had that much snow since.","index":100,"end_time":499.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":496.08,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I don''t remember when.","index":101,"end_time":501.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":499.8,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":102,"end_time":501.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.82,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s always good to relive those childhood moments when there was a lot of snow and no global warming issues.","index":103,"end_time":510.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I mean, so.","index":104,"end_time":512.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":510.46,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, it was really nice.","index":105,"end_time":513.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.26,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And when you mentioned Bellagio earlier, I just remember that.","index":106,"end_time":517.499,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":513.26,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, the only time actually I played roulette was in Bellagio.","index":107,"end_time":521.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":517.499,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I was in Las Vegas.","index":108,"end_time":522.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":521.14,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":109,"end_time":524.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.14,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":110,"end_time":525.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":524.78,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I was an exchange student in the us.","index":111,"end_time":526.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.1,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So we visited.","index":112,"end_time":530.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":529.25,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, so we visited Las Vegas.","index":113,"end_time":531.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":530.05,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And I was.","index":114,"end_time":532.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":531.89,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I knew that like, of all the casinos, I''m like, I''m not.","index":115,"end_time":535.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":532.65,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I''m don''t gamble.","index":116,"end_time":536.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":535.53,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"But like, of all the casinos, Bellagio was like the most beautiful to me because of the mountain, the fountains and everything.","index":117,"end_time":543.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":536.45,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So, yeah, we went there and just enjoyed the place, the aesthetics.","index":118,"end_time":550.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":544.29,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And I put like 20 or $25 on like a few numbers.","index":119,"end_time":558.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":551.17,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And I lost, of course, all of it.","index":120,"end_time":560.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.33,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I mean, that''s fine.","index":121,"end_time":562.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":561.53,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"But the feeling, it was just.","index":122,"end_time":564.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562.77,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, I was like, take me out from here.","index":123,"end_time":567.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":564.81,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I mean, after a couple days, I''m just kind of like, okay, it is a hike to get anywhere.","index":124,"end_time":574.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569.13,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I just want to stay in my room.","index":125,"end_time":576.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.89,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s quiet here.","index":126,"end_time":578.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":577.69,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I actually have been to Vegas like three times now and haven''t gambled.","index":127,"end_time":583.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":580.33,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''ve never gambled, so.","index":128,"end_time":584.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":583.69,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I don''t know.","index":129,"end_time":587.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":585.12,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''m just like, I don''t have enough money to enjoy this.","index":130,"end_time":590.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.04,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, definitely.","index":131,"end_time":594.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":591.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, then let''s go straight away into the.","index":132,"end_time":603.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":596,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s do it.","index":133,"end_time":605.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":604.08,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I guess Tim was like, she can handle it.","index":134,"end_time":607.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":605.28,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s fine.","index":135,"end_time":609,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":607.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know I can trust.","index":136,"end_time":610.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So we''ll go through delivered work, work in progress and some of the things we are actually one thing we are waiting on.","index":137,"end_time":622.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then the campaign and yes.","index":138,"end_time":627,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":622.04,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So so far we delivered in January, distributed actually two episodes and then the LinkedIn carousels for episode Pat Sullivan.","index":139,"end_time":641.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":627.72,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And this is something.","index":140,"end_time":642.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":641.51,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":141,"end_time":643.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":642.71,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That we can do in the future if you.","index":142,"end_time":645.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":643.07,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"If you like this one.","index":143,"end_time":646.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":645.47,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"This is definitely something that we enjoyed doing.","index":144,"end_time":649.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":647.35,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, we like the carousels, especially for those info heavy episodes.","index":145,"end_time":655.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":650.79,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Great.","index":146,"end_time":658.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":658.07,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Then what we''re working on now is the thought leadership blog post from episode Pat Sullivan and also the image ad creative packages.","index":147,"end_time":669.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":659.67,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"In our last meeting.","index":148,"end_time":671.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":670.67,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I don''t know if Christina told you so we basically had a little report for her.","index":149,"end_time":678.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.55,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then in basically we.","index":150,"end_time":681.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":678.79,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We figured that right now because it''s like the middle of the campaign, it would be good to refresh the creatives so both the copy and the.","index":151,"end_time":693.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":681.31,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The visuals, the white creatives showed better performance.","index":152,"end_time":697.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":693.67,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So we''ll go for the white ones.","index":153,"end_time":700.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":698.31,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"All of those will.","index":154,"end_time":701.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":700.55,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Will be the white ones.","index":155,"end_time":703.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":701.75,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And we''ll do this for both the Tofu and Mofou campaigns.","index":156,"end_time":709.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":703.15,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, she did send me over that report.","index":157,"end_time":711.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":709.67,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It was very thorough.","index":158,"end_time":712.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":711.91,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I appreciate that.","index":159,"end_time":713.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":712.87,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Thanks to the folks on your team.","index":160,"end_time":715.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":714.23,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, no, this is great.","index":161,"end_time":719.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":717.91,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And it''s relevant because we actually met about kind of like phase 2B of HR2808.","index":162,"end_time":728.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":719.43,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Because right now it''s kind of like we''re building up awareness to that March 4th enforcement deadline.","index":163,"end_time":735.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":728.5,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Like that''s when the government will start enforcing the actual law.","index":164,"end_time":738.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":735.5,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And we were discussing ideas for copy and also creative for that in a paid social aspect.","index":165,"end_time":748.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.54,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I think what I''ll do is I''m gonna draft some ideas for paid social creative specifically for LinkedIn.","index":166,"end_time":758.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":748.75,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So pretty much just replicating what we''ve done so far.","index":167,"end_time":761.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.79,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But the messaging is gonna change when we launch in March.","index":168,"end_time":765.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":762.67,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So instead of it being like this is coming, it''s gonna be more like enforcement is now is your house in order.","index":169,"end_time":772.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":766.35,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That kind of imagery of mortgage lending that.","index":170,"end_time":776.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":774.08,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, so we''re gonna.","index":171,"end_time":778.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":776.88,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''ll draft some ideas, but I would like to pass it off to the mid team to execute on that as well.","index":172,"end_time":784.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.44,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Of course.","index":173,"end_time":786.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.84,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So these are for March if I. Yeah, okay, great.","index":174,"end_time":792.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":787.04,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Of course.","index":175,"end_time":794.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":793.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And what about the.","index":176,"end_time":796.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":794.72,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The These that we are working on right now?","index":177,"end_time":799.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":796.4,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Do you have any ideas or suggestions on the copy for those?","index":178,"end_time":803.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":799.04,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I can draft some ideas.","index":179,"end_time":806.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.55,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Unless, you know, I.","index":180,"end_time":808.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":806.87,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"You know what, maybe m. Take a first stab of how you would approach refreshing, and then I can bring it to Jill and we can confirm.","index":181,"end_time":815.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":808.11,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Didn''t I add other ideas and suggestions?","index":182,"end_time":819.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":815.99,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So that''s fine.","index":183,"end_time":820.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":819.11,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And I think that the refreshed creative copy and assets visually can launch probably, like, the second week of February and see how it performs throughout that month.","index":184,"end_time":832.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":820.19,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then in March, we will start fresh with a new direction for enforcement.","index":185,"end_time":840.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":834.21,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":186,"end_time":841.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.09,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":187,"end_time":842.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.65,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Then we''ll do something like maybe the law is approaching.","index":188,"end_time":845.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":842.05,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s coming in less than a month.","index":189,"end_time":847.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":845.97,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Something like the urgency stuff.","index":190,"end_time":849.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":847.65,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":191,"end_time":850.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":849.73,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Definitely urgency at this stage when we relaunch the refreshed creative.","index":192,"end_time":855.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":850.73,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Cool.","index":193,"end_time":856.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.54,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":194,"end_time":857.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":857.26,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":195,"end_time":860.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":859.66,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then.","index":196,"end_time":862.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.5,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yes.","index":197,"end_time":863.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.7,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Still waiting for this for Tim to record.","index":198,"end_time":867.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":864.54,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Let''s not force it.","index":199,"end_time":869.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":868.38,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"He can take his time.","index":200,"end_time":871.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.74,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Is this in reference to the 2025 compilation of episodes?","index":201,"end_time":878.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":873.66,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yep.","index":202,"end_time":879.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":879.34,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I think at this point we can nix it.","index":203,"end_time":882.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":880.54,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":204,"end_time":883.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":883.44,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And also just because of everything going on with our migration into, like, our new systems with active prospect, that''s kind of all happening behind the scenes as we keep on keeping on.","index":205,"end_time":895.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":883.84,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I don''t think he''s gonna get to it.","index":206,"end_time":898.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":896.96,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''m just being honest.","index":207,"end_time":899.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":898.56,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And I''d rather put the points toward maybe more creative for the.","index":208,"end_time":904.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":900.4,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"For the March HR 2808 launch.","index":209,"end_time":908.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":904.4,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Mm.","index":210,"end_time":910.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":910.03,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":211,"end_time":911.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":910.51,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"All right, then.","index":212,"end_time":916.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":912.59,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"This is obviously the upcoming priority.","index":213,"end_time":919.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":916.67,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So when we received the assets.","index":214,"end_time":923.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":921.07,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Bailey, did this go through or.","index":215,"end_time":926.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":923.67,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I finally was able to log in to that portal, but I haven''t seen the new assets yet.","index":216,"end_time":933.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, interesting.","index":217,"end_time":935.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":934.59,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":218,"end_time":936.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":936.46,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I haven''t checked today, though, so I can check really quick.","index":219,"end_time":939.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sure.","index":220,"end_time":940.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.14,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And just something I was thinking about is, with ActiveProspect, we''re moving from Microsoft 365 into Google, so maybe now we won''t come up against so many barriers with uploading to a Google Drive folder.","index":221,"end_time":959.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.86,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I will give that a try and try to share it with you, but let''s see if I can even do it first.","index":222,"end_time":966.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":959.42,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Can we give you a link?","index":223,"end_time":968.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":967.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, if we gave you a link to upload it to, would that be a workaround?","index":224,"end_time":972.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":968.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We could try.","index":225,"end_time":973.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":973.27,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''m open to trying anything and everything.","index":226,"end_time":976.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":974.07,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, it will.","index":227,"end_time":978.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":228,"end_time":979.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If that''s, like, less of a conflict with, like, policies, we can just give you a link and have you upload, and then our.","index":229,"end_time":986.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":979.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Our team will already have access to everything.","index":230,"end_time":988.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So yeah, I''m not seeing anything new in there.","index":231,"end_time":992.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":989.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":232,"end_time":994.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":993.6,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s give it a shot.","index":233,"end_time":997.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":996.16,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"If you want to put a link in the Slack channel, I can throw the file, I can try to throw the files in there.","index":234,"end_time":1003.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":997.4,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":235,"end_time":1004.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1004,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And if not, I can then go back and try my Google theory.","index":236,"end_time":1008.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1005.36,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But we''ll see.","index":237,"end_time":1009.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1008.52,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay, we''ll try.","index":238,"end_time":1012.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1010.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":239,"end_time":1016.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1015.33,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yes.","index":240,"end_time":1018.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.97,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I already basically covered this.","index":241,"end_time":1020.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1018.41,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So we are refreshing the creatives to land better messaging and get more engagements.","index":242,"end_time":1026.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1020.77,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And the white background creatives were performing better and they will guide the optimizations.","index":243,"end_time":1034.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1027.25,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yep.","index":244,"end_time":1036.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1035.89,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":245,"end_time":1037.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1037.09,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It was interesting.","index":246,"end_time":1038.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1037.61,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"The white backgrounds were performing better.","index":247,"end_time":1040.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1038.37,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I just, I didn''t know, I guess from a design standpoint that people would have a, a draw to one or the other, but here we are.","index":248,"end_time":1049.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1040.37,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That''s how, that''s how creative works.","index":249,"end_time":1050.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1049.51,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":250,"end_time":1052.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1050.99,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Honestly, I, I prefer the like the LinkedIn carousels and everything that, because yeah, we do have two colors for, for Verisk.","index":251,"end_time":1061.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1052.95,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I, I, I like the blue one better, but I guess the white one is like more clear in terms of like when you read stuff on it.","index":252,"end_time":1071.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1062.07,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":253,"end_time":1072.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1072.08,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then since, since ads are just a quick skim through for most of people.","index":254,"end_time":1078.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1072.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So, yeah, I guess that''s the reason why.","index":255,"end_time":1080.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1078.64,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And also we wanted to ask you if you have any more ideas for February on, on content assets.","index":256,"end_time":1090.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1081.84,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, I had taken up with, Yeah.","index":257,"end_time":1094.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1091.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I had two design ideas.","index":258,"end_time":1096.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1094.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So beyond.","index":259,"end_time":1099.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1097.07,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Well, we can start with HR2808.","index":260,"end_time":1102.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1099.95,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So the, the blog that we launched for the current phase of that campaign has like that downloadable guide and I thought just another way to promote it on social.","index":261,"end_time":1115.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1102.19,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I would love to maybe take some of the points from that and just tease a checklist on LinkedIn.","index":262,"end_time":1121.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.79,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So like a carousel graphic that we can go with the white background.","index":263,"end_time":1126.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1122.05,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''m cool with that.","index":264,"end_time":1127.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1126.69,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But literally having some like check boxes on the first slide, that''s like maybe the first three suggestions or maybe the first two from that guide.","index":265,"end_time":1138.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1128.69,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then that last slide, something you''ve done in the past for us is like check out the, download the guide to get the full list of how you need to prepare something like that.","index":266,"end_time":1149.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1138.85,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh, that''s a great idea.","index":267,"end_time":1152.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1150.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So are you thinking to include that in like the paid stuff we''re doing right now or just organic or both?","index":268,"end_time":1159.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1152.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I, I was open to it.","index":269,"end_time":1161.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1159.5,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I mean I was like, in terms of like a paid ad, what people see, you know, is it, are they looking at it so quickly and then kind of just moving on or I thought that format would be good just as like a social post to start and then maybe if it.","index":270,"end_time":1177.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1161.38,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"If it gains traction, we could just boost it individually as opposed to, like putting it within a campaign structure.","index":271,"end_time":1184.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1177.94,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, so that was an idea I had.","index":272,"end_time":1186.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1184.34,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And I can put the guide into our Slack channel so that you just have access to it.","index":273,"end_time":1193.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1186.94,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"The full ungated thing.","index":274,"end_time":1195.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1193.7,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Is it the same one from a couple months ago or is this a new one?","index":275,"end_time":1200.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1196.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It should be the.","index":276,"end_time":1201.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1200.51,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I think we should have it Prospecting Beyond HR 2808 guide.","index":277,"end_time":1207.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1201.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I think we had it, but we can double check and I can always.","index":278,"end_time":1212.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1207.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Throw it back in there.","index":279,"end_time":1213.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1212.15,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"You just let me know.","index":280,"end_time":1214.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1213.19,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, we can look and see.","index":281,"end_time":1218.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1216.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":282,"end_time":1221.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1220.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that''s HR 2808.","index":283,"end_time":1224.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1222.99,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That''s kind of been our.","index":284,"end_time":1225.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1224.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Our world a little bit.","index":285,"end_time":1228.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1227.03,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then we''re also working on just promoting more about our Total IP address product.","index":286,"end_time":1234.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1228.47,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So, I mean, just from a basic level, like there, everyone has an IP address when they engage with something online.","index":287,"end_time":1243.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1236.95,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We know that, but, you know, between remote work, hybrid work, like shared apartment buildings, things like that, it can be hard to associate one I IP address with one person.","index":288,"end_time":1254.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1243.43,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And so this product helps marketers get more granular with who is actually engaging from what address.","index":289,"end_time":1263.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1256.34,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh, that''s super interesting.","index":290,"end_time":1266.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1264.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s the best way that I can put it, like, getting into the technical stuff, but that is the idea behind it is like, clarity of knowing who is engaging from what address.","index":291,"end_time":1279.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1267.3,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And Jill, I was literally just talking.","index":292,"end_time":1283.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1281.58,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"About that this morning.","index":293,"end_time":1284.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, that''s so cool.","index":294,"end_time":1286.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1284.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And people think that, you know, the debate, I guess, within the space, is our IP addresses stable enough as like a.","index":295,"end_time":1294.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1286.54,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"A metric that you would want to watch.","index":296,"end_time":1296.379,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1294.7,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Some people say yes, some people say no.","index":297,"end_time":1299.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1297.42,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I think we kind of sit in the.","index":298,"end_time":1301.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1299.82,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It depends and we can help you actually make it work and feel stable.","index":299,"end_time":1305.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1301.42,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Um, so that''s the product.","index":300,"end_time":1308.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1305.9,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But, Jill, I.","index":301,"end_time":1310.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1308.46,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And you know what?","index":302,"end_time":1310.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1310.02,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"The whole world was on a Stranger Things kick.","index":303,"end_time":1312.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1310.7,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And her idea was kind of like, you know, there''s.","index":304,"end_time":1318.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1313.74,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"There''s our world, like the reality or like the.","index":305,"end_time":1321.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1318.54,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"What we perceive to be true about IP addresses.","index":306,"end_time":1324.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1321.739,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then the upside down is like, there is way more to it than you think you can actually make it stable, blah, blah, blah.","index":307,"end_time":1330.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1324.26,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And I said, well, we kind of missed the Stranger Things boat.","index":308,"end_time":1334.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1330.9,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"The show ended like a month ago.","index":309,"end_time":1339.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1336.16,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And instead I, we could.","index":310,"end_time":1342.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1340.96,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I, I suggested maybe we fall back on the iceberg image of like.","index":311,"end_time":1347.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1342.88,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We''ve all seen the iceberg image of like, yeah, here''s the surface of the water, here''s the tip of the iceberg, which is like, what you know about IP addresses.","index":312,"end_time":1355.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1347.919,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then here''s Below of like all that you could be doing and like, things to think about with IP addresses.","index":313,"end_time":1361.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1356.16,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":314,"end_time":1362.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1362.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So she really liked that idea and I said I would pass it off to this team to design something like that.","index":315,"end_time":1370.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1363.67,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And just visually in my mind, I''m trying to work out the concept like words wise.","index":316,"end_time":1379.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1372.55,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''m thinking like a graphic that has the question over the top of like, this is totally off the top of my head, by the way, but what do you think you know about IP addresses?","index":317,"end_time":1392.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1380.79,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then tip of the iceberg has like resting IPs unstable.","index":318,"end_time":1397.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1392.44,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":319,"end_time":1397.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1397.32,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then the bottom is like household level IP resolution.","index":320,"end_time":1403.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1398.04,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"All the ways that you can solve to make it better, essentially.","index":321,"end_time":1407.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1404.2,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"What are exactly those terms?","index":322,"end_time":1409.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1408.2,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''m not sure yet, but I just wanted to run the idea by you guys and see if that''s something you could design for us.","index":323,"end_time":1417.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1410.37,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Always.","index":324,"end_time":1418.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1418.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":325,"end_time":1419.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1419.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I love that idea.","index":326,"end_time":1420.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1419.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''ll be a really cool visual.","index":327,"end_time":1422.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1420.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s just different for us.","index":328,"end_time":1424.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1422.85,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We don''t really use a lot of like, interesting visual metaphors, I guess.","index":329,"end_time":1431.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1424.13,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":330,"end_time":1431.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1431.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I think it would actually help people understand the problem more of what they come up against with that particular metric or data point.","index":331,"end_time":1441.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1431.97,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Definitely.","index":332,"end_time":1443.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1443.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then this is maybe a little off topic, but I think Don had reached out to Justin about how you''re transferring off Active Prospect.","index":333,"end_time":1454.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1444.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Did Don talk to you at all?","index":334,"end_time":1456.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1455.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think he was wanting cope with like some resources.","index":335,"end_time":1460.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1456.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I was a little confused.","index":336,"end_time":1461.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1460.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So what happened was we have a designer.","index":337,"end_time":1466.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1462.42,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Maybe it''s two of them.","index":338,"end_time":1468.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1466.9,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Actually, I''m not sure what he said to Justin, but we have two designers that were getting paid through Beeline.","index":339,"end_time":1474.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1468.06,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I don''t really know the system, but Varys decided to just completely cut off like our external third party designers.","index":340,"end_time":1483.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1475.3,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"They''re individual vendors.","index":341,"end_time":1484.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1483.38,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"They''re not like companies.","index":342,"end_time":1485.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1484.58,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":343,"end_time":1486.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1485.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And so he was like, you know what, let me, you know, gab, do you think that we can do what we did with Brian, with Mid, with Dawson and Vlad?","index":344,"end_time":1497.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1487.38,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I said, you know, maybe I would reach out to Justin and float it, see if that''s a possibility.","index":345,"end_time":1503.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1497.75,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"If, you know, they could get paid that way.","index":346,"end_time":1507.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1503.91,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''m really not sure how it''s set up, but I think that''s what he''s asking for help with.","index":347,"end_time":1512.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1507.59,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":348,"end_time":1513.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1513.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So there''s that.","index":349,"end_time":1515.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1514.23,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I also just did want to mention I spoke with who I think will be my new direct supervisor yesterday.","index":350,"end_time":1521.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1515.03,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"She''s really great and she is totally on board with, you know, bringing the relationship over into Active Prospect.","index":351,"end_time":1529.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1521.27,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And I told her like, I manage the relationship for the most part.","index":352,"end_time":1533.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1529.95,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I really like, working with their team, and we can offload some of her kind of duties onto the MIT team.","index":353,"end_time":1540.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1533.03,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So, for example, she is the person and she''s director of, like, brand marketing and stuff like that.","index":354,"end_time":1548.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1541.23,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So she.","index":355,"end_time":1549.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1548.92,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And for the whole organization, yet she''s the one who is editing every single webinar that they do.","index":356,"end_time":1555.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1549.44,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh, my goodness.","index":357,"end_time":1556.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1555.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s just kind of a time suck for her when she could be obviously, like, being strategic somewhere else or, you know, ideating with the team.","index":358,"end_time":1565.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1556.92,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I said, that is a great example of what we could offload to Bailey and the mid team.","index":359,"end_time":1572.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1566.2,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And.","index":360,"end_time":1573.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1572.76,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And with that, I was like, we need to start thinking about how we''re differentiating the webinar stuff that we do from the podcast that we do.","index":361,"end_time":1583.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1573.42,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I think they do two totally different things, and I think it can absolutely work.","index":362,"end_time":1588.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1584.14,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But with webinars, I''m thinking less is more, making them feel more exclusive because they''re so product heavy and, you know, repurposing those webinars into different types of content that aren''t video.","index":363,"end_time":1603.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1589.82,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Whereas TMR is definitely more thought leadership, brand awareness.","index":364,"end_time":1608.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1604.79,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Like, Tim is the face of our business unit.","index":365,"end_time":1613.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1608.23,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I think they do totally different things.","index":366,"end_time":1615.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1613.27,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I think they can coexist.","index":367,"end_time":1616.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1615.55,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And I floated all of these ideas to her and she''s on board, so.","index":368,"end_time":1621.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1617.11,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Love it.","index":369,"end_time":1622.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1621.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, love it.","index":370,"end_time":1623.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1622.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think, yeah.","index":371,"end_time":1624.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1623.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Whenever, like, the time''s right, we can maybe have a kickoff with her and then do like, a new graphics package, so, like, new designs, all for webinars and figure out what some deliverables would be for that.","index":372,"end_time":1636.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1624.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cause it''s probably a bit different than a podcast, like you said.","index":373,"end_time":1639.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1636.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":374,"end_time":1640.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1640.24,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And we''re gonna have to totally rebrand the podcast as well.","index":375,"end_time":1643.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1640.88,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I think we keep the name, obviously.","index":376,"end_time":1646,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1643.96,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But I''m wondering, like, is this Active Prospect branding?","index":377,"end_time":1651.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1647.6,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Is it branding that we''re coming up with for our division within Active Prospect?","index":378,"end_time":1657.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1651.68,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":379,"end_time":1658.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1657.58,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So lots of conversations to.","index":380,"end_time":1661.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1659.02,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"To be had.","index":381,"end_time":1662.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1661.74,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":382,"end_time":1663.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But for now, the direction I''ve been given is just keep on keeping on until we tell you otherwise.","index":383,"end_time":1670.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1664.62,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":384,"end_time":1671.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1670.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So really what we''re doing is just removing the Verisk logo from our podcast, from our visual assets for the podcast, and for now, we''re referring to ourselves as VMs.","index":385,"end_time":1683.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1671.34,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"What does it mean?","index":386,"end_time":1684.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1683.98,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":387,"end_time":1685.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1684.82,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I don''t think anyone does, but they''re.","index":388,"end_time":1688.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1685.74,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"They''re actually working on naming right now, so hopefully I have more answers soon.","index":389,"end_time":1693.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1688.02,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":390,"end_time":1694.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1693.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds good.","index":391,"end_time":1697.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1696.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m happy to sync with dawn too, if that''s helpful, to figure out a plan to to figure out.","index":392,"end_time":1707.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1699.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we can probably do something with your.","index":393,"end_time":1709.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1707.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Your other designers there and.","index":394,"end_time":1711.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1709.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, just lots of.","index":395,"end_time":1713.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1711.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Lots of stuff to look forward to.","index":396,"end_time":1714.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1713.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":397,"end_time":1716.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1715.27,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Definitely more work to come.","index":398,"end_time":1718.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1716.67,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We''re gonna be cranking I. I bet within the next couple weeks, so.","index":399,"end_time":1723.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1718.07,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, keep on keeping on.","index":400,"end_time":1725.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1723.51,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Love it.","index":401,"end_time":1726.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1725.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":402,"end_time":1729.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1728.95,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":403,"end_time":1730.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1729.67,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":404,"end_time":1731.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1731.35,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That''s everything I had.","index":405,"end_time":1732.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1731.75,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Are you guys set?","index":406,"end_time":1733.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1732.75,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":407,"end_time":1735.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1735.11,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"This is my only meeting today, and I am refraining from work for the rest of the day, so.","index":408,"end_time":1741.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1736.15,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":409,"end_time":1742.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1741.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I hope you guys have a great rest of your day and a great weekend.","index":410,"end_time":1747.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1743.35,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"You too.","index":411,"end_time":1748.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1747.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll see you.","index":412,"end_time":1748.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1748.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right.","index":413,"end_time":1749.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1748.99,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Bye.","index":414,"end_time":1749.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1749.51,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Thanks, everyone.","index":415,"end_time":1750.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1749.91,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Bye.","index":416,"end_time":1751.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1750.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2026-01-30T17:30:00.000Z","host_email":"igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84418344570?pwd=Q4jwjvSlBFex6HPeIBY3JaK1RFchWb.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com,gabrielle.verzella@verisk.com,tim.finnigan@verisk.com,christina.bila@verisk.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","gabrielle.verzella@verisk.com","tim.finnigan@verisk.com","christina.bila@verisk.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFX1YFVPTDQ0YF278D89NADB","organizer_email":"igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Finalized campaign direction for HR2808 with March 4th enforcement messaging and urgent tone.","Confirmed white background creatives outperform and will guide updated Tofu and Mofou ads.","Gab proposed downloadable checklist and iceberg visuals as fresh February content formats.","Webinar editing tasks to shift from brand lead to Mid team under new supervisory alignment.","Plan to offload design work for former Beeline vendors via Mid team is under review."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I''d rather put the points toward maybe more creative for the March HR 2808 launch.","speaker":"Gab"},{"quote":"Whenever, like, the time''s right, we can maybe have a kickoff with her and then do like, a new graphics package.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"So I said, that is a great example of what we could offload to Bailey and the mid team.","speaker":"Gab"}],"topics":["campaign","creative","delivery","handoff","branding","transition"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-0613","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-30T22:48:55Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Creative Refresh**\n\nThe team decided to refresh ad creatives mid-campaign to boost engagement and improve messaging clarity (10:09).\n\n- **White background creatives outperformed colored ones**, guiding the creative refresh for both ToFu and MoFu campaigns (10:39)  \n    - This choice was based on performance data showing clearer readability and stronger user response  \n    - Igor noted that ad viewers typically skim content quickly, making clarity crucial for engagement  \n    - The refreshed creatives are targeted for launch in the **second week of February** to optimize engagement leading into March  \n    - This refresh aligns with the strategy to build urgency ahead of the **March 4th enforcement deadline** for HR2808  \n\n- **Gab planned to draft updated copy ideas** for the refreshed creatives, focusing on urgency messaging (12:58)  \n    - Messaging for March will shift to enforcement status: “Is your house in order?” for mortgage lending audiences  \n    - Gab offered to collaborate with Jill to finalize copy before handing execution to the MIT team  \n    - This phased messaging supports a natural progression from awareness to enforcement readiness  \n    - The creative refresh aims to maintain momentum and improve campaign effectiveness through March  \n\n## **Content Strategy and Product Promotion**\n\nThe team outlined new content formats to support HR2808 awareness and Total IP Address product promotion (18:00).\n\n- **Baylee suggested creating a LinkedIn carousel checklist** from the HR2808 downloadable guide to tease key prep steps (18:10)  \n    - This format would start as an organic post with potential to boost if engagement is strong  \n    - The carousel will use white backgrounds consistent with the refreshed creative approach for brand cohesion  \n    - The goal is to drive guide downloads by offering bite-sized content that encourages deeper engagement  \n    - Gab committed to sharing the full ungated guide in Slack for easy access and content alignment  \n\n- **Gab introduced a new visual metaphor for the Total IP Address product** using an iceberg graphic to explain IP complexity (21:30)  \n    - The iceberg will contrast common IP misconceptions (tip) with deeper insights and solutions (below the surface)  \n    - This aims to simplify a technical concept to improve customer understanding and product appeal  \n    - Gab noted this is a departure from typical visuals, hoping it will stand out and educate marketers effectively  \n    - The design team was tasked with developing this concept, with Gab providing creative input  \n\n## **Podcast and Webinar Brand Strategy**\n\nThe team is preparing for a post-merger rebranding and clearer distinction between podcasts and webinars (24:50).\n\n- **Gab is working with her new direct supervisor to shift webinar editing and strategy** responsibilities to the MIT team (25:00)  \n    - This offloads time-consuming editing tasks from leadership to free her for strategic work  \n    - The supervisor supports differentiating the webinar content from the podcast to clarify their roles  \n    - Webinars will focus on product-heavy, exclusive content while podcasts emphasize thought leadership and brand awareness  \n    - Plans include repurposing webinar content into other formats to maximize reach and efficiency  \n\n- **A rebrand of the podcast visuals and naming is underway** due to the transition from Verisk to Active Prospect (27:30)  \n    - For now, the podcast will drop the Verisk logo and adopt a temporary “VMs” name while new branding is developed  \n    - Gab highlighted the need for clarity on whether branding will reflect Active Prospect or a division within it  \n    - The team plans a future kickoff to establish new graphics and deliverables tailored to the rebranded podcast and webinars  \n    - This transition reflects broader organizational changes and evolving brand identity post-merger  \n\n## **Operational and Technical Coordination**\n\nThe conversation covered file sharing improvements and vendor payment arrangements to support workflow efficiency (15:10).\n\n- **Baylee and Gab discussed new file upload workflows** leveraging Active Prospect’s move from Microsoft 365 to Google Drive (15:40)  \n    - A proposed workaround involves sharing upload links via Slack to bypass prior policy conflicts  \n    - This aims to accelerate asset sharing and reduce delays in creative production  \n    - Gab remains open to trying multiple approaches to ensure timely access to campaign materials  \n    - This change will support smoother collaboration as system migrations continue  \n\n- **Gab explained vendor payment challenges related to external designers** after Verisk’s decision to cut off third-party vendors (24:20)  \n    - She is exploring paying external designers through Justin’s system similar to other contractors like Mid, Dawson, and Vlad  \n    - This reflects a shift to internalize vendor payments and simplify financial processes  \n    - Baylee offered to sync with Don and Justin to clarify resource options and payment workflows  \n    - The resolution will help maintain creative capacity during the transition away from external vendors  \n\n## **Upcoming Priorities and Resource Focus**\n\nThe team agreed to deprioritize a 2025 episode compilation to concentrate on the March HR2808 launch (14:30).\n\n- **Gab recommended nixing the 2025 episodes compilation due to ongoing system migrations and resource limits** (14:33)  \n    - Focus will instead shift fully to creative development for the March enforcement campaign phase  \n    - This decision reflects pragmatic resource allocation to meet critical deadlines without overextension  \n    - Tim’s recording timeline remains flexible, with no pressure to accelerate delivery  \n    - The team will monitor progress and adjust priorities as campaign demands evolve  \n\n- **Baylee confirmed she had no new assets uploaded yet but will check and enable alternative upload methods** (15:27)  \n    - This proactive follow-up supports campaign asset flow without bottlenecks  \n    - The team remains aligned on timelines and open to iterative improvements in collaboration tools  \n    - This responsiveness helps maintain campaign momentum despite system transitions  \n    - Gab reaffirmed the intent to keep the campaign on track with fresh creatives launching mid-February  \n\n","outline":null,"keywords":["HR2808","campaign","creative refresh","LinkedIn carousels","Total IP Address","webinar branding"],"overview":"- **Creative Refresh Decision:** Mid-campaign refresh to boost engagement and clarity; new creatives launching second week of February.  \n- **Ad Performance Insight:** White backgrounds outperform colored ads for better readability; this drives creative direction for March campaigns.  \n- **Content Strategy Update:** New LinkedIn carousel from HR2808 guide planned to drive downloads; aligns with refreshed creative approach.  \n- **Podcast Rebranding Initiatives:** Temporarily renaming podcast to “VMs\"; focus on new visuals amid transition from Verisk to Active Prospect brand.  \n- **Vendor Payment Solutions:** Exploring internal payment processes for designers to maintain creative workflow amid external vendor cuts.  \n- **Resource Allocation Focus:** Deprioritizing the 2025 episode compilation to concentrate efforts on the critical March HR2808 campaign launch.","action_items":"\n**Gab Verzella**\nDraft LinkedIn paid social creative ideas for March HR2808 enforcement messaging and pass to marketing team for execution (12:00)\nUpload new creative assets using Slack link or try Google Drive folder upload to overcome portal access issues (15:30)\nShare HR2808 downloadable guide in Slack for marketing team reference to support social content development (18:40)\nCoordinate with new direct supervisor to formalize delegation of webinar editing to marketing team and continue to strategize brand differentiation between webinars and podcasts (25:30)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nCheck portal for new assets daily and share upload link for Gab to try file transfer (15:30)\nSync with Don and Justin regarding payment setup for external designers transitioning off Active Prospect (24:15)\n\n**Marketing Team (unassigned)**\nDesign ''iceberg'' style graphic explaining Total IP Address product''s technical value based on briefing from Gab and Jill (22:40)\nPlan and prepare new graphic packages and deliverables distinct for webinars and podcasts pending kickoff meeting (27:50)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"c0db8ce1-1ef6-44f2-882f-e10300840885","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
