INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Campaign Performance and Creative Refresh**

The team decided to refresh ad creatives mid-campaign to boost engagement and improve messaging clarity (10:09).

- **White background creatives outperformed colored ones**, guiding the creative refresh for both ToFu and MoFu campaigns (10:39)  
    - This choice was based on performance data showing clearer readability and stronger user response  
    - Igor noted that ad viewers typically skim content quickly, making clarity crucial for engagement  
    - The refreshed creatives are targeted for launch in the **second week of February** to optimize engagement leading into March  
    - This refresh aligns with the strategy to build urgency ahead of the **March 4th enforcement deadline** for HR2808  

- **Gab planned to draft updated copy ideas** for the refreshed creatives, focusing on urgency messaging (12:58)  
    - Messaging for March will shift to enforcement status: “Is your house in order?” for mortgage lending audiences  
    - Gab offered to collaborate with Jill to finalize copy before handing execution to the MIT team  
    - This phased messaging supports a natural progression from awareness to enforcement readiness  
    - The creative refresh aims to maintain momentum and improve campaign effectiveness through March  

## **Content Strategy and Product Promotion**

The team outlined new content formats to support HR2808 awareness and Total IP Address product promotion (18:00).

- **Baylee suggested creating a LinkedIn carousel checklist** from the HR2808 downloadable guide to tease key prep steps (18:10)  
    - This format would start as an organic post with potential to boost if engagement is strong  
    - The carousel will use white backgrounds consistent with the refreshed creative approach for brand cohesion  
    - The goal is to drive guide downloads by offering bite-sized content that encourages deeper engagement  
    - Gab committed to sharing the full ungated guide in Slack for easy access and content alignment  

- **Gab introduced a new visual metaphor for the Total IP Address product** using an iceberg graphic to explain IP complexity (21:30)  
    - The iceberg will contrast common IP misconceptions (tip) with deeper insights and solutions (below the surface)  
    - This aims to simplify a technical concept to improve customer understanding and product appeal  
    - Gab noted this is a departure from typical visuals, hoping it will stand out and educate marketers effectively  
    - The design team was tasked with developing this concept, with Gab providing creative input  

## **Podcast and Webinar Brand Strategy**

The team is preparing for a post-merger rebranding and clearer distinction between podcasts and webinars (24:50).

- **Gab is working with her new direct supervisor to shift webinar editing and strategy** responsibilities to the MIT team (25:00)  
    - This offloads time-consuming editing tasks from leadership to free her for strategic work  
    - The supervisor supports differentiating the webinar content from the podcast to clarify their roles  
    - Webinars will focus on product-heavy, exclusive content while podcasts emphasize thought leadership and brand awareness  
    - Plans include repurposing webinar content into other formats to maximize reach and efficiency  

- **A rebrand of the podcast visuals and naming is underway** due to the transition from Verisk to Active Prospect (27:30)  
    - For now, the podcast will drop the Verisk logo and adopt a temporary “VMs” name while new branding is developed  
    - Gab highlighted the need for clarity on whether branding will reflect Active Prospect or a division within it  
    - The team plans a future kickoff to establish new graphics and deliverables tailored to the rebranded podcast and webinars  
    - This transition reflects broader organizational changes and evolving brand identity post-merger  

## **Operational and Technical Coordination**

The conversation covered file sharing improvements and vendor payment arrangements to support workflow efficiency (15:10).

- **Baylee and Gab discussed new file upload workflows** leveraging Active Prospect’s move from Microsoft 365 to Google Drive (15:40)  
    - A proposed workaround involves sharing upload links via Slack to bypass prior policy conflicts  
    - This aims to accelerate asset sharing and reduce delays in creative production  
    - Gab remains open to trying multiple approaches to ensure timely access to campaign materials  
    - This change will support smoother collaboration as system migrations continue  

- **Gab explained vendor payment challenges related to external designers** after Verisk’s decision to cut off third-party vendors (24:20)  
    - She is exploring paying external designers through Justin’s system similar to other contractors like Mid, Dawson, and Vlad  
    - This reflects a shift to internalize vendor payments and simplify financial processes  
    - Baylee offered to sync with Don and Justin to clarify resource options and payment workflows  
    - The resolution will help maintain creative capacity during the transition away from external vendors  

## **Upcoming Priorities and Resource Focus**

The team agreed to deprioritize a 2025 episode compilation to concentrate on the March HR2808 launch (14:30).

- **Gab recommended nixing the 2025 episodes compilation due to ongoing system migrations and resource limits** (14:33)  
    - Focus will instead shift fully to creative development for the March enforcement campaign phase  
    - This decision reflects pragmatic resource allocation to meet critical deadlines without overextension  
    - Tim’s recording timeline remains flexible, with no pressure to accelerate delivery  
    - The team will monitor progress and adjust priorities as campaign demands evolve  

- **Baylee confirmed she had no new assets uploaded yet but will check and enable alternative upload methods** (15:27)  
    - This proactive follow-up supports campaign asset flow without bottlenecks  
    - The team remains aligned on timelines and open to iterative improvements in collaboration tools  
    - This responsiveness helps maintain campaign momentum despite system transitions  
    - Gab reaffirmed the intent to keep the campaign on track with fresh creatives launching mid-February  

',
