-- Meeting: NEACH // New North (2026-01-29 15:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '1d01a92d-8acf-44a9-ba25-535d596dab53',
    '2026-01-29 15:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KG54APDEM53A9ARZQ0V633Z5',
    'NEACH // New North',
    '{"Baylee Gunnell","Igor Zagradjanin","Carlos","Joe Casali","Meg Norlund - NEACH"}'::text[],
    1118,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81772236382?pwd=N0NGUdzB0hNqL7TEyT8apNIpwRWDsi.1',
    '{"id":"01KG54APDEM53A9ARZQ0V633Z5","title":"NEACH // New North","summary":{"notes":"## **Points Management and Internal Communication**\n\nThe team confirmed a clear understanding and improved alignment on points allocation and management to avoid past overspending issues (04:23).\n\n- **Meg Norlund clarified** that the backlog of points from the previous year was addressed by settling the invoice, enabling a steady flow of points into 2026 (03:25).\n    - The team, including Baylee Gunnell, Igor Zagradjanin, and Carlos, is exploring whether to restrict submissions to a monthly calendar or slow down point usage to maintain control.\n    - Joe Casali expressed comfort with this approach but requested further updates as planning progresses.\n    - Baylee committed to sending Joe a new portal invite with a 24-hour expiration to improve his visibility of point allocations and keep him informed.\n- **The gifting of points to support the new show launch** was confirmed, eliminating the need for an invoice related to 1500 points previously thought owed (11:59).\n    - Baylee explained that over-delivered points were paid off, and the gifted points are part of the new show setup.\n    - Meg acknowledged this cleared up confusion and appreciated the close monitoring to avoid future overspending.\n\n## **Podcast Production and Content Strategy**\n\nThe team is actively progressing on new podcast episodes and related assets while preparing for a significant season launch in February (06:07).\n\n- **Igor reported delivery of 31 points worth of work in January**, including two episodes featuring Phil Robin and Kevin Johnston, with final clarifications needed on episode destination between Wrestling Payments and Payments on Tap (06:07).\n    - Meg confirmed that Payments on Tap is the priority for the upcoming launch, as it will drive the educational program.\n    - The theme statement requires minor tone adjustments to sound less formal, with Meg offering to send feedback today.\n    - The plan is for Alyssa to record the outro independently via Riverside, with expectations of multiple takes for quality selection.\n- **The team plans a concentrated content push starting February** with season four, aiming for back-to-back episodes to boost engagement (14:11).\n    - Meg highlighted the goal to generate more downloads by releasing episodes quickly after a slow January.\n    - Igor noted that the previous episode from November still performs well, indicating strong ongoing interest.\n    - Visual assets and theme statement feedback are centralized in Miro and Markup tools for streamlined edits and approvals.\n\n## **Technical Access and Platform Integration**\n\nAccess to key platforms is being updated to ensure smooth content publishing and social media management (15:19).\n\n- **Igor flagged loss of YouTube access, requiring Megan''s IT team to add the production team to the new business platform**, with instructions to be shared for onboarding (15:38).\n    - Meg confirmed IT controls these accounts and will facilitate adding Igor and team members once procedures are provided.\n- **Baylee confirmed she has LinkedIn page access and will grant Igor the necessary permissions** to reconnect the Niche LinkedIn account to the Publer scheduling tool (15:19).\n    - This reconnection is critical to enable content reuse from Wrestling Payments LinkedIn on Niche LinkedIn, supporting cross-platform promotion.\n    - Baylee is taking immediate steps to add Igor to the page, allowing smoother management for future campaigns.\n\n## **Performance Metrics and Priorities**\n\nThe podcast team is tracking steady download growth and prioritizing visual and branding assets for the new show launch (13:26).\n\n- **Igor shared that the podcast received 177 downloads in the last month**, with a notable spike of **around 745 downloads on January 19th** (13:26).\n    - The episode featuring Wasserman and Proos from November maintains strong performance with **117 downloads**, showing sustained interest despite no new uploads since then.\n- **Upcoming priorities focus on completing the graphics package and finalizing Payments on Tap setup**, including visual assets and intro/outro recordings (14:37).\n    - Meg emphasized the importance of quick turnaround on feedback and asset adjustments to keep the launch on track.\n    - The team is coordinating closely to ensure all elements align with the educational program and overall brand strategy.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast production","points allocation","payments on tap","visual assets","social media management","Riverside recording"],"overview":"- **Points Management Improvement:** Team aligned on points allocation to prevent overspending, ensuring smoother transition through 2026.  \n- **Gifting Points for New Show:** 1500 points gifted for new show launch, resolving previous invoice confusion.  \n- **Podcast Launch in February:** New episodes ready, aiming for quick releases to boost downloads and engagement.  \n- **Steady Download Growth:** Podcast had 177 downloads last month, with a spike of 745 on January 19th.  \n- **Technical Access Updates:** YouTube access issue flagged; IT will assist with team onboarding to new platform.  \n- **Visual and Branding Priorities:** Focus on completing graphics and finalizing recordings for the Payments on Tap launch.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nSend Joe Casali a new portal invite for points access that expires in 24 hours (05:14)\nAdd Igor to NEACH LinkedIn page and connect it to Publer for social media management (15:50)\n\n**Joe Casali**\nReview points system with new portal and request further tutorial help if needed (02:20)\n\n**Meg Norlund**\nReview and provide feedback on the theme statement and intro/outro documents for payments on tap show (07:18)\nProvide additional visual asset feedback via markup and Miro, especially for speaker image effects (08:45)\nCoordinate with IT to add Marketers in Demand team to YouTube business platform and share instructions (15:40)\nEnsure Alyssa records multiple outro takes in Riverside and communicate completion via email (08:30)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nContinue developing payments on tap show visual assets and intro/outro segments in tandem with Meg’s feedback (06:00)\nCompile podcast download statistics and monitor upcoming season release impact (13:20)\nCoordinate reconnecting NEACH LinkedIn to Publer and resolve YouTube access issues (14:50)\nReview and implement Carlos’ design feedback on Miro/markup (17:20)\n\n**Carlos**\nDrop comments and feedback on design assets directly in Miro or markup for team review (17:20)\n"},"duration":18.639999389648438,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"id":2,"name":"Carlos"},{"id":3,"name":"Joe Casali"},{"id":4,"name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"}],"sentences":[{"text":"We will see.","index":0,"end_time":6.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s because of the link.","index":1,"end_time":109.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":108.36,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":2,"end_time":112.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":110.2,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Hey, hey.","index":3,"end_time":116.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":113.96,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Hey.","index":4,"end_time":116.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":116.4,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Meg.","index":5,"end_time":119.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":118.68,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"I think we''re just waiting for Joe.","index":6,"end_time":122.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":119.96,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Oh, awesome.","index":7,"end_time":123.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":123.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"He.","index":8,"end_time":125.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":125.16,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"He just has some questions about how the points are all allocated and all the things, so.","index":9,"end_time":131,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":125.56,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":10,"end_time":132.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":131.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we can chat through that.","index":11,"end_time":133.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":132.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":12,"end_time":134.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":133.8,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Hey, Joe.","index":13,"end_time":141.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Long time no see.","index":14,"end_time":142.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":141.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I. I read your blogs.","index":15,"end_time":145.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":144.12,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"Well, thank you.","index":16,"end_time":148.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":147.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I listen to your podcast.","index":17,"end_time":149.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":148.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, if you want, Joe, we can talk through your questions about points first, and then we can get into our normal agenda items.","index":18,"end_time":161.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You can stay the whole time or if you''ve got to hop off after that.","index":19,"end_time":164.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Good point.","index":20,"end_time":166.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":165.95,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"So I think it may actually be an internal communication thing.","index":21,"end_time":172.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":168.19,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"I just read Igor.","index":22,"end_time":174.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":172.75,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"Oh, hi, Igor.","index":23,"end_time":175.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":174.67,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"You were just a new name.","index":24,"end_time":178.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":177.79,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"Now you''re a face.","index":25,"end_time":179.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":178.83,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"Thanks, I think.","index":26,"end_time":182.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":179.59,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"So that the Clearinghouse Robin podcast I did way back when.","index":27,"end_time":188.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":182.91,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"I don''t think I''ve done one this calendar year.","index":28,"end_time":190.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":188.71,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"That was the fifth one you processed this year, Megan.","index":29,"end_time":197.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":191.99,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"Is there a schedule of Alyssa?","index":30,"end_time":201.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":197.47,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"We''re like.","index":31,"end_time":201.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":201.03,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"There''s, like a.","index":32,"end_time":202.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":201.47,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"There is a wall between us.","index":33,"end_time":203.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":202.03,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"You know, that whole silo thing.","index":34,"end_time":204.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":203.19,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"Yeah, I. I''m putting them both together.","index":35,"end_time":207.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":205.35,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I. I''ll get that over to you, Joe, just so you can see it, but we did have a bit of a backlog because last year we went substantially over our points.","index":36,"end_time":217.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":208.47,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And so once we got that invoice taken care of, then we started moving things into 2026.","index":37,"end_time":226.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":218.29,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So I think that''s what we''re seeing now is that sort of continuation of those from the previous year.","index":38,"end_time":234.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":226.93,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So a lot of things are coming out pretty quick and steady.","index":39,"end_time":237.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":234.53,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then Bailey, Igor, Carlos, and I have been talking about the best way to manage points.","index":40,"end_time":243.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":238.05,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Whether that''s us adhering to a calendar over here where we only submit to a month, or if they slow us down, if we''re kind of going a little crazy, more than we should be.","index":41,"end_time":258.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":244.65,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That''S good enough for me.","index":42,"end_time":260.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":259.13,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"You can circle back with me.","index":43,"end_time":261.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":260.05,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"When.","index":44,"end_time":263.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You get further in your planning.","index":45,"end_time":265.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":263.57,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"That was the piece of the puzzle I was missing.","index":46,"end_time":268.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":266.57,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":47,"end_time":269.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":268.58,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"And you, you''re okay with all things, then?","index":48,"end_time":271.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":269.54,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"You understand that some things are working?","index":49,"end_time":274.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":271.62,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, if I wasn''t as busy as I was, I''d certainly love to see, like, the.","index":50,"end_time":280.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":275.06,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"The points on that little report.","index":51,"end_time":281.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":280.26,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"And I. I.","index":52,"end_time":282.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":281.86,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"You know, I don''t think I ever got that report.","index":53,"end_time":284.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":282.66,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"And then all of a sudden, it started showing up, and I''m like, oh, what''s this?","index":54,"end_time":287.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":284.78,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"Yeah, it was a.","index":55,"end_time":289.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s a new development.","index":56,"end_time":290.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We just started sending that out, like, two months ago.","index":57,"end_time":293.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I may drop in sometime for tutorial, but I''m good for now.","index":58,"end_time":300.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":294.62,"speaker_name":"Joe Casali"},{"text":"Could you send Joe the portal link again with the information to access?","index":59,"end_time":307.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":301.9,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Because that''s a really clear view of where the points are all going, and I''m not sure he''s seeing that.","index":60,"end_time":312.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":307.34,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, I was like, that''s probably the game.","index":61,"end_time":314.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":313.26,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''ll send you a new invite, Joe.","index":62,"end_time":316.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just know it expires, I think, in 24 hours, so I''ll send it today.","index":63,"end_time":321.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":316.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, thank you very much.","index":64,"end_time":323.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":322.08,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, thanks, Joe.","index":65,"end_time":324.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":323.84,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We''ll see you.","index":66,"end_time":325.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":67,"end_time":330,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":329.12,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"All good.","index":68,"end_time":332.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Gotta make sure Joe''s on the same page.","index":69,"end_time":335.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"He''s our awesome podcast host, but we don''t chat with him much, so.","index":70,"end_time":338.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, we gotta keep the talent happy.","index":71,"end_time":340.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":338.88,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":72,"end_time":342.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I wonder how he''d feel about being called the talent.","index":73,"end_time":346,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":343.92,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Well, do you want to get into the stuff you have prepped, Igor?","index":74,"end_time":355.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes, for sure.","index":75,"end_time":357.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.81,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Let''s go.","index":76,"end_time":364.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.33,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Can you see my screen?","index":77,"end_time":366.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":365.65,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yes.","index":78,"end_time":367.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":367.33,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":79,"end_time":369.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":368.93,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay, so we''ll go through work delivered, work in progress, then some things we''re waiting on, and then some podcast stats.","index":80,"end_time":383.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.7,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So so far in January, we have delivered 31 points, including these two episodes.","index":81,"end_time":394.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.82,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Phil Robin and Kevin Johnston is pretty much done.","index":82,"end_time":398.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":394.78,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s just that we''re not sure if this was a misunderstanding or.","index":83,"end_time":404.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":399.34,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So when I sent this episode for review, then Elisa replied with like, is this go?","index":84,"end_time":414.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.24,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Basically.","index":85,"end_time":414.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":414.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Is this going to wrestling payments or payments on tap?","index":86,"end_time":419.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":414.8,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So this is something that we just need to figure out, especially since we''re still developing the visual assets and we need the intro and outro for.","index":87,"end_time":430.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"For payments on tap.","index":88,"end_time":432.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.99,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And also your feedback and updates on the theme statement for the new show.","index":89,"end_time":438.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.51,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Right.","index":90,"end_time":439.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":438.75,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"This one should be payments on tap.","index":91,"end_time":441.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":439.39,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"This is going to be sort of the first launch.","index":92,"end_time":444.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":441.79,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It launches the big.","index":93,"end_time":445.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":444.43,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like, this is the person that''s going to be doing our actual education program as well.","index":94,"end_time":450.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":445.87,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So let me take a look at your.","index":95,"end_time":454.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":450.99,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The document you sent over.","index":96,"end_time":458.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":456.76,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think most of it was fine.","index":97,"end_time":460,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":458.6,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It was just that sort of one part of it that felt a little.","index":98,"end_time":463.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":460,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"A little stiffer than we would have wanted.","index":99,"end_time":466.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":465.16,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But I thought.","index":100,"end_time":467.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":466.96,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think once we get that theme statement.","index":101,"end_time":469.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":467.72,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Good.","index":102,"end_time":469.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I love the idea of doing just the intro with some sounds rather than like a full announcement.","index":103,"end_time":477.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":469.56,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"What would be next steps?","index":104,"end_time":481.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":479.96,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We get that document over back to you.","index":105,"end_time":483.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":481.12,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then we were talking about Alyssa recording the outro.","index":106,"end_time":486.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":483.56,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Would that be something we could do, as you''re also working on the graphics, like, in tandem?","index":107,"end_time":492.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":487.22,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yep, for sure.","index":108,"end_time":494.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":492.42,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":109,"end_time":494.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":494.34,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Is that something.","index":110,"end_time":496.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":495.7,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"How should we do this?","index":111,"end_time":498.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":497.78,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Should she just go into Riverside and record something?","index":112,"end_time":501.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":498.7,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Do we script her?","index":113,"end_time":502.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":501.62,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like, what''s the.","index":114,"end_time":503.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":502.9,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"What''s.","index":115,"end_time":504.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":503.66,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Where do we go next?","index":116,"end_time":505.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":504.58,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think we made her a new Riverside production, Space Eagle.","index":117,"end_time":510.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":506.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Right?","index":118,"end_time":511.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or yes, I sent that.","index":119,"end_time":513.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":511.22,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Let me just.","index":120,"end_time":515.839,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":515.199,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, so essentially she''ll just need to log into that Riverside and record.","index":121,"end_time":524.159,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.359,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"She can just do it solo kind of.","index":122,"end_time":527.039,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.319,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, it sounds like she''s pretty familiar with Riverside, so it''s similar to having like a guest on there.","index":123,"end_time":532.999,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.679,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just have her record it herself.","index":124,"end_time":535.039,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.999,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And sometimes it''s nice to like maybe do two to three takes, so we can pick the, the best one.","index":125,"end_time":541.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.199,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":126,"end_time":543.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":542.61,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Do you, can you send me the access to that as well, or is it just a studio in our current Riverside?","index":127,"end_time":549.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":544.37,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s a separate login.","index":128,"end_time":551.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":129,"end_time":553.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":552.45,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yes, I did send this yesterday.","index":130,"end_time":556.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":553.33,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"All right, let me just have this.","index":131,"end_time":560.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.53,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"As a, as a follow up email to the content plan and graphics package feedback.","index":132,"end_time":567.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":560.93,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":133,"end_time":569.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.42,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And it''s the second email in the thread.","index":134,"end_time":575.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Can you remind me what the subject line is?","index":135,"end_time":582.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":580.54,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So it says payments on tap.","index":136,"end_time":585.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.34,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Got it.","index":137,"end_time":586.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":586.38,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Dash, content plan and graphics package feedback.","index":138,"end_time":589.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":586.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay, I see the username and the password.","index":139,"end_time":593.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":589.74,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":140,"end_time":594.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":594.06,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":141,"end_time":595.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":595.18,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So I will take a look at that theme statement.","index":142,"end_time":598.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":595.86,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then she did have a few comments on, like, she didn''t really like the drip going down on the speakers, images and stuff like that.","index":143,"end_time":608.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":600.52,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So I''ll mark that up and get that over to you today and then we''ll have her pop in there and do a few outro takes.","index":144,"end_time":615.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":608.88,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"What is the form?","index":145,"end_time":616.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":615.8,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Is that also in that email?","index":146,"end_time":618.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":616.76,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"How do we let you know this is ready?","index":147,"end_time":621.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":620.04,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So in markup, there''s the, the, the, the slide deck that we went through in our meeting last week.","index":148,"end_time":632.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":623.56,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So in markup you can leave feedback directly.","index":149,"end_time":636.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":632.75,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So basically it says in the first email, it says that the main things we need your feedback on are the theme statement and intro and outro.","index":150,"end_time":644.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":636.43,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So these are slide 15 and slide 20.","index":151,"end_time":647.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":644.63,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then the visual assets are in Miro and you can also leave feedback directly there.","index":152,"end_time":656.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":648.43,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yep, I''m comfortable with that.","index":153,"end_time":658.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":657.29,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Once she''s recorded the outro, though, usually we have like a form I think that we''re supposed to fill out to let you know stuff is in Riverside.","index":154,"end_time":666.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":658.97,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"You can just shoot us an email.","index":155,"end_time":668.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This is a little different than like a whole episode.","index":156,"end_time":671.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":157,"end_time":672.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":671.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":158,"end_time":677.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.61,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Then let''s just go back.","index":159,"end_time":682.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So, yes, we are working on the visual assets and it would be great if you could leave some feedback, additional feedback in Miro.","index":160,"end_time":705.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":696.56,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So we can just get all the edits potentially in one take, all the updates.","index":161,"end_time":714.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":707.22,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And.","index":162,"end_time":716.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":716.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This is it.","index":163,"end_time":720.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":719.3,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yes, and one more thing.","index":164,"end_time":724.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":721.7,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So, Megan, two weeks ago in our meeting when Bailey was out of office, you mentioned this Invoice that you would need.","index":165,"end_time":734.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":724.82,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Right.","index":166,"end_time":735.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":734.69,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So yeah, so talking with Bailey, we just figured out that.","index":167,"end_time":739.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":735.17,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We figured out that this was.","index":168,"end_time":740.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":739.37,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Those points were gifted.","index":169,"end_time":743.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":741.41,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So Bailey, that''s something.","index":170,"end_time":747.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.65,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, that.","index":171,"end_time":748.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":747.45,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, you won''t need an invoice for that.","index":172,"end_time":750.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":748.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We, we''re gifting the points to get the new show set up.","index":173,"end_time":753.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That includes the 1500 that we owed you, though.","index":174,"end_time":757.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":755.01,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I don''t think you owed 1500.","index":175,"end_time":762.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Did you see like an invoice or like did we send you a request for something?","index":176,"end_time":767.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I thought it was in one of your emails.","index":177,"end_time":770.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":767.98,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Let me take a look.","index":178,"end_time":771.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":770.94,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we should be all squared away because you paid like what was over delivered and then as part of that we wanted to gift you points to get the new show started.","index":179,"end_time":786.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, I may have misunderstood that.","index":180,"end_time":788.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":786.99,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay, so we''re all up to date.","index":181,"end_time":790.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":788.67,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we should be good squared away.","index":182,"end_time":794.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re keeping track to make sure we don''t go over again.","index":183,"end_time":797.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So yeah, we''re keeping a close eye on that.","index":184,"end_time":801.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":798.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":185,"end_time":802.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":802.11,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I appreciate that.","index":186,"end_time":803.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":802.59,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Sure.","index":187,"end_time":806.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":806.03,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then some podcast stats.","index":188,"end_time":810.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.15,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So 177 downloads in the last month.","index":189,"end_time":815.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":811.54,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And there''s an obvious spike on Monday last week.","index":190,"end_time":822.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":815.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Monday, January 19th.","index":191,"end_time":824.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.18,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"About 74 or 5 downloads that day.","index":192,"end_time":829.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":824.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Nice.","index":193,"end_time":830.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":829.86,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And these are the episodes.","index":194,"end_time":834.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":833.3,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So the last one, Wasserman and Proos is doing really good actually with 117 downloads.","index":195,"end_time":843.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":835.06,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, but that''s from November 18th.","index":196,"end_time":846.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":844.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So you haven''t uploaded anything since then?","index":197,"end_time":851.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":848.52,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Nope.","index":198,"end_time":852.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":851.72,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We''re starting our season four in February so we''ll have like the back to back to back episode.","index":199,"end_time":858.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":852.12,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So we should be seeing some stats after that.","index":200,"end_time":860.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":858.48,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That''s amazing.","index":201,"end_time":862.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.16,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":202,"end_time":862.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.12,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So actually some, some episodes back to back.","index":203,"end_time":866.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":863.96,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Can even get some more downloads.","index":204,"end_time":870.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":866.36,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''s what we''re hoping.","index":205,"end_time":871.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":870.6,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Give them something quick out of the gate slammed in January, so.","index":206,"end_time":877.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":871.72,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":207,"end_time":878.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":877.48,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"January is slow so it should be good.","index":208,"end_time":881.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":878.48,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And the upcoming priorities, so obviously graphics package for.","index":209,"end_time":890.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":884.2,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And everything else to set up payments on tap.","index":210,"end_time":893.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":890.52,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then this is also something.","index":211,"end_time":897.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":896.04,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So Megan, since you mentioned that you want to reuse posts from Wrestling Payments LinkedIn on Niche LinkedIn.","index":212,"end_time":906.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":897.72,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We will need to reconnect Niche LinkedIn to Publer when I request.","index":213,"end_time":913.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So basically what we need from you is LinkedIn login info.","index":214,"end_time":917.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":913.8,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"If I''m correct, Bailey.","index":215,"end_time":918.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":917.32,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Actually I think I already have access to this page.","index":216,"end_time":922.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Ah, okay.","index":217,"end_time":924.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":923.28,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay, so let me see if I can give you access Igor 2.","index":218,"end_time":930.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ll just look at that real quick.","index":219,"end_time":935.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But do you want to talk about YouTube while I look through that?","index":220,"end_time":938.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, for sure.","index":221,"end_time":939.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.72,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then also it looks like we don''t have access to your YouTube anymore.","index":222,"end_time":946.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":939.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Megan.","index":223,"end_time":947.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":946.8,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Megan.","index":224,"end_time":948.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":947.6,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So.","index":225,"end_time":948.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":948.48,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, so.","index":226,"end_time":949.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":948.8,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, yes.","index":227,"end_time":950.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":949.6,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":228,"end_time":951.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":950.88,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That makes perfect sense.","index":229,"end_time":952.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":951.32,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":230,"end_time":952.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":952.32,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We created a business, like, platform for like YouTube, Google all this stuff.","index":231,"end_time":960.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_ti