  VALUES (
    '18194a27-f4fd-4f8a-b974-7e8dcaea1d46',
    '2026-01-26 17:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFJM1QBJGZEV2E6223TQ0ZR0',
    'Igor Zagradjanin and Brandon Garcin',
    '{"Brandon Garcin","Igor Zagradjanin","Baylee Gunnell"}'::text[],
    2086,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85476489791?pwd=erwjQyfcUn7Q7oYZN7POLmENLxqNJF.1',
    '{"id":"01KFJM1QBJGZEV2E6223TQ0ZR0","title":"Igor Zagradjanin and Brandon Garcin","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Strategy and Leadership Changes**\n\nThe new CMO, **Carl**, has shifted Synchro’s marketing from mostly inbound to a blended inbound/outbound model focused on account-based marketing (06:23).  \n- Carl is introducing tools like **ZoomInfo** to identify buying intent beyond web visits, targeting companies with relevant executive hires or news.  \n- The sales team, previously not doing outbound, is building new outbound skills to support this approach.  \n- Brandon explained the plan to invert the current **70-80% SEO and 20-30% GEO split** toward about **75-80% GEO-focused content** by year-end, aiming to compete better in AI-powered search where GEO is less mature.  \n- This shift supports a faster growth trajectory by targeting more mature buyers with personalized outreach rather than relying solely on organic SEO growth.\n\nSynchro is repositioning itself as a **secure IT management platform**, weaving security deeply into messaging rather than just automation and efficiency (10:16).  \n- Brandon noted recent product releases and features strengthen Synchro’s security story, enabling this repositioning.  \n- The security focus aligns with market demand and higher valuation opportunities in security-centric IT platforms.\n\nPlanning is underway to review and evolve marketing channels, including blogs, social, community, and website updates, to support new campaigns and outbound motions (11:34).  \n- Brandon expects to finalize campaign priorities and channel strategies within the next **1-2 weeks**, followed by execution and optimization.  \n- Carl’s leadership is driving a replatforming of go-to-market systems to support these new approaches.\n\n## **Content and Podcast Direction**\n\nSynchro’s podcast saw **44 downloads** in the past 30 days with some spikes around new episode releases, but overall engagement is low compared to other channels (27:46).  \n- Brandon highlighted that past episodes were published somewhat isolated from broader marketing efforts, which limited growth and traction.  \n- The plan is to move from broad, random podcast topics to **highly targeted episodes tied to specific campaigns**, focusing on quality over quantity (20:30).  \n- This targeted approach involves identifying a narrow list of **7-8 key people** aligned to campaign themes to generate relevant content that directly supports marketing objectives.\n\nBrandon is considering repurposing existing podcast material more effectively rather than producing new episodes immediately (29:34).  \n- There are about **15-16 hours of recorded content** that could be sliced into more digestible or targeted clips to boost reach without new recordings.  \n- Video content is recognized as increasingly important, but decisions on social clips and video strategy are pending integration with the new campaign plans (24:50).\n\nThe podcast’s future depends on its fit within the broader outbound and GEO campaigns Carl is developing, with a decision expected within a few weeks (17:46).  \n- Brandon plans to share podcast performance data and content capabilities with Carl to align the show’s direction with growth priorities.\n\n## **Operational Shifts and Team Responsibilities**\n\nThe marketing team structure is flat, with pods covering multiple pillars but clear content ownership aligned to new priorities (14:40).  \n- Brandon’s pod will mainly handle the **SEO to GEO content shift** and about **75% of the security messaging** since they own most website content.  \n- The outbound account-based marketing (ABM/ABX) program will be run largely by the growth organization, leveraging AI tools to automate personalized outreach without heavy content demands from Brandon’s team.\n\nThis division allows Brandon’s group to focus resources on the GEO and security content transition while growth handles tooling and processes for ABM (15:58).  \n- Brandon noted AI-generated messaging has reached a quality level sufficient to replace much manual content creation for outreach, balancing efficiency and effectiveness.\n\nBrandon anticipates ongoing role and responsibility shifts as Carl’s leadership reshapes operating motions and marketing programming (06:23).  \n- He expects these changes to accelerate lead growth by targeting more mature buyers and incorporating security themes more deeply into the brand.\n\n## **Campaign and Timeline Outlook**\n\nSynchro plans to launch its first campaign under the new marketing model within the next **couple of weeks** (25:00).  \n- Brandon aims to clarify campaign deliverables, look and feel, and resource needs soon to enable coordinated content support.  \n- Early campaign work will focus on integrating outbound, GEO content, and security messaging pillars to drive more qualified leads.\n\nBrandon stressed the importance of not rushing new initiatives before strategic alignment is clear, holding social video and other new content formats \"warm\" until campaign plans solidify (24:50).  \n- He emphasized measured execution over volume, aiming for targeted activations rather than broad, untargeted content blasts.\n\nThe team plans to reconvene in about **two weeks** to review campaign progress and decide how to align content production, including podcast episodes, with broader marketing objectives (33:27).  \n- This cadence supports rapid iteration and ensures marketing efforts stay coordinated with evolving growth strategies.\n\n## **Performance Metrics and Growth Challenges**\n\nDespite positive marketing metrics in the second half of last year, Synchro’s growth rate is seen as insufficient, prompting the shift to outbound and GEO emphasis (11:34).  \n- Brandon indicated that while organic SEO delivered value, competitors’ longer investment history means Synchro must differentiate via newer channels like AI-powered search and account-based targeting.  \n- Podcast engagement remains low, with download numbers in the **low double digits per month**, reinforcing the need for a new approach to content tied to campaigns (27:46).\n\nThe outbound personalized messaging pilot reached about **50% response or engagement rates** on targeted lists, showing promise for more focused outreach (20:46).  \n- This data supports the strategic pivot to quality over quantity in content and marketing activations.\n\nBrandon flagged the need to evaluate whether to continue producing new podcast content or focus on repurposing existing material to improve ROI and audience relevance (29:36).  \n- This reflects a broader emphasis on data-driven, efficient marketing investment amid evolving leadership priorities.\n\n## **Stakeholder Collaboration and Next Steps**\n\nBrandon expressed openness to introducing new CMO Carl to agency partners and cross-functional teams once roles and plans settle (18:28).  \n- This will help align external and internal stakeholders around the new marketing playbook and campaign execution.\n\nBaylee and Igor remain ready to support content adaptations and integrations as campaign priorities clarify (18:45).  \n- Brandon committed to keeping them updated on evolving campaign plans and podcast decisions to ensure tight collaboration.\n\nThe next meeting is tentatively planned for about **two weeks out**, aiming to share clearer campaign direction and co-create supporting content (33:27).  \n- Brandon emphasized the importance of balancing planning with action to avoid a protracted Q1 of only strategy discussions.","outline":null,"keywords":["Outbound Marketing","GEO-first Strategy","Account-Based Marketing","Security Positioning","Podcast Strategy","AI-powered Search"],"overview":"- **Marketing Shift:** New CMO introduced a blended inbound/outbound marketing model, focusing on account-based marketing.  \n- **Content Strategy Change:** Transitioning to 75-80% GEO-focused content by year-end to target mature buyers and improve SEO competition.  \n- **Podcast Engagement:** Current podcast engagement is low; plans to create targeted episodes aligned with marketing campaigns instead of random topics.  \n- **Operational Structure:** Marketing team has flat structure with clear content ownership to support security and GEO content transition.  \n- **Campaign Launch:** First campaign under new model to launch in a couple of weeks, integrating outbound and GEO strategies.  \n- **Growth Metrics:** Outbound pilot shows 50% engagement; existing podcast content may be repurposed to improve ROI and audience reach.","action_items":"\n**Brandon Garcin**\nPublish Russell’s podcast episode this week (19:29)\nPublish Brian Lindholm’s podcast episode in February (19:29)\nFollow up with podcast guests (Eric and Amy) to confirm interview topics and timings (20:46)\nContinue to coordinate with new CMO Carl to finalize the marketing campaign strategy and operationalize new outbound and GEO-focused initiatives (11:34)\nReassess podcast strategy and content production based on early campaign feedback and new strategic priorities within next few weeks (30:53)\nReport to the team on campaign progress and implications for content production and podcast relevance in next meeting (34:07)\nOrganize later introductions between CMO Carl and the marketing teams/agencies for alignment (18:28)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nProvide updates on completed deliverables including the Tech Stack (19:01)\nShare podcast download analytics and feedback with the team to inform content strategy (27:46)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nOffer readiness to meet new CMO Carl to facilitate collaboration (18:18)\n"},"duration":34.77000045776367,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"id":1,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"id":2,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Igor, how are you, man?","index":0,"end_time":242.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.21,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Hey, Brandon, how are you?","index":1,"end_time":245.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":243.53,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":2,"end_time":245.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.17,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":3,"end_time":247.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.73,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It already feels like six months into the new year, but nice to see you guys.","index":4,"end_time":253.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.69,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"How are the holidays?","index":5,"end_time":254.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.01,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Almost.","index":6,"end_time":254.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.57,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, it was, it was nice.","index":7,"end_time":257.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.99,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Both Bailey and me had like about 10 days or seven days of like some rest time each, so.","index":8,"end_time":266.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.59,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, we definitely use the, the slow month of January to kind of relax and.","index":9,"end_time":272.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":266.63,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":10,"end_time":272.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.31,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"How about you?","index":11,"end_time":273.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"How are you?","index":12,"end_time":274.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":274.23,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"About the same amount of time off.","index":13,"end_time":277.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.75,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We were in Florida for the holidays.","index":14,"end_time":281.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.55,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"My in laws spend about half the year down there when it''s cold in the northeast there where they live.","index":15,"end_time":288.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.19,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It was good.","index":16,"end_time":290.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.78,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It was like, you know, kind of lay on the beach and do nothing for two weeks, which, despite living somewhat close to the beach, we don''t get to do very often because we''re always so busy.","index":17,"end_time":302.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.34,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So it was nice.","index":18,"end_time":303.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":302.34,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Wait, you''re in California, right?","index":19,"end_time":306.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I am.","index":20,"end_time":307.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.9,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''m in San Diego.","index":21,"end_time":308.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.34,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Um, so, you know, we, we have access to a lot of that stuff, but their, their place in Florida like touches sand, so that''s not what we have.","index":22,"end_time":317.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.95,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, you also have a cold beach usually, right?","index":23,"end_time":322.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":317.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, a little.","index":24,"end_time":324.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.07,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"The water, the water is certainly cooler on the west coast than, than there for sure.","index":25,"end_time":329.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.79,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But it''s nice.","index":26,"end_time":331.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.47,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And they''re, they''re older.","index":27,"end_time":332.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.19,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s in a slightly older community, so it''s like nice and quiet and like they have a pool there that''s heated to like 90 degrees because it''s for old people.","index":28,"end_time":340.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.35,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, you get to take advantage of like the things that are designed for old people.","index":29,"end_time":345.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.9,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"As a slightly younger person is nice.","index":30,"end_time":349.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.62,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It was good, good to relax.","index":31,"end_time":351.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.18,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And it has just been a whirlwind since then, of course, because there is no such thing as taking two weeks off of work.","index":32,"end_time":358.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.82,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It is just reallocating work to another date.","index":33,"end_time":363.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.94,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Um, but it''s been good.","index":34,"end_time":365.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.18,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We have new leadership that has come in, so we''ve had a new CMO start.","index":35,"end_time":370.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.54,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I forget whether or how much of that we were talking about before the break.","index":36,"end_time":374.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":370.7,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It, it was sort of a on and off conversation for the last couple of months, but around the holidays kind of kicked into overdrive pretty quickly.","index":37,"end_time":382.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":375.22,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":38,"end_time":383.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":383.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we were all together.","index":39,"end_time":386.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.3,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I got back from Florida for the holidays, had about a week here at home, and then went straight the fuck back to Florida for, for our, like, sales revenue, you know, kickoff for the year.","index":40,"end_time":396.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.66,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So we got a sense of kind of where the business is headed and what we want to be working on and blah, blah, blah, blah, blah.","index":41,"end_time":402.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.77,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So it''s, it''s, it''s been Very busy just trying to rally around some of those upcoming priorities as well as get a new leader up to speed.","index":42,"end_time":412.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.61,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And he''s already, you know, shaking things up and looking at what we''re doing and shifting some of our, you know, operating motions and things like that.","index":43,"end_time":419.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.25,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So he''s kind of off to the races.","index":44,"end_time":420.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":419.33,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And I''m just trying to know, hang on and, and do my part to help him, you know, start standing up the type of programming that he''s interested in, which we can certainly chat a little bit about here.","index":45,"end_time":433.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":420.93,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But don''t let me hijack too much if we want to get through some normal, you know, agenda first.","index":46,"end_time":437.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.11,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''m just curious, like, how''s that changing your job so far?","index":47,"end_time":442.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":438.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, there definitely are some role and responsibility shifts, probably a little less for me than some others on the team, but the way that we operate is, is definitely evolving.","index":48,"end_time":453.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.91,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So maybe I''ll try to keep it to a couple of crispy headlines.","index":49,"end_time":457.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.23,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So Synchro historically has been almost entirely inbound driven in terms of like, where leads and value and traffic are coming from.","index":50,"end_time":467.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.08,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We''ve done a lot of, you know, field of dreams, like, let''s build something cool and hopefully people will show up to it.","index":51,"end_time":475.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Carl, who is our new cmo, is a big proponent of Outbound and has a much more modern view of it than what I am used to.","index":52,"end_time":487.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":476.64,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So there''s a pretty big change kind of already early stages underway to shift us to more of a blended inbound and outbound motion.","index":53,"end_time":497.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":489.14,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So a lot more around like account based marketing and targeting, using tools like zoom info and other stuff to get much deeper understanding of like buying intent signals and not like, oh, somebody visited our, you know, these two web pages like they must be ready to buy, but like, oh, this company just, you know, hired a new executive in this role and they just had this kind of PR coverage checking out blah, blah, blah.","index":54,"end_time":522.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":497.86,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And he''s got some pretty interesting automation that like stitches all that together and prioritizes and stack ranks accounts that we should be going after and things like that.","index":55,"end_time":530.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.16,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Our sales team also is not really doing any Outbound today.","index":56,"end_time":533.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":531,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So there''s a lot of new kind of muscle development and that part of the business.","index":57,"end_time":538.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":533.68,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And then I''d say that the other two maybe pillars to start.","index":58,"end_time":544.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.2,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I mean this is like week three for him.","index":59,"end_time":545.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":544.59,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So it''s, it''s already, you know, pretty comprehensive.","index":60,"end_time":548.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.99,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But the shift from, in my camp, I suppose from sort of SEO first approach to, you know, keyword research and content creation and topic selection and things like that, toward a more CEO first and you know, we''ve, we''ve kind of been maybe 70, 30 or 80, 20 SEO, and geo being the minority, and he''s looking to really, you know, invert that scale so that I don''t know if it''s, by the end of this year, at some point, over the next couple of quarters, we''re kind of operating 75, 80%, you know, prioritized toward Geo in terms of the way we''re creating content, some technical things that we''re doing or should start to do more of, and just feeling like, you know, we, we have a faster, better opportunity to be competitive in AI powered search because it''s a much more level field, because it''s much newer and we''re not sort of chasing and playing catch up to the many years of SEO growth that a lot of competitors have had who have invested, you know, more time and dollars and resources and such into it over time than Synchro has been able to.","index":61,"end_time":615.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.47,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And then probably pillar number three, the, the sort of general evolution of the company''s kind of positioning and messaging toward becoming more security oriented, which is not surprising at a high level to, you know, it''s, it''s a very security centric market.","index":62,"end_time":634,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.35,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s where money is, that''s where higher valuations are.","index":63,"end_time":636.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I have kind of been a holdout on that feeling that, well, like, Synchro has some security features, but I have not really been ready to call it a security platform or a security company.","index":64,"end_time":645.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.08,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But there is work that is being done that I think sort of gives the company the right to now say that some new features being developed, some products that were shipped over the last couple of quarters and the sort of security story behind Synchro is much stronger today than it was, let''s say, entering 2025.","index":65,"end_time":662.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.8,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So kind of repositioning ourselves as a secure IT management platform and not solely relying on things like automation and cost savings and efficiency for, for the way we sort of, you know, differentiate and talk about what makes Synchro valuable, but really weaving security into that fabric as well.","index":66,"end_time":680.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.84,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So it''s been a busy January, I suppose, to say the least, but it''s all good stuff.","index":67,"end_time":689.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":681.88,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And, you know, these are the sort of bets I think, that are being hedged.","index":68,"end_time":694.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.56,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like Synchro was growing, we were doing pretty well.","index":69,"end_time":696.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":694.25,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"A lot of our marketing metrics, particularly about the second half of last year, we''re all pretty favorable.","index":70,"end_time":701.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":696.49,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I think there''s just a feeling that the growth rate is not sort of fast enough and that we would like to, you know, introduce some of These newer dynamics to kind of accelerate our ability to drive more leads, to kind of attract more mature or target and engage with, I should say not just attract, but go out and seek out these more mature buyers and to do so in a way that is more kind of security conscious than some of the ways we''ve talked about the platform in the past.","index":71,"end_time":733.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.05,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So now we''re trying to kind of bring that down to the ground floor because that''s all somewhat high level.","index":72,"end_time":738.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":734.84,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So we''re reviewing strategies for different channels that we are leveraging blog and social and community and other types of content development and just trying to sort of think through all that website evolution.","index":73,"end_time":750.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.84,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So there''s a lot of kind of planning work happening last week and probably this week and next week and then we''ll, we''ll just be cranking out, you know, hopefully the first pass of a couple of new kind of campaigns and kind of operating motions.","index":74,"end_time":768.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.36,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Again, a lot of this outbound stuff being new, some web updates being new.","index":75,"end_time":771.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":768.32,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So there''s, there''s some kind of replatforming to do from a go to market perspective and then some campaigns and some performance management around that and then we''ll see and hopefully things will be off to a good start and then we''ll kind of optimize from there.","index":76,"end_time":782.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":771.08,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I''m pretty optimistic and as always, like just happy to remain employed and you know, be along for the ride at a time where marketing is getting, you know, kind of disrupted and turned upside down in a lot of ways.","index":77,"end_time":800.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":785.06,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So Carl seems to have a decent kind of playbook or set of tricks in his bag that he thinks will help Synchro grow at a time where a lot of others in this space are having a hard time.","index":78,"end_time":811.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":800.34,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Find more than you''re asking for.","index":79,"end_time":813.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":812.3,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I mean, it is hopefully all helpful context because it, you know, it''s, he''s asking questions like what are all the channels that we''re using?","index":80,"end_time":819.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":813.7,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"What value are we getting?","index":81,"end_time":820.419,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.58,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, we have obviously already had conversations about like the future of the podcast and what we should be doing or, you know, evolving there.","index":82,"end_time":826.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.419,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So it gives us some good kind of lenses to think through perhaps or to look through as we think about the, the, you know, most kind of prioritized work that we want to do together and we want to spend our time together and things like that.","index":83,"end_time":840.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.38,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, but still in planning, it''s always helpful to know.","index":84,"end_time":844.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":841.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, like, no, no, like decisions made one way or the other still kind of in that, you know, planning and kind of thought exercise part of it, but probably within a week or two of having a good sense of all right, we want to do more of this, you want to do less of this and then we can think about how that, you know, evolves what we do together in this group.","index":85,"end_time":861.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.52,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Which of those.","index":86,"end_time":863.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":863.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you mentioned, like your three main pillars.","index":87,"end_time":865.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":863.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''ve got abm, GEO and your last one, your security messaging.","index":88,"end_time":874.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":865.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like which of those do you feel like you''re going to be spending a lot of time in?","index":89,"end_time":877.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":874.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or is that still to figure out?","index":90,"end_time":879.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":877.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean the group is pretty flat, so everybody''s going to be doing a bit of all of it.","index":91,"end_time":883.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":880.11,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I think the jump from SEO to GEO will be almost entirely in my pods responsibility.","index":92,"end_time":889.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":883.39,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I think the security messaging will be probably 75%, you know, in my camp because we tend to do most of that and we have ownership over most of the website, the abm or as Carl calls it, abx because, you know, it''s, that''s, that''s what you do nowadays.","index":93,"end_time":903.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":890.27,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s just everything.","index":94,"end_time":904.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":903.51,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, that will live largely within our growth organization because there''s a lot of tooling and process building and also because you no longer really need, I mean, maybe from a creative perspective, but you no longer need the services of a team like mine to develop content for things like that.","index":95,"end_time":924.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":905.47,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, he''s got some really interesting tools and AI engines that can seemingly crank out like pretty solid, personalized, contextualized, you know, communications and outreach messages and stuff like that.","index":96,"end_time":937.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.82,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So they seem pretty confident that they''ll be able to run a good portion of that, you know, without needing to put in a bunch of orders within our group, which is good because we''re going to have pretty full plates tackling those other two.","index":97,"end_time":948.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.26,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So a year ago I would not really have said that''s possible, but these tools have gotten to a point where, you know, is it as perfect as if we had written it by hand?","index":98,"end_time":958.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":948.99,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Probably not.","index":99,"end_time":959.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":958.27,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But the difference that we would make would not result in a large enough gain and like click or open or whatever for it to be worthwhile.","index":100,"end_time":966.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":959.03,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s like the, you know, if you''re prompting well and fine tuning things correctly, AI generated stuff, at least for written words, is has arrived at a point where it is good enough to kind of meet the bar of what I think we''re, we''re trying to do.","index":101,"end_time":980.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":966.75,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":102,"end_time":985.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":984.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Big updates is always crazy when you get new leadership.","index":103,"end_time":990.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":986.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I hope goes well and I know you''re probably going to be pretty busy for, for a while, for sure.","index":104,"end_time":998.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":991.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I never expect the beginning of the year to be quiet.","index":105,"end_time":1001.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":999.18,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But it is particularly, you know, let''s go pour some gas on the fire and ramp stuff up.","index":106,"end_time":1007.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1001.58,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But we''ll see.","index":107,"end_time":1008.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1007.07,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And I don''t, you know, I have trouble kind of sitting still and doing the same stuff over and over again.","index":108,"end_time":1012.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1008.43,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So, you know, as long as folks see a place for me to be a part of it, which they seem to, then, yeah, I''m game to, like, change it up or try something different or shake it up or whatever.","index":109,"end_time":1023.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1012.83,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, well, so we''ll see.","index":110,"end_time":1025.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1023.39,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We''ll see kind of what that means for us.","index":111,"end_time":1027.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1025.95,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, the question of, like, the future of the show, of course, remains in my mind, and there''s just going to be a lot of sort of new operating motion for us.","index":112,"end_time":1037.599,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1028.11,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I don''t.","index":113,"end_time":1038.599,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1037.599,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t have enough information, nor have we actually built enough of anything because it''s been very abstract conversation these first couple of weeks, and now we''re probably this week really transitioning into, okay, let''s start building and actually, you know, architecting these systems.","index":114,"end_time":1051.359,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1038.599,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So we''ll see.","index":115,"end_time":1052.879,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1052.159,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''ll get some feedback and kind of share, you know, with Carl what we''ve been up to lately and how the show''s been performing.","index":116,"end_time":1059.639,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1053.519,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And, you know, I''ll talk to him about.","index":117,"end_time":1061.279,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1059.639,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''ve already kind of briefly gotten them up to speed on all of our agency partners and the various capabilities they have.","index":118,"end_time":1066.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1062,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I''d say within another few weeks, we''ll have a sense of, again, what we maybe want to do more of or less of, and then we can figure out, you know, where the gaps are and what type of content, whether it''s the podcast or other work, you know, where we should be spending our time.","index":119,"end_time":1082.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1066.44,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":120,"end_time":1083.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.32,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t have enough of an opinion formed on that yet to really talk about it today, but at the rate at which we are starting to do things, only being four weeks or whatever into the new year, I don''t think it''ll take very long before we have a sense of, you know, what might be shifting or where we want to go from here.","index":121,"end_time":1098.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1083.12,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, well, and if Carl ever wants to meet us, we''re happy to do that.","index":122,"end_time":1103.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1098.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that would be fun.","index":123,"end_time":1104.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1103.78,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"People have.","index":124,"end_time":1105.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1105.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think so.","index":125,"end_time":1108.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1106.34,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":126,"end_time":1108.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t know that he''s going to want to be in the weeds too regularly, but, yeah, it''s.","index":127,"end_time":1112.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1108.9,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I always like making an intro and just, you know, otherwise you guys will just be like a logo somewhere on a slide for him.","index":128,"end_time":1118.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1112.74,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Right.","index":129,"end_time":1118.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1118.5,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So at some point, when some stuff settles, we''ll do like a round of intros.","index":130,"end_time":1122.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1118.78,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"With you guys and a couple of the other teams that I work with.","index":131,"end_time":1124.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1122.38,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":132,"end_time":1126.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1125.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know Igor has a few updates too, we can go over as well.","index":133,"end_time":1131.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1126.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Great.","index":134,"end_time":1131.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.58,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay, so just quickly go through the agenda.","index":135,"end_time":1146.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1141.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Not really a lot going on in January.","index":136,"end_time":1149.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1147.43,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So 12 points so far delivered, including Tech Stack.","index":137,"end_time":1155.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1151.35,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then regarding the previous episodes that we delivered in December, did you have any feedback on them?","index":138,"end_time":1163.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1156.31,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I saw that you were planning on publishing one of them.","index":139,"end_time":1168.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1163.67,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yep.","index":140,"end_time":1169.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1169.34,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":141,"end_time":1170.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1169.9,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Wednesday this week.","index":142,"end_time":1171.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1170.78,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Russell.","index":143,"end_time":1172.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1171.98,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''ve just been waiting to, you know, get out of the.","index":144,"end_time":1175.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1173.34,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"The kind of dead zone of December spilling into January.","index":145,"end_time":1179.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1175.78,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So Russell''s episode will publish this week and then we still got Brian Lindholm in the can.","index":146,"end_time":1186.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.34,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''ll probably publish that at some point in February.","index":147,"end_time":1188.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1186.46,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I have a couple of open conversations with folks that I will continue to, you know, keep warm and, and see what people are interested in doing.","index":148,"end_time":1200,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1189.5,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''m, I''m trying not to sort of overbook right now, given, you know, everything that I just rambled about and some of the changes there.","index":149,"end_time":1206.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1200.08,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I am certainly not going to just dip on people that have, you know, responded or who were sort of in mid conversation with.","index":150,"end_time":1213.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1206.96,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So there''s, there''s one guy by the name of Eric that we''re playing a little bit of tag with and trying to think about a topic.","index":151,"end_time":1218.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1213.4,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Um, and we had, we had at least one or two of the kind of really targeted list that, that we did respond, which had been good.","index":152,"end_time":1229.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1219.53,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I haven''t totally followed through on all of them.","index":153,"end_time":1232.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1229.45,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, at least one person was like, yeah, sounds great, I''ll go ahead and book something.","index":154,"end_time":1235.569,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1232.41,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And then they haven''t.","index":155,"end_time":1236.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1235.569,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I have to maybe chase them down.","index":156,"end_time":1238.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1236.33,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And then I spoke with somebody else, Amy, I believe her name was.","index":157,"end_time":1243.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1238.57,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I think she might have been from our list.","index":158,"end_time":1244.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1243.09,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And I just need to reconnect with her on LinkedIn.","index":159,"end_time":1247.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1246.05,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We had a little bit of tag there and decided, okay, let''s reconnect it, like end of January, February, and you know, we''ll touch base because we both had a bunch of stuff going on when, when the LinkedIn messages were first firing.","index":160,"end_time":1258.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1247.81,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I''d say there''s a couple of good warm opportunities.","index":161,"end_time":1261.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1259.01,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Nothing on fire right now, but I think the overall, the kind of more personalized messages and stuff that we did there seem to get decent response rates.","index":162,"end_time":1273.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1263.49,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Nice.","index":163,"end_time":1275.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1274.79,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I think maybe half of those folks had some acknowledgment, either a click or a response or something, which is pretty good.","index":164,"end_time":1280.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1275.19,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Cool.","index":165,"end_time":1283.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1283.27,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''s great to hear, especially regarding the Microsoft experts.","index":166,"end_time":1288.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1283.71,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":167,"end_time":1290.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1289.91,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, and that might be where we end up Heading here, you know, we''ll see.","index":168,"end_time":1293.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1290.27,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Again, I don''t want to decide anything today one way or the other because I still just have this large cloud overhead of, like, the future of the show as a question mark.","index":169,"end_time":1301.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1293.63,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But if we do continue to, you know, produce this particular show, I''m definitely open to less Spray and pray and being more targeted and more narrow and, you know, saying something like, which we haven''t done a lot of in, you know, our time together.","index":170,"end_time":1317.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1301.03,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, okay, you know, Synchro has a campaign coming up about this topic, and it''s going to be building these deliverables and this sort of theme, like, can we try to go out and find a person, you know, or eight people that would speak really well to this very specific topic and then that''s our target list.","index":171,"end_time":1333.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1317.8,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And, you know, we try to get one of those seven or eight people to come record and talk about that topic, and then it''s part of, you know, larger campaign conversation and less of a, you know, kind of random one off podcast conversation.","index":172,"end_time":1347.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.35,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Those, to me, are the ways that the show would live on.","index":173,"end_time":1350.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1348.07,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Right.","index":174,"end_time":1350.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1350.31,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"If, if we can build some momentum or if the team, as they sort of evolve these outbound campaigns and think about sort of the future of their growth engine, you know, if.","index":175,"end_time":1361.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1350.55,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"If this as a channel is something that would feel valuable or give them good content ammo, that.","index":176,"end_time":1365.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1361.46,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s how I could see it potentially, you know, sticking around and still having some legs.","index":177,"end_time":1369.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1365.82,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t think it''s going to make sense to continue doing it the way that we did it last year, which is sort of, you know, off to the side, kind of in a silo, not really tied back to some of the other stuff that Synchro is doing.","index":178,"end_time":1379.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1369.94,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I know we''ve had a fair amount of dialogue about that and thinking about how to kind of bring this more into the core of what we''re talking about and, and materials that we''re building.","index":179,"end_time":1387.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1379.78,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So we''ll see again, that sort of campaign, you know, level thinking is in its pretty early stages, but I was happy with our ability to, like, find a narrow list, build some very personalized messaging and get a couple of bytes from that list.","index":180,"end_time":1403.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1387.94,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I think we''ve kind of proved to ourselves, you know, the last cycle here that we can do that, which is good.","index":181,"end_time":1409.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1403.62,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yes, yes, yes.","index":182,"end_time":1411.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1410.74,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Great.","index":183,"end_time":1412.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1412.02,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And also, if.","index":184,"end_time":1414.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1412.38,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"If we do something like that in the future, the targeted lists, then that would definitely, I think, provide more valuable, like more.","index":185,"end_time":1423.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1414.19,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"More relevant conversations for, for the audience.","index":186,"end_time":1427.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1423.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":187,"end_time":1429.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1427.31,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And just like a sort of quality over quantity, like you know, general thread above that even, which I think is a good hat to wear heading into this year, doesn''t mean we want to like cut the volume of stuff we''re publishing in half.","index":188,"end_time":1447.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1429.43,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I''m getting the sense that from like a go to market perspective there''s going to be a lot less sort of broad brushstrokes from Synchro and more narrower targeted intentional activations and outreach and account targeting and channel usage and things like that.","index":189,"end_time":1466.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1447.6,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So it''ll be good to think through how we can support that.","index":190,"end_time":1470.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1466.2,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And I think we''re already again sort of generally on that path with this last run, you know, going from hey, let''s reach out to 800 people to like, well, let''s try 10 and see if we can get them to talk about a very specific set of topics.","index":191,"end_time":1481.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1470.76,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I think that was good, good sort of first step in that direction for us.","index":192,"end_time":1485.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1482.28,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Nice, nice.","index":193,"end_time":1487.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1486.84,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":194,"end_time":1488.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.8,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I have not recorded shit.","index":195,"end_time":1491.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1490.44,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We''ll see if that happens.","index":196,"end_time":1493.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1492.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"About those, those social clips.","index":197,"end_time":1495.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1493.88,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, I figured that was the next slide.","index":198,"end_time":1497.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.56,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We''ll see.","index":199,"end_time":1499.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1498.65,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, I really go back and forth on it.","index":200,"end_time":1501.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1499.13,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I think it''ll just to avoid rambling on it for 10 minutes.","index":201,"end_time":1505.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1501.93,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I think it will come down to like where this sort of campaign level thinking shakes out.","index":202,"end_time":1510.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1505.13,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I think video continues to become more and more and more important.","index":203,"end_time":1513.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1510.73,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I, I, I just, I''d love to be able to publish as much video content as we can.","index":204,"end_time":1518.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1513.93,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s just sort of TBD of like, you know, where what shelves it''s going to sit on, what the intended use is going to be, how we''re going to measure its impact and so forth.","index":205,"end_time":1530.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1521.45,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I''m going to hold on this for a little bit because I don''t want to sort of activate a new series or work stream off to the side.","index":206,"end_time":1541.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1530.46,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''d want it to be kind of integrated thinking alongside all the other stuff that I''ve been sharing with you guys this morning.","index":207,"end_time":1546.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.58,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So let''s just sort of keep this warm on our list and you know, I''ll keep you guys posted as to like in my mind what, what I''m, what this is all sort of leading toward is that at some point in the next couple of weeks, I think Synchro is going to like launch its first campaign under this new, you know, look and feel of, of those kind of core pillars that I was mentioning.","index":208,"end_time":1568.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1546.78,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I want to get a better sense of how that''s going to shape up, what that''s going to look like, what the deliverable expectations around that are going to be and then we could figure out.","index":209,"end_time":1575.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1568.56,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay, is this the idea that still makes sense?","index":210,"end_time":1576.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1575.28,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Is it something slightly different?","index":211,"end_time":1578.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1576.96,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I think, you know, what we''ve been sort of, you know, guesstimating this to look and feel like, you know, may shift a little bit, but I want to keep that idea of that sort of resourcing available.","index":212,"end_time":1592.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1578.16,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So we''ll see, we''ll see.","index":213,"end_time":1594.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1592.87,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We''ll see what it ends up looking like.","index":214,"end_time":1595.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1594.47,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Thanks for keeping it on our radar, you know, if nothing else.","index":215,"end_time":1599.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1595.83,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"No problem, no problem.","index":216,"end_time":1601.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1600.31,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Don''t want you to feel that like we''re forcing you or something because.","index":217,"end_time":1605.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1602.55,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"No, not at all.","index":218,"end_time":1606.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1605.91,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Every meeting this comes up, so.","index":219,"end_time":1608.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1606.79,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, no, it''s just been me dragging my feet on it and now I feel like I have a decent excuse.","index":220,"end_time":1613.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1608.79,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It was just bandwidth before the holiday, but now I really want to make sure that it''s the right, you know, format and deliverable and use of time again, Like, I don''t know how much social media will play.","index":221,"end_time":1626.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1613.27,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, you know, it''s.","index":222,"end_time":1627.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1626.23,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s a very broad, like megaphone type channel, at least in the ways that we''ve been using it historically.","index":223,"end_time":1632.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1627.83,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Does that need to become more targeted?","index":224,"end_time":1634.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1633.27,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Are we going to start doing more whatever.","index":225,"end_time":1636.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1634.79,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t even want to go down that tangent, but there''s just some high level, you know, conversations that are still open right now of like, how much time are we going to invest in these different channels or, you know, if we decide, hey, we need to like triple the amount of content we have on YouTube because that''s a huge part of GEO, because all these AI results are, you know, dipping into YouTube and pulling transcript holding.","index":226,"end_time":1655.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1636.83,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Great.","index":227,"end_time":1655.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1655.05,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"This makes a lot of sense, you know, so we''ll, we''re kind of waiting through those conversations now, but we''ll figure out what we want to do with this.","index":228,"end_time":1661.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1655.29,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Whether it''s the, the current idea or some refined version of it.","index":229,"end_time":1665.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1661.25,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay, sounds great.","index":230,"end_time":1667.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1666.78,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then some of the podcast stats for the past 30 days since you haven''t uploaded a lot.","index":231,"end_time":1679.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1669.82,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So yeah, basically these are the numbers.","index":232,"end_time":1684.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1679.26,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"44 downloads.","index":233,"end_time":1686.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1684.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yeah, we can see some of the spikes here in January.","index":234,"end_time":1691.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1686.38,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So yeah, Wednesday 14th and then over this weekend actually there was a spike also in downloads.","index":235,"end_time":1700.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1692.71,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Nice.","index":236,"end_time":1701.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1701.35,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s what was me and yep.","index":237,"end_time":1707.429,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1702.63,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s Russell there at the top.","index":238,"end_time":1708.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1707.429,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, Wednesday.","index":239,"end_time":1711.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1708.87,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Wednesday.","index":240,"end_time":1711.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1711.27,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":241,"end_time":1712.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1711.91,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":242,"end_time":1713.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1712.63,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":243,"end_time":1714.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1713.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":244,"end_time":1714.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1714.31,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yeah, these are.","index":245,"end_time":1715.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1714.55,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":246,"end_time":1715.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1715.39,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I mean our engagement in other channels has been stronger than this.","index":247,"end_time":1718.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1715.83,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like people come to our site to watch some of it on our blog.","index":248,"end_time":1720.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1718.39,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"YouTube does.","index":249,"end_time":1722.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1721.59,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":250,"end_time":1722.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1722.31,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I'' Although I don''t think people are actually watching the full Thing they just kind of skim around or the short clips do okay when uploaded as shorts.","index":251,"end_time":1730.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1722.71,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But yeah, this is, this is part of the challenge is that these numbers are just low and the growth rate has been much flatter than some of our other channels.","index":252,"end_time":1737.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1730.69,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And the in, you know, the other side of that coin as well, that is perhaps because these things have been published slightly off to the side in the silo and not really, you know, part of the, the larger sort of fabric of what we''ve been building.","index":253,"end_time":1749.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1737.49,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So it''s hard to say if it''s, you know, A or B or a little bit of both.","index":254,"end_time":1753.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1749.33,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But that, that''s, that''s part of what will make this, you know, kind of a like data driven conversation of like, okay, we''ve done like 17 or 18 episodes.","index":255,"end_time":1765.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1753.92,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We have X thousand total views across all that.","index":256,"end_time":1767.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1765.08,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, is that enough?","index":257,"end_time":1768.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1767.28,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Have we been getting, you know, enough traction fast enough to continue spending the time per month?","index":258,"end_time":1773,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1768.56,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":259,"end_time":1773.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1773,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We''ll see.","index":260,"end_time":1774.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1773.6,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"See.","index":261,"end_time":1775.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1774.96,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Makes sense.","index":262,"end_time":1776.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1775.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Or do we try to repurpose the existing content more effectively?","index":263,"end_time":1779.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1776.48,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, do we not record new episodes for a little bit and just say, look, we''ve got like, I don''t know, 15 or 16 hours of material here.","index":264,"end_time":1784.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1779.12,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, should we just be doing more to slice and dice and, you know, promote?","index":265,"end_time":1788.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1784.89,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":266,"end_time":1789.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1788.73,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We''ll see.","index":267,"end_time":1789.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1789.13,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":268,"end_time":1791.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.73,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Makes.","index":269,"end_time":1791.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1791.13,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Some of these are good.","index":270,"end_time":1792.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1791.41,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"They''re not all bangers, but some of these are pretty good.","index":271,"end_time":1794.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1792.13,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, that, that I think are ever great enough to, that we could be maybe doing more with them.","index":272,"end_time":1798.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1794.01,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds interesting.","index":273,"end_time":1801.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1800.25,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Let us know when, when you figure out.","index":274,"end_time":1805.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1801.85,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Hopefully by the next time we get together.","index":275,"end_time":1806.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1805.37,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Because I know folks are trying to move quickly here and, you know, not spend all of Q1 just planning.","index":276,"end_time":1813.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1808.5,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know.","index":277,"end_time":1814.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1813.3,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Let''s, let''s just hold on this for a little bit.","index":278,"end_time":1816.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1814.26,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s a fair question.","index":279,"end_time":1817.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1816.5,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t know if we''re still doing any final touch for the previous batch or if we''ve kind of exhausted that, but let''s just hold for a couple of weeks.","index":280,"end_time":1827.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1818.02,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t think we''re going to lag here for months, but I don''t want to do another batch and blast while there''s so many of these large conversations happening across the team.","index":281,"end_time":1834.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1827.94,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Let me figure out what''s going on here and I''ll probably be able to, you know, have a more informed opinion about where we should be spending time wrapping up.","index":282,"end_time":1845.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1834.94,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And if that means we don''t have anything primed and ready for like early Feb, that''s Fine.","index":283,"end_time":1848.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1845.22,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We''ll let a couple of points accrue.","index":284,"end_time":1851.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1850.18,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Nothing wrong with that.","index":285,"end_time":1852.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1851.78,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":286,"end_time":1854.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1853.62,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":287,"end_time":1855.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1854.5,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And that would be it for the agenda.","index":288,"end_time":1860.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1856.98,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Anything else from you?","index":289,"end_time":1862.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1860.26,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":290,"end_time":1863.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1863.24,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Oh, thanks for the swag.","index":291,"end_time":1865.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1863.96,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I haven''t seen you guys since then.","index":292,"end_time":1866.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1865.52,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''m rocking my beanie and.","index":293,"end_time":1869.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1866.92,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Was a mug, I think.","index":294,"end_time":1871.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1870.52,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Do you guys.","index":295,"end_time":1872.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1872.04,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I had.","index":296,"end_time":1872.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1872.56,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I had a good laugh when it arrived.","index":297,"end_time":1874.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1872.92,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Do you guys ever get or, like, joke about.","index":298,"end_time":1877.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1874.76,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s just like, mid, right?","index":299,"end_time":1879.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1877.64,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, that''s on purpose.","index":300,"end_time":1881.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1879.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re like, making fun of ourselves.","index":301,"end_time":1882.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1881.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s.","index":302,"end_time":1883,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1882.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I like.","index":303,"end_time":1883.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1883,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I like that.","index":304,"end_time":1884.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1883.48,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, I kind of hoped that''s what it was.","index":305,"end_time":1887.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1884.76,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And there''s something sort of, I don''t know, like, you know, fun and.","index":306,"end_time":1892.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1887.48,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And ironic of like, the hat especially.","index":307,"end_time":1895.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1892.76,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, I. I got a kick out of that.","index":308,"end_time":1899.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1896.84,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I should have included something on the card about that because I found a couple people be like, was this on purpose or.","index":309,"end_time":1906.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1899.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, you got.","index":310,"end_time":1907.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1906.84,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You got to find a way.","index":311,"end_time":1908.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1907.6,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, it''s like, I don''t.","index":312,"end_time":1910.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1908.52,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, it''s like it''s mid, but it''s not mid.","index":313,"end_time":1912.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1910.64,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, you gotta, like, find some way to, you know, get cute with that.","index":314,"end_time":1916.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1912.72,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But yeah, it''s.","index":315,"end_time":1917.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1916.08,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s fun.","index":316,"end_time":1918.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1917.69,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And I''m sure you guys have, like.","index":317,"end_time":1920.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1918.57,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I mean, you must have so much fucking swag from, like, all of the brands over the.","index":318,"end_time":1925.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1921.61,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, like, they''re.","index":319,"end_time":1928.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1925.85,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Have you.","index":320,"end_time":1929.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1928.81,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Do you also have.","index":321,"end_time":1930.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1929.33,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I wish.","index":322,"end_time":1931.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1930.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, is it all.","index":323,"end_time":1932.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1931.33,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Is it all mid and like, is there a new north swag line around or, like, other stuff or.","index":324,"end_time":1937.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1932.17,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s all.","index":325,"end_time":1937.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1937.17,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s all, you know, washed or like, motion.","index":326,"end_time":1941.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1937.77,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, that''s what I want to feel like a real og.","index":327,"end_time":1943.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1941.37,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, I want like the motion hoodie or, you know, the.","index":328,"end_time":1946.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1943.93,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"The real original stuff.","index":329,"end_time":1948.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1947.5,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I know Justin and Tristan have a bunch of motion stuff.","index":330,"end_time":1952.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1948.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m sure they do.","index":331,"end_time":1953.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1952.14,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, they have stuff.","index":332,"end_time":1954.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1953.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I have a new north jacket that branding.","index":333,"end_time":1960.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1954.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I did.","index":334,"end_time":1960.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1960.26,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, I think I just like purple.","index":335,"end_time":1962.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1960.62,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And they mostly had purple, right?","index":336,"end_time":1963.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1962.02,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s probably.","index":337,"end_time":1965.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1963.66,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I like the purple too.","index":338,"end_time":1966.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1965.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t have enough.","index":339,"end_time":1968.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1967.26,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t have enough purple.","index":340,"end_time":1969.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1968.38,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But yeah, it was fun.","index":341,"end_time":1970.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1969.54,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And my jam, my partner.","index":342,"end_time":1971.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1970.22,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I was like, mid.","index":343,"end_time":1972.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1971.54,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, what is this?","index":344,"end_time":1973.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1972.74,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s even funnier because you have.","index":345,"end_time":1976.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1975.58,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"No, but.","index":346,"end_time":1978.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1976.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Anyway, yeah, it was fun.","index":347,"end_time":1982.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1981,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":348,"end_time":1982.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1982.12,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I always love getting that.","index":349,"end_time":1983.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1982.4,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That sort of stuff.","index":350,"end_time":1984.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1983.56,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Can''t argue with free clothes and mugs.","index":351,"end_time":1987.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1984.36,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Two things I use almost daily.","index":352,"end_time":1988.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1987.04,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So.","index":353,"end_time":1989.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1988.92,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, I need one of the synchro mugs.","index":354,"end_time":1991.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1989.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That one you have is cool.","index":355,"end_time":1992.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1991.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":356,"end_time":1993.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1992.48,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I could probably hook you up with one of these.","index":357,"end_time":1994.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1993.16,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, these are good.","index":358,"end_time":1995.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1994.8,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I like that.","index":359,"end_time":1998.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1997.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The inside''s orange.","index":360,"end_time":1999.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1998.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":361,"end_time":2001.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1999.52,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We do all of our stuff through printfection.","index":362,"end_time":2004.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2001.36,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Pretty good.","index":363,"end_time":2005.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2005.07,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":364,"end_time":2006.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2006.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They''re pretty good.","index":365,"end_time":2008.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2007.79,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We just got a couple new things.","index":366,"end_time":2010.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2008.67,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"A couple shirts and stuff at that.","index":367,"end_time":2012.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2010.35,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"At that revenue kickoff anyway.","index":368,"end_time":2015.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2012.19,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":369,"end_time":2017.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2016.51,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Well, great to see you guys.","index":370,"end_time":2018.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2017.11,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"My hope is that when we get together in another couple of weeks.","index":371,"end_time":2021.069,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2018.51,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Oh, do we need to book a series?","index":372,"end_time":2022.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2021.069,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"By the way, this was one off, right?","index":373,"end_time":2024.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2022.35,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t mind doing another one off since it''s still a little wonky around here, and then we can figure out, you know, some.","index":374,"end_time":2029.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2024.03,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Something recurring.","index":375,"end_time":2030.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2029.51,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But let''s touch base in 2ish weeks.","index":376,"end_time":2034.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2030.63,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And I will do my best to have a sense of like, okay, here is a campaign that Synchro is working toward launching.","index":377,"end_time":2041.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2034.31,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And then we can kind of use our time to brainstorm.","index":378,"end_time":2043.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2041.27,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, okay, how can we team up to build some content in support of it?","index":379,"end_time":2046.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2043.15,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":380,"end_time":2048.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2047.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":381,"end_time":2049.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2048.95,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Great.","index":382,"end_time":2050.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2050.07,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Well, happy New Year.","index":383,"end_time":2051.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2050.43,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Good to see you both.","index":384,"end_time":2051.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2051.15,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We''ll talk soon.","index":385,"end_time":2052.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2051.87,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Great.","index":386,"end_time":2053.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2052.71,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"See ya.","index":387,"end_time":2053.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2053.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bye.","index":388,"end_time":2053.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2053.51,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Bye.","index":389,"end_time":2054.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2053.75,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Bye.","index":390,"end_time":2054.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2054.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2026-01-26T17:00:00.000Z","host_email":"igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85476489791?pwd=erwjQyfcUn7Q7oYZN7POLmENLxqNJF.1","participants":["igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com,brandon.garcin@syncromsp.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","brandon.garcin@syncromsp.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFJM1QBJGZEV2E6223TQ0ZR0","organizer_email":"igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Announced pivot toward blended inbound-outbound marketing under new CMO Carl''s leadership direction.","Shifted content strategy from SEO to GEO to better align with AI-powered search trends.","Repositioned Synchro as a secure IT management platform based on recent feature growth.","Planning team''s first new campaign under updated GTM strategy, expected to launch within weeks.","Podcast continuity under review; tighter alignment with future campaigns is a likely path."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Carl seems to have a decent kind of playbook or set of tricks in his bag that he thinks will help Synchro grow.","speaker":"Brandon Garcin"},{"quote":"We''re reviewing strategies for different channels that we are leveraging… then we''ll be cranking out new campaigns.","speaker":"Brandon Garcin"},{"quote":"There''s work…that gives the company the right to now say [Synchro is] a secure IT management platform.","speaker":"Brandon Garcin"}],"topics":["strategy","marketing","leadership","campaigns","positioning"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-30T20:36:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Strategy and Leadership Changes**\n\nThe new CMO, **Carl**, has shifted Synchro’s marketing from mostly inbound to a blended inbound/outbound model focused on account-based marketing (06:23).  \n- Carl is introducing tools like **ZoomInfo** to identify buying intent beyond web visits, targeting companies with relevant executive hires or news.  \n- The sales team, previously not doing outbound, is building new outbound skills to support this approach.  \n- Brandon explained the plan to invert the current **70-80% SEO and 20-30% GEO split** toward about **75-80% GEO-focused content** by year-end, aiming to compete better in AI-powered search where GEO is less mature.  \n- This shift supports a faster growth trajectory by targeting more mature buyers with personalized outreach rather than relying solely on organic SEO growth.\n\nSynchro is repositioning itself as a **secure IT management platform**, weaving security deeply into messaging rather than just automation and efficiency (10:16).  \n- Brandon noted recent product releases and features strengthen Synchro’s security story, enabling this repositioning.  \n- The security focus aligns with market demand and higher valuation opportunities in security-centric IT platforms.\n\nPlanning is underway to review and evolve marketing channels, including blogs, social, community, and website updates, to support new campaigns and outbound motions (11:34).  \n- Brandon expects to finalize campaign priorities and channel strategies within the next **1-2 weeks**, followed by execution and optimization.  \n- Carl’s leadership is driving a replatforming of go-to-market systems to support these new approaches.\n\n## **Content and Podcast Direction**\n\nSynchro’s podcast saw **44 downloads** in the past 30 days with some spikes around new episode releases, but overall engagement is low compared to other channels (27:46).  \n- Brandon highlighted that past episodes were published somewhat isolated from broader marketing efforts, which limited growth and traction.  \n- The plan is to move from broad, random podcast topics to **highly targeted episodes tied to specific campaigns**, focusing on quality over quantity (20:30).  \n- This targeted approach involves identifying a narrow list of **7-8 key people** aligned to campaign themes to generate relevant content that directly supports marketing objectives.\n\nBrandon is considering repurposing existing podcast material more effectively rather than producing new episodes immediately (29:34).  \n- There are about **15-16 hours of recorded content** that could be sliced into more digestible or targeted clips to boost reach without new recordings.  \n- Video content is recognized as increasingly important, but decisions on social clips and video strategy are pending integration with the new campaign plans (24:50).\n\nThe podcast’s future depends on its fit within the broader outbound and GEO campaigns Carl is developing, with a decision expected within a few weeks (17:46).  \n- Brandon plans to share podcast performance data and content capabilities with Carl to align the show’s direction with growth priorities.\n\n## **Operational Shifts and Team Responsibilities**\n\nThe marketing team structure is flat, with pods covering multiple pillars but clear content ownership aligned to new priorities (14:40).  \n- Brandon’s pod will mainly handle the **SEO to GEO content shift** and about **75% of the security messaging** since they own most website content.  \n- The outbound account-based marketing (ABM/ABX) program will be run largely by the growth organization, leveraging AI tools to automate personalized outreach without heavy content demands from Brandon’s team.\n\nThis division allows Brandon’s group to focus resources on the GEO and security content transition while growth handles tooling and processes for ABM (15:58).  \n- Brandon noted AI-generated messaging has reached a quality level sufficient to replace much manual content creation for outreach, balancing efficiency and effectiveness.\n\nBrandon anticipates ongoing role and responsibility shifts as Carl’s leadership reshapes operating motions and marketing programming (06:23).  \n- He expects these changes to accelerate lead growth by targeting more mature buyers and incorporating security themes more deeply into the brand.\n\n## **Campaign and Timeline Outlook**\n\nSynchro plans to launch its first campaign under the new marketing model within the next **couple of weeks** (25:00).  \n- Brandon aims to clarify campaign deliverables, look and feel, and resource needs soon to enable coordinated content support.  \n- Early campaign work will focus on integrating outbound, GEO content, and security messaging pillars to drive more qualified leads.\n\nBrandon stressed the importance of not rushing new initiatives before strategic alignment is clear, holding social video and other new content formats \"warm\" until campaign plans solidify (24:50).  \n- He emphasized measured execution over volume, aiming for targeted activations rather than broad, untargeted content blasts.\n\nThe team plans to reconvene in about **two weeks** to review campaign progress and decide how to align content production, including podcast episodes, with broader marketing objectives (33:27).  \n- This cadence supports rapid iteration and ensures marketing efforts stay coordinated with evolving growth strategies.\n\n## **Performance Metrics and Growth Challenges**\n\nDespite positive marketing metrics in the second half of last year, Synchro’s growth rate is seen as insufficient, prompting the shift to outbound and GEO emphasis (11:34).  \n- Brandon indicated that while organic SEO delivered value, competitors’ longer investment history means Synchro must differentiate via newer channels like AI-powered search and account-based targeting.  \n- Podcast engagement remains low, with download numbers in the **low double digits per month**, reinforcing the need for a new approach to content tied to campaigns (27:46).\n\nThe outbound personalized messaging pilot reached about **50% response or engagement rates** on targeted lists, showing promise for more focused outreach (20:46).  \n- This data supports the strategic pivot to quality over quantity in content and marketing activations.\n\nBrandon flagged the need to evaluate whether to continue producing new podcast content or focus on repurposing existing material to improve ROI and audience relevance (29:36).  \n- This reflects a broader emphasis on data-driven, efficient marketing investment amid evolving leadership priorities.\n\n## **Stakeholder Collaboration and Next Steps**\n\nBrandon expressed openness to introducing new CMO Carl to agency partners and cross-functional teams once roles and plans settle (18:28).  \n- This will help align external and internal stakeholders around the new marketing playbook and campaign execution.\n\nBaylee and Igor remain ready to support content adaptations and integrations as campaign priorities clarify (18:45).  \n- Brandon committed to keeping them updated on evolving campaign plans and podcast decisions to ensure tight collaboration.\n\nThe next meeting is tentatively planned for about **two weeks out**, aiming to share clearer campaign direction and co-create supporting content (33:27).  \n- Brandon emphasized the importance of balancing planning with action to avoid a protracted Q1 of only strategy discussions.","outline":null,"keywords":["Outbound Marketing","GEO-first Strategy","Account-Based Marketing","Security Positioning","Podcast Strategy","AI-powered Search"],"overview":"- **Marketing Shift:** New CMO introduced a blended inbound/outbound marketing model, focusing on account-based marketing.  \n- **Content Strategy Change:** Transitioning to 75-80% GEO-focused content by year-end to target mature buyers and improve SEO competition.  \n- **Podcast Engagement:** Current podcast engagement is low; plan